Growing up, I was raised on all kinds of music, none of it Motown. But secretly, I loved the stuff, and would listen to it and sing to it all the time. And now, today, I sing at various bars and restaurants with a predominantly country audience simply because that is the area where I live  out in the country! And whenever I sing a Motown classic, like Stevie Wonder's "Superstition," I see feet and hands a tappin' to the beat! But when I do "You Make Me Feel Brand New" by the Stylistics because, yes. I can sing both the low and the high parts myself, people start slow dancing. And I get all kinds of compliments. If you can pull it off vocally, then you really owe it to your audience, and to yourself, to share this wonderful love ballad with the world.

I absolutely loved the Rules of Ascension. I could not put it down, and read it in three days. I raced out and bought this book to continue my journey through the Forelands.  Boy am I glad I did. This book picks up pretty much where ROA left off. The pacing and characterizations were excellent as well. Political intrigue, swords, socerey, magic, romance, fighting, poisoning...what else could you possibly ask for. I am frankly surprised more people have not discovered this author or series. Very fine work, and great mindless fantasy.  My only complaint about this book and the reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 was that there was not nearly enough interplay with the 2 main characters, Tavis and Grinsa, as I would have expected. I realize Coe's setting up the next book, and introducing Aneiria to the audience to  show the evil Weaver spinning his magic down south of Ebithar, but I would have liked more focus on Tavis and Grinsa.  Oh well, I will just have to wait until the next book, Bonds of Vengence, which hopefully will be out soon. I can hardly wait to see what happens. PIck this book up, as well as ROA if you have not already read iti guarantee you will not be disappointed.

Words cannot adequately express how I truly feel after reading Owned. As the last book in the Lost In Oblivion series, I was prepared for an emotional ride which Cari Quinn and Taryn Elliott delivered in spades. I laughed, I cried, I wanted to slap the characters silly....but most of all, I felt immense joy as the band found their way back together while each reaching a new level of happiness within their personal relationships. There are MANY surprises in Owned and all are incredible. Quinn and Elliott truly reward their readers for being loyal readers by giving us exactly what we want. Owned was bittersweetI could not wait to read it but I did not want it to end. I did not want to say goodbye to my favorite characters. Thankfully we will catch glimpses of them in future books written by this dynamic duo but I am still left with that ache in my chest knowing they will not be front and center any more.

One thing among the hundreds that I loved about Owned is that it is not as fast paced as their other books. The storylines are well written, fully developed and progress at the kind of pace that allows the reader to savor every.single.second of the story. And because this is the last book in the series, that was a big deal to me. It did not go by in a flash for me and for that I am beyond grateful. Readers will truly be thanking these two fabulous authors for the perfect end to one of the best rockstar series out there!
summary: 5+++ Rocking Stars For the Final LIO Book

It dispenses much like my foamy sunblock does, like a thick whipped cream. The scent is really delicious, it reminds me of spa products I have used over the years from highend brands like JE Atkinson. It is definitely scented with essential oils rather than synthetic fragrance. My skin is super dry due to medical issues but this product gives my skin an appropriate level of moisture thanks to the almond oil that is in it. In fact, my skin feels so soft and sweetly scented, this has become my alltime favorite shower cleanser. It is truly an indulgence to use and has a very calming quality about it. My skin feels very clean without the Ph being stripped away. If you love spa products vs those purchased in the drug store, you will love this too....it is divine!  So divine, in fact, I caught my hubby using it recently. Highly recommended unless you are a Mr Bubble fan.
Would order again!

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

Avalon Organics has products that I tend to love because they are so natural and deliciously scented. I have combination skin where I have an oily Tzone and dry cheeks. This cream is not greasy so it is OK for the oily skin and it is moisturizing so it also soothes the dry skin conditions on my face. I have not found this to be irritating like other Vitamin C creams and serums. In fact this seems to calm my skin significantly so it is not overly sensitive. If you want to look ten years younger, this is the cream to try. I find it helps with elasticity and skin resilience. I also notice I break out less and have overall clearer skin. I love this and hope it works for you too. Always test a bit on your wrist before applying.

It might be obvious, but this version does not include the state tax program.  To file state taxes you will have to purchase and download the state product from within the Federal application.  I am using this on a Apple iMac with latest OS and Turbo Tax installed and is working as expected.  I was able to import prior year data without issue.  My taxes are not complex so this version works fine for typical home write offs.  I have performed a preliminary tax run for 2015 taxes and I did not run into any issues.  My prior year data was there and I was able to enter in my 2015 information without issue.  I have not purchased the state yet but will do just before filing taxes.  I have purchased the state filing in the past without issue.  Turbo Tax and Intuit did not make customers happy last year with higher prices and reduced functionality, but it is still a good product and hopefully the company learned its lesson.

I am but a mere novice when it comes to playing the guitar, but I purchased this SN1 to replace the piece of junk first tuner I had. I am very happy with the size of the SN1. It is small, much smaller than I expected which was a big bonus. It takes up very little room on the headstock, and does not interfere when I make tuning adjustments. The "chipclip" style clamp does a surprisingly good job of staying in place on my Ibanez acoustic and I think my guitar sounds better than it did while using my previous tuner.

The user interface is very simple, and the display is easy to read and understand in both higher and lower lighting conditions. The instruction manual is adequate, but the SN1 seemed very intuitive for me to use. The product arrived on time, as shown, well packaged, for what I believe to be a fair price at about eight dollars and change. I have had this SN1 for a couple months now, and will update this review down the road. Thanks for reading, and if you have any questions, feel free to ask and I will do the best I can to answer.

As an artist, parent, and educator, I can envision all kinds of possibilities to use the AtmosFlare 3D Pen.  The set includes the pen with 4 tips and a cap, along with two ink cartridges red  blue.  The cap has a pin to clear the tips after use, but a paperclip works quite well too.  There is supposed to be an AA battery included in the set, but the one I received for review purposes did not include one.  The set up was very easy, with the illustrated instructions included.  There are a couple of models to look at on the package, but you can find others on the company's website.  Although I am very good at sculpting realistic figures with various types of clay, working with this pen will take a little more practice.  However, the human figure I made on my first attempt looks like a piece of abstract art, so I do not think that is bad.  I recommend that you work on a smooth surface, and that it is not bright white, since the shininess could cure the ink inside the nozzle.  I also found out that the refill cartridges will be available on Amazon for around $10 for a set of 3, and are available in a variety of colors, which pretty good.  I know I am going to have a lot of fun playing more with it in the future!

What gets me is how this man has scammed himself into so many five star reviews. When you receive the gauge, a little piece of paper tells you a 'secret'. If you post a five star review and notify him of your post, which he checks,  this generous guru will send you a free leather case for your gauge. If that is not buying reviews, I do not know what is. As far as the gauge goes, it is like a pimped out Mazda with fuzzy dice real luthiers do not use gauges like this. I took mine in to Martin Guitars in Nazareth, PA and everyone laughed. Big, big scam. And by the way, the guru has been telling customers to get one while you can! for years.

iLife is a collection of fun and useful apps. I would call them toys because they are fun, but they are much more powerful and useful than that.

iPhoto  great for organizing your photos and videos. Face detection is lots of fun. Several basic enhancement tools are included that eliminate much of my need fornbsp;a datahook"productlinklinked" class"alinknormal" href"/Photoshop/dp/B001EUIVZG/refcm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ieUTF8"Photoshop/a. Now I just spin up GIMP when my needs go beyond what iPhoto can offer.

iMovie  I have not used iMovie 09 much, but older versions of iMovie were great for building simple videos out of DV footage and still images.

iDVD  I have not used the latest version of iDVD yet, but it has always been a great app for mastering simple DVD content.

GarageBand  Amazing musical toy. Very serious musicians will probably find GarageBand too limited, but it is lots of fun for people who are casually interested in making music. You get plenty of loops and sounds to throw together your own tracks. MIDI support is limited, but it is a very fun environment to play around in.nbsp;a datahook"productlinklinked" class"alinknormal" href"/Logic9/dp/B002ISDD1K/refcm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ieUTF8"Logic 9/anbsp;will give you far more power if you feel constrained by GarageBand.

Update  If you got iLife with your new mac, be sure to drop in the DVD and install the extra GarageBand instruments and loops. A lot of great creative content is included.

I purchased Kaspersky Internet Security 7.0 3user so I could load it in my computer and my daughter's laptops. This software is very protective of my system. It has so many settings; I could see where it might be a little difficult for people not completely computer literate to figure out how to utilize its full potential. This software protects you in every area, from being on the internet to scanning your emails before you open them. It can become a little annoring if the settings are set too high. But once you get the hang of it, you will be so glad you bought it. I guess most importantly, it gives you real piece of mind that your system is protected fully.
It will not slow your system down. And it does not take over your computer like many of the other brands. And Amazon performs great as usual. I have been a member of Prime since it is beginning and never had anything but great things to say about the service I have received.

The interface is easy to navigate and the information is appropriate for the level the set is targeting. The videos are well produced and show the functions in a way that is easily transferable to actual realworld tasks.

Setup could not be eaiser, just pop the DVD into your computer's drive, then peel the book off the back of the package and you are ready to go. The book and DVD compliment each very well, but you can use either separately without loosing a thing.

The package covers all the basics and a few things a bit more advanced. I highly reccomend this series as a thorough introduction to this software.

Yes, I am yet another "Triffid" lover fooled into buying this DVD.  The Cinemascope 2.35:1 film is cropped down to 4Happy face smiley so the title of the movie barely fits on the screen, the picture is grainy and out of focus, and the color is drastically shifted to the right!  Allied Artists' idea of digitally mastering is copying an Nth generation VHS tape to a hard drive and burning a DVD!  I have the widescreen PAL version of this movie on DVD and even with PAL to NTSC conversion it is 1000 times better than this miserable excuse for a DVD!  Hopefully the Second Sight Films version of "Day of the Triffids" will make it to the US.  Until then, do not fear the Triffids, fear this DVD!!

I have been using TurboTax for the past 10 years, and find that it is an excellent product. The software is extremely easy to use, and all that is required is for you to answer a series of simple questions for each category.

With that said, the customer support needs improvement. After efiling my return, the IRS sent me a letter stating that they needed additional information on one of the forms that I had filled out. Being unable to get through to the IRS, I opted to speak with someone at TurboTax. While I was connected within 30 minutes, the person at the other end of the call was clueless about my situation. I was told that my call was being transferred to a tax expert, and that I would only be on hold for a few minutes.

My few minutes of hold time ended up being well over 2 hours, at which time I gave up. Subsequently, I have still been unable to get through to anyone in the know at TurboTax, and when I call the number provided to me by the IRS, I am met with a recording that states that they are unable to accept calls due to extremely high call volume. This is despite the tax filing season having ended.

The bottom line is that while this software is great, if you cannot get through to a knowledgeable person in customer support, you are in trouble. Since your only other alternative is to call the IRS, and they are never able to accept calls, you are left in a no win situation.
summary: Product itself is good, but customer service leaves a lot to be desired ~ Almost as bad as the IRS

The basic essentials are covered in this package providing word processing, spreadsheets and presentations. Installation from the USB stick is a simple task.

Corel Home Office is a fine product for its price point. The applications look and operate much like their Microsoft Office [2007] counterparts and provide adequately comparable functionality  there are fewer transitions for presentations, fewer charts for spreadsheets, less complex word processing features, a slightly less streamlined and featurefilled interface. Core features and tools are included; most of what is lacking would be missed primarily by the power user.

It is a fine product for smallscale business or for anyone unwilling to she will out big bucks for productivity software  not a bad choice for students on a budget.

Transitioning to and from a larger suite is easy enough: Corel Write's "Tools" menu encapsulates some of the tools you find on Word's "Mailings" and "Review" tabs; the "Insert" menu contains trimmed down "Reference" tab features.  These dissimilarities are characteristic of the entire suite.

If your small business does mass mailings or if you are tackling any largescale writing projects, you might do better with a more advanced suite whose convenience features could quickly add up to countless hours of saved time. If you are an individual needing a productivity suite with a small footprint at a good price, I think Corel Home Office Personal  Business should satisfy.

There is a lot to like in this this small and simple suite, but it is not comprehensive nor is it compatible with any of Microsoft's products. Since Word, Outlook and Excel are enterprise standards, it is important to have a compatible office suite. With Wordperfect, this is simply not the case. Wordperfect chokes on the simplest VB scripts, is not compatible with Office tables and macros and such a foreign interface that any reasonably qualified office worker would find it a hassle. It is an XMLbased word processor, however, and this is good for writers/workers who are also capable XML programmers. I have never had a publisher, editor or evaen a college course that allows the WP format in any setting. The reveal codes is a neat gimmick but it is only helpful because formatting Wordperfect documents is so difficult to start with I am speaking as a secretary and publisher myself. If you want your office production to operate smoothly and easily for all of your workers, WordPerfect is not an option. The bottom line is that WP is not easy compatible, or as thorough as any version of Microsoft Office. If you care about compatibility and your company's bottom line, spend an extra $50 and get the suite from Microsoft.

On the other hand, if you have no need for compatibility or efficient production, get Wordperfect, it is smooth, goodlooking and is wellsupported by Corel who continue to improve as a company owned by Microsoft.
summary: great suite but incompatible with business apps.

I think this drive is pretty awesome, but I still do not know why it has issues with my MacBook Pro. I suspect its a Mac OS issue, coupled with a hardware glitch, but I cannot trust the computer to not crash when it goes to sleep with the computer closed. At least not with the SSD inside. Never had the problem with an HHD.

So now I shut down anytime I want to close the computer up for a while, unless I know Ill be back within a few hours. Fortunately this SSD is really really fast, so boot times are consistently below 15 seconds, and often closer to 12 seconds.

So if you want to speed up your computer, consider that your old mechanical drive is probably what is holding you back and get one of these. Its a great product. I Have used mine for over a year and have not had a failure, plus I have two that I put in enclosures USB3 and thunderbolt to have really fast external drives. My externals are faster than an internal HDD. One caveat: make sure you have the latest fast bus speed to take advantage of the SSD performance. If you have a slow bus, it does matter how fast you pedal.

Who does not love those awesome paper figures like the swan, flowers, or even complex geometric shapes known as origami? They Have been a hit for a long time in my  house, and so to get this Orchid Origami Paper filled with the special origami paper plus instructions was perfect!

Origami was always a project that I never thought I could get a grasp on, even though I always admire the pieces I find at museums or even at craft shows. Like, my brain understands its just paper and folding, but my hands never catch on!

What I really liked about this set is I have a choice of 10 colors in the same pack, plus step by step visual instructions! And that seemed to be the ticket, instead of just reading the words or following only pictures with no explanation. It took a few tries to get the hang of it, but now my office and mantle are filled with various pieces of art.

I enjoyed how the paper folded for the different pieces we were making. It held its shape very well but did not tear like some other kinds we have tried in the past. And the nice thing about the eBook that comes with the paper is you can start right away since no other supplies are required.

This LED camping lantern is really nice and the silicone is very soft.  The top can be taken off and charged, but it can be topped off my Solar power via the solar panel on it.  There are three modes in which the light will work, high, low and flashing.  It puts off a nice blueish light due to the silicone part of the lamp.  Oh but the silicone is hollow so you can store things in it.  Yep you can keep things you might need to keep dry in it and it will keep them safe from water or anything else that might harm them. The handle can be removed on one side if you need to do that.  And as I said earlier the silicone is soft so it can actually be folded into a more compact size for storage.  Over all this is a really nice multipurpose lantern that can be used for pretty much anything you might need a light and storage for.

I received this item at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. While my review might be an initial one, if something changes while I am using the product I will update my review.

Cry, which the title suggests is a counterpart to Scream, is actually the new Man In The Mirror; a fact you might not recognize until the end. Change the world, is the final message. Aesthetically both philanthropy anthems are about the same, but the message sounded more urgent in 1987. This adapter may have saved me from needing to buy a new TV set.  I have to say that while not "top end" its anything but "Cheap, garbage" that you will not know if it will even last a day of use.  I have a few RCA devices hooked up into a switch multi in and one out where the out of THAT adapter goes to the RCA inputs of this unit.... I have had NO problem on any device and to be 100 honest ... the picture quality is BETTER then when I had RCA connectors directly into the RCA connectors of my TV the picture was darker than it should have been and not as sharp as it is now.... eventually the RCA connectors ON THE tv "went bad" and while I am sure I could get the skills to fix it ... this Adapter allows me not to have to worry about fixing it for now

The one issue is that "switch" inside the unit that changes from say your TV tuner to the RCA device when that device is turned on ... It is just my personal opinion but I would rather have an 'on/off" switch for this or an "RCA/Coax" switch on the side but that is not to say the automatic switcher is not working, so far It has been NO PROBLEM

If you need a device like this, I would recommend it as like me a simple adapter like this could save you from having to buy an entirely new TV for example.

This cargo bag is very durable and spacious.  Heavily constructed, strong zipper, very reinforced at the strap anchoring points.  Amazing capacity.

Used this bag on a cargo carrier behind our vehicle on a 1600 mile trip.  Drove though some heavy rain storms and nothing in the bag became the slightest bit damp.
The straps held it in place perfectly.

The bag held 4 beach chairs, 2 beach umbrellas, 3 skim boards, several bags of food, luggage, and odds and ends, with room to spare.

After using this bag one time, I will not be afraid to use it again.
love it.

I got my first Shubb capo when playing a gig. A previous touring band had left it behind and was not coming back. Score.

If you plan to perform and care about staying in tune, buy this capo.

It adjusts so you can get the right tension wherever placed on whatever neck. On my acoustic I loosen it a few turns capoing at 8, tighten up a bit capoing at one. Easy and fast, can do it between songs no problem.

It applies even, straight down tension all at once, not a "pinch" like the Keyser style does. Yes, you should still check your tuning, your guitar setup/intonation would have to be flawless to not need to, but you will have about 1 of the tuning issues with a Shubb that you would have with a Keyser.

Okay  I get it. The Keyser clips onto your headstock so easy. If you want to pass a guitar around a campfire and make noise, use your Keyser. If you want to play guitar, buy one of these or something of a similar design.  Yes, you are going to lose it. And then you are going to buy another one. And it will be worth it. And maybe somebody else will find your other one and they will sound better. Everybody wins.

I already owned a black Elchim hair dryer for over a decade. Never had a problem with it. A friend of mine needed a hair dryer and I gave her a nondescript one I had  in my Guest Bathroom. Then I saw that this was offered on Amazon and ordered it in white. It is identical to the one from 2001, which is now in my Guest Bathroom for all my guests to use.  The newer model has a tad more power and is both attractive , easy to use , not loaded with unnecessary features. It is AS exactly described and dries my very thick long hair to perfection very quickly. There is a cold switch if you need to have your temperature a little lower, Medium as well as High for heat . Also three variables for speed. It is Made in Italy... What more can I say? This is the best hair dryer you can spend your money on and a worthy investment. Enjoy!

I am a professional musician and make my living playing sax among other things.  I have played for thirty years.  I have tried many different types of reeds, and I have never found one I am 100 happy with.  But I seem to always come back to Rico Royals.  Why?  It is simply a matter of consistency vs. cost.  Out of a box of 10 Rico Royals, I might pull two or three bad reeds, plus a couple "iffy" ones I can break in with effort.  That is really not bad, for the price.  I have tried more expensive reeds, but for me, they just do not seem worth the cost.  These play fine,  and have a fairly consistent strength from reedtoreed except the bad ones, of course.  Overall, I simply think Rico Royals provide the best value, whether you are a beginner or a pro like me.
summary: Keep Coming Back to Rico Royal

Like its parent magazine, the photos are professionally done and large. The content of the magazine is even more impressive. Nearly every page our son will come and tell us another "did you know this" fact.
Many topics are a twopage spread so that you can hold it open and see the whole topic at a glance  very nice. There are also some jokes, mazes and other brief entertaining items as well.
The magazine is a slick glossy around 32 pages and very nice. If you are looking for an upgrade from "Highlights", this would be it.
Great applications if you have a Mac.  Very compatible with mac but if you are familiar with Microsoft Office, the transition is a little difficult.

Outstanding glove and padding for leanover riding style on ATBstyle handlebars.  I bought the fingerless version of these gloves and after a couple months of wearing them 90 minutes daily with no issues, I bought these to complement them.  Even in 100degree heat they are not uncomfortable.  The mesh on the back does its job on that score.

About fitment:  I have found after two purchases the sizing formula for me is to use the size chart provided by the manufacturer and go one size up from what the measurements tell me.  I usually wear a 2XL bicycle glove and I only wear an XL from this manufacturer using the above method.  In my case the XLs are possibly the best glove fit ever in terms of proper finger length, palm size... everything.  Very pleased.  I will be socking away an extra pair to make sure I have them after I wear these out.

I do a lot of daily riding and I go through gloves quick.  Its really nice to find a quality product that costs so little compared to some of the big brand names that have come apart on me after a couple of months of daily rides.
summary: In my case the XLs are possibly the best glove fit ever in terms of proper finger length

John Mueller has a wonderful ability to take the layperson through a highly complicated and nuanced issue without dumbing things down, and at the same time showing wonderful scholarship. "Nuclear Obsession" really challenged a lot of my preconceived notions and assumptions, and I am so delighted that I read this. A great piece of persuasive and informative nonfiction, everyone should read this!

I only issued a three star rating to raise a caution flag with this harp.  It is not a typical diatonic harp, and if you are expecting it to sound and perform like one, you will be disappointed.

It is a fine, wellmade partiallyvalved harmonica, and if you desire to experiment with a valved harp, the Promaster Valved Harp is a fine choice.  But, to reiterate, if you like the sound of standard diatonic harp and want a harmonica that will perform like one, this is not the harmonica you are looking for.  It can be harsh and unpredictable in tone and its reeds can sometimes buzz, blurt, or honk abruptly.  I am an experienced harp player and perform regularly. And I have no doubt an experienced player could have some fun with this instrument.  And If you are interested in this harp as a musical experiment, go for it.  But, if you want a good diatonic harp that will play and perform as you expect one to, this harmonica will be a squawky, quirky disappointment.  Order the regular Promaster or Crossover, or Special 20, or Bluesmaster, or Olive, or, to save some money, a Big River.
summary: Caution.  A fine harp, but not a conventional one.

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

I would never have tackled this novel if my daughter had not given it to us for Christmas and kept asking if we had read it.  So when we needed a good book to read aloud in the spring, my husband and I began Our Mutual Friend.  What a treat!  I am amazed by any novelist's ability to create an array of characters and circumstances and then weave them all together in surprising ways.  Dickens not only  does this with great skill; he is also a caustic satirist of great humor, an absolute genius of character study, and a spirited social critic to boot.  When the wicked finally get their comeuppance, those who apply the verbal medicine do so with an articulate fervor that is deeply satisfying. Not always an easy read, this book is definitely worth the effort.

My husband loves this shaving kit. Would he or I ever actually pay for it? No.

$120.00 is a hefty price to pay for such a set. You get:
1 Shaving brush super soft
2 Preshave oil the size of about 1/3 of a cup
3 Shaving cream about a cup
4 Aftershave balm 1/2 a cup
I estimate, if you use these products every day, the set will probably last you about 2 months, especially shaving cream which fills up the biggest just but is very fluffly and light and will surely be used up very quickly.

Granted, all these products of a great quality. My husband loves the feel of his soft and smooth skin after his shaves. The scent lavender is very sophisticated, light and soothing no AXE and Old Spicelike fragrance overload hear. He overall enjoys the whole shaving experience, even though it does take extra time over his usual routine.

This would definitely be an extra special gift for a man. If you can and want to afford it.

Update: after just a few uses the brush started to lose hairs. I expected it to have a better quality than this.
summary: A great product (if you can afford it)

I used to use an enzyme product that was produced locally, but they dropped out of business several years back. Nature's Miracle is almost as good as it at removing odours, and much better at removing stains. It is all I buy now.

Since I have 3 dogs ranging in age from puppy to supersenior 17, pet stains are at least a monthly occurrence. Nature's Miracle and a carpet cleaner are life savers and work great together. Seriously, I have had 2 dogs having explosive diarrhea at the same time before, I would have gone mad trying to clean that up without NM. NM is also reasonably priced compared to other enzymatic cleaners and is cheapest here on Amazon.

I definitely recommend this product to you if you have cats, dogs, exotics, or even children. Your carpets will thank you.

text: At some point, whether we like it or not we are going to run into a conflict of one form or another with a coworker and because I Have always been interested in psychology and the sources of conflict, not to mention having a desire to understand conflict and how to resolve it on amicable terms regardless of the situation. I decided to do a little research into conflict resolution and see what I could come up with so that I could add these skills to my psychological and social interaction toolbox should a conflict ever arise in my workplace between myself and a coworker. I stumbled across this book while serving through the Kindle section of Amazons website and I Am glad I chose to download it. This book does an excellent job of explaining the sources and/or reasons as to why conflicts can and do occur in the workplace between two or more coworkers. It does a solid job of explaining the definition of conflict as well as offering skills in understanding and empathy for the other person when it comes to resolving conflicts by the time you finish the book, you will have a solid understanding and the tools necessary to understand conflict and hopefully bring your workplace conflict to an amicable solution between yourself and your coworkers. I feel fairly confident that this book will be able to do that for me so I Am sure it can do the same for you. I am very pleased with my purchase and would recommend as a starting point to anyone dealing with conflict in their workplace.
summary: Laying the solid foundation for workplace conflict resolution skills

text:
These are very pretty brushes.  The handles are much prettier than pictured the wood has a nice grain and has been well stained and polished.  They are not that thick these are fairly thin handled. They are 11 inches long, including the filbert.
The filbert is copper per the ad, but I cannot test that  they appear to be nickel, or nickel plated, so please note that if you have allergies.  They are double crimped.

The bristles are well crimped and the entire brush is tight. They have a good bit of bounce, and maintain a good point when wet with oils.  I did not test them with water colors as I paint in oil  acrylics mainly.  They have a fair bit of bounce and are easy to control.
I am not sure what the mix is, it appears to be natural though.  I do not see any synthetic fibers in the brushes that I received.  Not that it matters to me, today's synthetics are just fine to me.  These are nice brushes in this price range.  Just one of this quality would cost more than 7.99 at my local art supply store.

I did receive a sample set for purposes of evaluation and review.
summary: Tight overall, well crimped, fair bit of spring, maintains point when wet.

Lifehouse went a totally different direction on this album, away from the pop oriented sound on their debut album, and onto a more mature, dynamic sound.  My first few listens were judgmental, and I did not give the album a fair chance to shine, because I was expecting more poppy hooks and rhythms.  After I let that out of my head, I listened to some pretty excellent music.
Without a doubt, the two best songs on the album are "How Long" and "The Beginning", two of the last songs on the album.  They show maturity as a band, and there is a Pink Floyd kind of feel to them, as the songs make you drift off and you feel like everything will be OK upon listening, and shortly thereafter.
"Just Another Name", "Anchor", and "Am I ever Going To Find out" are other stand out tracks, and sort of have a pop sound to them, with catchy hooks.
Jason Wade is a brilliant writer, and has a unique voice.  I look forward to Lifehouse's future work, as they are on the verge of putting out a masterpiece with their current evolution.
What can I say?  It is a windshield wiper, it works.  Have not tried it in the snow yet, but seems to work well for rain.

Do not forget your scarf as you head into icy waters with a protagonist hell bent on taking the whole ship down.
What works so well with this novel is the psychotic breakdown of events as told by the narrator. The way he mesmerizes the reader with his illogical psychopathy    one simply cannot believe that he is going to do what he does; and this is the essence of the story, that he just keeps going one step further into dreaded villanous territory; every description including the weather notations, almost seem to advance like blankets of ice hell bent on covering every crime he commits. I kept waiting for him to slip up and really get it; but he does not, and that is the gristle of the novel. The writing is so pure it is as of standing on the bow of a ship forging through icy water; pure grit. Mankell is in fine form, and no one can touch him. An absolute stunner of a novel.
summary: Seafarer's journey finds craggy shore of madness

text: "The Messenger: The Story of Joan of Arc" is nothing more than a bythenumbers film created with liberal use of "The Complete Idiot's Guide to Directing the Medeival Epic." I have been vastly entertained by director Luc Besson's work in the past, but this film is a plodding, goredrenched nod toward Mel Gibson's vastly superior "Braveheart." "The Messenger" completely lacks all of the finer emotions that make an epic story compelling, despite the true nature of the people and some of the events. "The Messenger" also revels in its violence and grit, rather than trying to create something realistic and more convincing. Milla Jovovich turns in an annoying performance as the shrieking saint, who does not inspire her troops so much as berate them in her holierthanthou manner. The film's topics are interesting was Joan really a saint who could speak to God, or was she just insane and driven by rage?, but the execution is poor. On top of this, the scripting and dialogue is just plain bad. If you want an epic, I suggest looking elsewhere. Maybe somebody out there will make a better picture about this fascinating historic figure.

"NIST Traceable thermometers" include a certificate of calibration; which from what I have seen have an accuracy of 1 degree centigrade compared to / 4 degrees or more for others.

Control3 company is an NIST standard manufacturer who rebrands its products for other companies.  They have a page of distributors on their site; unfortunately, none appear on Amazon.

Regarding the AcuRite product, my wife bought this model about a year ago.  It worked well until the battery needed to be changed.

One of the "suckers" had come loose from the window.  After changing the battery, I cleaned the suckers and the window with alcohol, then put the thing up.  The suckers were noticeably flattened from the time spent in the shade on a north window, out of direct sunlight, but it seemed to stay in place.

A few hours later, I happened to notice it was missing.  Went outside and found that it had fallen on some rocks,  broken and unusable.

Until its demise, it worked well.  Or seemed to.  It was always at variance with the local weather stations by as much as ten degrees.  There is several factors that can account for these differences, but I wanted something a little more trustworthy, short of a thousand dollar setup.

Spent several hours looking at critiques on Amazon, did not like anything.  Found a product elsewhere with the same display for about $10 more that not only is certified, but uses a velcro attachment for the window.

If you need a highly pigmented, heavy concealer, I recommend you try this one.  I am very happy with it, but I might need to try another shade. This Vichy shaving gel is the thickest, creamiest shaving cream I have ever used and yet it rinses off the blade with ease. In the past, when I have used thicker shaving gels, the tradeoff is always that the cream is so thick that I have to spend a lot of time rinsing the blade between strokes. This cream somehow dissolves immediately when you get the blade wet.

I have been using this with Gillette Fusion 5 blades and am very happy with the results. I have very sensitive skin and have not had any rashes or irritations with this product. The smell is mild but fresh.

One piece of advice: a little bit goes a long way. You can probably do your whole face by starting with a nickelsized dollop. So make sure not to spray too much because it keeps expanding as you put it on your face! And given the high price, it is good that a little goes a long way!

text: This is the Ray I like bestthe RB chart topper of the mid 50'sWhen he belonged only to Black America. Great mid 50's top 10's like "I have got a woman", "Comeback", one of my personal faves "A fool for you", "Drown in my own tears", "Greenbacks", and "What I would say" were all big sellers in every African American community and on every juke box from Harlem to Miami to LA to Kansas City. His vocal styling incorporates the sound of Charles Brown and Percy Mayfield with a whole lot of Ray thrown in for thickener. This is the Ray that only Black America knew at the time which does not make these songs any less powerful but instead full of rich substance. "A fool for you" is one of the all time great RB singles of that wonderful decade called the 50's. Another priceless piece of Rock n Soul history. It was not watered down top 40 pop radio material but that is why this stuff is so addictive to listen to. By the way if you want to hear soul music being single handedly invented listen to 1955's "Comeback" and "A fool for you". This was not the sound of RB in 1955 and these songs predated James and The Flames 1956 classic "Please,Please,Please. In fact "Comeback" and "A fool for you" could have easily been released in 1965 and neither song would have stood out like a sore thumb right smack dab in the middle of the soul music explosion. There is proof in this cd that Brother Ray single handedly invented Soul music.
summary: A major R&B star before the pop hits came

"Message" is the first Nancy Drew Pc game that I have tried and I was very favorably impressed. The game is literate: it is not directed towards very young players per se and young people will have to read well to appreciate the many tidbits of literature scattered around the Victorian mansion. I am 76 and could read them quite well. Happy face or smiley

The sets are beautifully rendered in elegant color and the Chinese antiques are a feast for the eye. The characters are well animated with gestures that are completely natural. The voices are good, too.

"Message" is Nirvana for the Point and Click enthusiasts. No expert mouse maneuvers are required such as jumping into a fast moving bucket in "Uru." Nothing is timed. We take our PC games very seriously and it is an affront to the ego when one is not fast enough to perform an intricate mouse gyration. In fact, I could get stage fright just looking at a high ledge I knew I had to vault upon and therefore could not perforn at all.

"Message" is scary. This is by no means a plain dish of vanilla. There are creaks and groans and shadowy forms passing in the night. Atmosphere plus. And you can wander around just as you wish poking into this and that and getting a delicious scary thrill when a curtain suddenly billows into your face with hissing sound.

Captions are provided which are very helpful as the characters speak rapidly. All in all "Message in a Haunted Mansion" is a very solid piece of work for all ages.
summary: You are never too old to go sleuthing!

I was really excited about this little thing and bought it at other place, but returned the day after.
Two things.

1. It has TRS jack the 3rd contact is used for charging, Depending on the type of socket used in your guitar, it may not work. Guitar may "expect" ground where the charging contact is positioned.
For example, it does not work with PRS piezzon equipped models I have P22, piezzon output works with this, but main out "MAG/MIX" just does not. Google your guitar model before buying.

2. It uses 2.4 GHz to transmit signal. I assume it just uses WiFi. And if you have your WiFi router close to G10, it does not work. They mention it in the manual it should be 3 meters apart, but who reads manual before buying, right? For most of the people it may be Ok, but if you have WiFi router next to where you plan to use G10 like I did, do not buy.
summary: Does not work with every guitars

We moved to a house without a mailbox, previous owners used this place as a weekend getaway, never received mail here. So when moving in, we needed to get a mailbox. Since I never needed to buy a mailbox before, I came to Amazon to shop. We wanted something big, something that could receive packages and not just letters. And we wanted something more than a mailboxonapost.

Well this is it! It does everything we need, and it has some style too. It sits on top of a 4x4 inch wood post which is secured in the ground. That was the hardest part of the installation  getting the 4x4 wood post installed and straight! Assembly was easy. No, there were not any predrilled holes. But there were dimples in the plastic that make starting the selftapping screws really easy!

There is a door in the floor that you open up for the letter carrier to drop your mail or smaller packages. Note, you have to do this. The letter carrier will not move the floor panel for you. And this is just for mail. UPS is not going to deliver to your PO Box anyway.

Parents magazine is a very good publication about raising kids to be happy, healthy adults. It offers some good advice about the task of parenthood, illustrating the hard work and rewards that go hand in hand if parents perform their role in the best possible manner.

I like this magazine as a whole, but there are a few things that potential readers need to know about before they pick up a copy to read. First of all, the articles in Parents magazine deal mostly with younger children, below twelve years of age. You will not find much of value in this magazine if you have teenagers. It is intended more for families with youngsters.

Another thing about this magazine that makes it less practical than it otherwise would be is the suggestions for family activities. The ideas presented here are all pretty good, but the problem is that the majority of them involve outlays of cash and/or time that are unrealistic for most families. I can agree, for example, that adding a game room would make a nice addition to one's house and would add tremendously to a family's time spent together. But how many among us can afford a home addition? Parents magazine talks about activities and enhancements like this in an unrealistic way, making them seem much simpler and easier to implement than they really are.

Aside from distractions like that, however, Parents is a very good magazine to read. It is one of the longest magazines you can buy, with 200 to 300 pages per issue. Add to that the low subscription price, a few pages of coupons, and the generally sound parental advice and you have all the makings of a good magazine for young families.
summary: Raising Kids in the Modern World

text:
This is coming from the perspective of a longtime fan of FFIV.  This has been my favorite game of all time since I first played it, I think in 1993.  I have played all the remakes.  I am not going to be too longwinded here, most people playing this game and reading the review have probably played it before in earlier incarnations.  This is a good remake, but for me, not perfect.  My main complaints:

 The translation, while for the most part is very good, differs from the original in a few places for the worse.  Specifically, a key confrontation about halfway through the game lost much of its impact for me due to the translation change.
 The music lags.  When something happens in game, it takes 12 seconds of disc access before the accompanying music starts.  In some cases this really reduces the impact of the moment.  For example, when a character joins your party, you get the text notification, then 2 seconds later the exciting music plays, woo!  Sometimes the music is cutoff before it ends because of this lag issue.
 I wish they had not changed many of the magic animations.  I thought Firaga/Blizzaga/Thundaga animations from the original were awesome.  The new ones are cool, but why change it?

These are pretty minor issues.  In many ways, the game is very archaic.  Most people that play this will do it for the nostalgia, and for that reason it does not disappoint.  The graphical overhaul was nice, though not a vast improvement over the original.  Definitely worth $30 for fans of the original, especially if they did not get to play After Years on the Wii.

I purchased these knurled knobs mainly for the price. It seemed like all the other ones were much more expensive. I did not even pay attention to the "lock nut" in the description. I did not even know they made these with nylon locking nuts. While I have used nylock nuts on quite a few items where I do not want the nut coming off,  like on some kind of a pivoting joint one of the main reasons for ordering knurled nuts to begin with is because they are tightened and removed frequently. A nylon bushing does not make sense here, and to me is just a bad design. Not sure what they were thinking.

I just took 0.25 x 20 tap that I happen to have, and got rid of the nylon, but it takes a while, and something I did not anticipate having to do. I like the knobs well enough that I am not going to bother to send them back, but I think the manufacturers should reconsider the locking part. It is really inappropriate for knurled knobs.

This headset is comfortable and provides great sound quality. The range appears to be basically the same as that of the PS4 controllers, providing clean signal for about 3040 feet around the console. The inset mic works very well and I enjoyed not having some grasping antennae threatening my lips while communicating with my friends.
My main qualm is that the battery life seems to be even shorter than the PS4 controllers; while running a raid in Destiny I was forced to quickly switch to a wired headset as the battery in the headset gave out, while I still had two bars of juice left in the controller, despite both having been taken off the charger at the same time.

UPDATE

I need to update this review and downgrade my original 4 star review to two. After two months of using this headset, the plastic headband began to crack and quickly came apart entirely. Unfortunately, this headset fails the durability test in a big way.
summary: A comfortable, unobtrusive gaming accessory that is sadly too fragile for regular use

I wore these for a trail race in the mountains on a hot day. Previously I had gotten a rash from the tall weeds and grasses along the same trail, and these prevented that on race day. They also served their intended purpose of preventing sunburn and helping me cool. When dry, I noticed a cooling sensation in even a slight breeze, but I poured water on them when the temperature started to climb and it was like heaven.

A lot of runners wear arm warmers in cool weather, but it seems that very few have discovered cooling sleeves for hot weather. I got some strange looks and comments like, 'Are not you hot in those?' but I think they will catch on.

I have another pair of arm coolers that is more like compression fabric. I think the fabric of the Eclipse brand is more effective and is easier to dampen. I also like that they cover my hands.
summary: These provided three benefits for a hot trail race

This magazine has a lower cover price than some of its competitors, and makes up for it with a massive amount of ads. A few ads contain coupons, for those that like to cut those little things out unfortunately they are hardly ever for anything I want !. The paper is also a lot thinner than the higher priced home/garden publications, and the photographs do not reproduce that well on it.
On the bright side, there are many nice deacute;cor ideas, and simply terrific recipes.
Taking the October 2003 edition as an example, Fall colors and produce are the theme. It has some ideas on how to display gourds, and an article on a community pumpkin patch, from the June planting by 140 neighbors and friends in a 6000 square ft. area, to harvest time.
There are numerous articles on remodeling, "Foolproof Potted Plants", on the joys of having hardy succulents in your home, and a lovely piece with lots of photographs on actor Peter Strauss' gorgeous Ojai, California garden.
The best article of all, is "The Magic of Soup", and some of these recipes are so good they might end up in your family for generations. They are simple to prepare, with easy to find ingredients, and will make a healthy, hearty meal for those frosty days ahead. Also included with the recipes is the preparation and cooking time, and nutritional statistics.
As someone who writes a lot of notes and cards, I appreciate the final page which is about letter writing, and how this vanishing form of communicating is good for the soul.
All things considered, this magazine gives good value, and is meant for those of us who do not live in a mansion or have hours to devote to a single recipe.

I bought this bronzer because in the package it did not look the least bit orange.  However, upon application it was most definitely orange.  Packaging can be deceptive!  This is disappointing because every bronzer I have tried thus far, from high end to low end, has ended up orange, if not immediately then after a few hours of wear.  I guess it is that I do not like the look of bronzer,  I prefer just blush.  What a waste of cash!  I wanted something that would sculpt my cheekbones and give me a nude look.  But it is as orange as can be and makes me look way too made up.  Now I have a somewhat expensive makeup item that I cannot do a thing with.  I bought it on vacation in San Francisco and cannot return it anywhere.  What a shame!  I will find someone to give it to.  I simply have no use for yet another bronzer that is as orange as a pumpkin!  I definitely do not recommend this product.

I really like this fragrance. It is relatively muted and I feel that it leaves a rich aroma. Kind of interesting that some reviews comment on the longevity of the product. Understand that this product is a Eau de Toilette. Eau de Toilette sprays are 515 and last typically for about 3 hours. A perfume is 1520 and can last for 58 hours, so know what you are buying and how long you want your fragrance to last.

The bottle itself has a nice black leather wrap. The spritz is not a huge blast, which I have found to be an issue in some sprayer bottles. You will not be overpowered with one shot. I typically spray into the air and walk into the spritz so it is not too much. Do this in my undershirt, mainly aiming for the base of the neck and chest area. This allows products to combine with your natural pheromones, producing a unique scent which is only you. A dab under your ears is great when your date is leaning in close to you. If you have dry skin, you can use a bit more since your skin absorbs more of the product.

I will just say that I like the scent, colognes smell differently on everyone for the reason I mentioned above. So it is not much point getting too much into the layers of the product which the manufacturer has already laid out.

Okay, here is how the marketing mentality works. Take an already released album, add new tracks and the fans, even the ones who bought the original, will rush out and buy it. Right? Absolutely.  Sure, there will be those who will be mad as hell. Why are we being treated this way? We are being cheated!

I suppose there may be a slight argument for that sort of thinking, but not, in my opinion, where Blake Shelton's MORE PURE BS is concerned. His hit, "Home," is, all by itself, well worth the extra money and even the addition of what seems a duplicate album to my collection. "Home" is quite easily the finest song that Shelton has recorded and the other two new tracks, "Chances" and "I Cannot Walk Away," are wonderful additions to the excellent tracks on the original PURE BS album.

Besides, if you are really bent about the prospect of having to buy the new album, simply download the new tracks from Amazon for a nominal fee, add them to the original album and have a great listening experience.

With PURE BS and the new MORE PURE BS, Shelton truly emerges as a bona fide Country star and I will expect a lot more great stuff from him in the future.

I was questioning the efficiency of my central air conditioner, but really had no definitive data to confirm my belief.  I decided to spend the money on this device to help me determine what was happening.  By measuring the temperature at different air registers I was able to see that the unit, in fact, was not performing well.  Since it was over 17 years old the decision was made to replace it.  Again, I was able to measure the performance of the new system.  Average temperature was 10 degrees lower at each register with the new unit.  That made the cost of the thermometer well justified.  I am sure I can find other things to measure that may expose opportunities to save money on heating or cooling.  Easy to use and seems acceptably accurate.  I agree with another reviewer that it was challenging to get the battery cover off.
summary: Not a necessity, but very useful

15yearsold acolyte, Quentin is wakened by a commotion in the temple of Ariel one night. A very badly wounded knight had stumbled in to the temple. His name is Ronsardhe is one of my favorite characters and he has an extremely important message for his Queen Alinea. Ronsard asks if anyone could go and give the message for him. Quentin agrees to go but he can no longer return to the temple. The knight tells him to go to a hermit named Durwin and to give the message without stopping. So, mounted on Ronsard's horse Balder, Quentin rides to Durwin's house. He meets Durwin and also Durwin's friend, Theido. Theido and Quentin rides to Askelon where the Queen was, but they are caught by the crafty coward, Prince Jaspin. The Prince is the King's brother and he wants to have the crown. Quentin escapes and goes to the Queen. The message he gave was that King Eskevar had been captured by the evil necromancer, Nimrood. Then, the Queen, Durwin, and Quentin meets Theido. He had escaped and together they ride to save the King. Quentin learns of a new God, the Most High and he turns away from Ariel and the other gods to worship the true one God. Durwin teaches him more about God on the way.
Can they rescue the King from Nimrood? Can they win the battle with Prince Jaspin's 100,000 men with their 10,000?

A fascinating discovery for a European: there is a black upper class in America  in the book they are sometimes called "The Gold Coast". But they still feel marginalized, full of rage and suspicion, isolated within their professional communities.
They distrust the liberals, but for historical reasons cannot trust the conservatives  or those among them who convert to the conservative because. The father of the narrator  a ClarenceThomaslike judge  did and was subsequently embroiled in a confirmation battle that destroyed his reputation and his family.
His death means trouble for his son; a lot of people want to know about the "arrangements" of the dead judge. They are a riddle  a chess problem with a hidden message  and they mean trouble. As if the hero had not enough of that already: with his ambitious but unfaithful wife, at his university, with his family history and his life in general.
The story is fascinating as a glimpse into life on the Gold Coast, but it rather fails as a mystery. The narrator cheats, because he discovers something, acts and then tells the reader two or three chapters later what and when he found out. Besides: the plot is either too arcane  the big conspiracy that involves them all: liberals and conservatives  or too obvious and sometimes facilitating between those extremes
Still: this is a book to be recommended.

text: These boots are great and affordable. I work doing organics recycling, aka composting and that means I am constantly walking around on fairly muddy sites. The wedge sole is great, they keep traction well and Idon't track mud everywhere. They are easy to clean and look nice. The white soles are now brown, but it is a work boot after all. They are a bit big, I probably could have done with a 7.5 instead of the 8 that I chose. I do a little trick with the laces to keep them on my feet more securely. After lacing them up to the final eyelet, go normally around the first hooks. Then, take the laces and wind them around each other 3x and pull tight. Then loop them around the last hook and do your normal knot and bow. It helps to keep them locked more securely to my heel.
summary: These boots are great and affordable

Did my homework on these networkthroughyourhouseholdwiring things, and was skeptical.  Found reviews of the Corinex HomeNet Powerline HD200 adapters, found lots of either onestar or fivestar ratings, and lots of sob stories about how poor the installation instructions were, and what a terrible ordeal it was to get them installed and working properly.  I needed what they offer, though, so I ordered a pair and braced myself for a terrible experience.

I have to say that the "2 Minute Installation" note on the front of the package turned out to be a significant understatement.  It took me at least five minutes to get the adapters cabled, plugged into wall outlets, and synced.  I did exactly what the instructions said to do  six easy steps  and everything worked perfectly.  I did not have to touch any of our network settings.  I can now stream Netflix movies on my PS3 in an area of our house that has been a dead zone for the signal from our wireless router.  I had resigned myself to spending hours screwing around with these things, and now I can watch movies instead!  Could not be happier with this product.

I bought this blade because I was making a box with keyed miter joints and I needed a blade that had truly flat bottomed cuts. I did not want to spend a fortune on a blade that I would only use for this kind of joinery.

This blade is a true FTG  not like the Freud glue line rip blade Frued does make one like this though

The cuts came out beautifully and the joints are excellent.

There was an added bonus in that this is a full kerf blade and the cut is exactly 1/8". This made it very easy to calculate the key spacings and to account for the cut when I finally sliced the top off the box.

This would have been much more difficult with a narrow kerf blade.

This is a wellwritten book concerning a subgenre of women in the late 18th to early 20th centuries: the courtesans, or women who used their sexual allure to attract men to give them financial backing for their extravagent lifestyles. It is a fascinating glimpse into another type of life, and what amazed me is the avidity with which the careers of these women were followed by the majority of people of the time. In an age that did not boast supermarket tabloids, the "respectable" newspapers ocasionally had articles about these women and their exploits. There was, to be truthful, a double standard operating here: a woman courtesan was not necessarily welcome everywhere in "polite society", but a man who dallied openly outside of his marriage vows had no such shunning problem. Have we advanced more in our supposedly "enlightened" days? I guess so, but it is not much of a gain for us, I believe. Read this book to get a feel for a style of life that is gone now, but is very interesting all the same.

Photo Director 4 is a good product for people starting to use photo editing software. It is easy to use. Handling multiple photos and organizing them is easy. Plus, there are many special effects that make photo editing fun.

However, the program is not much better than many others on the market for less money. The program handles only JPEG, TIFF and RAW formats. While these are the ones most frequently used by amateur photographers, it is not satisfactory for a professional, or semiprofessional who also uses GIF and BMP. While not a major disadvantage, it is a limitation.

The program has several presets for enhancement of photos and more are available online. However, I found that they are usually too extreme for my photos, so I do not use them. Still, it is a major advantage to get additional enhancements on line.

This program is good for people just starting to use photo editing software but to be honest, there are cheaper alternatives available, some of them free. I use both Photo Director 4 and Power Director 11. The slideshow alternatives on Power Director are truly astonishing. I would like to see something like that on Photo Director. It would be a much more interesting product.

text:
I Have used primers in the past and have never seen much of an improvement.  Even with Clinique and Elizabeth Arden primers my makeup seams to evaporate from my face within a few hours.  But I have found that this Bliss primer actually does something.  When I use the Bliss primer I find that I still have makeup on my face when I get home from work about 12 hours after application.  My face gets very oily, and I find that the Bliss also holds down the shine amazingly well.  The Bliss keeps my makeup looking matte and uniform all day.

So 5 stars for the primer itself, but I do not like the sunscreen component as much.  The cream has a very white, opaque look that gives my skin a ghostly appearance.  Once I put the makeup on my color is fine, but this Primer is not something you could use without applying a serious amount of foundation on top of it.  The dispenser design is another big miss.  When I first opened the box I found that half the contents had leaked out.  Primer covered the inside of the box and the cap.  The dispenser has a twisting top that let us you turn the dispenser On or Off, but regardless of how I have it set, primer will come out if the bottle is squeezed.

I do like this primer so I probably buy it again, but I wish they would rethink the design of the dispenser.
summary: The primer keeps my foundation looking fresh for hours, but the design of dispenser is a big miss

I found this game to be quite fun. However it does fall short on a few points. The description does not exactly portray the gameplay and the controls can be difficult to get used to you. Once you get the controls worked out the game becomes more fun to play.

The problem with this openworld game style is there looks to be many different missions/styles, however after a while you realize they are all closely related. Most missions have you killing, hacking, running. I was hoping for a bit more variety, but it does have a leg up on the GTA series which i have played since the topdown views era.

My main takeaway from playing this game is this... just play it your own way. Yes the missions can be linear, but the world has a lot to explore. I can see this game occupying a good amount of playtime. Some gamers are comparing the shooting to Call of Duty, but that just does not make any sense. This game is most similar to the GTA franchise, if anything.

This was somewhat smaller than I expected it to be, but that is my fault as each size does come with measurements.  The fabric is this slick nylon/canvas type material that, while tough, is not very soft and is prone to some serious static electricity even after it was washed and dried with fabric softener.  I really like the memory foam quality, as it is not too soft, but still squishy enough that my dog enjoys it.  My dog is a 70 lb black lab mix who measures almost three feet long from the back of her head to her tail notch.  She DOES sleep curled up, so the bed works for her for the most part, but we had to supplement with a body pillow for her to be truly comfortable.  I have included photos to show how the bed looks.  We have put a plush blanket on the bed since then.  While I did mention that it was smaller than I expected, it does fit in the space I had to put it in, and my dog DOES use it and seems fairly happy with it.  Also, you can remove all the padding including in the tube in the top, as well as the memory foam. It comes with an extra protector to go around the memory foam mattress, which i thought was genius.  It is a well made bed, but I really wish they would chosen a softer, less staticy fabric which is why I marked it down from five to four stars.

2/9/16 Update:  The company emailed me letting me know that they were looking at different fabrics for their beds, as I am not the only one who would prefer something a bit less slick.
summary: Really well made and thought out bed, but slightly smaller than I thought it would be, and very slick fabric.

For most people's needs, this will suffice. If you are a highlyexperienced or professional user, you would do well to acquire the professional version of CorelDRAW. And to check your system against this product's requirements before buying. It may seem stingy of a company to put out a version like this, that is not fullyfeatured and not professionally usable, but that is the way it is. And Corel, in the world of "paint" software, is a leader.

I personally am finding this more than adequate for my limited use, which involves photo enhancement and occasionally a foray into morphing pictures just for fun. One aspect I particularly appreciate is the 3user capability. It is not that I want to give it to lots of people, it is simply that computers die all the time, taking their expensive software with them. And I use two computers, one at home and a laptop on the road, so right there is the need for two copies.

This is a sturdy stand, adjusts to comfortable height for sitting or standing. Great once it is set up, portable with its own bag, and at a good price. Holds my trumpet mute holder great.

It is a little on the heavy side, but that goes with being sturdy. I suppose 3/4" perforations could make it lighter without weakening it, but that is labor and adds cost. Minor complaint.

The bag is strong, and the stand just barely fits. So it works fine, just takes a little bit of fiddling to get it in and zipped. Minor complaint.

The main shaft collar that opens and closes the legs has a tendency to bind. Again, a little fiddling and the legs open and close ok. Minor complaint. Maybe it will loosen up over time, hope it does not loosen up to the point where it will not stay set.

If you are looking for a good, sturdy stand that takes down and comes with a bag for transport, this is a good choice.

text:
I love Zoya's polishes!  I first tried them a year ago and since then they have won me over with their consistent, easy to apply formulas and wide range of colors and finishes.  If you love bluegreen polishes and subtle shimmer, Selene is a beautiful polish.  It is a pretty teal with a micronized metallic pearl finish.  If you are looking for an ocean/water inspired polish, especially for a pedicure for the beach, this is perfect.

Application wise, it is consistent with the great user experience I have come to expect from Zoya.  It is easy to apply evenly and does not go on streaky.  I also find this to be pretty pigmented, so for me 2 thin coats has been perfect to get a more opaque look.

It also has great longevity.  I can go a week without chips when used with top coat on my finger nails and even longer when it is used as a pedicure.

I would highly recommend!  I love colors that remind me of water and this water is perfect.
summary: Selene is a great color with a user-friendly formulation

I think this is actually a very good OS. There are a lot of new features and Home Premium appears to be the best Vista OS for the money.
I purhased a new PC with this OS and have really found no compelling reason to upgrade to Ultimate for $150.
Only legitimate gripe concerns drivers for nonmicrosoft products. Not excatly sure why this is microsoft's problem though.
Regardless, this OS is the smart choice for a new PC for home use. Accept a minimum required graphics and audio card until suppliers catch up with this new OS. Then upgrade. Otherwise, wait till you need a new PC.
I have developed one caveat with this product after months of use. The Digital Rights Management system in Vista can be a real hassle for those of you that enjoy downloading music from web sites with WRM licenses. For whatever reason, Vista forgets the licenses and tells you that your player is corrupt. This only happens on legally acquired music downloads. The problem can be corrected but it is irritating since you have done nothing wrong. One problem stems from alternative players that may not be licensed to play your purchased WRM format. Say a Walmart download on a Real Player that limits you to just Windows Media Player. I found on one occassion that my audio card was shut down by Vista and that even baffled Dell. If you do not mind messing around with fixes or you do not download music from the internet, this is not an issue. It does not effect purchased CD's that are ripped on your computer or open licensed MP3's.
summary: Not Sure Why So Many  Bad Vibes Exists

Scottish rockers The Fratellis burst onto the scene in 2006 with their debut "Costello Music" with its chirpy hit single "Chelsea Dagger" which was maddeningly catchy and heard everywhere.

The arty cover photo to "Eyes Wide, Tongue Tied" hints at something edgy or experimental. However, what we get are americanatinged rockers that owe a great debt to Springsteen "Imposters Little By Little", "Baby Do not Lie To Me", and the ballad "Slow"  the latter rather nice, as well as songs that almost sound like pastiche the groovy rocker "Thief" strongly recalls Ray Parker Jr's "Ghostbusters" while "Dogtown" recalls The Beatles' "Come Together". They are not bad, just deficit in originality.

Saving the day are the epic opening number "Me And The Devil" with a delicate piano intro leading to a bouncy theatrical sound and Jon Fratelli singing lines like "I am going to sell this soul of mine", the mellow and melodic "Desperate Guy", the bluesy "Getting Surreal", and the ballad "Moonshine" with a world wearysounding performance. "I may be bleeding but I feel just fine" go the lines in part. More like these and this could have been a winner.

With an aging baby boomer population, products like this are flooding the market.

And speaking as a baby boomer, I am thrilled with this pillowcase!
It is not any more expensive then a highend pillowcase from Frette or Sferra, and it has the look of a bed throw pillow, and we all know those can be well over a hundred dollars if adorned with embellishments.

Add in that it feels fabulous on the skin, and the fact that it is 'rejuvenating' is just icing on the cake.
But does it work to help skin look it is best?
In my opinion, yes, I believe it has made a difference in the month that it is been my sleep companion. A subtle difference, to be sure, but considering all of the above, that is just fine with me.
summary: All Things Considered, a Excellent Value

It was worth a five star rating 'till I went to empty it. It drained VERY slowly. Investigation found that at the sharp bend of the drain, a thick membrane restriction has been molded in with two approx. 1/4 inch holes in the membrane. I ended up cutting the drain off at the bend and after quite a struggle, removing the restriction. I then epoxied the drain back together. The pan is now worth five stars but, only three of the stars belong to the company. The other two stars belong to me.

When it comes to packaging, bliss either excels or fails miserably. This is a case where they excel. This is one of the best compacts I have ever used. First of, the mirror is actually large enough to be useful. Most compact mirrors are too small. I love the bit of built in plastic to separate the puff from the powder. This needed to keep oils, dirt, etc. from the face off the compacted powder. This truly is great design!

When it comes to the actual product, it is fairly ordinary. It is actually not that different from L'oreal or Maybelline's pressed powders/compact foundations. While this is called foundation, it is actually pressed powder and can be used likewise.

Still, the products is more than fine for most people's needs, and I would recommend this if only for the compact. It is worth it.

text:
4 stars for what it is

If you are considering buying this, then you presumably already know that this is no Newsweek or Time magazine.

If you are considering buying this, then chances are you are looking for a light read filled with items from popular culture.  And that it is.  The glossy pages are filled with pictures of beautiful people: actors, singers, models, and reality stars.  Along with all of the sordid but secretly entertaining details of their lives.  If that is what you are looking for, you have found it.

I secretly enjoy the Who Wore It Best and Loose Talk What the Stars Said this Week features.  This is a fun magazine to read when you are looking to relax and pass a few hours, like at the beach or on an airplane.  Just do not expect to learn any real newsworthy news.

To be honest, I do not typically read this magazine because I personally find People magazine to contain better writing, a better assortment of stories, and better coverage of current events.  But we subscribe to both because my husband prefers this one for having more pictures and lighter reads.

So, if you are considering buying this, my best advice is to consider People instead.
