There is nothing wrong with a book about people you would not necessarily want to know in real life, as long as something about them is sympathetic or you are really interested in their lives.

In Dissident Gardens, Lethem gives us two women, who are not that likable but for the fact that they are surrounded by people less likable than themselves.

In Motherless Brooklyn, Lethem made the reader feel what it was like to have Tourette's Syndrome.  His protagonist was so fresh and interesting, and his plight so sympathetic, that it did not matter that the story was a kind of silly, mediocre mystery.

Here, the action takes place largely in the area of the perceived Red Menace, and the lead characters are a Jewish communist party member and her daughter.

Maybe if you are really interested in the subject matter and era, you will not mind that the characters do not feel fresh.  I felt sometimes that I was reading someone trying to write like Junot Diaz and not quite succeeding.

Maybe next time Lethem will go back to writing like Lethem, which he does really well.
summary: A bit too intellectual - and I like intellectual books

text: Great ideas, but very annoying to read. If the author had not repeated herself so many times, this very short book would have been a pamphlet. Worth the money for the excellent method explained.

What a helpful little cookbook this is! DELICIOUS MEALS FOR 1.22 EUROS is wellorganized into main courses, sides, and desserts. Recipes are liberally illustrated at important steps in the preparation. I am a lessthanstellar cook, and photos explaining "The batter should now look like this" were a great help. The recipes are easy, varied, tempting, and healthy emphasizing fresh ingredients, including fruits, veggies, fresh fish. Preparation steps are very clearly explained. Ingredient measurements are given in both grams and ounces/cups/tsps. Average prices are given in Euros, but it is quite easy to convert to dollars. Euros are currently worth about $1.35 US.

Author Kat Miller has cooked in restaurants and pubs, and she has a wonderful, common sense and very readable approach to making actually yummy food without sacrificing health and nutrition, nor breaking the budget. These are not just meals you should eat, they are meals you will want to eat. No cauliflower "steaks" nor batterdipped tofu in this book, thank goodness. Ms. Miller uses comfortingly recognizable foods, even when encouraging notsoadventurous cooks as I am to stretch a bit and give risotto, couscous, and gnocchi recipes a shot. At the same time, there are plenty of comfort foods: fish and chips, jacket potatoes, pizza, soups, pies and cakes among them. Little helpful hints, such a making chocolate shavings with a potato peeler, are suggested.

I should not give the impression this book is just for the novice cook, though, as it is not. Experienced and talented chefs will enjoy playing with and adapting the recipes to make their own delicious variations.
summary: Well-organized, well-illustrated, good family meals without breaking the budget

text: fun challenging game but only if you succeed. Like most the biggest thing is difficulty. It can be very rewarding to beat levels but also punishing as well. When comes to strategy like games I have always been the chess mind set, sacrifices have to be made. In Doctrine no such thing is allowed hence the difficulty. Its not that characters can easily be killed off without game strategy that bothers me its fact that get a game over if do let a single person die. While adds realism just not personal a big fan. I love demon souls, dark souls, roman total war, rottk, civilization. Point making is this is a harder game i am going to than those and can be fun but wished they add more difficulties. Nothing worse than spending more than 50 minutes in dungeon working hard only to make one small error and restart. This was a year game for me that cannot just pick it up and power through it to enjoy story. Advice to those that buy this is be expecting to redo same levels over several times and each time can take up at least an hour.

I love this collapsible dog bowl. It is small enough to fit right in my pups hiking vest that she carries on her back when we go for a hike. My pup has mega esophagus so I cannot just let her go into the lake to get a drink or she will get sick and throw up so this bowl helps me monitor her intake. I also like that it is in measuring sections and do not need to be open all the way if you want a smaller portion. Easy to use easy to clean and very portable about the size of my hand. I was lucky enough to have a chance to review this  log bowl at a discounted price for my honest unbiased review.  This collapsible dog bowl has made our hiking trips so much easier for me and my pup.
summary: Hiking made easy with my pup

text:
I read the blurb and was so excited to read this modern day retelling of Jane Austen Pride and Prejudice! I went into this book with high expectations and they were all met! Lizzie makes a choice right off that bat that changes the course of her current year at school. She learns a lot about people and that her initial judgment could be off. I Loved spunky Lizzie the managing editor of the school paper who gets to the bottom of things and change happens. Dante is an amazing character and I liked how standoffish he was in the beginning. I liked getting to know him. Dante's sister Georgiana has history and Dante means well in wanting to protect her. I liked seeing how friendships change and evolve throughout the story.

The flow and plot of this story was awesome. This book does not have any lulls. I hate when a story drags. You will not find that here. My favorite part is the tree and the end of the book. This story totally rocks and is super sweet! I read this story and was left wanting more. Now off to read book two about Ellie!

just fyi this story does not have any sexual content or swearing

text: Works as advertised

I purchased two boxes of these after reading a few of the reviews. These are really good quality top loading document protectors, and for the quantity a great price. Not only is the quality good, but you can also place more than one sheet of paper in the document/sheet protectors. I use these for sheet music so it is important for me to have the ability to turn the pages and have sheet music on both sides. It is also very easy putting two sheets of paper in the protector. Another positive aspect, especially using them for sheet music is they do not have a glossy or glary finish, or like some I have bought a dull finish. Just clear, easy to see through. I was able to use a 2inch binder and fill it up with 100 loaded sheet protectors. Which is 200 pages of music, plus the 100 sheet protectors. Just so you will have an idea of what type binder you might want to think of using. I bought the Amazon Basics value pack of 4, 2inch Binders. I plan on separating the music out later into the other binders. But rest assured these are well worth the money.

I have owned this FP for over 20 years.  One of my very favorites.  For an inexpensive pen it writes very smoothly.  The window let us the writer see how much ink is left.  The piston refill is simple to use and the pen cleans up easily.  Very flexible nib and leaves an excellent line with any ink.  Highly recommended for those first trying a fountain pen.  It is truly a shame that few people use fp's any more.  They are very elegant to use and using a piston means saving a lot versus throw away cartridges.  One becomes very attached to their beauty and function.

Cyberlink PhotoDirector 5 Ultra is a rather limited photo editing and retouching application compared to something like Photoshop CS or Photoshop Elements, but it does a VERY good job at simplifying several rather complex editing tasks ... making it possible for amateurs to do very difficult retouching.

For starters, many people would like to quickly remove blemishes or make themselves look thinner in photos, and PhotoDirector 5 makes it so easy to do those things I am actually surprised they are so difficult to do well in Photoshop.

The contentaware object removal tools make it easy to remove distracting objects from the backgrounds in photos, but like Photoshop and Photoshop Elements you have to be careful since the software can get confused by complex backgrounds.

In short, if you just want to quickly edit your family photos and do not want to learn more complex photo editing techniques then PhotoDirector 5 Ultra is probably the right software for you.
summary: Quick retouching for people who are scared of Photoshop

I have to say to start off this review this book was such a awesome addition to this series!
I Loved Bull and Ian's story so much!
Bull is a tow truck driver who comes to tow Ian's car after it breaks down on the side of the road. Ian was on his way to a interview trying to get a better job than McDonalds so he could support himself better. Ian has had a horrible life with the way his mom treated him and what she did, then there were the foster homes he had been sent to. Bull loves helping people so when he meets Ian and sees were he lives he knows right away he wants to help him.
Can I just say how much I loved these two together. Between the sparks flying between these two and the steam which was off the charts hot! You could really feel how much they cared for each other from the start.
You get the angst and steam with this book which I thought was perfect! Plus you meet all of Bill's friends and family in this book which I loved!
All together I really loved this book!
I would definitely recommend this book!

I was looking for a relatively inexpensive soap for ever day shaves. I like to save my artisan stock for special occasions and I am not made of money ya know. As a mass produced soap it is actually really nice. It loads well, though I will say it loads better on stiffer brushes than softer ones. The scent is nice and has some staying power. The slickness is about average I would say and it provides decent cushion. Is this the best soap in the world? Nope. Is this soap a decent proformer at a great price point? Absolutely. One of the advantages of this soap over the cream in a tube is that it has a better post shave. Not sure why but it is definitely more moisturizing and has a better finish than the tube creams from Proraso. This is their sensitive skin formula and I have some sensitive skin. Let me just say a preshave is a must. I use an oil but you could use theirs as well. A good preshave and prep will make this soap preform better. without a preshave treatment this soap is still to drying for me but it does have some good antiinflammatory properties.
summary: A relatively inexpensive soap for ever day shaves

Good Will Hunting is basically a story that is wrapped around one big huge anti NSA message. The main character paints the NSA out to be some omnipotent, sinister organization which is out to drop bombs on harmless people in Africa. It is part of Hollywood's enormous campaign to brainwash the American people to agree with their line of thought, which is liberalism. In Hollywood land, every intelligent person is a liberal and of course the most intelligent person on the planet who is played by Matt Damon in this movie has come to the conclusion that the NSA is evil.

The NSA actually protects Americans from terrorism. It is simply an informationgathering organization and it is a vital part of our national defense. Do not let the Hollywood writers fool you. They are not as intellectually superior as they think they are. Steer clear of this film if you want to avoid being brainwashed, but I doubt if you will be able to, as it is a favorite movie for cable companies. They play it over and over and over again, like it was one of the greatest movies ever or something. They must be in on the conspiracy too.

This quick, fast paced book is without a doubt Gertie's  latest, craziest, funniest misadventure into mayhem and madness, and believe me that is truly saying something... All she wanted to do is create a special color for her kitchen walls. A trip to Cosmos magic shop without Cosmos and a borrowed book courtesy of Esmeralda from the union library.... she got special alright.... and anyone or thing  who touched the "special" paint, all ended up back in time to the Tutor era. It is an absolutely side splitting adventure of magical madness as Gertie and company try to fit in epic fail as they search for a way home. I had to wipe tears away in order to keep reading... Dirty Dancing at  King Henry's castle?... Sasqutches smoking a bong?... And can you even imagine Esmeralda with amnesia?... I recommend this as a lighthearted get away.

Rise of Flight has an updated release called Iron Cross Edition, found here. As of posting it is also cheaper and comes with more airplanes, so do not buy the older version.  See this one:
httpSkeptical, annoyed, undecided, uneasy or hesitant/www.amazon.com/RiseFlightFirstGreatCrossPc/dp/B003Q65ZLO/refsr_1_1?svideogamesieUTF8qid1288006725sr11

Not to get personal, but the last guy to review on Oct 15, 2010 is whistling out his sphincter.  To me his ubernegative critique smacks of someone who had preconceived notions, and never gave RoF an honest chance.  To list all his sim experience and then call this an "arcade" shooter is ridiculous unless of course he did not take the time to set advanced physics in game, or he likes arcade shooters....

The advanced physics models altitude pressure changes, temperature changes, wind, turbulence, the physics/lift and handling of all the different wing cross sections, etc, etc, etc.

I also suspect he does not own a system capable enough to run the sim at high settings and there is the rub, RoF really shines if you have a quad core computer and at least a 1 GB graphics card.

Please research online and read some of the other reviews for a less biased take on what is otherwise a very excellent simulation of WWI air combat.  And with every planned monthly patch it only gets better with more airplanes!  I rate it one star short of perfect 5 because it does not have a good campaign systemyet that should come out next month.

EDIT: deserves 5 stars now that the campaign system has been released and has proven itself, as well as an English Channel map will be released very soon.
summary: This IS a serious flight SIM

I am picky about flash drives, at least ones I use as my main drive. It must not have a cap, it must be made of metal, and it must have a keyring. This one meets all the above criteria, and has the bonus of being USB 3.0. Read/write speeds are as fast as I need them to be. Two caveats, though:

1. The keyring loop is tiny. I had to add a metal loop because the builtin hole more like a slot, actually was too small for my cable keyring to fit through it. If I used a more conventional loop keyring, I think it would not be a problem.

2. This thing gets HOT!!!! IF you are transferring a lot of files to it, the metal acts like a heatsink, and it can get very hot. Probably not hot enough to leave a burn mark, but definitely hot enough that you will instinctively drop it after removing it from the USB port. It does not seem to affect speed or usefulness, but I have had it less than a month.

This will be my only review for all of this "alphabet" series by Sue Grafton:

With acclaim for the recently released "Z" book of the series, I decided to try out the series with "A".  I am on "F" now after about 2 weeks, and I am enjoying them a lot.  A dedidedly talented crime/detective writer, Sue Grafton's heroine, Kinsey Millhone, first name is after her mother's maiden surname is a feisty survivor type not to be taken lightly.  She is gritty, tough, athletic, can handle a gun well enough to save her skin and then some, and is not above the occasional dip into romantic interlude.  She is got a sense of humor as well, and a philosophical disposition that is built up over each successive "submission" or story.  A likable gal to be sure,  she is more of a persistent character than a master of deduction and reason like, say, Sherlock Holmes for example, who invevitably stumbles onto the full discovery of her pursuits through determination and hard work armed with her detective's 'nose' that grows keener with experience.  What makes this and other tales fun to read is the adlibbing that permeates the novels, which are really just a "thinking aloud" kind of running commentary on whatever is confronting her at the moment, and those help to define Kinsey' personality, likes and dislikes, motivations and feelings.  I guess I am hooked now, but the cost per book was only 2.99 for "A" through "E", and now nearly $7 from here onward, so that is not so cool.
summary: this is a general review for the series.......

I have been running this for a few months now and I have nothing but good things to say.  The interface is pretty simple, it runs scans quickly and does not seem to hog a lot of resources.  I am running on a Win 7 Pro machine with a Core i5.  Whereas with Norton, I always could tell when scan stared, with Kaspersky I only notices if I check, or I get a report at the end of a scan.

Other than a few email viruses it has not reported much.  I still have Norton on the system, and I run a few scans occasionally to see if Kaspersky has missed anything: so far nothing.

The only negative I could give is that a power user might find doing "deep tweaks" to be a little more frustrating, but I think the average user will be pretty happy with the streamlined interface.  Most the reputable review sites give Kaspersky high marks for detection, which is most of what I care about, followed by performance.  Overall this does everything I want.

One thing I will note is that Internet Security Suites seem born to have conflicts with different systems.  Sometimes what works for me on one system crashes another.  Be prepard to scrap any Internet security software you buy if you system does not react well.  It just seems to be part of the game.

I just received Coal Miner's Daughter: A Tribute to Loretta Lynn yesterday and enjoyed it. It could have been a two CD set to fully appreciate the body of Loretta's work. Missing was The Pill which took Loretta's career to a whole new level. The choice of White Stripes for RatedX and Paramour for You Are not Woman Enough is interesting. I especially liked Gretchen Wilson on Do not Come home A Drinkin and Carrie Underwood on If You are Looking at Country. Reba's cut was also enjoyable as was Faith Hill on Love is the Foundation. The idea to do Coal Miner's Daughter with Loretta, Miranda Lambert and Sheryl Crow brought the album to a nice close. My kids had been trying to create their own stop motion videos, having this software really helped quite a bit. Keep in mind, this is a software package geared towards extreme novices and children. What you can create will not be powerful, but it is a great way to start with working with stop motion and coming up with a final product that gets a flew claps from family. The program was easy to load and worked well with our laptops and using a nokia camera.
I cannot really compare it to other programs because what this software promises is basic level stop motion where other programs promise you will create professional looking final products. I can highly recommend this for people looking to learn the bells and whistles, if you need to do a quick project, or if you have kids interested in learning. If you are looking for something to submit to a Hollywood studio, this will not be the software package for you.

I love the concept behind this, although I have had no need to implement it thankfully. It allows you to sign up multiple devices and track them, but what makes me nervous is what if someone steals my laptop and manages to hack my account and change the pw before I can track them? I suppose that is being hyper paranoid, but it is a possibility. Overall though, the concept is inventive and helpful and you can log on you account and check your devices from any access point. This software is only good for one year before you have to renew so its just like having to pay for home security, not a one time fee. I probably would not continue the use of this but I would recommend this to people who are more high risk, such as people who ride public transportation with their devices daily, work in common areas where they may be more open to thievery, etc., aside from my cell phone most of my devices are home all the time except my laptop for school, but everything is always on me. I do not live in a high traffic city where I would imagine this would also be more useful. Still, I recommend it depending on scenario, not really for me. Others may find it more for them.

Using vermiculite and coconut coir along with this product, you can transform a claylike soil such we have in Hawaii into a loamy garden soil. The tropical sun here burns off topsoil at a rate of roughly half an inch a year, so I am faced with the need to replenish it. You will still need to pay attention to the microclimate of your garden bed, but I have found that adding these soil amendments makes for much better drainage and higher yields.

I have what I call "my chicken orchard." It is a nice sized plot with 6 fruit trees and berries etc... Side note: I live in the city and keep the fruit trees cropped at 15' and compact by trimming side limbs. They are like BIG fruit bushes! You can grow fruit trees on a city lot!
I let my chickens run free in that area. I did want some type of ground cover as they love to "forage." Check your city ordinance if you want fresh eggs. Where I live you can have up to 4 hens, NO rooster.
I fenced off 1/2 the orchard and sowed this white clover with a little rye grass, for the chickens to chew on. I will leave it like this until the clover flowers and drops seedlings before I turn the chickens loose. Then I will seed the other side. Chickens love rye and WHITE clover.

I am also using clover as a "fill in" between stepping stones in my "sitting" back yard area, fenced off from the chickens. It is short, stays green, and looks better than the grass I have in front. Since it does not get very tall it is also easier to mow. The mowing just removes the flowers. And I do not mow as often as grass! Big bonus. Of course I do not mow at all where the chicken orchard is. My hens take care of that. Dual purpose!
summary: Came up quickly and completely covered the area I sowed them into.

So, this is what life comes down to when you are 50 years olTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry  reviewing dryer vent cleaners while sitting at your kitchen table waiting for American Idol.  This is not what I envisioned when I was 12, I can tell you that much.  You kids who think it will not happen to you?

It will.  Sorry to burst your bubble.

That said, the product works great.  Our dryer pretty much stopped working and we were thinking we needed a new one, which was seriously going to eat into my plastic surgery budget.  One last shot before a trip to the appliance store was this Gardus LintEater.  My husband, who is not the handy one of the family, had to do the work as I have a torn labrum.  Which sounds dirtier than it is  that is part of your shoulder.  He, the clumsiest man in the world, had absolutely no problem using this.  I warned him to read the directions first, and he actually listened and followed.  He hooked it up to the drill, and away he went.  He got a bunch of musty, wet lint that had probably been up inside the wall since 1977   probably consisting of bell bottom material and macram.

Now our dryer actually dries clothes again, and I can continue to save for my facelift. Thank you Gardus.

I do not know how to describe the color  maybe a brassy gold color.

Lily moves to America to study Music, while sharing an apartment with her friends.
Heading to the campus to organise her classes, Lily heads to the meet and greet area for new students to meet existing student.  On the way, she hears music and stops captivated by the musician playing the guitar. After watching him for a while, she learns his name is Alfie and he is a big flirt, but she cannot help the way he makes her feel.
With the chemistry between Lily and Alfie undeniable they agree to be friends with benefits and no commitments as Alfie says he cannot offer her that. After a while Lily realises that she is starting to develop feelings for Alfie and needs to put some distance between them and see if he has feelings for her as well.
With things moving on well for Lily, even though she still sees Alfie, they keep their distance until, Alfie tries to get what they had back and Lily let us him know she cannot because of her feelings for him and needs someone who can love her, they decide to give being friends a try.
Lily always tries to do the right thing and keep everyone happy but decides that its time for her to work on what she wants to make her happy. I cannot wait to see where Lily and Alfie go in the next book.

I received the Hot Dots Jr. PreK Math set from Educational Insights for review purposes. My daughter goes to preschool a few days a week, but I have been looking for ideas on how to help get her ready for Kindergarten on the days she is home. I really love this math kit for her. Like nulltvwell, I was around 10 or so when Jodeci first came out. I immediately fell in love with their revolutionary sound which mixed RB and Hip Hop flavor. This was also around the time when Mary J. Blige came out, and her style at the time was similar that is why no matter what Puffy does, I will always have a certain level of respect for his hand in creating what is now my favorite genre of music; before Jodeci/Mary J. Blige I was mainly a rap fan.

"Forever My Lady" has got to be the best RB love song of this hip hop generation. I can still listen to it now, 12 years later, and feel the same emotions. It is my favorite song on the album, and still one of my favorite songs of all time. Following right behind are the songs, "Come and Talk To Me," "Stay," "I am Still Waiting," and a little further down my list of favorites, "YOU  I." KCi and JoJo are the main vocalists on this album. I always wondered why they did not go solo since they did all the singing anyway, but I have come to understand that DeVante/Dalvin also were crucial to the sound that is Jodeci.

Over the past decade, many groups successfully imitated Jodeci i.e., Dru Hill, etc.. I hope one day they will get back together and make us fans happy.
summary: Best Hip Hop R&B Group Ever

text:
One of my alltime favorite movies will always be RAIDERS OF THE LOST ARK.  Great movie, great memories seeing it when it came out in the summer of 1981, still a good movie to watch.

Then in 1984, the sequel was releaseTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry INDIANA JONES AND THE TEMPLE OF DOOM.  The thrill was gone.  All of the action scenes looked like models and bad special effects where was the stunt work that made the first film so exciting?.

I did not like the heroine although the director certainly did since he married her.  Someone actually counted the number of times she screamed to see if she set some kind of record Kim Basinger beat her in 1989's BATMAN.

I hated that little kid.  Even worse than I hated the little brat from the old Godzilla movies.  Just annoying.

And the story was just gross and meanspirited.  Bugs, monkey brains, human sacrifice and incineration.  Nice.

A big, induglent, ugly sequel.  A few years ago, the defunct Premiere magazine did a retrospective of these films and nearly everyone interviewed made excuses for it.  "Well, George Lucas was going through a divorce at the time...."

I was not a huge fan of THE LAST CRUSADE either but...at least it was not as bad as TEMPLE OF DOOM.

RAIDERS still rules though.
summary: The Bad Sequel Everyone Went to See

My interest for The Orb ceased with 1997's "Orblivion". I confess that I have not kept up to date, as for the most part the curiosity for them and their music was gone. I read "The Dream" was causing a stir as a return to their former sound, so I decided to check it out.

And what a disappointment! A very awkward album and a shadow of their past. They have abandoned their vast excursions into hyperspace in order to take their sound to accessible levels. I can barely hear any if any influences from the old times apart some ambient intros that work as fillers between the... songs.

Gone are the vast spacey arrangements, the kraut influences from Popol Vuh to Tangerine Dream of the early albums, the Steve Hillageisms although Mr. Rainbow Dome is present on several tracks here, his glissandos are absent and the "openair" ambient house feel of their early days. Instead, you get generic ambient electronica, Dreadzone influenced dub gone r'n'b, cheesy singing struggling to be catchy, slick late era Pink Floydisms, even some hillarious rap...

For completists maybe "The Dream" is a suggested listen, but be forwarneTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry if you are looking for a sequel to "Adventures Beyond the Ultraworld", "UFOrb" or "Orbus Terrarum", bypass! Being adventurous and innovative is ages behind this band. It would be better for Alex Paterson to do something else instead, and let the old days remain in the fond memories. A closed case for me.
summary: The package is better than the music...

As pretty much anyone knows, evaluating a particular fragrance is entirely subjective and personal.  With that in mind, I quite like Rochas Eau Sensuelle and find it pleasantly fruity/floral with an appealing hint of spice to counteract and balance the sweetness.  The bouquet which is comprised of Rochas' signature white flowers plus mango and a smattering of dried fruit, is neither overwhelming nor cloying but as fresh and clean as a warm spring day.  And while its complexity certainly makes a statement, it is not so heavy that it cannot be worn during the day as long as you take care not to apply it too lavishly.

To avoid overapplication when using a spray bottle, rather than spraying it on myself directly, I prefer the old trick of lightly spritzing the air  and then walking into the cloud of fragrance.  I have never gone wrong with this technique.  You derive the subtle benefit of the lovely scent without stopping people in their tracks.

Let me start off by saying that I am not a professional publisher nor do I create magazine ads for a living.  I am a programmer who often has the need to creative professional looking graphics for internal webpages and the like.  And, like most folks, I really would like to use Photoshop, but I can never justify the cost of a license to myself or my employer.  Why cannot there be a quality product for the rest of us that does not cost and arm and a leg?  And the answer is Corel Paintshop.  When I first installed the software, I was not expecting much  but after using it on several occasions, I can say that it is intuitive, easy to work with, and produces the same type of effects and functionality that I would use in Photoshop at 1/6 of the price.  Oh, I am sure that Photoshop can do more than this, but for your average person, I think that Paintshop is perfect.  I have nothing bad to say about this software and think it is a great value compared to Adobe Phtoshop.
summary: Great Inexpensive Alternative to PhotpShop for the Rest of Us

As you may already know, this DVD was released with a serious defect back in November of 2001. Subtitles would pop up randomly whether you had them turned on or not. After numerous complaints, Columbia TriStar Home Entertainment fixed the problem and sent out the corrected discs. Unfortunately, they did NOT recall the bad shipment just like Anchor Bay with Heathers, and there is nothing on the box to indicate which version is which. Ah, but there is a way to distinguish the two. The initial shipment had a sticker, in the lower lefthand corner, advertising "VIP MOVIE POINTS  Buy and Bid!" The newer, corrected version, does NOT have this sticker. Hope that helps everyone out. As far as the first Swedish subtitle being omitted, it was like that on the theatrical rerelease, too. So who knows? Now, as far as the DVD goes...wow. This is a Monty Python fan's dream come true. Oh sure, the transfer is far from perfect, and the 5.1 sound would not impress your grandmother. It is still leaps and bounds ahead of the VHS ugh! release, and the extra features are too numerous to mention here. I believe they are listed at the top of this page. Really, the only drawbacks are the missing subtitle at the beginning and the fact that there are two versions out there; one defective, the other not. But at least now you know how to distinguish them. Just another helpful tip from your uncle Jason.
summary: If it has a VIP MOVIE POINTS sticker, it's defective

After going three mice from Razer that all died within 6 months to a year, I decided to drop them completely. I was a bit iffy about getting this to replace my mouse since the majority of Logitech products I ever got were all $20 headsets which I went through within a few months each. We have only had the product for two months, but out of the box, it felt MUCH sturdier and less cheap feeling than any of the Razer mice we have owned. The mouse is slightly heavier than a Death Adder because of this, but it is still a very light mouse. My boyfriend is the one primarily using it I have been too busy with work to game, and he says he absolutely loves it. He says the feel and overall sensitivity of the mouse is a lot better than any of our previous mice. My only dislike about it is that it is kind of blueish. I wish it came in more color options, or at least in plain black. But this is just an aesthetic preference. Also, the packaging was beautiful. I loved how they designed the box.

Shave cremes need lather and a feeling of fullness. There should be a richness to the lather and one should not have to use too much of the product to achieve that. Products like The Art of Shaving my personal favorite, Kiehl, and Lab all have excellent shave cremes that when applied with a brush give a sense of moisture that leads to a smooth shave. This Baxter product is inexplicably tepid. Even using alot of the creme on the brush, I never quite had a feeling of satisfaction with the richness of the lather. I had to use alot of the product to equal much less of the other three I have referred to. Now, I use a brush to apply the shave creme. Baxter shave creme was one of the most disappointing I have ever used.

Francamente es una lastima que en esta grabacion, hecha a mayor gloria de MADONNA, que proporciona una 'Evita' muy bien cantada pero que peca de distante por momentos, se hayan descuidado algunos papeles, como el fundamental 'Che', que aqui esta a cargo de un ANTONIO BANDERAS muy bien el la vertiente psicologica del personaje, pero muy flojo en la parte meramente musical. Lo mismo puede decirse del 'Peron' de JONATHAN PRYCE, que es actor pero no cantante.
Cumple mucho mejor como 'Magaldi' un JIMMY NAIL, que sin tener la fuerza de un tanguero real sabe sacarle partido a su rol. De lujo la 'Amante de Peron' que nos brinda ANDREA CORR la vocalista de "The Corrs", que aqui se luce con ganas. Secundarios y coro cumplen con suficiencia, y algo mejor la orquesta.
Un disco que para los amantes de Madonna puede tener mucha calidad, pero para los amantes del musical es francamente de un nivel de correcta suficiencia, pero es que acaso no se puede hacer nada mejor a dia de hoy con 'Evita' que una version solo correcta?

Presto does not sound like the other Rush albums. It is still three guys from Canada being loud and playing well  still a progressive rock band in every sense. But Presto has some kind of underlying theme that is easy to hear but hard to describe. The lyrics are very good; this is probably the single best set of lyrics written by Neil Peart.
The only thing that stops me from listening to this CD over and over is the bad production. It is just too quiet. Put it in a multiple discchanger with any other rock album, and you will see or hear what I mean. It is like you turned the volume WAY down every time a Presto song plays. It needs to be remastered. If it is, it will be tied with Grace Under Pressure and Moving Pictures for the title of "Best Rush Album Ever."

I used this to remove some of the startup items that it recommended and lost my wireless strength indicator, my Media Center volume controls, and my PSI status indicator.  Restoring the registry only got back the Media Center controls.  If you use this program make sure to back up your registry before making any changes, look at the changes it recommends, only choose the ones that are applicable and only make a few at a time.  Do not let it "repair" your system automatically.  My computer still crashes, freezes and takes a long time to boot, although it seems to operate a little faster between crashes.  I will be making some more changes recommended by the program but very selectively.  As somebody else noted, they want $30 every year I do not know if the program stops working after a year or it it just stops updating.

I did not buy these from Amazon, but still felt the need to leave a review here. These are some truly fantastic speakers and are very close to being "pro" gear. The three way design obviously adds a lot of clarity to these speakers, and the mid and highs really benefit from it. The construction is rock solid, and even though they are heavy this is the price you pay for a premium box that will provide pro level sound. Built in DSP options are nice, and I have learned that they definitely sound best to me in "Live" mode. Crossed over with 4 QSC KW 181 subs and they are devastating. Great speakers and I hope to add more to my rig very soon!
summary: These are some truly fantastic speakers and are very close to being "pro" gear

I still do my Mac processing with IWork instead of the office suite but given my work uses Office I find that when I am receiving a document from a coworker I will load it up in this suite just for the best compatibility. I know that Pages and TextMate can both open word docs but I find that using Office tends to work the best for me.

In general I would suggest going with Microsoft Office for Mac if you tend to deal with a lot of Office documents for the most part but ignore it for IWork if you have the chance to use that exclusively instead.
summary: Useful for all my document needs

text:
The jack black conditioner is wonderful. My hair is so dry that I after I shampoo and rinse, it feels like straw in my hands. The Jack black was working as I was running my fingers through my hair, I could feel my hair soften and the texture become smoother right in the shower.

 I like that this is also a scalp conditioner with the tea tree oil. A lot of conditioners tell you to only put it on the ends of your hair, because it will weigh down around the scalp. The Jack Black is light and rinses out easily. Afterwards my hair was shiny and smooth, even the ends which desperately need a trim.
summary: Softens hair and treats scalp also

I dogear the recipes I want to revisit and then end up making many of them once the rest of the family has gotten their hands on it and the requests start pouring in.  Fun ideas.  Healthy ingredients.  Loved the bookmarks provided.  Photos are so cheerful.  Articles are great at introducing new foods, ideas and cooking methods. After using two of these in a watertight safe over a period of 2 years, I have found them to be ineffective. The problem? The silica is supposed to become clear when in need of a recharge  only they remain pink for months/years on end. Meanwhile, important papers curl up, their staples become rusted. I am going to the oldfashioned silica packs and a moisture gauge and hoping for more positive results with those.

I have been using "Vichy LiftActive Retinol HA Eyes" for the past several days and though my fine facial lines have not disappeared yeah, dream on, they do seem to be somewhat fainter.  I have used it on the crow's feet actually, I do not have much of a problem with them yet, but also on some fine lines in the corners of my mouth.  Those seem to have gotten fainter.  I do not think this is a permanent thing, and would have to continue using this product or one like it to keep them at bay, but for review purposes I think it works at least a little bit.

You do not get much   only half of one fluid oz for $42.00 cost as of this review.  The delivery system is different but it seems to work o.k. if you do not press it down too hard.  I did that once and lost my wrinkle cream to the sink.  It goes on smoothly and seems to last for several hours as far as the moisturizing properties are concerned.  And it has little to no smell which is a very good thing.  I hate smelling perfumed lotions all day that I have applied to my face because they make me nauseous after a while.  The Vichy has no detectable scent.

I know this game is available for PS3 in Japan, however I do not speak Japanese and do not want to read a translator so I am writing this review from that perspective.

If you own a 360 and like RPG's you should own this game, no questions asked. It is the first GREAT RPG I have played this console generation. I should not have expected less from the "Tales..." games.

Pros:
1. Fighting system is very fun and addictive.
2. Story is good not great but very good.
3. Graphics are anime style but very fresh and crisp.

Cons:
1. There is almost TOO much to do. For perfectionists you will be spending over 100 hours.

Works great. I used it and an extension kit with extra rods to to clean a 21 foot long vent with a two right angle turns and it did a fantastic job with the adapter that let us you put the rod through and attach a shop vac. Got a TON of lint out, about a 5 gallon bucket full. Inside of the vent was left shiny and clean. Good for safety especially with such a long vent and to my surprise the dryer actually works quite a bit better now. On the auto cycle I used to have to run it again if I was drying heavy things like jeans or blankets/comforters etc... to fully dry things. Now it does it in one cycle and take about 25 less time to go through the auto dry cycle.

I was just wanting to clean out a potential fire hazard but it really does make a big difference running through a dirty vent vs. a clean one. Might be due to the long length of my vent but very happy with this product.

I have this hanger on the inside of my metal range hood and it is the perfect, convenient spot.  I would highly recommend this product.

Personally, I think this is the best James Bond theme/promotion song since Die Another Day by Madonna. Skyfall is different from her previous work. In a way it is almost like the lyrics are telling the listener to never lose their cool or give up. Not in a poppy, club like way or whatever do not worry Ke$ha, you are still cool to me but with a firm, calm voice. I even like the orchestra too. They seem to have gotten the James Bondish feel with the orchestra at least in the beginning of the song. If Adele were to ever make a video for this, that would be kind of awesome. Adele singing in a James Bond suit.

All in all, this is worthy of a James Bond theme song. Away from the breakup songs from her 21 album.

I give this a 9.5 out of 10 if she did not repeat the chorus numerous times I would give it a perfect 10 out of 10 but this is still a good song.

I will never buy again from this seller  Micca Distributor.  They do not operate their business with integrity and they have no concern for their customers.  They are unresponsive and dishonest.

The one star is for Amazon for making this right and giving me a refund.

OK, on to the product.  There is NO reason to buy this product.  It is cheap, inferior quality.  The supplied toskink cable that comes with the FiiO is a throwaway.  Better to spend another $10$20 and get a decent cable.

Thanks to another reviewer, I ordered the Orei and did a sidebyside comparison.  The Orei produces exponentially superior sound quality.  Using the Orei with an Apple TV streaming from my iTunes library, it works fine for whole house audio distribution of background music.  Let us be honest  Neither is an audiophile level DAC.  If you want that, think about spending hundreds, not $30.  I have not tried the Geffen, which is a good company, but the reviews are worse at twice the price.

Do yourself a favor  Do not make my mistake  Do not buy this product.

And compared to my other essie polishes I have used for the past few years, it does seem to stay a little longer without chipping. But I have yet to get 14 days of chipfree wear from it. I can usually get about 3 days before I start to see the first chip. I then touch it up with some polish and put a new topcoat on and that will get me another day, but after that it is chipping badly enough that I need to redo my nails. It is a pretty polish and worth picking up if it is available in a color you love, but it is by far not at all the most chipfree polish I have used.
summary: Great colors and goes on beautifully, but seems to last about as long as most other polishes.

The instructions are slightly confusing due to an imperfect translation. Following them did not work for me. It said to tilt the phone and insert the left side first, then the right side. Doing so squished the silicone layer between the cracks, making it impossible to apply.

Instead, I devised my own way of putting on the skin. I took off the silicone layer, putting that on first, then putting the hardshell layer on afterwards. You will then have to make adjustments and wiggle around the skin so all the holes and phone buttons line up exactly. It takes a few minutes to get it all right. After that, the volume buttons and on/off toggle are easy to push and everything is as it should be.

The skin wraps around part of the front of the phone as well, giving it some additional protection if placed facedown. I like the Thunderbolt flap. It protects the port from dust and other hazards.

We were heading out on vacation and wanted a way to take some of our favorite movies and shows along to watch. The Surface accepts a MicroSD card, so it was easy for us to load up 64GB of films and kids shows for the road, and we took the chance that our hotel room would have a TV with an HDMI input, since most hotels do nowadays.

The cable arrived just before we left, so I did not even have a chance to test it beforehand, but once we got the hotel I plugged in the cable, switched the TV input, and voila, there was my Surface screen duplicated on the television!

Microsoft wanted four times the money for their solution, and I would still have had to add an HDMI cable extension.  This worked like a charm and creates a great solution for traveling.  I bought the 15' version, and may get the 25' version as well so that I have better cable routing options, since with the 15' the cable was stretched a little tight and created a walking/tripping hazard.
summary: Works perfectly with my Surface RT

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

This is such a great tool for researching your roots and recording your family tree. These are two distinct tasks: researching and recording. Researching your background is where you find relatives you never knew you had. Recording is where you save the results of your research and report them to your future generations.

The 90day free access to the Ancestry genealogy records is outstanding. After 90 days, there is a monthly fee and the fee is pretty significant. Check their website for pricing.

One misconception about the research service is that you can find your living and recent relatives. I do not know all the details, but there are privacy restrictions that prevent the web service from giving you info on living people.

All in all, the software tool and the online service are really incredible, but they are not cheap. I recommend you do not activate the 90 day service until you know your calendar is free enough that you will be able to actually use it. Otherwise, you will not get the full benefit from the service before your 90 days elapse.

Researching your family's past really is an incredible journey. My mother traced one branch of our tree back to the Mayflower. Obviously this research was not simple. I cannot even imagine how much easier it would have been for her with a product like this.

Have fun with your personal history!

It is a real tragedy in the world when when the best word processor in history must take second place to MS Word, but that is what has happened here. Office x4 could not be a better program but pressure from Microsoft20 owners, Vector capital 69Drunk or confused and other groups have caused it to lose most  of its unique features. The .wpd format is said to not be a  industry standard any more though I highly disagree. The existence of WP x4 is a testiomony to the strength of the program. Word has never faced this kind of fire before and probably would not survive if it had.

 Corel has done its absolute best to keep this fine piece of software together. Wordperfect has been a stable solid program since the seventh edition of the family pack and this edition is no different. People would argue that the lack of change is bad for WordPerfect. I think that Corel has made a very stable product that can do anything and everything better than any Office suite out there. The problem? The increasing similarity to MS Word. These days, the only things that Corel banks on is the "compatibility" with other Microsoft products like Word and Excel. The fact is that WordPerfect x4 does not need to imitate others. It is already good. For that matter, so is Quattro Pro which is an excellent spreadsheet that does not need to be compatible to excel or 123 to be good.. Buy Wordperfect Office because it is a good program and not because it is approved by Microsoft.

Having given up on bar soap and its innate ability to dry my skin out, I have been using shower gel for years.  Until recently, I have had no preference to any brand, as I felt they were all pretty similar.  After seeing some of the awards that Pattern Body Wash has received in various men's magazines I decided to try it for myself.

On opening the bottle, the fragrance was not overpowering or chemicalsmelling, at all;  in fact, it was quite the opposite,  It has a great aroma with, not really a subtle scent, rather more subdued, and certainly not overwhelming.  In addition to nutmeg, I have also tried citrus, eucalyptus, cucumber, sage and black pepper, and all of them have been outstanding fragrances.  I was also impressed by the small amount of gel needed to clean the entire body.  Many of the other brands that I have tried seem to overfoam and usually leave a little residue that needs a secondary rinse to remove.  This is not the case with any of the Pattern products I have tried.  The body wash is silky, with just the right amount of lather, and it cleans exceptionally well.

One of the other areas, in which I compare body washes, is the dryness that ensues after toweling off after a shower.  Pattern is exceptional in this realm and leaves the skin smooth and soft, even in a very dry climate with little humidity.

The price point is certainly several dollars more than I would normally spend on a standard body wash, but in all truth, one bottle lasts longer than all of the other companies I have tried over the past 20 years.

Great job Pattern on a fantastic product, you have made a routine shower a much better experience.

text: . . . . back in the day, at my old school. This is their best album. Like a lot of groups in this time frame, they came off the fantastic epic of Birthday with an earthier new direction. I remember playing this the first time, the first few times, and it did not overwhelm and hook me like the previous albums had. But on continued listenings, I kept discovering hooks and licks, chorus bits strategically intergrated into songs, inversions of melodies that were just infectous. About a month after I would gotten the record I had it playing in my head, from first track to last, every day for quite a while. I have since concluded that, all told, this was their best album. The goal of it reminds me of another album by another group: "Fearless" by Family, which came out a couple of years later. Now, those of you who know Family know they are an entirely different sort of group from the As. But, the point of comparison here is that each band set out to fully show what they had the potential for. Each track is in a totally and completely different style of music from the rest. And, in that sense, each track is a masterpiece.
summary: "Moonhenge" was what we used to call this album . . . .

Purchased this unit a month or so back and combined the unit with Roomie Remote Apps. I find the combination works well and I have not problems.

Setup and configuration were easy and straightforward. The one issue that I did have was not with the GC IP2IR or with Roomie Remote, but with my router. I have a Fios router and needed to adjust the setting "Enable Multicast" by assigned IP address on my network. This took a little bit of effort to find the proper tables in my router setting, but the support at Roomie Remote was great and therefore I never needed to contact Global Cache. The unit works well without any problems. I would suggest you go to Global Cache website and download the iHelp tool for PCs there is a MAC version from a 3rd party that is needed to verify and update your firmware Mine was up to date. I will also say that SmartHome the seller did followup on the sale to make sure everything was ok.

I would recommend this product for those needing a remote control solution for your media center. Some IP networking technical knowledge is needed, but the support forums are powerful tools and will help you get everything setup and functioning.

Just picked this CD up.  It gets 4 1/2 stars only because it could have included a couple other faves like 'Dangerous' or 'Almost Paradise' from Loving Every Minute Of It. 'Strike Zone' from 'Keep It Up' would have been welcome here as well. Anyways, I have all the main studio albums and the compilation disc 'Loverboy Classics' but this is a better compilation for two reasons:

1 It is NOT mastered so loud that your ears bleed. You can actually crank this up a bit and it sounds great! The classics disc is mastered loud and can be tough on the ears...

2 The 2nd track 'For You' is an absolutely awesome track that I do not remember hearing back when these guys were all over the radio. This may be because the song was written in 1989 just before the band called it quits. They reunited briefly to support "Big Ones" and we are fortunate this song even made it to an official release. It is a true rocking tune in the spirit of 'Loving Every Minute Of It' and should be listened to cranked up to fully appreciate it.

Some of the reviewers complain about the lack of having this song or that song but I feel it is far more important to get a great tune that was never released anywhere else than getting songs that we already own on another disc...

Bottom line...do your self a favor and purchase this before it goes out of print. You will not be disappointed.
summary: Worth it 'For you' - Not available anywhere else!  4 1/2 Stars

Well, I have never had canned Papaya before. But there it was! My local Fresh and Easy Srore had a stack of about a dozen cans of Native Forest Organic Papaya Chunks on sale at a big discount. I guess they were stopping stocking the item and just wanted to get rid of the ones they had. Well, I will certainly give it a try. My previous experience with papaya was fresh in Hawaii, oh man was it good! and dried in several varieties quite good. Okay, here is fresh organic papaya chunks packed in organic pineapple juice. Does that sound good, or what? Hmmm. It is a product of Sri Lanka. Well, I have never had anything from Sri Lanka before.

This can of papaya chunks is excellent!! The taste is real good and it must have been canned right at the peak of ripeness. Good as it is, it is not very high in calories 60 per serving and three servings per 14ounce can. It is quite sweet, but I note there is no added sugar, it is just papaya and pineapple juice. Of course, it is got zero fat and no sodium either. Plus there some fiber and a lot of vitamin C. Boy, this stuff is not only delicious, it is just the nutrient mix I seek. I am going to have to go back and buy up the whole display!

Gary Peterson
summary: Delicious! And Just the Nutrient Mix I Seek.

This album is comparative to the type of best friend who does not see you often, but will always be there for you when no one else could understand you.  So much like a great friend as such, I may not always listen to this album and choose something more "flavor of the month", but this album is great for certain moments.  I have listened to this when I have suffered the late hours of the night on long assignments.  The music is salve for when I am going through deeply sad times in life.

I have had people say to me that this album is too dark for them.  I completely disagree.  I think this album is full of hope in the face of misery, like the rising sun that banishes the night.  Maybe it is just me.

I was recommended this album by a friend, an avid fan of black metal.  I, however am not into metal, yet Shadows of the Sun quickly grew on me.  I have listened to other Ulver albums before but this is still my favorite.  I cannot really describe the music besides introverted and sentimental  almost spiritual.

I know when an album deserves five stars when I can listen to it over and over again without feeling worn down or sick of it.  I could go on and on about my relationship with this album, but I think buyers should just try it out.  This may not be for everyone, but this is still an album unlike any other.  Maybe it will find its way into your life, too.

Forget the competition! I have had them all, similar laptops that I have had from HP and Lenovo, cannot hold a candle to this unit.

First, let us start with stylish exterior, you can feel the quality of the finish and the precision fit and finish of this product, unlike the consumergrade crap you will get from HP.

Next, I want to thank Dell for not loading the unit with marketing crapware, like HP and Lenovo do, this unit boots quickly and cleanly!

I got this unit for my 12 year old daughter and the bringup was seamless, no drivers to find and load, or even to update! Bravo again to Dell.

Lastly, let us talk features! The keyboard is backlit, which is a very nice feature that you usually do not find, and the screen is a touchscreen too, even though neither Amazon or Dell seem to be trumpeting these features.

Finally, let us talk battery performance! This unit gets awesome battery performance while still being lightweight, even when my daughter plays Minecraft on it!

So, as far as price/performance/quality this unit is the way to go, as I strongly recommend this device for anyone needing a Windows 10 Laptop PC!

I do not even know where to begin with this software. Let me start off by saying that it is not very user friendly. There is a lot bloatware that comes along with it. I was really disappointed at the fact that I kept getting errors when trying to upload to You Tube. What is the point of having the option incorporated if you cannot even use. I did finally get a video uploaded but it took forever. It is hard to find support on their website plus they want to charge you for calling in to ask for advice on how to get their software to work properly. I like the fact that there are many options available to you in the software but I hardly get the opportunity to use them because the software itself is always freezes up and then I have to hit ctrl alt delete to get the crappy software off of my screen. I have tried using this software for several months in order to really form an accurate opinion and I honestly cannot recommend this software to anyone. If you want to continuously feel frustrated while editing videos then Pinnacle Studio 16 Ultimate is the perfect software for you! I have finally given up and uninstalled the software. At least Corel Video Suite is a little more user friendly.
summary: I Didn't Really Care for it

Here are the reasons I find these USB extension cables so convenient:

1 It makes it easy to connect a device to USB ports on the back of a desktop.
2 The male end of my printer's USB cable is a bit wide and prevents access to adjacent ports.
3 The same applies to wide flash drives.
3 I have a USB port on a monitor that is not convenient to access.
4 If you have a tight cluster of USB ports, it just makes it easier to plug into an extension.
5 I have a USB ports on the left side of my laptop, and plugging into the port with my clumsy left hand is not too smooth and may possibly damage the port over time.

It is a little difficult to explain the above examples in words, but hopefully it helps.

QUALITY:
This USB extension cable appears to be made very well. The two that I purchased a year ago have been problemfree. I just purchased a third one.

The connections are a little snug, depending on the particular device that I am attaching. However, it has not been problematic for me. I would still recommend this product based on my positive experience.

PROS:
 Very handy for accessing USB ports that are not easily accessible.
 Allows access to adjacent ports that are blocked from cables or flash drives that are too wide.
 Good quality
 Reasonable price

CONS:
 Might be snug with some devices. However, not really an issue for me, but it is a personal preference kind of thing.
summary: Multiple reasons I find this very handy.

text: After reading the reviews of the DVD, I am actually glad, for once, that I have the VHS instead! I first saw "Destry Rides Again" on TV back in the 1990s, and fell for it hook line and sinker. It is one of my favorite films of all time. Every Western clich is presented in a perfect balance of kitch and seriousness. Dietrich and Stewart sizzle on the screen together, truly  the chemistry is undeniable. And there are so many, many classic scenes  you have probably seen many of them parodied, but seeing them in context, for real, is just a priceless experience. Marlene plays the role she was born to  it is so great to see her early films where she plays a refined woman, and then to watch this and have your jaw drop over the character she is playing  she is so obviously having a ball. I had the pleasure of seeing this film in a theater as well, and the colleague I took was no fan of old movies, but not a quarter of the way in, she started sighing over how adorable Jimmy Stewart is.
summary: Glad I have it on VHS instead of DVD

I have medium yellowisholive skin tone which has been difficult to find a neutral.  This shade "Tea and Crumpets" is beautiful!  I was looking for a color that would match as closely as possible to my natural nail bed color, and I was not having any luck!  Finally I went less pink, more neutral/tan, and this is so flattering!  Contrary to what I thought, it is lighter than my skin tone, and it actually brightens my fingers.  I mistakenly thought lighter colors would darken my skin, but this is a splendid exception.  nice word  splendid  It is definitely a frost, and I find it streaks a little, but I am not a professional, so that is fine for me.  I am just thrilled to death I finally found a color that is not goth or weird or screaming for attention.  I like subtle and refined, and this is it!  It is so pretty!

Bought this as a replacement for a junk one that came in a Washburn Dime 332. The ones that I got with the guitar were 250k and mini pots.

These are a tight fit compared to the mini pots that were in there but they do fit very nice, almost perfect, in the back control cavity
Unfortunately the shaft that gets screwed to the body of the guitar is shorter then the OEM. That means you cannot use the lock washer or 1st nut if you plan on using this on a Washburn Dime of any type. I do not own a Dean so I cannot tell ya either way

I also had to use a round file to open the shaft holes on the body of my guitar a little more for the turning part of the potentiometer to fit. So that also means your original knobs will not work on this pot either.

These knobs are not linear and have a custom audio taper set by DeMarzio that I like so far. It makes it easier to get a clean tone with only using your volume knobs... that is what I have noticed at least.

This is overall a great visual system for accounting , tracking, and pulling numbers and images for presentation purposes.  After you get used to everything here, it becomes second  nature but just takes a while as with everything else.  Once I got the hang of this system, I really enjoyed it is "depth" the most.  Yes, it has depth or breadth of functionale, but what I mean is, you are really able to easily pinpoint numbers from a statement.  If you have a question about some number on an income statement, you are able to click on that for much further detail to figure out what it entails.  This kind of depth is extremely beneficial as it saves a lot of time trying to search for the meaning behind a number.
summary: This software has a lot of depth, in more ways than one

Great product, I wish I had discovered this sooner!!!  I used to stay away from spread and estate collared shirts and mostly stuck to button down collar shirts because they looked more refined without a tie, the collars stayed in place.  But these shirts do not look as good with a tie unless you use a tie bar or pin to bring the collar together.

Enter the Wurkin Stiffs magnetic collar stays, and you get the best of both worlds, with a slightly rolled collar that gives you a great standup collar look with or without a tie!

Most of the pictures hint this product works best without a tie to keep your collars attached to the shirt, but I found you can also use them with a tie for a great collar roll effect without pins or buttons.  Just tie your tie and leave your top button unbuttoned.  Then reach in and put one of the small magnets near the collar stay and it will find its place like a heatseeking missle.  Repeat on the other collar, button your top button and cinch up your tie!

Wonder look, check out the pics!
summary: Technology and Sartorial awareness combine to make a great product!!!!

text:
I have been using TT for probably close to 20 years.  I was about to switch to something else this year when I initially learned that the Deluxe version would no longer support information for stocks and bonds. TT backpedaled and prior year buyers of TT Deluxe received a free upgrade to the Premiere edition.  However, I will jump ship next year if the Deluxe version does not include the above, as it has every year up to now.

Anyway, I like the convenience of how TT automatically imports information from previous years without a lot of effort on my part.  I do not like how it almost forces you to efile your state return, even though it costs an additional $24.95 only Fed efile is free.  Then, if you want to print out your state return and mail it in there is no easy way because you have to include certain fed tax return forms if you itemize, etc.  The easy solution would be if TT offered a box to click on to efile or another box to print out and mail in your state return right next to it.

Just a small gripe.  We will see what TT does with the Deluxe version next year.

These are good bits, in a good holder.  While not industrial quality, the bits work well, and seem more than sturdy enough for average homeowner use.
The storage roll may be a bigger selling point, than the bits themselves.  Finally, someone realized that those cheap vinyl tool rolls that crack and let things fall out of them right away, are not much better than nothing at all.  This is a sturdy roll up pouch, with an elastic band to hold every bit in place, and a protective strip to keep the bits sharp, and not let them poke through under normal circumstances. I found "Tender Is The Night" to be a very captivating story  from the beginning to the end. It is an engaging story which grabbed not  only my attention, but also my imagination by leading me to make early  conclusions about how the story was going to turn out. I was reading the  book always waiting for my predictions to come true, which kept me in some  suspense. I found this facet of the book to be very exciting. However,  unfortunately for me, I was wrong in some of my premature conclusions, and  so, I was inevitably a little disappointed by the end. My suggestion is to  read with some wonderment about what is to happen, but try not to set  yourself up for any initial conclusions you might come to about the final  destiny of the characters. Speaking of the characters, you definitely take  on their emotions or develop your own about them, making the book that much  easier to read and enjoy. I was liking some, feeling sorry for others, and  still completely disliking others. The only negative thing I would say,  looking back over the book, is that I do believe that there are some  aspects of the characters' emotions and predicaments, which are alluded to,  but then dropped. So, I was left with the feeling at times of expecting the  deeper meaning of a character's wants, needs, and reasoning to unfold  later. However, I found they never did. I, of course, could have been reading  more into the words than what was intended. All in all, though, I recommend  getting a copy and allowing yourself to be drawn into this emotional story.  I think most people will find it enjoyable and easy to read.

text: very reasonable

We live in a different world now than it was 10, 20, and 30 years ago.  Life is hard with all sorts of uncertainty about the future.  When you are investing into that future not knowing what challenges are coming, it can be like playing Russian roulette.  But Ian Bremmer and Preston Keat believe there are ways to keep yourself educated and protected even when the questions are there.

THE FAT TAIL is a virtual primer for investing in these volatile times with terrorism, unstable foreign leaders, political opportunism and instability, and governmental intrusion into the private sector worse than they have ever been in the history of the world.  Where do you put your money to safely grow it so your future is as secure as it can possibly be?  That is what this book helps to answer for you.

By clearly identifying the problems that all investors must face and defining the terms under which the investment game is played, the authors offer practical, reallife solutions to give you hope for your investments that will have you worrying less about your future nest egg in these troubled times.
summary: A Virtual Primer For Investing In Volatile Times

Rose is a quiet studious girl, at nineteen never been on a date, never been kissed. Then she meets Lee he is transferred to her college. What Rose does not realise is that Lee has transferred especially to get to know Rose because he knows something, that she does not.
Rosie's grandfather had died recently, it is then she discovers that her grandfather has left her a large sun of money. Provided she marries Lee. From then on Ros is totally distrusting of him, why else would this tall gorgeous and really popular guy be interested in her. But Lee claims that they know one another from when they were children, and he has always had a thing for her. But Rose does not remember him at all.

I liked this story, the characters were well drawn, especially Rose. The book picks up the further you get into it. The ending really sucks. It is a cliffhanger. Had I known that this was only the first instalment I might not have bothered with it. I am really getting tired of these stories being dragged out over more than one book. You lose the momentum while waiting for the next book. It might have been nice if the author had included in the blurb that this is a series. I feel a bit annoyed about that!
summary: LIKED THE BOOK, SHAME IT'S ONLY PART ONE!

Wellness is a quality grainfree source of dog food, however our German Shepherd Dogs simply did not seem to like the food nor did it seem to perform quite as well as Taste of the Wild Salmon flavor.  Our dogs coats and vibrancy proves which food is the best.  Wellness Core is far superior to Purina or Iams or Hill's Science diet but it is a far cry from the best commercial dog foods. Obviously the very best food for most dogs is a species appropriate diet of raw food and bones, but it is not as convenient to feed as a commercially prepared food.

July 2015 Update:  We were given an opportunity to try this food again.  I have upgraded this food to 5 stars because it is grain free and it is overall quite healthy with a list of READABLE ingredients. Our dogs still prefer TOTW Salmon flavor but overall this is indeed a decent dog food, just not the best for the money according to our dogs taste preference.
summary: Superior to Purina toxic crud, our dogs still prefer Taste of the Wild Salmon Flavor

Yes, it really works. The problem I seem to have with the thing is getting the litter right. My cat leaves huge urine clumps the size of a football, which are obviously too large for the drawer. I have taken to mixing two types of litter, clumping and nonclumping. That works all right, but I cannot say it is perfect. Other than that and wishing the plastic were a little bit sturdier in a couple of places, it is great. It gets 4 stars because it is a brilliant idea that actually works, but it needs to be constructed better it could be a bit sturdier. If it came with litter suggestions, that would be great.

UPDATE: We no longer even try to use the "selfcleaning" feature. I would love to use cheap, environmentallyfriendly, nonclumping litter, but it just does not do the job. Even if we mixed it with half clumping litter, it ends up being a dirtier, stinkier litter box. In the end, we gave up because the urine clumps are generally too large for the drawer.
The best upgrade possible!

text:
It is a garage door opener, used to open garage doors.  I do not pretend to know how; magic, elves, magic elves.  All I know is when I push the left button the door rises and disappears.  If I push the right button, nothing happens.  Probably some ingenious security device to thwart criminals who may have acquired the device through subterfuge.  Coincidentally, if I push the left button a second time the garage door reappears and returns to the close position.  Just exactly to the correct spot. I have not once encountered the door going down so far as to lift the garage off its moorings or destroy the concrete floor where in makes contact.
The people at Chamberlain KLIK1U Clicker Transmitter Universal Garage Door Remote Control have a lot to be proud of with this product.  There may be an YOU.N. Ambassadorship in their future!
summary: Before you do anything read this!  I am not kidding! I really, really mean it this time!  Don't make me come in there...

I found this book at the library first, and kept referring to several recipes to make from it. That decided me that I had to have my own copy so I would not keep the library's copy hostage any longer. I use the bean recipes frequently, as a way to use the abundant quantities of peppers and herbs coming from the garden. They are convenient and very tasty. I especially like that the recipes are not the standard "Crockpot Conformity" kind you see everywhere, they are different and flavorful, and unique. The crockpot helps keep dinner on the table during the work week by letting things cook slowly while I am away, and this cookbook is one of my favorite goto resources to keep dinner interesting. I never liked the old "open a few cans, dump them in, and walk away" versions of cooking in the crockpot, so this cookbook is in a different, much better, league of its own. I refer to this cookbook weekly for new ideas to try out, and it just keeps on giving inspiration. Plus, the house smells great of dinner cooking when I walk through the door!
summary: Healthy and Tasty - A Great Crockpot Cookbook

text:
This is the second Vita Liberata selftanner I have had the chance to try recently the first was theirnbsp;a datahook"productlinklinked" class"alinknormal" href"/VitaLiberataPhenomenal23WeekTintedTanMousseMedium422floz/dp/B00865610O/refcm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ieUTF8"Vita Liberata Phenomenal 23 Week Tinted Tan Mousse, Medium, 4.22 fl. oz./a, and they really are the best selftanners I have ever used.  In the past, I have tried Jergens, Nivea, St. Tropez, Banana Boat, and Dave's.  The color on each of those has varied, but this Vita Liberata one has left me with a consistent color that looks natural even on my fair skin.

I did end up purchasing the VL mitt for six dollars to use with this and the mousse, and would really recommend doing to.  The mitt helps keep the product off your hands and thus avoid orange palms, and helps you apply it in a more even way.  I had an Ulta brand mitt I used with previous products, but the VL is a bit thicker and softer.

This does dry out your skin, so it is important to use a more moisturizing body wash in the shower and lotion.

Although the VL products claim to not have the selftanner smell, they definitely still do.  I will say, though, that it is not as strong as other selftanners.

This really does give a natural, bronze glow!
summary: This brand makes wonderful self-tanners -- but they do still smell and I wish the price was less expensive!
