text: I love this song. Of course, it is Stevie Nicks, and I enjoy listening to her. I will be doing it often!

This album was not released in the States and was only recently added to iTunes. One of her strongest albums, "So Natural" finds Lisa favoring midtempo grooves over the club and disco beats that dominated her first two releases. Tracks like "Never Set Me Free," "I Give You Everything," and the title track are as silky as RB gets, and the lush "Sweet Memories" will no doubt win over any fan of Sade. Great bonus content too, including the orchestral film version of "In All the Right Places" and a healthy helping of remixes. This one's a keeper.

text: This is a fun book and just as enjoyable as the Kane Chronicles and the Percy Jackson stories.  However, the story is divided into three small parts that cost $1.99 each, so you end up paying $6 for a novella not even a full book.  Riordan's books are well written, and teach history and mythology in an enjoyable way, but I really do not like the sneaky marketing.  I probably would have gladly paid the six bucks for the full package, but I hate being conned.

Fits my 2014 Ford CMax Energi steering wheel perfectly. Reasonably comfortable to drive and steer with it installed. It does come out of the package with an unusual smell which I believe to be from the base rubberlike material. I left it in my garage for a few days and the smell was greatly reduced, but the smell is still somewhat noticeable after a week in my car. It is not bad and I notice it more after my car has sat in the sun all day, but if you are sensitive to smell you will not like this cover. Maybe a few days in the summer sun would help.... too bad it is November!
summary: Reasonably comfortable to drive and steer with it installed

I was looking for a leather jacket, that I could afford, but was still quality made. I read some of the other reviews, and it seemed to fair well, so I got it. I love this jacket. I got it in a small, based upon the reviews saying the sizes run small, but i probably could have gotten away with an xs. It did seem tight at first, but, the leather just needs to be broken in. I love the fit, the removable lining, the over all look, and the quality. I do not feel like i am going to loose my hide if i ever end up off my bike. It is gone over 6000miles in 3 months with me and my bike, and if I ever need another jacket, I will be sure to get this one.

Not much to review here.  The screen material is exactly what you would expect...fiberglass screen material. The vinyl spline and the tool are just right to attach the screen to my windows.  I replaced the screens on the front windows in my living room holes and fraying and the new screens are barely visible.  This screen material seems to be much better than what was in my existing windows assume the old screens were original to the windows.  I am not sure if this is a trick or a widely known practice, but I would start the spline on one end of the window and then as I ran the tool along to get the rest of the spline in I would pull on the spline stretching it so it would go in easier.  The technique worked well for me and the windows still look great a few weeks later.
summary: Screens look better than the original screens

musically the album is quite good, and that is commented by others here.  I want to add though, dropping 'Fing' in the middle of a ballad is a nono for a reason.  It is not just that maybe I am a prude.  It is not that I have not done it myself, in conversation, when I should not.  But it is this: you cannot do that.  Now, I cannot play the album in my restaurant or for my kids, unless I build a playlist and take that one song out, if I can remember which one.  There is a reason .. Degas only goes so far in his paintings.  Allusion is good, but unless tossing away families with young people is a desired factor, it should be kept in mind.  Another thing is ... MIck Jagger was a phenom at burying really tart lyrics in his songs in a manner that if you know what the words mean and you also want to really think about them, then you pick them up, and meanwhile the kids and the grandparents, it goes right over their heads.  That is a good trait to learn from.  Food for thought, for the next album.  I mean, a soft ballad, with "F'ing" right in the middle of it?  DId the Ramones even do that?  Has anyone ever done that before?
summary: musically the album is quite good, and that's commented by others here

text:
I have been wearing some dark makeup throughout the winter, but when I pulled MaryLou Manizer from my beauty drawer, I knew it was springand time to change up my look.

MaryLou Manizer, a highlighter, should not be confused with BettyLou Manizer, a bronzer.  The adorable package will help you make the right choice.  MaryLou comes in a round mirrored compact with a mug shot, that is right, a mug shot of bad, blonde MaryLou.

My skin is pale, my hair is dark, and my eyes are green.  I love MaryLou Manizer for daytime as an allover eye shadow.  It highlights under my brow and on my eyelid it really makes my lashes stand out.

The honeycolored powder adds a lot of shimmer without looking glittery.  It is very soft and easy to apply.  I do find that it can gather in the creases of my eyelids by the end of the day, but because the color is so light, I really have to look for it.

I find that my eyes look brighter and much less tired when I swipe on MaryLou Manizer in the morning.

Personally, I would not wear it as a highlighter on the rest of my face unless I was heading to a party or to the beach.  I just do not think it is the right look for me.

I almost did not read this book after reading the reviews but I like to form my own opinion.  Come on ladies!  Are we that tainted by all the sexy books that we have to be so critical of a few minor editing issues?  The book was FREE!  I for one can overlook the grammatical errors, they certainly did not interfere with the storyline!!  Emma has been convinced by her best friend Violet to fake being an escort for just one night.  Violet's handsome, rich older brother Conrad has just broken up with his girlfriend.  He had planned to propose but a bitter argument caused him to change his mind.  His sister finds out that he had requested that his secretary arrange an escort for a charity ball because he was tired of romantic entanglements.  Both Conrad and Emma feel an instant attraction and succumb to a one night fling.  Lucia Jordan did a fantastic job describing the instant attraction between Emma and Conrad and the sexy bedroom scene was Hot! HOT!  I look forward to the rest of the Nailed series and strongly encourage other readers to do the same!

text: This is one of the greatest cuddleup pieces of all time, produced by the Master, Quincy Jones. With the voices of Patti Austin and James Ingram playing off each other and an arrangement by Mr. Jones that keeps things quiet but intensely emotional, this song is perfect for those moments of affection with your signifigant other, and is especially good on a cold, snowy winter night. It became a big hit in early 1983 due to its being featured on the TV show General Hospital, but is as fresh today as it was back then.

I have got digestive issues with wheat and tried this about a year ago.  That first time you try it you will probably find the texture to be a little weird; a slightly rubbery feel and somewhat chewy.  I did not notice a different taste when using spaghetti sauce.  This is so much healthier with the fiber and the drastically lower carbs per serving, but what initially had me coming back to this was the lack of digestive discomfort and needing to take something for it.  This is my default pasta.

I have tried some other pastas made with rice or other beans, but this one is the easiest to work with.  There is a very small window for rice pasta to not be under or overdone and the other pastas I have used made from other beans clump together.  I spend the entire time cooking those attempting to declump them.

I just wish you could purchase this in larger quantity from this website.  Costco sells a much larger box of this, making each serving a lot less expensive.

I will leave it to you, the reader, to research the Straight No Chaser phenomenon if they are new to you. For those of us already in the diehard fan club, this new recording just cements the brilliance of the group's arrangements and vocal chops. The sense of humor evident in many of the numbers is the perfect antidote for those who suffer from ChristmasisjustSOOOOserious syndrome.

The recording is quite good, with just a bit of cuppedhands/boxy coloration on some of the lead vocals. Imaging is spectacular on my system, with lots of apparent depth and good use of panning on some of the songs. There is unbelievable instrument mimicing, too. You will not believe at times that these guys' voices are all you are hearing.

I think two of the selections are not quite up to snuff, stylistically speaking, but I will leave it to you to figure out which two. Your mileage may vary.

My only OMG moment was in reading the song titles on the back cover. Someone at Atlantic's graphics department managed to misspell Dreidel they spelled it "Driedel." Shame on them!. It is nice that the group cites the sources of some of the snippets they incorporate into their material.

This will definitely go into my Top 10 Christmas CD collection. With dozens of discs in my collection competing for the honor, that is saying something.

And an afterthought: sometimes SNC reminds me a bit of Manhattan Transfer in their precision and extratight harmonies. Both are Atlantic Records artists. Can you imagine a supergroup made of these two acts? Maybe they could call themselves "Straight No Transfer." G
summary: More a cappella fun from SNC

I never used it to charge my phone from 35 yet. I have been using it at work around lunch time when the battery level drops to 84. I am using this portable charger with my Samsung Epic 4G Touch Samsung Galaxy S II. I call it "The Mighty Mouse Charger" because it is small, very portable but it is powerful at 5600mAH. The price is nice. I showed it to people they thought it cost more than the $49 I paid for it.

This portable charger charges at the same rate as the AC charger that comes with the phone. I can take this charger everywhere I go, it can be placed in a pants pocket with a lot of room to spare. The Samsung Epic 4G Touch has a battery life of 12 to 13 for medium use. I am a heavy user, I use the internet, Netflix, play games/music. Netflix alone can drain your phone battery pretty fast if you watch a more for one hour. I am still testing it out. You have to charge it for four to five hours the first time you get it. After that it should last 3 to 4 days before you have to charge it again.

This Anker Power Bank charger really comes in handy. I highly recommend it. Oh I had the New Trent iCruiser IMP1000 11000mAh External Battery Pack. It is 11,00mAh but it was too bulky too carry around without a backpack. I use to carry it in a hard drive case that had a belt loop. I sold it and got this one.

These Urban Spa Moisturizing Gloves are a very effective way to moisturize your hands when they are dry and rough from gardening, household chores or dry cold weather. Simply use your favorite oil or moisturizer and then slip on these gloves. They keep the creams or oils on your hands instead of having it get all over the bedding while you sleep. In the morning, your hands feel softer and smoother, having been bathed in moisturizers all night. This can be very good for fingernails as well. If you have dry, brittle or peeling nails, the moisture will help to condition them. These gloves ensure that the hand or nail products stay on your hands or nails.

I washed these in cold water the first time, but it was difficult to get much of the oil I used removed from them. The next time I used warm water that seemed to work better, with no detrimental effects to the gloves that I could see. They feel soft and hold up well.
summary: The most effective way to moisturize your hands

I must disagree with the previous reviewer.  This version of the O'Connor story is beautifully produced as well as acted.  It has a stateliness and sadness that approximate the themes of the story, that man cannot be saved  by his reason and logic alone but in a world of inexplicable evil must  submit to Christian salvation.  Like it or not, politically correct or not,  that is how O'Connor felt.
Irene Worth is magnificent as Mrs. McIntyre,  too consumed with "practical" matters to recognize the lost state  of her own soul.  And she is matched by the likes of Shirley Stoler, Lane  Smith hiliarious, John Houseman, and a very young Samuel L. Jackson.
Lastly, plaudits go to the gentle, elegiac photography and Bill Conti's  ravishingly beautiful music score.
summary: A short film deserving of more attention

text: I have bought several Hamelin CDs recently  this one, Scriabin and the Composer Pianists.  All are benchmarks for technique.  Perhaps the ease with which he navigates the obstacles is the problem, I just do not get the feeling that his heart is in it.  And I am tired of hearing his recurring mantra about how virtuosity is artistry in itself.  I do not agree.  While I am happy to hear how he avoids the pounding that Ashkenazy inflicts on Scriabin, he could use more of Vladimir's emotion.  Perhaps I just do not "get along" with his style well enough.  I think he is trying too hard to be different.  If you want to hear breathtaking technical performance and excellent recorded sound, then by all means, this is a great choice.
like it

I have been using Quicken since the late 80's.  I switched to Microsoft Money when it came out  a far superior product  but was moreorless forced to revert to Quicken when Money was discontinued.  In the early 2000's I switched to mostly using Mac computers, and started using Quicken Mac, but Intuit rapidly begin stripping essential features from the program, so I had to go back to the Windows version.

I just upgraded to the 2014 version, and like every Intuit product upgrade I have ever had, it is extremely buggy.  I will just mention a couple of items, but there are plenty more.  First, if you use flags to identify particular transactions, you can expect them to be lost when you convert.  Gone, like the wind.  Second, when working in the "Unreconciled" screen using that filter, the program constantly crashes, and has to be reopened over and over.  Third, and most annoying to me personally so far, whereas you simply had to enter your password vault password to download transactions from your bank and other financial institutions, once you do that now you are prompted to log in to Intuit with your Intuit password.  I have no interest in logging into Intuit to download transactions that are none of their business.

I have long wished there was a suitable alternative to Quicken, as I have come to avoid Intuit products like the plague some of you may remember when the company foisted it is CDilla copy protection scheme on purchasers of Turbo Tax one year, until consumer outrage forced them to back off.  I am going to redouble my efforts to find something else to track my finances.

The Stewart ProTreat Freeze Dried Treats are made in the USA without additives or preservatives in a USDA inspection facility. Though the liver is freeze dried, it still maintains the fullflavor, aroma, and nutritional value of raw liver. These treats are so simple, it is not funny! There is one ingredient; 100 turkey liver. The treats can be fed three times daily  I personally think that is too much. And for a dog over 60 pounds mine is 100 pounds, they recommend 46 of the treat pieces. The good thing is that there is only 6 calories per treat.

My dog loves these treats! But, I personally do not like them. And it is not that I do not like the brand, the flavor, the product itself. What I do not like is the smell. It is so strong and nauseating. Thankfully, I have gotten out of giving Gavan these treats. My mother has been giving them to him. It is crazy how much he enjoys these Stewart ProTreat Freeze Dried Turkey Liver Treats. He gobbles them right up and then looks around to see if there are more for him. It took a few weeks, but he is finally gone through the whole tub of the treats.

I was sent the Stewart ProTreat Freeze Dried Turkey Liver Treats in exchange for my honest opinion. However, all the opinions expressed here are my own.

Noone who has really read this book can find that this is a rewrite of Lords and Ladies. While Lords and Ladies was the weakest book of the whole series and made me somehow dislike the Witches sphere, this one  reconciliates me with it.  Finally the other witches have stepped out of  Granny Weatherwax's shadow. This makes the book far more interesting than  e.g. Lords and Ladies or Witches Abroad. The weakness of Granny Weatherwax  in this book makes her a more human and less dominant character. While with  the other books I nearly feeled that Granny would somehow take over  sometime, this one puts her in her right position again. Nanny Ogg, Magrat  and especially Agnes finally get the role they deserve.
Beside the  Witches theme, the vampire theme has also been treated in an excellent  manner. By exaggerating and mixing the attributes usually identified with  vampires, Pratchett has created a marvellous satire, only comparable to  Pyramids.
Finally, with the priest of Om, the religious theme is again  treated in Carpe Jugulum. I was very pleased with that because I think that  Small Gods was one of Pratchetts best books and regretted that religious  controverse did not reappear in his following books.
Conclusion: a  masterpiece in every aspect
summary: Certainly not a re-write of Lords and Ladies

text: It is really hard to find a shooter nowadays that I can say is close to flawless within it is genre, but Vanquish is such game. Vanquish's quick, heart pumping action elevate it is gameplay ahead of the pack, while delivering a short, but thrilling experience. You will not care much about the forgettable story and cheesy writing, because the game never attempts to take itself seriously. What you will enjoy is it is gameplay. Vanquish boasts a small, but effective arsenal. From a shotgun to a rocket launcher. The game allows you to upgrade the weapons all throughout it is 7 hour length... 7 hours? Yes, it is short, but if you are a gamer that values quality over quantity than you will spend many more hours with the highest difficulty setting and challenge mode. The visuals will keep you hooked. It is art direction while bland, gives the game a rather futuristic and distinct look. But the animations and overall scale of the game, make up for it. It is a great looking game. The audio is up to par. The electronic music matches perfectly, while the audio design is top notch. Overall: If you like shooters and love action games, you must play Vanquish. What it delivers in 7 hours, very few action games can match.
summary: Your heart won't resist this much action.

I saw this at a shop recently and bought it on a whim, mainly because I used to really enjoy this band's creative versions of two Springsteen songs, "Blinded by the Light" and "For You." Those are both on here, but there also been other fine tunes that I have found myself liking a lot as well. I do not think I would ever listened to an entire album by Manfred Mann before getting this CD, and now I could kick myself for ignoring them for so long. I suppose they were considered "too pop" because they had a few hit singles, but most of the material on here straddles the line between progressive rock and the heavier side of poprock. Some very creative compositions and long instrumental passages with wicked guitar riffs and blazing keyboards. And this particular collection has over 70 minutes of music, including some decent live tracks I am sure that felt like they had to include alive version of "The Mighty Quinn", but it is far from the best cut on here. All in all, a very satisfying listen.

This is my favorite chocolate I use to make my own. I melt about 4 Tbs of coconut oil gently. Then I have grated the chocolate in a turning grater and stir in 2 TBS chopped or grated cocoa butter well until melted. This is the most difficult to melt! Heat a little if necessary. Then stir in 5 T of grated chocolate or chopped. rounded a bit,  5 TBS real maple syrup or honey, 1 tsp vanilla extract 1 tsp mint extract or 2 tsp vanilla. Stir and stir together and let cool or refrigerate. I have an immersion blender I use to quicken the mixing process. Many people never go back to eating chocolate bars again. You can stir in anything you want...nuts, fruits, bacon, ginger and so on. I like it plain, however, you can make it anyway you want! If you like darker flavor, leave out the cocoa butter and  add more chocolate.

We all have different tastes. I have tried several organic varieties and use only organic ingredients. This is also fair trade and I love the flavor.

Most people in the public at large now know Peter Jackson for his amazing "Lord of the Rings" movie, and his upcommig latter two installments. His older movies, laced with devilish wit, extreme violence, and original plots are definitely worth taking a look at.
The story is about a young man with an overbearing mother, your typical dysfunctional family with a tainted history. One day, when her son is on a date at the zoo, she follows them and is bitten by the zoo's most gruesome and  unusual display, a "Rat Monkey" the offspring of foreign rats mating with tree monkeys.
Without giving too many details away, the results are horrific. The amount of violence in this movie is extreme, but done so in a way that is more silly than horrifying. Graphic as it is, it is all part of the fun. People who are sensitive to blood and gore should probably avoid this movie all the same.
The "Dead Alive" DVD is worth getting mainly because it contains the Unrated version, which is the only way to see this movie. Where I live, the Unrated version was not available on video, so the DVD was a great find. The "R" version in question is not worth taking a second look at, since it is extremely watered down, and much of the satirical fun is removed. The DVD has the standard DVD functions, such as subtitles and widescreen. A bit lacking in the extra features department, but I am not complaining.
If you are curious about Jackson's older movies, this is definitely one of his best. I would recommend watching this with "Meet the Feebles" and "Heavenly Creatures". It would be one unusual film fest. Enjoy.
summary: Peter Jackson's best cult film. Not for weak stomachs.

text:
As is the case with anyone that has a drop of Nordic blood in them, I am a huge believer in the benefits of dry brushing your skin for health.
If you have never tried it, you will not believe how great it makes your skin feel and look, and this brush is a wonderful tool to start with.
First of all there are slight curves on the handle. This means that whether you grip the brush at the top or closer to the bottom it will be comfortable and not slip around. The bristles look to be natural, and have just the right amount of stiffness for exfoliation. Simply rub on your skin gently so that all of the dead skin flakes off.
Next, I like to get in the shower and use the brush while it is wet to both cleanse and to use the bumpy side to massage my legs and rear.
Afterwards, a good quality moisturizer or oil and you are all set.

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

with all that said, if your vent duct does not have to many bends, and you want to take the risk maybe i had a defective kit that the brush broke, you might save a lot of money doing it yourself!

text:
The short version:
There are a couple fairy tale creatures, a tiny bit of action, but mostly this story is about relationships.

The longer version:
So I was bummed about the amount of fairy tale creature interaction this book had. The horned boy in the coffin does not have much "page time". I feel like we barely meet him, barely get to learn his story, barely have some adventure with him. The story is mostly about a sister and brother. It is about them being neglected as kids, the problems with her brother's gift, why she kisses a lot of boys, wandering the woods pretending to be knights, why they keep secrets from each other...on and on. It is good to have relationships build and stories shared, but it was not what I thought this book was offering. For how much could have happened with this fairy tale land around them it felt empty. Even the interactions with the horned boy that we have been looking forward to since the book started felt empty and boring. I liked the relationships and the characters stories, but the rest of the aspects of the novel did not deliver for me.

SEXY SEXY SEXY!!! This is a very short story, maybe a 2030 minute read, if that and is part of the Roommate series that are all stand alone pieces of YUM!

This one a f/f/slightly allowed to be there male.

Rene is a gifted writer seen in a book even with an erotic topic and written in so few pages. Her words weave a tale of seduction and hot sex and the reader gets to dive right in w/o the drama of a full novel. It is so refreshing to have a stash of short reads that get down to business but do not read as a trashy novel. The sex is steamy and very well written. MORE!!

This is f/f/with a guy thrown in there.

Would I recommend? YES YES YES!!!

text:
This case is really two pieces, leather front and back, and a harder plastic case. The outer case is the better of the two in terms of quality and design. It has a magnet  on the flap to keep the front cover closed. Should you want to leave it open on you desk, you can fold it back, even using the flap to keep it open or you can use it as a horizontal stand.. Additionally there is a small pocket inside the front flap, large enough hold a credit card, ID, and bills. The plastic case seems like the weakest part of this case. While I do like the openness of the case on the bottom to avoid any lightening adapter issues, it is too open elsewhere, meaning if you drop this phone and it lands on an unprotected side, your iPhone will damage at least slightly. I also wish it gripped the phone tighter. It seems like with use, especially if you take the phone in and out of the case  too often, it might stop holding the phone altogether.

 These two issues, aside, I recommend this attractive case as long as you do not plan on abusing your iPhone or its case. text: It does what it is supposed to do, however the radio sounds a bit distant and trying to load it can be frustrating. I ended up having to buy another card reader/writer in order to use this to the fullest extent. It is quite small and compact, which is mostly a good thing.

There is no reduced visibility as far as being able to see numbers and letters.  Remember, however, this is a glare reducer  not just a screen protector.  The screen is just not going to be as bright as before.

It does its job.  I can now read without eye strain.

I just put this up this morning. I had seen another review where the millet the tiny white seeds in bird seed fell through the holes. I could see they could, so I "think" I solved the problem. I cut a piece of landscape fabric to size, and placed it in the bottom, on top of the screen. That way water can still pass through, but the seeds will not. When there are too many hulls, I will just lift the fabric out, shake the hulls off, and then replace it. I have not had any experience yet, but it SHOULD work. I will update my review later.

Well, this feeder has been up through a couple of rains and snows. I am happy to report that the landscape fabric really works, so if you are concerned about small seeds falling through, try the landscape fabric!
summary: Love my feeder, have great idea for making it better

I am loving this game. It is wholeheartedly a game I can lose hours to. Not many games I play can get me to sit down and play and dread turning my console off but this game is one of them. As a huge fan of the original trilogy I was closely followong the development of this game. Every November 7th I would look forward to an update and hope for a release date. Now it is here and I am so happy.

There seems to be a bandwagon with bashing this game. People keep complaining about the facial animations, but neither I nor my husband have seen an issue. I called him into the room and asked if the faces looked weird and he said no. And he is one to let others opinions influence his. Now I have seen the occasional frame rate dip but it was only for a couple seconds and had no impact on my experience at all. Amazon reviews have become quite hard to trust. You have people who have never even held the product writing bad reviews cuz they are upset they do not have it and want to lash out. It is sad. This truly is a great game. I am enjoying the new story line immensely. Who would not want to find a new home for the human race? Or form new connections with alien species?

Bottom line. Do not pay attention to these reviews. Form your own opinion. If you loved the first 3 as much as I did, then you will love this one. I am so happy to be back exploring the galaxy with a new crew and new interesting characters.

He is wanted him for years. When fate puts Eric in the same town as the man he is wanted for years, he knows this could be his only chance to have him though the timing could not be worse. He will do whatever possible to get Jordan Barr in his bed, even if it is just for one night.

Jordan has to resist him. At least that is what he keeps telling himself as Eric continues to pursue him. He knows he cannot risk his future and responsibilities on just playing around with Eric Higgins.

Play Hard is JT Fox's debut novel and it was a really good start. This serial has a lot of potential to be great. I think Play Hard was developed well considering the length of the story. It is a very quick read and it is freaking hot to say the least! The characters were relatable and easy to connect with. I just feel as though certain parts of the story were redundant. The chemistry between Jordan and Eric is palpable and I honestly could not get enough of them. I cannot wait to read book 2.
summary: This serial has a lot of potential to be great

You have to look at this magazine in comparison to the one that is ranked right above it in its category  The Economist.

Both magazines download every week and you have the content ahead of anyone who might be waiting for the physical hard copy.  You can be done with next week's magazine before the weekend starts.

Both have a fairly wide ranging look at the business world.  However, the Economist goes further in depth with regions that are not America.  There is a lot of content in the Economist, so much that it is almost hard to read cover to cover every week if you have other things you might want to read.

BusinessWeek's brevity, in this light can be either a detriment or a selling point.  Most of the nonfeature articles are around five hundred words.  There is even a greater way to save time, where the bottom of the article has a onesentence synopsis called "The Bottom Line".  It is kind of reductive, but nice if you are pressed for time.

A big drawback is the formatting.  There are no photos in BusinessWeek, nor are there any charts.  It is all text.  The Economist has some photos from the print edition, and as far as I know, all of the charts Even if they are hard to read at times on the screen.

The selling point is price.  The monthly price is about 30 of that which the Economist is asking for.  As much as I like the Economist, I am keeping my subscription to Business Week because of the premium and the less time I need to spend, even though I am not entirely comfortable with my choice, it feels like the best one.
summary: A Better Value, but with some issues

Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.

Other info:
 My phone 2014 Moto X was having issues connecting to my bluetooth HRM while they were already connected to these headphones. My solution was to connect the HRM first, headphones second. Problem solved.

I have only worked out with them once, but if there is another con over time for example, the battery does not last as long as advertised, or sweat makes its way in and ruins them, then I will update my review accordingly. However, for the price I paid, I would not be terribly disappointed if I only got a year out of them.

Overall, if poor sound quality is not a deal breaker for you, then get these phones.

Headsup, folks! If you are tempted to buy the bundled group of coffee maker, water filter and permanent gold coffee filter featured on this page, please note that the cone filter 04933 does NOT fit the Krups KM9008!  I discovered this the hard way  I simply assumed that the featured filter was offered because it fit this machine and thought I would be saving myself some shopping time by ordering it along with the machine. This machine requires a basket type filter and not a cone filter.  I found that a standard Mr. Coffee gold basket filter for 812 cup coffee makers fits this model.  As to the machine itself  I am delighted with it  it is very easy to operate and solves the problem of different "coffee times" within my family.  No more sludgy coffee sitting in the warming carafe. I noted that one reviewer complained of the temperature of the coffee produced, but I have found it to be piping hot even after it is been in the machine for close to two hours. Bottom line is this machine produces a delicious, hot cup of coffee. I think you will be pleased with it.
summary: Great machine, but bundled filter doesn't fit machine

It may be hard now to understand the depth of loathing that was directed at Paul McCartney when "Ram" was originally released in the dark days of the postBeatles breakup era.
Indeed, much of Paul's work after the Fabs imploded is hard to take. But the fact is the strength of the Beatles was collective in nature, and each member served as a counter balance to the massive egos not necessarily a bad thing involved. And each member's solo work suffered the same inconsistent quality that plagued Paul.
To be honest, you could probably only cobble together a couple of strong LPs of "greatest" hits from the solo Fabs body of work
with Ringo faring the best in terms of comparison to his Beatles songs.
But "Ram" hardly deserved the unremitting barbs hurled at it from all critical and "hip" sides. It is a wonderful and entertaining pop work that has aged very gracefully.
In my opinion, "Ram" is Paul's best postBeatles work other than his masterful and gutsy "Band on the Run."
summary: Not a masterpeice, but hardly a disaster

text: All right, I have something I need to get off my chest. First, though, the review. This is incredible. While not quite in the class of Blood on the Tracks and the electric trilogy of 6566, its still a dern fine piece of work, right next to Freewheelin', John Wesley Harding,  and Time Out of Mind, masterpieces all. Tweedle Dee is a great opener, bluesy, a little bluegrass, awesome, straight through the finale Sugar Baby, which is a song that can take it is rightful place in Dylan's canon next to the other greats. Po' Boy is a wonderful song along with the fun Summer Days, the blues rocker Lonesome Day Blues, and especially Highwater, the second best song on the album, behind the instant classic, Mississippi. This brings me to what really cheeses me. How, how I ask, can people criticize his voice? A conventional voice singing Mississippi would have made it just a good song. Dylan's voice does something to it that is unimaginable if you have heard the Sheryl Crow version. His voice is an additional instrument that no one else knows how to play. Dylan's is truly beautiful singing. This voice is a worldweary, but I have survived dangnabbit voice and is truly a revelation. Feel free to follow Ricky Martin and his crew of phonies who are destroying American music, if that is your thing; eventually you will find that road leads nowhere and long after they are gone, Dylan will remain.

text: The iPod Touch 4th Generation can now function as a stand alone computer, or at least what most people use their stand alone computers for, anyway........surfing, email, skype, books, music, and videos. The best surprise is the Retina Display. I can curl up anywhere and watch a movie. The picture is sharp, sharp, sharp. The image almost jumps right off the screen. Even the briefest of app research tells you that you could use the iPod Touch as the ultimate personal assistant from the time you wake up in the morning until you finally go to bed at night, all with something you can shove in your jeans pocket. The iPod Touch completely exceeds my expectations.

What do you get when you have a hot Cuban MMA fighter and a bossysexy Brazilian gym owner? You get one hot story, that is what ! I Have been following the Worth the Fight series from Sidney Halston from the beginning and was really looking forward to Tony and Francescas story.  Tony is the kind of hero that if you did not love so much, you would hate.  Hes macho, arrogant, a womanizer, overly jealous and has a raging temper.  Hes horrible, right? WRONG! I wanted yo hate Tony so many times during the book, wished that Francesca would just slap his smug face and tell him to get lost.  But then he would say something totally sweet and unexpected with his smooth Latin accent and you just cannot help it, you turn into a gooey mess, wishing you were in Francescas skyhigh stilettos
These two getting together was not a big surprise.  What was surprising was how insecure Francesca turned out to be underneath that tough, polished armor.  Only a very determined man could have broken through it. And  Tony is the perfect man for the job.  The story has its ups and downs. Frankly, I thought that Francescas insecurities were a bit too much, but in the end even she could not ignore Tonys charms.
I have to say that the men of Worth the Fight Academy seem to be getting sexier and sexier as the series continues.  I Am guessing that Cains story is going to be  next . I absolutely love this series and believe that its one of the best sports romance series out there.  Do Not deny  yourself this pleasure!!!
Thank you Netgalley and Random House Publishing for providing this ARC in exchange for an honest review.
summary: Would have hated Tony if I didn't love him so much!

Red Star Active Dry Yeast is my favorite of the two familiar retail brands.  If you frequently bake yeast breads and rolls, you know that you use a significant amount of yeast.  A 4 oz. jar of active dry yeast at the local grocer costs between $3.68 and $4.38 or the equivalent of between $14.42 and $17.52 a pound.

I had formerly been able to purchase a 1 lb. pouch of Red Star Active Dry Yeast at one of the warehouse stores, but they no longer have it available.  I was pleased to find Red Star Active Dry Yeast, 2Pound Pouch on Amazon and contacted their partner America Anywhere about the products expiration date and the conditions under which the yeast was stored.  They responded rapidly and their information was both specific and accurate.

For home use, I transfer 4 oz. of yeast to an old yeast jar and store it in the refrigerator.  I use a clip to fasten the opened pouch, place it in a freezer bag that I seal and then store it in the freezer until I need to replenish the smaller jar.  This maintains the active aspect of the yeast until several months after the expiration date.

Purchasing Red Star Active Dry Yeast, 2Pound Pouch resulted in a tremendous savings and, with an expiration date of January 2017, the product is fresh and has enough longevity remaining that I need only use between 9 oz. and 10  oz. to reach the grocers price.  If you bake yeast breads, I definitely recommend purchasing your yeast from Amazon and their partner, America Anywhere.
summary: Best Price for a Favorite Yeast and a Wonderful Amazon Partner - America Anywhere - Made This a 5-Star Purchase ...

At first this contraption was a little confusing. I read the directions about 3 times before I felt okay about going through with the project  was not fully confident as there were a lot of warnings about making sure the drill was going the right way/you turned it the right way so you would not lose rods in the dryer vent. Scared me a little. However, the project turned out really well. We did not lose any rods thankfully and we got out the birds nest that had taken residence in our dryer vent!!
The part that was for the lint catcher was convenient as well and is actually recommended to be used at least once a month in order to clean out the lint catcher. I do need to keep up with this but it is not convenient to have to put together and tape the rods each time when you only really use it for a couple of minutes. However, if you have a handy space to keep it already together, I can see how this would be even better for keeping up with cleaning the lint out.

Rimelda is a seer with great talent and she is sure she can help end the war. Trying to work with Prince Ander to do so, proves to be a little more challenging than she bargained for, as he doubts her abilities and there is some attraction present.

Most of this book takes place on the quest to stop the war, which keeps the adventure going. Things often happen suddenly, which spikes the tension levels, and then they would drift down to a steady pace again. Personally, I would have loved the romantic interactions to be more gradual, as they often happened out of the middle of nowhere and were very impulsive, with regrets as to the outcomes, more often than not. Prince Ander is definitely a bit frustrating!

I enjoyed the minor mysteries surrounding the quest and the surprises that crop up. The characters are fun and are not your stereotypical ones. The adventure and battles are what really drives the story to the climax. This is a great addition to a high fantasy series.

Content: violence war, talk of death and killing in nongraphic details; mild romance kissing. Clean!

text:
Lexie Kowalsky is all grown up and making us laugh out loud all over again. We first meet Lexi when she is a little girl in Simply Irresistible but now that she is an adult her life is one crazy roller coaster ride that you need to be on with her.
Sean Knox is the newest player for the Chinooks. A Fantastic player but also a cocky one at that and when your coach The Wall is not your biggest fan you really need not to get on his bad side, little does he know that Lexi Kowalsky will come running into his life literally and that is when all mayhem ensues.
Lexi  Sean meet under the craziest of circumstances but when the story snowballs you can help finding yourself getting caught up in their crazy and loving the ride it takes you on.
This book will bring back memories of how GeorgeAnne and John met but with a fun twist. All I know is the minute I saw page one I was hooked and did not look up again until I saw the words The End.

text: Classic.

So, this is what life comes down to when you are 50 years olTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry  reviewing dryer vent cleaners while sitting at your kitchen table waiting for American Idol.  This is not what I envisioned when I was 12, I can tell you that much.  You kids who think it will not happen to you?

It will.  Sorry to burst your bubble.

That said, the product works great.  Our dryer pretty much stopped working and we were thinking we needed a new one, which was seriously going to eat into my plastic surgery budget.  One last shot before a trip to the appliance store was this Gardus LintEater.  My husband, who is not the handy one of the family, had to do the work as I have a torn labrum.  Which sounds dirtier than it is  that is part of your shoulder.  He, the clumsiest man in the world, had absolutely no problem using this.  I warned him to read the directions first, and he actually listened and followed.  He hooked it up to the drill, and away he went.  He got a bunch of musty, wet lint that had probably been up inside the wall since 1977   probably consisting of bell bottom material and macram.

Now our dryer actually dries clothes again, and I can continue to save for my facelift. Thank you Gardus.

I guess there will be two versions of DGD, Jonny Craig, and Kurt Travis.  Like a lot of people, I was hooked by Craig's voice and followed him to Emarosa and kind of dismissed this album and Happiness.  I came back to them in the last year and they are really fantastic and I have grown to love Kurt's voice as well.

The songs definitely get more experimental than on Downtown Battle Mountain, and that is a good thing.  They seem to have a little more fun with this release, and less aggression.  Musically, I believe they stepped it up.  They are free from pretty much all cliches and it is incredibly original.  Songs like Hot Water on Wool are just brilliant.  I also love Rock Solid, the breakdown gives me chills.

Kurt has a different approach than Jonny, less taking over the song and more fitting into it.  They also feature some guest vocals, which are terrific.  All the musicians are terrific with their instruments, meshing together better than the first album, something they have continued to do with each release.

Overall, really a unique album, well written, another great chapter by the band.

text:
I am a recess aide and on my feet all day long. I tried these shoes on in the store before purchasing them on Amazon. They are very lightweight and comfortable. I was surprised how great they felt. I have not had a pair of Nikes since Nike shoxs came out. They are so much more lightweight than those. I wore them an entire day the first day and had no problems. The second day; however, I got a pain in my hip to the point where I started limping. As soon as I got home and took them off, the pain was gone the rest of the evening. I am only 30 by the way. Nothing else in my daily routine changed except wearing these shoes two days in a row. I do not understand why it would make my hip hurt since they are comfortable on my feet, but I am sure that was the problem. I wore different shoes today and had no pain. I do not think as much as I am on my feet I will be able to wear them an extended amount of time. I will have to rotate wearing them every other day. For normal wear, I believe, people will be fine. I am literally walking or standing six hours a day straight.

UPDATE: So, initially after wearing them, I had hip pain after wearing them. I do not know if they just needed to be broken in, but I wear them all the time now and have not experienced any pain since the first couple times of wearing them. They are comfortable, and I love them even more now.

Easterly simply points out the fact that nothing will work across the board, and that western interventions based on appeasing the western public and economic interests does not work in all cases. In fact, it hardly works at all. He shows that specialized plans created by those who will be implementing and gaining from them are much more effective than grandoise schemes created "planners." This idea can be directly translated to sustainability where scientists are quickly finidng that many different solutions is the real solution. The problem most people find with this is that a he says things they do not like to hear and b some claim that he does not provide evidence of what would have happened without intervention. BUT he uses many examples such as China and Chile to in fact show this, so clearly these people just have not finished the book. He really does not say anything that can be contradicted as if there really was "one giant plan" to end all plans, it would be discovered from the bottom up, as equally as  the top down which I do not think would be the case at all. My only critique is that he is pretty hostile towards Sachs for an academic work, but I do not care because I think that Sachs is a pompous idiot that is needed to be knocked down a notch for a while. I think that combining Easterly's work with those of Paul Collier and the theory of Amartya Sen would be the ideal combination, but that is just me.
summary: My favorite book on development thus far

This is my first 3D printer so I am working though some adjustments and settings for optimal printing.  I had a couple of issues but Printrbot quickly responded with a replacement part and answered questions.

From what I have seen of some 3D printing results I am getting very good results from the Printrbot metal.

The kit is fairly easy to put together, but you will need to pick up some Blue LocTite and be sure you have an assortment of Allen wrenches handy.  They included several Allen Wrenches but I still needed to dig one out of my tool collection.

The instructions are pictures with some notes on them.  There are a couple of spots where the pictures are not clear, so if that is a big concern then go with the assembled printer instead of the kit, it is only $70 more.  But building the kit will help you when you need to repair something on the printer in the future, and the Printrbot forum is very active and helpful.

I would purchase another one if I needed it.

I am blown away by the number of positive reviews I have been seeing about this game.  I am starting to wonder if we are all talking about the same product.

This is a nice, light cover that does a good job at keeping the rain and sun off your RV.  Caveat: this thing rips at so much as a stern glance.  The metal trigger for the awning punched 3 holes  very easily  while pulling the cover over the side.  Very frustrating.  Further, duct tape does not adhere very well to this cover, making said holes a bit of a challenge to patch.
The side straps install very easily and I really like the padded tabs with metal inserts  allowing you to bend to fit to whatever nook or ledge you find to hook them in.  I also appreciate the side zippers allowing easy door access when I go out every couple of weeks to exercise the engine and generator.
I would probably buy this again, knowing what I do now, as it is very easy to get over my 40' RV and  so far  has held up to some fairly strong wind.  I will definitely be jamming a tennis ball or something over that metal trigger as soon as possible as it continues to chew through the cover with every little breeze.
summary: Serviceable, easy to install, easy to tear.

I got this in the shade "dark beige".  This concealer pen is very easy to use and the shades are perfect for olive skintones.  The color blends well, does not crease, and lasts all day.  My only concern in regards to this concealer is price.  The pen itself is tiny. Even smaller than most ink pens.  This would not be that big of a deal if the price were lower, but given the current price point, this pen is outrageously tiny.  Great concealer but not nearly enough product for the price!

I have a hard time putting down a $20 flexnib fountain pen because I am so used to having to spend so much on fountain pens to get the quality I am looking for.  But in the end, this pen is a disappointment for two major reasons:

It requires too much pressure to flex.  It is not that I feel uncomfortable or it takes to much strength, it is that the force results in heavy scratching or even breaking through the paper.
It requires "tuning" constantly and frankly despite trying multiple of the suggestions online, I can never find a good balance between good flow when not flexing and good flow when flexing a lot.

I have tried high end flex pens from multiple sources and trust me, this is a cheap, low quality pen.  And I do not even mean that as harshly as it sounds, because it is very, very inexpensive.  It is just not fair to compare a $500 pen to a $20 pen.

But at the end of the day I need something that will write well and this is not it.  I think the folks at noodler need to come up with as cheap of a 14k flex nib as possible the softer gold is needed to get a good flex.  I bet they could do it for $75 and I would be first in line to buy it.

This pot replaced a round pasta pot that came with an ultra cheap kitchen starter set. The quality of this new pot is excellent, the heat transfer area on the bottom is sturdy and I cannot see this pot becoming misshapen like my thin, cheap older pot.
I deducted a star because it took several hand washings to stop getting purple residue in the water. Also, the oval shape of the pot leads to an awkward locking method for the lid that is not as secure as I would like. The cheap older pot was round, and the lid positively locked by inserting tabs on the rim of the pot and rotating 90 degrees. When boiling water and steam are involved, I do not want to be concerned about a lid coming loose and dumping my food in the sink or scalding me.  For the options I found when looking though, this still seems to be the best combination of quality, price, and utility.

Edit: after  several months of use, I do not recommend this pot at all. It is nearly impossible to keep the lid on when draining; I have to use oven mitts and hold the lid while trying to drain... Not something I will let my wife attempt. This is an accident waiting to happen.

I have spent about 30 hours with it and have made several amazon review videos. It can do lots of advanced things when you want. I found the interface confusing and nonstandard. It took me 10 minutes to find "Help." My dislike of Corel was reinforced during the initial learning curve.

PROs:

  Very Affordable at 30 bucks
  Very few bugs so far
  Tons of capability for advanced editing

OKs:

  It sometimes freezes until you reposition the timeline window Infrequent and easily worked around.
  The online help system usually solves your questions. Sometimes not.
  Lots of effects, but mostly cheesy. Not enough tasteful transitions, for example.

CONs:

  Interface does not follow Windows conventions. Quite frustrating at first.

 Comments  questions welcome
summary: Good Value, Lots of Features, A Few Gripes

Little did I know that Dr. Vampyre has no vampyres in the story. It is not even a paranormal. I primarily read paranormals, and in the end it made no difference. The book held my interest and the characters were interesting and according to author, real people with the exception of the two main characters John and Ylati, bet you always wondered if authors did this.

The main character is John who has Lupus. Horrible disease, and one I knew little of before reading the story. Afterwards I have appreciation for those who suffer from the disease must go through.

I enjoyed the interaction of the characters. And how John went from someone who his disease controlled him to how he controlled him. Some of the ways that he controlled it was well interesting. Turns out some Lupus patients do drink blood, so guess it was a tiny bit of vamp to the book. And also learned something about SM. That is in the book too. The sex scenes were well written and not overdone and fit into the story line.

I like Ylati as the female lead. She was just the character to shake John up and their byplay was great. I cannot tell you too much about that, it gives the story away.

The story read easily and I finished most of it during my lunch hour. Try this story, you will enjoy it.
summary: This is not a story about a Vampyre who's a doctor, but still give it a try

I bought this iBert after reading reviews of many different types of seats and trailers.  My son is 7 months old and he loves bike rides!  He is 26" tall and will be riding in this iBert for a long long time.  Definitely make sure your child is able to hold his/her head very well, the bouncing of the bike would be rough for the newly sitting babies.  I have a Trek 3speed cruiser bike.  The iBert clamps to the steer tube and turns as I turn.  It is very well centered so it does not affect my balance or steering ability.  I have not hit my knees at all.  I read that as your baby gets heavier, steering and balance may be affected.  I put a 26 pound, 2year old in there and it still did fine.  She even had growing room for her feet.  The box says up to 42" tall.  Also, you can get extra parts from the iBert website.  I got the pad for the seat, the seat I bought here did not come with one.  I would recommend this seat to anyone.  You can see your child, talk to him/her, and know if they fall asleep Happy face or smiley

I really enjoyed Kaffir Boy, I found it very engaging and interesting. My husband was born the same year as Mark in Cape Town. His upbringing was very different from Mark's as a white boy. As a matter of fact he was not even aware of apartheid until the early 90's. I figured I needed to read Kaffir Boy in America to find out what happened in Mark's life. It has been a huge disappointment. As one of the reviewers mentioned Mark continually pats himself on the back because he is so wonderful. I am about 75 through this book and all it has succeeded in doing is making me angry. He made stupid decison after stupid decision while living off of Stan Smith's money. He could not keep a scholarhip or stay on an athletic team because of his bad attitude. He changed undergrad colleges 4 times. Yes, Mark you have an attitude. I hope that you paid Stan back for the college education he bought you. I spent $50,000 on my education, I did not have any help. Mark quit working on a master's in journalism at Columbia University while on a full scholarship because he did not feel like finishing it. Wah, wah, wah. How many people would have loved an opportunity like that? Does not matter if you grew up in SA or the US or are black or white or purple, that is not an opportunity you just pass up.  Mark, listen to your Momma. Jesus Christ is the only way you are going to be saved. Your own enlightenment because you think you are so intelligent is not going to get you anywhere.

I enjoyed Michael Kiwanuka's debut album, "Home Again" but felt that it fell short of greatness and did not quite live up to all the hype. Some terrific songs and others that sounded more like filler. But this new one, however, his second full album, is much more impressive in all respects, fulfilling the promise shown on his debut. This time around, Kiwanuka sounds more confident, the songs are stronger, and the whole package is enhanced by Danger Mouse's stellar production. From the first track to the last one, this album commands your attention.

Vocally, Kiwanuka truly sounds like he is more of his own man on this album, shedding the Bill Withersisms of the debut. Not that that was a bad thing at all  if you want to be compared to someone, Withers is a great benchmark  but his approach on this album sounds less derivative and more natural, and also much more passionate. And as good as this album is, I have a gut feeling that his next album will be even more powerful and memorable. Cannot wait to hear more music from this very impressive young singersongwriter.

first thing first: it works. the kit is great in what it consists of and the price is just right i think. to call someone to clean my dryer vents i got quoted from 80 all the way up to 200 bucks. so if you were able to do it yourself you will need to invest a bit more in a "construction" vacuum that cost about 80100 bucks and start the savings basically from the second time you do it.

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

with all that said, if your vent duct does not have to many bends, and you want to take the risk maybe i had a defective kit that the brush broke, you might save a lot of money doing it yourself!

I have had two computers with Windows 98SE and three with ME, and now have one with Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry, so I know all the different quirks.  Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry is quite stable.  No run time errors like 98SE, no crashes and reboots.  I find it a very easy to use, very stable system.  I also like many of the features, such as the error log.  Instead of listing errors that mean nothing to you, when you right click on the event you get an explanation of what that error means, what caused it and a hyperlink to link to click for further informations and solutions.
I highly recommend this to anyone tired of the constant errors and crashes if other windows versions.

When it arrived, the box was dented up. Maybe it was a returned one repackaged? Then I actually tried using them... I have arthritis in my hands, and the only wire this would bend and cut was extremely thin wire I could bend myself with my arthritic self. Thicker crafting wire, where one would actually need working tools bent them side to side and would slide off and make a loud snapping noise. Do not even get me started on the sniping/cutting tools. I just had to laugh at the situation. I do not have the time or patience to send them back. Do not waste your money unless you plan on using strictly thin wire. Also the before nose are too thick to get any detail. Please save your money, unless I just got a completely jacked up set, I would never even think of buying again or recommending to anyone. It is just cheap junk.

You will have a hard time finding a name brand tv of this quality for this price. Easily the best tv I have ever owned. Slim profile, sick bezel, sick picture, sick price. Great blacks, great motion. If you are looking for a 55" or around there that is not one of those $3,000 4K infinity pools you will have a hard time finding a better one. I was sold on LGs after I had a cheapo brand break after a year and a half and decided I was only doing name brands from then on. Since then none of my tvs have broken. LGs tend to have great pictures and really intuitive, wellthoughtout features. This tv is no different. I really love the Smart TV interface. I did not even want a Smart TV because I already have two streaming devices, but I have found myself using it just because it is better than what I am currently using a chromecast and an xbox 360. The only real problem I have encountered has been the Van Haus wall mount they sell on Amazon an amazing wall mount for $25 by the way covers some of the outlets on the back the ethernet cable input, and some colored video/sound things. None of them are inputs I use, but it would really piss me off if they were. They are right where I think most mounts would cover which really begs the question what they were thinking with placement. In any case though, it is a great tv. Buy. Buy. Buy.

text:
I have played 2 hours into the game so far, and would have to say that I am totally excited to finish this game, its always a good thing to have a game that you really want to keep playing. Reasons why? It has a story that keeps you interested, and characters that are not the same old thing. This game its totally story driven, and dark and awesome. Its about a 21 year old girl named Jen that has a violent wake up call, and finds out she is half demon and has been specially picked for greater perpose.
Graphically this game shines, it has some of the best graphics out on PS2 I have seen, huge levels and crazy detail.
The controls are different but refreshing and new, its not like your typical 3rd person adventure.
The combat is awesome, I have not actually gotten into many fights but the ones I have gotten into are really fun, but simple.
Voice acting is superb, they seem to have chosen some great voices to put these characters together.
Music is very immersive and dark, they even play heavy metal during the fights!
I was really excited to when I saw the preview on this game, because they have not released many dark gothic games for the PS2 that shinedall...if you want to play the DMC series I would suggest the first one. So this is definately a great game what I have played so far, I will give a complete review when I finish this game. So, go buy this game!

This toy is absolutely awesome. I seriously have been looking for "Shimmer and Shine" toys everywhere for months and had not been able to find them, much to the dismay of my 2 and 3 year old. When this came in the mail today their faces lit up like it was Christmas.

The set comes with 2 dolls and a flying carpet. You will need 3 AAA batteries to get the carpet to talk it is the carpet that talks and not actually the dolls. The dolls are very cute and well made. My daughters love playing with their hair.

Now, the reason this is getting 4 stars instead of 5. My daughters cannot get the dolls seated in the "holders" on the carpet by themselves so now every 15 minutes or so I am hearing "Mommy can you put her on the carpet?" That and you have to be very careful taking the dolls out of the box which is not easy or the shoes are going to fly off and disappear. We were able to find the shoes for one doll and not the other hence one barefoot doll. They should have just painted the shoes on instead of making them removable.

Other than that this is one of the only Shimmer and Shine playsets I have been able to find and my daughters absolutely love it.
summary: Finally a Shimmer and Shine Playset! My Daughters Love It.

The music on this CD is mostly for punctuating the action scenes in Iron Man.  Those looking for a something with more emotional depth like Danny Elfman's "Batman" Score, or John Williams "Superman:TM" soundtrack should look elsewhere.  This soundtrack does not have memorable themes like those two CDs.

This soundtrack served the movie very well though.  If you listen to the CD, and you have seen the movie you will probably be able to picture the scene during which a piece of music is used.

I liked it, and I am sure I will put it on from time to time over the next few months, but in all fairness, I recognize that it is probably because I enjoyed the heck out of the movie.  Aside from the hilarious "Institutionalized" track by Suicidal Tendencies, there are not any real gems on this CD.
summary: Fine If You Liked The Movie

So far, I have tried the three varieties of Rosamonte yerba that caught my attention. The tradition, the suave and the special selection. This seems to be the best but none of them are by any means bad. I have tried a couple of other brands. Taragui comes to mind. I ordered a lot of that because it had an outstanding price for a lot of yerba and I could not pass it up. It was OK but pretty strong and I regretted it.

 After that, I just went back to Rosamonte and never looked back. I do not want to discourage yerba mate drinkers from experimenting but if you are going to do it, always order in small amounts until you know what you like. Believe it or not, everything about yerba mate can vary dramatically from one brand to the next and it sucks to have a bunch of yerba mate on hand that you are not that fond of. And it is not cheap when you pretty much have to order it.

 Anyway, the Rosamonte Seleccion Especial. I love the extra smoky flavor. I use cream and sweetener and it mingles perfectly. Nice thing about yerba mate is it seems to be perfect for experimentation. Add a little lemon or mint flavor and it tastes like it was meant to be.

I have gone through more bead storage options that I care to remember.  A lot of it was great on  paper, but ineffective in reality.

These have a several  good things going for them.  First, I just love the rounded bottoms.  Do you know what it is like having a crimp  bead on the bottom of a flat container?  These rounded bottoms save  a lot of aggravation.  Secondly,  the tops fit  tight to the dividers.  No more mixed colors.  Thirdly is that a word?  is the fixed compartments.  Why is that good?  well, because, despite the best intentions, the adjustable compartment dividers NEVER sit flat enough to keep tiny items from sneaking in from one compartment to the next.  Finally, you can stack them.  While they are not  interlocking so one will not keep the next from falling They do sit flat on top of the one beneath.

So what would I change?  Well,  I would like them to stack tighter.  Not necessarily locking, but a protrusion that fit into the next would be good.  I would also like  fixed compartments of different sizes for such stuff as three inch long eyepins.  I currently use an adjustable organizer for my eyepins/headpins and guess what they do.....yup....they slide underneath the divider into the compartment next door.  so Darice, if you are listening....same concept, more sizes please!

Busdriver is an incredibly agile MC who I believe can somehow fit 1000 syllables in a mere 16 bar verse. I came across this album not too long ago thanks to a couple suggestions from music websites. Even though this album was made over a decade ago, it turns out that I actually heard one of his songs "Imaginary Places" in a video game long ago. I find it almost criminal to not have found this album until now, but I guess its better late then never. The album is incredible from the complex flow delivered from Busdriver himself, to his relatable lyrics to the hybrid production with a mix of early 90's boom bap with Jazz and funk samples. The album is a treat for underground Hip Hop fans alike and an underrated Hip Hop albums overall.

P.S.  If you are a fan of artists like Aesop Rock than this guy will be right up your alley.

The Jouer Essential Lip Enhancer makes two claims:

1.  it is an ultra rich lip moisturizer protects lips from environmentally damaging elements while hydrating and volumizing to provide lasting results; and
2.  it naturally increases the fullness of your lips while decreasing fine lines.

In my use of this Jouer product, I found that the lip enhancer, with a consistency thicker than a standard lip gloss, does a great job moisturizing my lips and works as a nice base layer for a tinted lip product.  However, as a lip enhancer and/or volumizer, the Jouer product is a bust.  I did not see any difference in my lips other than they kept moisturized for a slightly longer period of time than a standard lip gloss.

Lip Moisturizer, yes
Lip Volumizer/Enhancer, no
summary: Good Moisturizer, But Not a Lip Enhancer/Volumizer

Works great. I used it and an extension kit with extra rods to to clean a 21 foot long vent with a two right angle turns and it did a fantastic job with the adapter that let us you put the rod through and attach a shop vac. Got a TON of lint out, about a 5 gallon bucket full. Inside of the vent was left shiny and clean. Good for safety especially with such a long vent and to my surprise the dryer actually works quite a bit better now. On the auto cycle I used to have to run it again if I was drying heavy things like jeans or blankets/comforters etc... to fully dry things. Now it does it in one cycle and take about 25 less time to go through the auto dry cycle.

I was just wanting to clean out a potential fire hazard but it really does make a big difference running through a dirty vent vs. a clean one. Might be due to the long length of my vent but very happy with this product.

Cyberlink's Power DVD is a pretty well known name in video playback programs, and for good reason.  It does what it is supposed to well and has a wide range of features.  There are good number of screens to move through in Power DVD 11, but the interface is fairly intuitive and not all that difficult to navigate.

My only major gripe with the arrangement is how the full screen option is set up.  Selecting the full screen option does not actually change the interface to full screen  instead it keeps navigation bars at the top and bottom of the screen.  It took me awhile fiddling around with the software to figure out you have to switch from "Classic" mode to "Cinema" mode to get real full screen, which is annoyingly unnecessary.

Power DVD 11 has a dizzying array of options and will play pretty much any video file format, but it seems like only a very small percentage of serious videophiles will actually need or use all the extras.  Cutting right to the chase, you probably do not need this program unless you really want to watch Bluray in 3D while being able to play videos from your iPhone and upload clips to Youtube or Facebook.  For those who just want to watch movies or view photos, there are already dozens of cheap or free options readily available that are more than up to the job.
summary: Mixed bag - lots of features, but will you actually use them?

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

We built a dedicated theater in our basement and had some problems with the bass.  First my big receiver was not putting out any signal for the subwoofer channels.  Annoying, but then fixed itself, I assume with a firmware update.  Right after that, one of my subs died, inexplicably.  Fuse was still good but it is dead.  So I considered a few options, with an infinite baffle sub being one.  I could relatively easily set one up under the risers for the theater seating, but I was concerned about the rattles, etc, associated with that.  And the theater is beneath our two girls' bedrooms, so I did not want to keep them up. Ultimately I decided that I would buy two of these F12s and replace the two smaller subs I already had in the room.  The price was right so I bought two and got them quickly.  Set up is very easy and adjustments were similarly so.

Holy cow, the house was rocking.  I am a very happy camper today and I expect to watch many more action movies in my theater now.  But only during the waking hours...
