I have been reading Entertainment Weekly for about twenty years now, and although it is gone through a lot of changes, it is basically still my favorite magazine to receive and to read. It is a sort of a good mix of pop culture plus a teeny, tiny bit of gossip, but the "interesting" kind, meaning you will not find out about Snooki's latest drama, but you will get the scoop on how a much anticipated Hollywood franchise might be headed for trouble.

The best thing about EW is their coverage of upcoming movies, books, television, music, and stage, plus interesting articles on the business of entertainment everything from in depth coverage of TV shows to an inside look at a much anticipated film to long interviews with directors, etc.

The only thing I do not like about the magazine is that it is starting to get very web and tablet focused meaning, the content of the magazine is slowly getting leaner and leaner, and on every other page there is a reminder to check the EW website or iPad edition for the rest of the features. I am not happy about this I really like it when they had about six or eight pages of movie reviews. I am not happy that now it is four pages of movie reviews, and two of those pages are tiny "one sentence" reviews and charts. It is the same for books and television and other media, as well.

Regardless, I still eagerly dive into every issue that pops into my mailbox, and out of all the magazines I start and drop subscriptions to, this is the only one I really consider "necessary". I love that I know about every movie, television show, and CD before they even get released.
summary: slimmer than it used to be, but still an invaluable source of entertainment info

text:
This really is not a photo editor, it more of an enhancer.  It will make pictures look their natural best without much of a learning curve to the software.  If you are a student or just dove into a new camera, and starting to lose track of your collection, it is also a great organization tool.

Though it is light on features, it is great for a quick fix, and even if you screw something up, it is okay, as it keeps a copy of the original file you pulled. If you like the enhancement, and want to keep making new versions, your original will still be there.

The software is quite intelligent with intuitive capability that will pull the data from your images, even older ones, and use the correct tools for that camera.  The organizational aspects of this is spot on.  With the information of each shot immediately available, files are much easier to sort as it begins to do that for you.

I keep two external drives for my photos.  One drive as the "master" source, and the other is a backup of my backup.  The software works just fine with the drives.

People will compare this to Lightroom and Photoshop etc., but those programs require a bit more skill and patience.  And they have many more features.  But for the money, it is a pretty good buy for a simple easy to use tool to clean up your collection without worries.
summary: Keep track of your growing collection without risk of losing shots

Antivirus and spyware programs offer some of the choicest morsels in the freeware phenomenon.

 This program is typical of its commercial genre: big, slow and a resource hog. Antivirus and spyware programs should be left to run t night or whenever else you are not using the computer.

 I do not have any kind of formal procedure for testing spyware programs. I run a commercial antivirus and spyware package and occasionally run freeware programs to see how each performs against the others. PCTools Spyware Doctor is not perfect when measured against competitors. It did not miss anything on my pretty clean system, nor did it find anything the others did not. Identifying actual malware from entities such as legitimate Registry entries and Cookies is as tedious as it is with other programs and not as bad as some others. The great danger of these programs is that for many users, they are dangerous weapons  it is very simple to delete a critical Registry entry.

 Overall, I think experienced users would probably be just as happy  if not happier  with one of the well known freeware products. Inexperienced users might be better served with a better featured program that includes antivirus capabilities.

Jerry
summary: Typical of its kind - and free programs do much the same thing

I am Caucasian and pretty white, but for some reason, a lot of red nail polishes have just made my hands look kind of dirty and unappealing. Another problem I have often had with them is that they end up looking brownish instead of properly red. Come to Bed Red is different. To me, its the perfect red, a true red that is not pink, is not Brown, and is not neon. I get a lot of compliments on my long, natural nails and part of how I keep them from getting damaged is to apply many layers of this, which creates a thick finish that is surprisingly durable, often lasting several days with little to no tip wear and zero chipping. One complaint I have is that I have found BL polishes take a very long time to dry, but the fact that the polish is thick and that I apply many layers overall probably worsens that. Also, it is frustrating that it seems to get thicker as you use the bottle up. Even so, I love it and repurchase again and again in this colour.

And i must admit... there are some occassions where i will get frustrated with the camera but i still do not find enough reason to give it anything below a 4 star if anything.

If there is one reason to buy a Wii... Mario Galaxy should be it.

The reasons i gave it a 4 star... maybe even a 4.5:

1 Difficulty settings are set way to easy. I understand that this meant for the younger generation but i wish they had a difficulty option. I also know that difficulty options never existed in mario games but... i am totally flying through this game and the fun i am experiencing right now is soon to end!!!!! nooSurprisedSurprisedSurprisedSurprisedSurprisedoo!

2 Camera Angles. Difficult to deal with at some points, and the camera locks at the oddest times.

3 I wish we had more opportunities to enjoy the Bee and Boo outfits..etc.

4 I wish luigi had a bigger role. I know this is a Mario game... but still.

5 And of course... the Wii is all about fun... i understand that... but.. PLEASE PLEASE!!!... Nintendo!!... upgrade the graphics!! You can still do the whole GREAT INNOVATION route... but you can do that with great graphics as well.

The last Mario i really... really... really enjoyed was Mario 64. And this game just brought all those great memories back and has to be one of the greatest games out right now... hands down.

[...]

In a crowded Delhi marketplace in 1996, a "small" bomb is detonated, killing several people. Among the dead are 2 young brothers. Their friend, a Muslim, survives the blast. What follows in this short but brilliant book is the aftermath of the explosion on the lives of those involved. The Khuranas are dealing with the death of their boys, which serves to reveal cracks in their seemingly strong relationship. Surviving boy Mansoor grapples with the physical and psychological injuries it has inflicted on him. His parents struggle to help him and their friends whose sons were killed, as Mansoor begins to associate with groups fighting for the rights of his fellow Muslims in the country. We also learn the fates and motivations of the 2 men who detonated the bomb, and follow one of Mansoor's new friends as he descends from someone fighting for social justice into radicalization. Grief permeates the novel, with some form of it affecting the decisions of everyone involved. Understandably this means this is a very sad story. But it is a necessary one. There are many books that tackle mourning or the loss of a child, so that aspect, while excellently handled, is not really anything new. Very rarely does anyone succeed in really getting inside the heads of terrorists though, instead opting to portray them as cartoonishly evil. Not so here. While not in away condoning or glorifying their actions, it does make the reader understand them, and shows how frighteningly easy it is to turn people into one. This is a gripping tale that is deserving of the many accolades it has received and is easily one of the year's best books.

I had my doubts when I purchased this stuff, and confess to only buying it to be able to follow a recipe verbatim.  But I am very impressed.  I made a carrot wine, and decided to use a juicer instead of slicing and soaking in sugar to extract the juices.  Using a juicer also extracts the pectin.  I was going to deal with a cloudy wine since it will taste the same anyway.  I added a teaspoon of this Pectic Enzyme to every gallon of my mash, and to my surprise, it worked!  I had a very thick and cloudy wine after the first racking, but now that the wine has had its second racking and has been fermenting for nearly three months, it is a beautiful clear orange color, with no cloudy qualities to note!  Now that I am a believer, I use it in all of my white or lighter colored wines, and no matter the extraction method I use, I am getting a nice, clear wine a few months later.

The worst thing is that when the tile was being placed inside the metal holder, so much thick presumably glue has been used that when the tile was pressed into the frame a lot of the glue was pressed out along the edges of the tile and up onto the printed tile itself as well as onto the black frame.  Instead of cleaning the excess gunk off of both the frame and the tile, it was just left there to dry.  Very poor quality standard to say the least.  This item is WAY OVERPRICED given the sloppy assembly, poor painting and the cheap, rough unfinished quality of metal used.  Cannot recommend this product.  Caveat Emptor!

This is a strange one. An Alfred Hitchcock movie that is absolutely anonymous. In fact, Hitchcock made a couple of forays outside the thriller genre and both were very poor. "Under Capricorn" is a kitchen sink, tearjerker and "Mr and Mrs Smith" is, ostensibly, a screwball comedy. The problem is Hitchcock does not understand the screwball format and the pace is slow and the jokes unfunny. Montgomery is badly miscast as the obnoxious husband, and his asides and grimaces make it seem like he has a bad case of constipation. Lombard is, as always, good, but she cannot do much with this material. Did I mention that the screenplay is also extremely poor? The thing just does not hold together. On the one hand, Montgomery is so stupid he does not mention the fact of the illegal marriage to Lombard until it is too late we never learn the reason for his reticence. On the other hand, Lombard who has been desperately waiting for Montgomery to tell her about the unofficial marriage though she already knowsthen becomes completely unforgiving of someone we have previously been led to believe she loves deeply.

A farrago of nonsense. Just do not go there!

I love this coffee because it makes such a satisfying drink. I also bought 48 K cups for my sisterinlaw and she said its the first coffee she is had from her machine that really tastes good. She is tried a number of wellknown brands over the years she is been using the machine every morning. She does not like dark roasts; I do. Yet we both enjoy it because it is so very tasty, like coffee is supposed to be: satisfying and flavorful without any bitterness. It provides a very good wakemeup without any harshness.

Sometimes I brew it with less water and microwave milk for a cappuccino, and it is strong enough and flavorful enough to make a very delicious, satisfying cappuccino with two thirds milk.

I recommend this coffee with no reservations, which is rare for me for any product.
summary: Delicious, full bodied coffee at a reasonable price

Update: I have now been using this printer since Christmas.  I have used many different types of PLA and once I find an ideal temperature for the different brands of PLA I get amazing prints.  I have been printing nonstop since Christmas and would like to buy another one, to keep up with business, but Amazon tells me that it will be 35 months for delivery.  I had been using a Davinci printer which I must say I am glad to be rid of...  The proprietary PLA that xyz printing forces you to use for a very expensive price is just crap. text:
I owned Q2008, Q2005  Q2002 and I used them daily. during that decade, I observed no significant product improvements, just a huge increase in software bugs.

Look up the Q2010 and/or Q2008 products, where I posted detailed logs/diaries of the endless bugs, errors and frustrations I endured as a Quicken user.

In August, 2010, I finally migrated to the Moneydance product andafter the migration and learning curve issuesI find it swims slick as an eel. I wish I would done it years sooner.

Since at least 2002, Intuit has been using Quicken as a pure 'cash cow'  a product to milk revenue out of, but making no investment in it  while it continues to toy around with other new product developments toward future revenue streams.

The history of the Quicken product does not suggest a bright future for Quicken users. Do not get suckered into starting up with Quicken. Go with Moneydance.
summary: A lousy, buggy product since 2002. Go with Moneydance.

text: Bob Ezrin played Phil Spector on this one...a departure from what preceded it, Destroyer pissed off some of the KISS Army, yet steadily brought in a wider fanbase. From the tragic narration of a drunk driver in Detroit Rock City,the songs just open up with denser melodic textures. The slowpaced yet heavy God Of Thunder...deep cuts like Flaming Youth and Sweet Pain and of course...Beth, the first KISS ballad. Ironically the Peter Criss crooned tune was what saved this album from burying KISS after succeeding with Alive, unlike Peter Frampton when he sought to follow up on his famous live album. There are early signs of bad things to come though, such as not every member of the original band played throughout the entire record, or Ezrin buddy/session guitarist Dick Wagner doing the solo on Sweet Pain, but the finished product is not the worse for it. Not my absolute favorite, but an utmost essential KISS album if you want to earn the right to call yourself a KISS fan.

They do not make a Mac version so I had to buy the PC version. That was painful because my $3,000 Mac was unsuitable to prepare business taxes. So, I exportedQB data into a Window version, loaded the file on my old PC and continued working. Every year for the last seven years or so I have used Quick Books and Turbotax to prepare and file my business taxes. Every year the QB balance sheet never matched imported balance sheet data in TurboTax. Although the Federal Government does not need the Balance Sheet, the New York requires it. So, I ignored that the Balance Sheet data were not matching and filed the taxes. If New York State wants a Balance Sheet, I will mail the one printed from my QB.

It is rather sad that even though QB, Quicken, TurboTax software all developed by Intuit, they have this issue that still is not addressed. I have brought it to their attention every year.
summary: QB imported balance sheet data do not match QB data - this is an age old problem

I have owned previous Livescribes, and used them for awhile. The were fun at first, but later proved less useful. They usually worked by synching them a computer and downloading the notes you took along with the text you wrote. You could tape on a word in your notes, and have the Livescribe replay them at that  synchronized moment.

The problem was that, in the end, typing was faster for me than handwriting. It was easier to take notes on the computer, than write them by hand and then transfer them over.

This new Livescribe seeks to transfer your writing in real time to your tablet or phone. However, it did not always work. Moreover, if I wanted to transfer my scribing over to an electronic device, it would probably be a laptop, not a tablet. You may feel differently.

After the text appears on your tablet, you can swipe over it to do a few thing  transcribe it into computer text, dial a telephone number, etc. However, I could not find any way to convert all of the text at one time  it seemed possible only one line at a time. This was somewhat tedious.

In some ways, I give LIvescribe credit for trying to develop new technologies and leverage existing ones. But I am still not sure they solve a problem I have. When I want to write, I write, when I want to type, I type. I just do not find myself needing an ability to do both concurrently, with mixed results at that.

summary: Designed for professionals with high end systems, but fun to use

text: It demonstrates the horrors of battle and the incredible courage that common soldiers have to summon in battle.  It also demonstrates the ego and stubbornness that high command sometimes displays by insisting that its grunt soldiers succeed in executing a flawed battle plan rather than reexamine their own thinking.  The story line is mostly about a young man determined to stay alive, and makes good battlefield decisions to protect his own life.  This gets the attention of his command, and he is put in a squad leader, and then a platoon leader position which is the last thing he wants.  The movie gives a very ambivalent portrayal of this young man.  Is he a villain who would sacrifice his comrades to save himself, or is he a hero with an innate sense of battlefield tactics that ultimately saved many lives in this battle.  Watch the movie and decide for yourself.
summary: and makes good battlefield decisions to protect his own life

I have tried numerous antivirus and Internet Security products and have come back to Kaspersky again and again.  I tried Kaspersky Pure as well but it was difficult to remove when I decided to use Internet Security the next year.  I understand that the difference between Kaspersky AntiVirus and Internet Security is that the latter has a second firewall.  I do not notice performance issues using the Internet Security, so I will stick with it.  Be prepared for numerous banner alerts weeks before your version will expire, which is annoying, but I suppose other antivirus and Internet Security makers do this as well.

My daughter accidentally downloaded some malware one day clicking on "your computer is infected" links from a compromised website and Kaspersky emailed me instructions on its removal.  As long as your software is up to date, Kaspersky has a help line and great insight for ascertaining what has infected your computer as well as detailed and easy to follow instructions to eradicate it.  Highly recommended!
summary: For cybersecurity, the Russians make a product that can't be beat.

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

with all that said, if your vent duct does not have to many bends, and you want to take the risk maybe i had a defective kit that the brush broke, you might save a lot of money doing it yourself!

Wow  this eye serum is fantastic.  From the very first application, it works well to tighten the skin around my eyes and give it a silky texture.  Even better, my extremely sensitive skin tolerates it well enough for me to use it every day.

The applicator takes a few tries to get used to, mostly because it needs to be primed.  You also must pull on the trigger and then sweep the wand over your skin.  At first, I tried to expel the eye treatment by pressing it against my skin.  Ouch.  The serum glides on effortlessly.  You can feel the tingle within seconds.

I like that Juice Beauty uses organic and natural ingredients to improve the look of the delicate skin around the eye.  It is soothing, brightening, and tightening, all without irritation.

 Debbie Lee Wesselmann

text:
At first this contraption was a little confusing. I read the directions about 3 times before I felt okay about going through with the project  was not fully confident as there were a lot of warnings about making sure the drill was going the right way/you turned it the right way so you would not lose rods in the dryer vent. Scared me a little. However, the project turned out really well. We did not lose any rods thankfully and we got out the birds nest that had taken residence in our dryer vent!!
The part that was for the lint catcher was convenient as well and is actually recommended to be used at least once a month in order to clean out the lint catcher. I do need to keep up with this but it is not convenient to have to put together and tape the rods each time when you only really use it for a couple of minutes. However, if you have a handy space to keep it already together, I can see how this would be even better for keeping up with cleaning the lint out.
This is a great toy but wish it had a switch to turn off the music. It is very sensitive and will go off even if someone just walks heavy across the floor.
summary: Great toy but needs an off switch!

I can remember years ago when I first got into Pearl Jam when 10 was their only album. That album was filled with energy and inspiration that I have rarely heard on an album. Songs like Once convey a sense of raw power while songs like Alive and Jeremy have a strong emotional attachments to them. Vs continued this tradition with songs like animal and go having that raw power and W.M.A and elderly women have that emotional attachments. However with vitology, the band began try things which is good but sadley the execution of that expirementation did not sound as good as their previous works. No Code sadley follows that tradition. It is difficult to listen to because of its unfinished sound. Songs like Hail Hail seem like they would have been good if Pearl Jam had worked more on the song. In the end, No Code fails to make a connectin that is strong with listeners.
summary: the downfall of what once a great band

I purchased one of these not long after they first hit the market. I should have known by past experiences with Black  Decker drills not to buy one but the fancy 'Smart Select' feature had me sold. As soon as I got it I noticed that it was not very powerful nor very 'smart'. I never could get the right setting, even though there are pretty little pictures all around the chuck illustrating each setting. Even for simple around the house jobs this drill was too weak. If I had to drive a screw through anything thicker than a piece of plywood it would struggle. Finally while drilling a hole through a twobyfour it crapped out on me. Needless to say I will not be replacing it with another BD.
Bough this watch for my son. It is a gorgeous and classy looking watch. He loved it.
Very poor quality compared to Champion's 'favorite' Capris of the past several years.  Very disappointed.

I already own one pair and have now ordered a second pair of Cali Women's ToneUps Meow Wedge sandals.
It is true that there is a wee bit of a breakin period for the material that is in between the toes.
I am a patient person and it is well worth the very temporary discomfort.
Whether or not they actually help you to "toneup"; I do not know.
They are soooo comfortable that I do not really care whether or not they assist in toning.
I love the cushion that that these sandals provide. In the past, I have rarely worn flipflop style sandals due to plantar fasciitis. These sandals are not only cute.....they prevent my feet from taking a pounding.
I even wear them at home while walking on the treadmill.
If the price is a barrier; watch for clearance styles. The first pair that I purchased was from JcPenney for $9.95 and the second pair that I have just ordered through Amazon came to only $22.00, including the shipping costs.
They are worth it.

Fit and finish are good, the only complaint I have is that it is difficult to fit the stainless shelves into the frames without scratching the powder finish  no big deal.  I am completely satisfied.

Pros:

Cons:
Knob placement is strange.  If you use the sideburner, you will have almost no room on the shelves  why not place the dials up front?  I guess they want you to move up to the Summit Series?
 Accessory hooks are kind of recessed and large so they will not fit all utensils.  Maybe the Weber ones fit?

Given the Dio/Blackmore combination and the sound of the other Rainbow records of this era, you would expect this to be a really heavy hard rock album, but its not.  I think Blackmore was still suffering a funk hangover  from the last two Purple records which infects some of this, keeping it  from rocking as hard as it ought to and making this the weakest of the  albums with Ronnie James Dio.  Actually, if you listen to  "Stormbringer" and "Rainbow Rising", its easy to see  this as a transitional record between the two.
That said, Blackmore is in  great form here and the songs are generally pretty good.  The only complete  stinker is "If You Do not Like Rock 'n' Roll".  This is a good  record, just lacking the expected heaviness and aggression.  "Man On  The Silver Mountain" and "Sixteenth Century Greensleeves"  are great songs, but these original versions barely hint at the power they  would have live.
I read somewhere that Blackmore originally wanted Purple  to cover "Black Sheep Of The Family", but the rest of the band  refused.  Apparently, they were more interested in playing garbage like  "High Ball Shooter" and "Holy Man".  Not that  "Black Sheep" is all that great, but it is better than most  everything on "Stormbringer".

Purchased this for a 12 gallon shrimp tank the 100. I was using sponge filters and the bio load was getting out of hand. I have used the "waterfall" filters in the past but this is my first experience with this type with the wheel. It moves a lot of water which is what I needed. It did not however come with a filter. I filled the back with the sponges I am going to remove from the tank to so the biological stuff moves to the wheel quicker and has no ill effects on the shrimp. I did not use the extension tube, only the bottom piece and put a sponge over the intake shrimplets would definitely be sucked into it. I would not use this on anything less than a 10 gallon unless you have strong swimmers.
summary: Moves a lot of water but the 100 did not come with a filter. Ok overall.

Some things are just better off being left in 2D.  Anyone familiar with the Castlevania series at all knows this to be fact, as Konami's attempts to bring the long running series to the realm of 3D have just fallen flat.  Now we get a Castlevania fighting game do not ask why with Castlevania Judgment for the Wii, which even though it says it is a Castlevania game, is really a generic fighting game with little personality to it to seperate it from the rest of the pack.  There is a decent roster of fighters that Castlevania fans will recognize, such as Simon Belmont, Alucard, and even Dracula; but there is not much variation or real differences between most of the fighters.  The fighting system appears to offer some depth, but it really is not anything you have not seen countless times before.  The game does not look too bad though, and there is some great music as well, but there just is not enough here that helps the game stand out on its own.  All in all, Wii owners who are Castlevania fans and/or fighting game fans may want to give Castlevania Judgment a look, but other than that, your time is better off served elsewhere.
summary: Generic fighter that leaves much to be desired

text: Cannot rate this.  I bought it as a gift

Man, is this stuff good. For health reasons, my wife is on the FODMAP diet avoiding foods with a tendency to ferment, and wheat is a big nono. We have already switched to oatbased pancakes deliciousWink or smirk, but pasta was a big issue.

We found this stuff at Amazon and took a chance on it a big chance because it is six boxes!, and man, is it great. It cooks, serves, eats, and tastes virtually identical to standard wheatbased pasta, and in fact it appears to have less tendency to stick together or get soft and squishy in sauces or when reheated.

In fact, at this point, even if FODMAP was not an issue we would probably use this stuff as our primary macaroni. Highly recommended.

Also, for anybody out there who is avoiding gluten because of digestive issues but find it does not work 100 of the time, investigate FODMAP as an option. My wife's digestion has improved 100, and even her dad has switched to it. It is not woohoo, it is science, and worth a look.
summary: Fantastic pasta, a virtually indistinguishable replacement for standard wheat-based offerings

I absolutely loved this book. I think I am finally going to start reading fiction regularly again now that I have tried a couple of Japanese authors. Japanese writers seem to demand more of their readers than American authors do. If you are looking for a typical storyline, this book is definitely not the one you want to choose. There are three entirely separate stories with different protagonists and physical contexts. One is even set fifty years before the other two.  Murakami alternates between these three stories, picking up where he left off with each one at the beginning of the chapters. Eventually it becomes only two stories, but all the plots do not converge until near the end of the book.

Also, I am beginning to see that some Japanese authors seem to share the predilection of many Japanese animated filmmakers when they use the superstitious beliefs embedded in historical folk tales as plot devices to move the story forward in unusual and sometimes seemingly ambiguous ways. There are parts in the latter half of this book where it is never clearly explained where physical reality ends and the realm of daydreams begins. The reader simply has to sketch out both possibilities in his mind and enjoy sucking the marrow out of the themes that would be implied by both options.
summary: A sublime, if a bit surreal, novel

I got the 20gb and ran a 25" $15 Ethernet wire. It worked out perfect. I do not miss anything the 60gb had to offer. Wireless is not the best. Lost a signal is very upsetting. I do not save any music or video on my PS3 HDD since i can use an external hard drive and share it with the Xbox. Also the PS3 HDD is easily upgradeable. The graphics are better than the Xbox 360 because it shows a little more details. Not a major difference. Games display in only 720p just like the 360. If you have a 360 and love it, I would recommend sticking with it till the PS3 goes down in price. You are not missing much.

text:
A possible reason why reviews of this book are so divergent is that BRUNELLESCHI'S DOME is so much more than an architectural triumph that for some it seems unlikely that such a slim book by a journalist could do it full justice. Ross King however fully recognizes the significance of the dome of the Santa Maria del Fiore cathedral and the mastery of it is creator Filippo Brunelleschi. He pays tribute to how both the man and his creation were symbolic of the great creative genius that we have come to see as typifying the golden age of the Renaissance. King also clearly shows how such individuals and their work were a boon to the continuing growth and influence of the Renaissance as a whole. Not only is the dome a wonderful architectural triumph  at 143 feet in diameter it is still the largest dome in existence  the very act of creating it spurred other developments. Construction techniques, machines and tools, methods of organizing work, architectural design and drafting; all had to be modified, improved, and in some cases newly invented to accomplish the goal.
Any reading you do on the Renaissance will be sure to mention southern Italy and the pioneering role Florence had in the movement. With Florence you are dealing with the finest sculpture, painting, and architecture, and with Brunelleschi's dome you have got distilled into one creation all that the Renaissance stood for.
summary: "il Duomo" as icon of an age

This is a 20 Gallon pail. It fits under my counter in the kitchen which is your standard table height.
I use 30 gallon garbage bags which are perfect for this size pail.
NO Venting channels to allow air to flow into the garbage can making liners easier to lift out of the trash can. As a result, when you pull the full garbage bag out of this pail, it creates a vacuum and the bags are difficult to pull out of the pail. Dumb design. Rubbermaid has venting channels.
NO Integrated cinches that allow bags to be attached to handles so that the bag does not fall into the pail.
My Rubbermaid pail has these two features.
Not enough thought was given in the design of this pail.
I am no engineer but there are only TWO things to know about when making a plastic pail. VENTING CHANNELS and a place to ATTACH the bag to the handles so the bag does not fall into the pail.
Could have been a great pail.
DOES NOT COME WITH LID. Do not forget that when ordering if you do decide to go with this pail.
Next time, I will check for venting channels and a place to attach the bags to the handle like my Rubbermaid.

Everything has been said. All I can add is that Days of the New just got better as they went along. Why they are not world renown comercially successful superstars I just do not know. I say "comercially" because in my book they are superstars with or without the enormous fortune and fame. I could name dozens of bands in the same position. That does not make them any less great. Especially II and then even more so is III. They are just adventures in music that you will only hear from DOTN. I can pop these discs in and I never want them to stop. Their music is complex. You will hear more every time you listen to them. It is mature, not particularly for the kids. Perhaps there in lies the rub. Great mature music that does not appeal to the preteen with all mommy and daddy's money. Certainly that would be simplifiying. But, to a degree I believe this is what happens when you do not sell out. When you create with integrity first, getting rich second. At least they have earned respect and this band will be talked about now and then for as long as rock music is being played and when the nu metal sorry ass crowd becomes a pathetic joke like disco did. Man, how I hated the radio in the 70s. I wish Mr. Meeks would find a way to continue laying down some of the highest quality rock music a person can listen to.

Every attempt to install it on an Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry machine resulted in my failure.  I quickly say that I do not blame the software.  I blame myself for the failure for not getting it on the Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry.  Any number of unknown issues may have caused the failure.  As far as the laptop's use with Bitdefender my only complaint is that it does slow the machine's operation some but not enough for it to be an issue.  The program must work with few problems.  I have not been hacked, phished etc and therefore it does what it says at least on one machine.

Bottom line:  it works but I cannot recommend it highly.

So, this is what life comes down to when you are 50 years olTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry  reviewing dryer vent cleaners while sitting at your kitchen table waiting for American Idol. That said, the product works great.  Our dryer pretty much stopped working and we were thinking we needed a new one, which was seriously going to eat into my plastic surgery budget.  One last shot before a trip to the appliance store was this Gardus LintEater.  My husband, who is not the handy one of the family, had to do the work as I have a torn labrum.  Which sounds dirtier than it is  that is part of your shoulder.  He, the clumsiest man in the world, had absolutely no problem using this.  I warned him to read the directions first, and he actually listened and followed.  He hooked it up to the drill, and away he went.  He got a bunch of musty, wet lint that had probably been up inside the wall since 1977   probably consisting of bell bottom material and macram.

Now our dryer actually dries clothes again, and I can continue to save for my facelift. Thank you Gardus.

I have given this five stars not as a review of Windows 8 itself, but of the upgrade product and its installation process.

Basically if you know you want to upgrade to Windows 8, then you can rest assured that this is a good way to do it assuming you are on Windows 7 to begin with.

If you hate Windows 8's guts, then you will not be interested in this to begin with. Personally I have been hoping that 8.1 would resolve the issues, but so far that is sounding like only a partial solution. I can survive in Windows 8, but on a desktop system it is a struggle to get used to the "tablet style" user interface that it forces on you each time you want to start a program. Fortunately there are 3rd party addons that will restore the Start button and bypass the Metro UI at startup.

Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

I installed these strings on a guitar I built by hand, and am very pleased with them.  They are a bit heavier gauge than I normally use, but seem to work great on this instrument, I do not have the fret buzz I experienced with other brands.  The packaging is quite nice, each string has a different colored ball, so you can install them in any order you please.  They are all packaged in a single plastic bag, but separate easily.  They were easy to tune, got them close to pitch, gave each a good pull then final tuned them.  I gave them each another tug when in tune with no noticeable difference.  I checked again the day after installation, and they maintained pitch as well as other strings.  I do not see much sound difference in these strings versus the others I have used.  These are a good product at a good price, so no complaints here.

I did not shoot with my SAMSUNG WB2200F until AFTER I got my lens cover on, the UV protection filter. I have a second, because the lens is irreplaceable and the filter is notI can mess it up and replace in "mere seconds."  Coating on lenses these days are a very important part of your optical quality. Finger prints and such have acids that will eat that coating. The UV filter is so cheap, the lens so good, why not be safe.
summary: First thing to do to save that lens

I was looking for a relatively inexpensive soap for ever day shaves. I like to save my artisan stock for special occasions and I am not made of money ya know. As a mass produced soap it is actually really nice. It loads well, though I will say it loads better on stiffer brushes than softer ones. The scent is nice and has some staying power. The slickness is about average I would say and it provides decent cushion. Is this the best soap in the world? Nope. Is this soap a decent proformer at a great price point? Absolutely. One of the advantages of this soap over the cream in a tube is that it has a better post shave. Not sure why but it is definitely more moisturizing and has a better finish than the tube creams from Proraso. This is their sensitive skin formula and I have some sensitive skin. Let me just say a preshave is a must. I use an oil but you could use theirs as well. A good preshave and prep will make this soap preform better. without a preshave treatment this soap is still to drying for me but it does have some good antiinflammatory properties.
summary: A relatively inexpensive soap for ever day shaves

text: For the first quarter of this book, I did not really care for it much and wondered how this novel could have been so acclaimed. The style was so spare and stark, and the story not all that interesting as it got started. But I am not one to quit reading a book, and I am glad I stuck with it. I found that Coplin's writing style became more interesting and richer as the story unfolded, and as life became more interesting for the orchardist. There is much to admire in this book: the complexity of the characters as you get to know them and as their lives become more complicated; the interactions of the characters or their very failures to interact and the lost opportunities that result; the depiction of life at that time in our American history. My early frustration with a sparse writing style and slowdeveloping story turned into admiration for Coplin's story line and literary ability. I recommend this book.
summary: Highly recommended in spite of a slow start

For the past 5 years, keeping track of him and planning on bringing him down has been her sole focus, but now things are more complicated.  Aiden has been taking care of Essie from afar also.  After avoiding Aiden, he finally gives her no choice but to go on date with him.  Both Aiden and Essie are confused by their feelings but Aiden comes to term with his feelings long before Essie does.  Essie runs off to think; Aiden gives her this but eventually his patience wears out and he goes to find her and confess his feelings.

I will admit, that I have not read the first book in this series. It took me a while to establish what was going on.  After I finally figured out the foundation of what started in Hearts Revenge, the book was okay.  The writing was solid but I thought it was lackingit went on for quite a while; Are they going to be together or not?  After a while of this backandforth, I just wanted them to decide and move on.
summary: Reviewed for A Wanton Book Lover Blog Hearts of Fire ...

This is the last Beatles album before they really got serious with their  music. And the four big songs Help, You have Got To Hide Your Love Away,  Ticket To Ride, and Yesterday show it. These four songs are of the highest  caliber, and their inclusion on the album automatically makes this an  essential part of any Beatles collection.
And do not worry, there is some  great stuff here to help complement the four big ones. The Night Before,  You are Going To Lose That Girl, I have Just Seen A Face, and Dizzy Miss  Lizzie are all great songs. A really entertaining listen.
This album  would easily be 5 stars if not for the amazingly uneven feel to it. The  Harrison songs are complete throw aways and Act Naturally has absolutely no  business being on a Beatles album.
Should people buy this? Most  definetely. Although, if you really want only the bare essentials, and you  already have the Red Album, then and only then should you even consider  not getting this to complete your Beatles collection.
Fit on my Ruger 9 e just fine.

Val is the official Washington State liaison between humans and the vampire community.  Her office keeps track of which humans are turned into vampires, and who does the turning.  It is a highly regulated process.  When she and her partner, Will, need to investigate illegal attacks on humans called "blooding", they are assigned to a vampire prince who swears a lot.  He is the "bad mouth" of the title.
Val and the Prince, Kade, go on a series of interviews with vampires who have witnessed the bloodings.  At first, Kade let us Val conduct the interviews without assisting her, but by the third interview, he is pressing the vampire she questions for more details, and using his royal authority for results to help Val.  The vampires would like their activities to stay under the radar and as unregulated as possible, and the rogue vampires undermine their interests.  So Kade wants answers, too.
I like the connection Val and Kade feel for each other, and it is fun to watch it develop.  I wish the book were longer.  Look forward to more books by this author.

This thing is pretty amazing. Bought it for the wife for Christmas to go in the kitchen/den. Connected instantly to her iPad Air 2 with no issues whatsoever. The battery lasts an unbelievably long time between charges. It came fully charged out of the box and after playing an hour or two here and there a few times a week we literally did not plug it in to recharge until sometime well into February.

My only complaint is that the sound is not quite as full as I was hoping for, but considering the actual size it is smaller than you think it is pretty amazing that it sounds as good as it does. If you are looking for floorshaking bass, look elsewhere and spend a lot more. If you just want reasonably roomfilling sound from a reliable, compact, portable unit, I highly recommend this.

This material leaves a hydrophobic coating on the glass. This means the water will not wet the surface so it beads and runs off the glass. RainX is a silicone but Aqualpel is a flouropolymer. I apply this product in the fall and spring on both my cars. It is great stuff and it works.
summary: Best glass treatment on the market

Battle Assault 2, obviously, is a sequel to the first Gundam Battle Assault game, but ultimately falls short of what it could have been. The story mode is very GGundam/Gundam Wingcentric; I do not even think a game like this needs a story mode at all. It gets in the way of the point: robots beating the crap out of other robots. If they would eliminated the story mode and added about 20 more mobile suits, the game would have been much better as a straightforward fighter. As it stands, to unlock all of the available mobile suits you have to beat the game numerous times on numerous different difficulty settings, with numerous mobile suits. This proves supremely tiresome and timeconsuming, and in the end is not worth it.

As for the moves/gameplay, the game is awesome with two players and will provide hours of entertainment, and the special moves, music, and sound effects are welldone. For 1player mode, though? Yawn. My advice is to only purchase this game if you have someone to play it with, or if you are very bored and have a ton of free time to unlock everything.

This album is a good example of why I collect albums rather than "Best Of" compilations. I have owned Echoes for some time now, but heard a song on a web radio station from this album, which prompted me to get Moonmadness. Right in the middle of this album are three songs not on either of their official 2CD anthologies; Chord Change, Another Night, and Spirit Of The Water which is on the Lunar Sea anthology but not Echoes.

Chord Change is reminiscent of the Allman Bros and is one of this band's better instrumentals and that is saying a lot. The fact that it was played at nearly all their live shows for 20 years after should tell you something.

The live 'extras' on this reissue are pretty good as well, but typical if you already have one of their live albums. All in all, a great album. Too bad I missed the boat for say, 30 years. Highly recommended.

The features found in Office Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry are almost a clone to the previous Office suite's.  Yes, you can now hold 24 items in your clipboard and that is indeed something but is not that a nifty trick that could have been added as a download?  The task panes, etc. look nice but nobody in the work world is going to use them.  Also, you need a full screen when you are seriously working and some of Office Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry's innovations reduce the work area.
If you are happy with the Office suite you are currently using, keep it and ignore this upgrade.  There are no improvements big or small that justify the cost.  Yes, it has the best programs going but it is difficult to install and after you finally get it on your system you are left with  a clone of the Office Suite you were previously using.

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

This is the best purchase I have made for my dog on Amazon! I use it every day on multiple walks. My dog is 55 pounds, but very tall and lean. She is not a puller, but she walks fast and there is always some tension on the buckle. There are times when she sees something she wants to go after and REALLY pulls hard, still no wear on the strap at all. It has helped control her and keeps her from choking when attaching the leash to her normal collar. I sized the neck buckles to a close fit, not too tight, then with the back sized I just have 2 plastic buckles to do each time. When she is ready for her walk she just sits and points her head up and it slides right over. Pull the chest pad up under, then snap the 2 buckles and you are good to go in less than 10 seconds. There has not been any rubbing or irritation, and our dog has thin short fur too. Also, I have not used the included seat belt clip much, but it is very solid and has a heavy duty clip on it. I love this thing!
summary: Extremely durable and seems to be a comfortable fit to my dog

I purchased these despite of some poor reviews, as I use driveway markers yearround to prevent the.kids from driving the car over our lawn,  Now, I can easily remove and reset the driveway markers when I mow the lawn. To prevent these stakes from breaking DURING THE WINTER MONTHS, from the freezethaw cycle, I came up with this workarounTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry Partially fill the perimeter holes with foam caulk backer 3/8 Inch diameter. Then seal the top and bottom of each hole with silicone sealant. You MAY need to either enlarge the center hole, or wrap electrical tape around the bottom 1 inch of each driveway marker, depending on the diameter of the marker. The center hole is much deep than the perimeter holes. The perimeter holes are basically useless, as a " to " deep.hole will probably not support a 4' driveway marker very well. Yes, you could hammer the stake thru the perimeter hole and into the ground; but that defeats the purpose of purchasing the stakes.
summary: A great idea, but it needs to be re-engineered to make is more useful and durable.

So when I looked on Amazon, I found this Wellness brand and decided to give it a try.  The shipment arrived yesterday so I opened a can and of course, my dog came over to check it out. This is my second pair of these exact same slide sandals.  I have never been a Teva "sandals" type of guy with the straps that go up and around your ankle.  I have always preferred flops or slides.  I decided to try these slides and I have the matching flip flops about 2 years ago.  I wore these into the ground.  They were put into every situation, and I was rough on them.  I mowed the yard in them on my tractor, ran the weedeater, jumped in the pool with them on, raked leaves, tilled up the garden, remodeled a room in the house, etc.  If I was not at work, I had these on.  They are extremely comfortable, and the next best thing to being barefoot.

Well, a couple of weeks ago, one of my slides decided to give up the ghost as the fabric pulled away from the sole on one of them, and became too loose to keep on my foot.  It was a nobrainer for me to reorder some more Teva's.  It was a bonus that I was able to get the exact same ones!  I put these on, and I was back to having the same great slides on my feet.  The matching flops I have are still going strong.  I wear them a lot too.  Buy these.  You cannot go wrong if you like comfortable slides that allow to roam outdoors with no concerns.  Great allaround casual footwear.
summary: The best slides I have owned!

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

text:
This is one of the better TEOTWAWKI novels.  Earth is hit by an undefined event that wipes out the power grid and most electronic devices.  The protagonist is a young man on a school trip to Chicago, far from his actual home in northern Texas.  Law and order quickly deteriorates as starvation and chaos sets in, and he is on his journey to rejoin his family in Texas.

The plot sounds simple, and it is, but this particular "SHTF" story is more readable than most and more enjoyable than many.  I quite enjoyed this series, and this first installment in the series.  Do not read this one unless you plan to complete the four novel series, as each novel is more or less simply a portion of a single story.  RJB
summary: Above Average "End of the World as We Know It" novel.

text: I have owned two pet strollers previous to this purchase, and have learned the hard way that I should have held out for the better one right from the start. This is an excellent pet stroller. It does not feel rickety or cheesy like my other dog strollers. It turns on a dime and is super smooth on pavement, cobblestones and grass. It is also taller than I expected. I am 5'4" and the handle reaches my ribcage, which makes it easy to hold on to. It took me a minute to get the "one handed fold" but I figured it out. It is not compact. This stroller takes up a big chunk of my passat wagon, but I do not mind at all. I wanted a durable stroller that would last, not another cheap one to throw away after the summer. I have two long haired chihuahuas. There was plenty of room and 360 viewing so they love it. I am not a jogger, but after an exhaustive search of available pet strollers, I chose this one for the smooth ride, the durable construction, and because I saw a video review on youtube that convinced me that it was a good investment. The only thing I would change is the color. There is only red. I would have liked something more understated like a nice green or light mango color. Aside from that, I highly recommend the pet gear jogger stroller.
summary: Well constructed pet stroller with thoughtful features.

I originally posted a review where I gave this album 3 stars, but it has grown on me and I think it deserves 4 I only give a 5 to albums I consider classics. Stadium Arcadium does show how the band have matured so much over the years and now that I am 30 years old it is hard to believe the Chilli Peppers have been around since I was in junior high! Not many bands out there have that type of longevity, but the Peppers seem to get better with age. My favorites on this album are Charlie, Strip My Mind, Wet Sand, Tortue Me, Desecration Smile, She Looks to Me, and Animal Bar. Some have complained about filler and though some songs are better then others as with any album I do not think this CD has any throw away songs. My only complaint is that I wish there was a few more flat out rock songs instead of the midtempo songs that mostly dominate, but that is a mild complaint as from beggining to end this is a highly enjoyable album. Recent weeks have seen the release of album from Pearl Jam, Tool and now the Chilli Peppers so it is nice to see that rock is alive and well. Stadium Arcadium is one of those albums that will remain in my CD player for a long time to come.

I have been buying Butter London nail polishes for a few years and have always loved them, and have been happy to see that they have branched into creating makeup now, too.  This mascara creates a nice, dark, glossy color, and I really like the volume it gives.

The unusual brush shape takes some getting used to if, like me, you are used to a more conventional mascara wand.  After using this for a few days, though, I got the hang of it.  It is a bit tricky to use on your bottom lashes, but still coats those well.

While this is billed as a volumizing mascara, it also does add some length, without weighing down your lashes.  My current favorite mascara is Buxom Lash, and this is comparable in terms of giving a natural look to your eyes that is not too dramatic for daytime wear.

The formula also has not irritated my eyes, which water quite a bit because of allergies, and does not bleed when they have become teary.

Overall, I really like this!
summary: The unusual brush takes some getting used to, but then it stays in place all day, even with allergy-prone eyes

Give four stars because this is a great sturdy guitar stand that folds up nicely.  Not giving it five because it is better suited to hold an acoustic than an electric.  The short indentations for the thinner electric guitars is towards the front of the stand which means that an electric guitar leans "back" from vertical at a higher angle than an acoustic.  The angle of the acoustic is perfect, but the electric angle causes the headstock to go too far behind for my taste I play bass, so my necks are longer than a guitar neck.  Ideally, the indentations for the electric would be closer to the frame of the stand as opposed to being spaced farther away from the frame as is the case here, but i suspect that the one guitar design that is available with that configuration On Stage is patented because it is about twice the cost of this one.  Regardless, this stand is sturdy and universal, and it works well.  Cannot beat it for the price.
summary: Give four stars because this is a great sturdy guitar stand that folds up nicely

text:
Let me start by saying this game is amazing. It is increadibly expansive and new. Streetball has been around for a long time but this is the game that made it mainstream. Street 2 combines the craziest fake outs, dunks, and tricks with cool ghetto lingo You know that stuff that sounds good untill you say itand alot of classic appreciation. The controlls are slightly tricky if you have not played street1 but other than that the game is a complete head rush. Here Is the deal on the game modes. Of course you can choose an NBA team and play a game with all the fancy junk still in it. There is an NBA challenge where you take an NBA team and dismantle NBA divisions in a row to unlock courts. The best mode is definetly be a legend! You create a character and play games against the local play ground teams. For winning you can steal the other teams characters and get ability points so that you no longer stink. Eventually you face street legends like Dimes, Bonafide, Stretch, biggie little and you get a ghetto nickname.Ice water, Strings, CosmicYour team becomes good with the edition of the legends and you get to try out their signature moves. The goodies continue from there with NBA Legends like Bird, Wilt the still, Pistol Pete, Three versions of MJ, The lord of the Dunk DR. J Julius Erving it becomes insainly fun.
Give street a try and you will not be dissapointed. In fact you will probably be awstruck.
Rattings out of 10
Fun 10
Controlls 8

text:
I bought this to hang on the side of a bowl to make my cat a water fountain since I did not like the look of the bulky white plastic pet fountains. This is exactly the size I was hoping for! I purchased some small "pod" shaped charcoal pet fountain filters from Walmart that I can drop in the filtering side of it. That said, I really only bought this to create the waterfall effect and have some moving water, so I cannot speak to how it works as an aquarium filter.

There is a line of the side to show where the water line should be up to. Because it is on the edge of a more shallow bowl, it is not as submerged on the "water" side as it would be if I were using a fish tank. If I fill the filter up with water before I plug it in, it is fine even if power is temporarily removed then restored if there were a power outage while I am not home, for example.

UPDATE: Since this moves my cats drinking water, it needs to be cleaned every couple days. I stopped using it because one of the tubes is curved and does not come apart. A grayish sludge has built up and I cannot reach to clean it. I ended up getting a regular unattractive, oh well pet bowl that comes apart and can be cleaned properly.
summary: After a few weeks of use, just OK...

I love the La RochePosay BB Blur Foundation I have been using for a year.  I decided to try this hydrating one to see if I could skip a step or two my moisturizing and age defying steps in my morning routine.  I like my current foundation by La RochePosay better than this one.  I wish companies would keep the same color names across foundations, It would be so much easier to try multiple formulas.  I tried the 2 lightest colorsLight Beige and Ivory.  I am very white, but the Ivory is ridiculously light.  When my husband saw me he said "boo."  I said "what is that for?"  "You look like a ghost," he replied.  The light beige was a better match to my skin tone, but still lighter than the other La RochePosay foundation.  This foundation is thicker than the BB Blur mouse.  It can be hard to apply, especially in the summertime.  I tried spreading it with my fingers and a foundation brush.  The brush spread better than my fingers, but left streaks, so I have to do a little of both to get the best coverage.  I took off 1 star for the coverage being hard to put on.  Powder helps set the foundation, so I only need to apply once a day.  It looks better with powder.  I was concerned the moisturizer might make me break out, but did not.  I decided not to skip my other morning routine steps.  I am not sure if this foundation helps, but it does not hinder moisturizing and age defying from my normal product routine. I am going to use the rest of this foundation, but stick with the BB Blur.  I Am going to save this for the cooler fall/winter.
summary: Prefer La Roche-Posay's other foundation to this one

I loved this book!  Not having any interest in rowing races I would not have thought of reading this book except that I heard a glowing review on TV.  This is a true story about the Washington State College crew that won the Olympic Gold Medal in 1936 in Hitler's Germany.  Although one learns a bit about each remarkable  crew member, the story hinges largely on one,Joe Rantz, who had overcome extreme poverty and abandonment as a child to earn his way to college and the rowing crew.  One learns about all the skills needed in rowing, the building of the boats as well as the history of the time with the rise of Hitler, building of the Grand Coulee Dam, climate disasters such as the drought that forced farmers to give up their farms.  The research done for this book was extensive and completely documented in notes. And this book reads like a novel.  And I will be watching the rowing events in the next Olympics.

text:
So, this is what life comes down to when you are 50 years olTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry  reviewing dryer vent cleaners while sitting at your kitchen table waiting for American Idol.  This is not what I envisioned when I was 12, I can tell you that much.  You kids who think it will not happen to you?

It will.  Sorry to burst your bubble.

That said, the product works great.  Our dryer pretty much stopped working and we were thinking we needed a new one, which was seriously going to eat into my plastic surgery budget.  One last shot before a trip to the appliance store was this Gardus LintEater.  My husband, who is not the handy one of the family, had to do the work as I have a torn labrum.  Which sounds dirtier than it is  that is part of your shoulder.  He, the clumsiest man in the world, had absolutely no problem using this.  I warned him to read the directions first, and he actually listened and followed.  He hooked it up to the drill, and away he went.  He got a bunch of musty, wet lint that had probably been up inside the wall since 1977   probably consisting of bell bottom material and macram.

Now our dryer actually dries clothes again, and I can continue to save for my facelift. Thank you Gardus.

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

This followup to the sublime Powerslave is rather weak. Part of the problem is the new sound they are using. The compositions themselves are obviously in the tradition of Iron Maiden but they come off sounding very flat compared to other Maiden discs. Sounds more like prog rock than straight heavy metal.
The best part of this disc is the superb lead guitar work by Dave Murray and Adrian Smith. They really play with a lot of feel. The solos are fast in the tradition of good metal but also melodic.
The worst part of the disc is Bruce's vocals and some of the lyrics. Bruce is trying to sound operatic on some of the songs and he is just not up to the task. Sometimes he sounds like a howling old lady.
Some of the lyrics take a stab at being deep but come across as just silly  Loneliness of the Long Distance Runner being the main culprit. Alexander the Great was an attempt at doing another Rime of the Ancient Mariner. The Rime, adapted from Samual Taylor Coleridge sp?, is a piece of epic metal genius. Alexander the Great sounds like Bruce is reading the lyrics out of a high school text book on European History. Simply foolish.
To sum up, the approach here is obviously similar to Powerslave but the results do not even compare. Somewhere in Time is one of Maiden's weakest.
An intriguing story with thrilling action.  A must have for the PS3.

text: ok

In No God But One, Nabeel examines Islam and Christianity from a theological and historical perspective. Does the evidence support one worldview over the other?
Nabeel is a Christian, but he grew up in a Pakistani Muslim family in the US. He converted to Christianity after not being able to fully believe that "There is no God but Allah, and Muhammad is his messenger"the shahada there is more to that story detailed in "Seeking Allah, Finding Jesus". He does not think an objective observer would be convinced of the arguments for Islam, whereas the evidence for Christianity is supported by many sources.
I approached this book to learn more about Islam, since it is the second largest and fastest growing religion in the world. It puts into proper context some basal things: for example, the Quran and Bible are not theologically equivalent in each religion, what is the nature of Yahweh compared to Allah, how do the Crusades contrast with jihad there is more to read about the jihad in "Answering JihaTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry A Better Way Forward"?
I understand Islam more on account of this book, and I now feel that I can dialogue with Muslims about their faith and why they believe what they do. And remember, as Christians, we are called to "in your hearts honor Christ the Lord as holy, always being prepared to make a defense to anyone who asks you for a reason for the hope that is in you; yet do it with gentleness and respect" 1 Peter 3:15.
summary: Well-Researched Treatise on Islam and Christianity

I have children 14, 11, and 9, and I was looking for software that would appeal to their creative side.  I am a fairly sophisticated software user, and used to do some programming myself, but had never really ventured into these type of painting/art programs.

Bottom Line: I was blown away by this program, totally impressed!!

Why?

1 It is easy to use out of the box many of the controls are easy enough to figure out just by using them, it installs easy on both Mac and PC systems I installed the program on both an old eMac and a low end Vista laptop successfully.

2 It is really powerful once you really get into the software, it is amazing all the different brushes and textures and effects that you can do to make really impressive art.

3 The tutorials are first rate A thick instruction manual that actually is well written, and actually teaches you about basic principles of art and painting.  There are also a whole series of video tutorials included free.  You can tell that a lot of hard work and frankly a lot of love went into this, which is a rarity for computer software these days.

4 It is a great value For all you get, the price is very reasonable.  And check the company's website, if you are still not sold they were at the time of this writing offering a 60 day free downloadable trial.

One more tip:  Get even a lowprice graphics tablet to go along with the software you will be glad you did!

I have had "Rock 'N Soul, Part I" for years, and I played it for my nowwife on the day we first met.  While that collection captures the prime of this great pop/rock/soul duo, this one is much more complete.  Virtually every hit I can remember by these guys and there were many is here, plus a lot of great material I had not heard.  Including the newer stuff e.g., "Everything Your Heart Desires" and Darryl's big solo hit "Dreamtime" is a nice touch.  I do not need to rave about all the old classics; if you are reading this you know how great they are!  This is by far the best collection of these guys you will find anywhereridiculous that it is only an import but definitely worth the price.  Gorgeous pop music for the soulsomething that does not seem to exist anymore.
summary: Only H & O collection that has it all!

The plastic pedals or cams used to raise the wheels on the unit are not of adequate quality.
This tool does not get moved a lot, but after maybe the 4th time used, the plastic cams broke.
I called HTC customer service and they are sending me replacement cams in an upgraded metal version.
They offered to do this at no charge, even though the warranty is out at 15 months.
BY THE WAY
The text listing the features say "limited lifetime warranty" but if you download the warranty paper it has only a ONE YEAR warranty.
But they are honoring the warranty anyway.  That is a good sign.
So, for now I am doing the review as a 4 star.  Would be 5 if I did not have to replace the cams.
It sounds like they figured this out, so new units may be OK...
summary: Maybe not as good as I thought.

M Ward's Transistor Radio is an eclectic mix of genres that is captivating in its beauty and scope. If I needed one word to describe the album it would be ethereal.  With influences both classical and popular this album hearkens back through the years giving it an ultimately timeless feel.  I highly recommend this one.

Transistor Radio opens up with "You Still believe in me" which showcases Wards musical ability with this purely American tune that is reminiscent of Bluegrass and Folk.  And of course worthy of note is his cover of Louis Armstrong's "Sweethearts on Parade". I am always fearful when an artist sets out to cover Armstrong.  It usually sounds more like a mockery than serious art.  But Ward is so focused and creative that he can pull it off making the work something entirely new while still keeping the feel of the Armstrong original.  Lastly, I must mention "Fuel for Fire"  which is exemplary of wards haunting vocals and "Four Hours in Washington" with its shuffling rhythm sound like a Tom Waits song.

M Ward is a true artist and this is a great work.  If I had to compare him to anyone it would be to Tom Waits.  They both have a real knack for mixing genres and adding subtle hints and allusions to other styles and songs. They are both true American Artists. Transistor Radio has wide appeal and I think fans of "emo" to fans Billie Holiday will find this a great album. M Ward is one to watch and this is a super album.  Buy a copy today.

Ted Murena
summary: Beyond Definition but Astounding: This is one to Buy

The album also caters to the hardcore fan: 1 "The Hardest" 2"On Da Grind." The album has appeal to even rock fans: 1"Lay it on Back" w/ Fred Durst does have a hiphop beat, though. This album is not so much set trippin' and gang banging as in Tha Streetz Iz A Mutha though that one is tight too! This is his main party album,  something to relax to  and party to!

I think this is a terrific disc.  Rameau's music is wonderful  full of energy, melody and variety  and Angela Hewitt does it proud.  As others here have noted, Rameau on the piano is a different experience from Rameau on the harpsichord, but for me it is a wonderful experience when the piano is this well played.

As with her magnificent Bach recordings, Hewitt brings a flawless technique, deep scholarship and an obvious love of the music to this disc.  She judges tempi and ornamentation perfectly to my ears, giving the music exactly the right feel and she uses the expressive capabilities of the piano to bring out the music's qualities without ever imposing flashy tricks or inappropriate sentiment on it.  It is a joy from start to finish and I never tire of listening to it.

I love my wonderful set of Rameau on the harpsichord by Christophe Rousset and this certainly does not replace it, but it complements it beautifully.  The recorded sound is as always from Hyperion excellent and the notes and presentation are very good and I recommend this very warmly  it is a beauty.

The music here is easily worth 5 stars.  But this outdated and extremely incomplete collection is not.

Sure, in 1976, this was not a bad idea.  But in 2010, you would be much better off buying the 2CD set "Very Best of the Eagles."  It spans their entire original period, 19711980, and includes all the big hits.  This album seems like a budget release in this day and age simply because more definitive collections have been released since.

The Eagles are one of my top favorite groups but to buy this album would be to ignore the brilliant second half of their career  the half that gave us the masterpieces "Hotel California" and "The Long Run."  The 2CD set from 2003 covers it all, and that is what true Eagles fans ought to have.
summary: Not Bad, But You Can Do Better

This review is for essie Gel Couture Nail Polish set with the 144inside scoop and platinum grade finish top coat.  "Inside Scoop" is a tea rose pink with a slight blue undertone. The color goes on streak free and does not require a basecoat.  I am able to get consistent, nonstreak opaque color with one application  second application not needed but does seem to prolong the wear.  The top coat provides protection and shine.  It creates a hard she will which prevents chipping and has a high gloss.

I find this easy to remove and it lasts about 6 days with 2 color coats and one top coat.  I let it dry 35 minutes between each color coat and 10 minutes after the top coat.  The results look like what you would get from a nail salon and lasts the whole week.  The shape of the brush allows for precise application.

Overall, I would recommend this product to a friend.
