Nice sprinkler  the base is heavy enough to keep the sprinkler in place, but you still have to get the hose just right so a twist in the hose does not help it lose it is balance  maybe another 5lbs would do the trick, but then I know it would be more expensive to ship too...ugh...decisions.

Other than that, the sprinkler works great, is typical of most impact sprinklers we have several and it has the "better" type of stop guides  solid metal, rather than just a loop of lighter metal...makes it easier to adjust and I am sure it will hold up longer too.  I love impact sprinklers and once people understand how to adjust them, most of the people I have showed say "OH!" and then they understand it is infinitely adjustable...OK infinite may be a stretch, but you CAN adjust it in very small doses over many categories of spray  distance, width, spray, area covered....  This is a good heavy duty model sprinkler that looks like it will last a lifetime.
summary: Great Sprinkler - Ought to last me a lifetime.

Want To know what I dislike? Saying good bye to characters of a story that I have come to love since day one, ever since I read the first book in The Invisibles series I fell in love with each and every one of their stories and now that I have read Love Me Always I really did not want to say good bye to the gang. Michelle has always done such a wonderful job of capturing these characters emotions that you cannot help but to feel what they are feeling. Sadie and Brady are planning their guys one that I Have been waiting for, but what we get to see is them trying to still battle the ghosts of their past. Sadie with the death of her brother and the fact that hes not there and then Brady gets a blast from the past, one that has left him scarred. The thing I love watching was seeing that both Brady and Sadie had to realize that there are things that they are still learning and will continue to learn from each other. Then we have the fact that the gang always has each other backs, they are there for each other through thick and thin, and boy did they need each other. I am very saddened to say goodbye to Brady, Sadie, Grant, Jessa, Dex, Chrissy, Rob and Paige.
summary: Perfect ending to a wonderful series

The spare styling makes it an ideal unisex gift and should blend with most decors. The lush floral scent is accented with a bight of lemon and the tang of mint. This product works OK and is especially friendly to novices, but there is two things about it that make me wonder if Symantec has a monkey for a product manager on this product.

1 Users cannot migrate settings for firewall, trusted zones etc. from one version to another. So for each upgrade you pay for, you get to spend a couple hours rekeying in all your special rules for your firewall so your P2P,  game software, tunneling etc. keeps working.  and of course, a year's worth of "let that program talk to the Web" responses are also lost.

2 You buy the product, but at the end of the yearly update subscription, you do not just lose the ability to update. The morons at Symantec have programmed it to TURN OFF YOUR FIREWALL COMPLETELY! Boom  you are left unprotected by the software you PAID for just because you have not PAID AGAIN by a certain date for the new virus subscription. So if you happen to be traveling,  your computer could be left w/o even basic firewall protection until you get back and notice. This is TOTALLY unacceptable!

So my recommendation is to spend your money elsewhere until Symantec wises  up. Unless these two issues are properly addressed, it really does not matter how good the other functions are. The product is not worth the effort to reprogram the firewall each year and the risk of being left without even basic firewall protection just because the update subscription runs out makes it a nonstarter.  I would give it zero stars if I could.
summary: Norton is clueless about user requirements

I have several silicone rings, and this is by far the most 'dainty.'  It is not super dainty, of course, because it is silicone.  But, because of the color and size, it feels that way, comparitively.  I originally started getting these for my husband, who is very active in both life and work.  But, then I realized they are perfect for holding my grandfather's wedding ring onto my thumb. So, any time I get an option to receive a discount in exchange for an honest review, as I did this one, I take it.  I want as many colors as possible.  This one is enough smaller that it does not hold on the ring as well.  It works, more or less, but it sometimes slides over it.  I think if I were getting one to use as a wedding band, however, as a woman, this is the one I would want.  It is a little more ringish, a little less siliconebandish.

Military members that are deployed are frequent gamers.  May carry over their XBox's, Laptops, PS3's, etc to the deployed location Europe, Middle East, Africa, anywhere really.  It is one of the few things left to do that bring some joy from home and give us a chance to escape reality and just have fun.

This is the second game now I have found that REQUIRE a constant highspeed internet connection, just to play single player.  The first I saw was Assassin's Creed II and now this one, another highanticipated game.  What in the world are these companies thinking?  They do not even have servers that can handle the loads of people trying to sign on to the SINGLE PLAYER games, so you may find yourself waiting hours upon hours just to sign in.  Then you will find yourself knocked off when the server slows down too much.  [...] for this?

As far as the military community hundreds of thousands of people are concerned  NONE of us can every play these games while deployed, TDY or just traveling around the country.

I can understand companies doing what they can to prevent copyright infringement, but this is TOO FAR.  You have alienated an entire corps of people and the hatred for this type of program requirement is growing drastically among the public.  It is time to wake up and release patches that will allow single player people to play these games with no internet connection at all.  that is what install ID codes are for inside boxes at install.

Wake up Steam and fellow companies that keep this internet requirement insanity.
summary: Creater refuses to allow deployed military to play this

Although this is only one of a few of Pete Townshend's solo works, I personally feel that Pete was a much better songwriter with the Who than without.  As a solo artist, there are only a few songs on this CD, "Empty Glass" that caught my attention; namely "Rough Boys", "Let My Love Open The Door", and "Going To Get Ya".  While Pete can still rock on this CD, he does not show the bravado as he did on the early Who works, like "Live at Leeds", "Tommy", "Who is Next", and "Quadrophrenia".  In my mind, THAT was The Who I want to remember; that had consistently good songs throughout the album that qualified them as megarockstars.  Pete can still rock on the few cuts from "Empty Glass" I mentioned, but does not do as well elsewhere on the CD.  Dang, I miss the old Who....

At first this contraption was a little confusing. I read the directions about 3 times before I felt okay about going through with the project  was not fully confident as there were a lot of warnings about making sure the drill was going the right way/you turned it the right way so you would not lose rods in the dryer vent. Scared me a little. However, the project turned out really well. We did not lose any rods thankfully and we got out the birds nest that had taken residence in our dryer vent!!
The part that was for the lint catcher was convenient as well and is actually recommended to be used at least once a month in order to clean out the lint catcher. I do need to keep up with this but it is not convenient to have to put together and tape the rods each time when you only really use it for a couple of minutes. However, if you have a handy space to keep it already together, I can see how this would be even better for keeping up with cleaning the lint out.

I have a PowerMac G5 and Dell notebook. The notebook went bad so purchase MacBook with Windows Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry and Parallels. After working all day getting Parallels and Windows installed and up and running, I thought my life was great. Then after a week things quite working. Parallels would not boot Windows no matter what I tried. The manual is not written for the average business user and has several mistakes in it. They provide an additional manual to try to correct the mistakes in the first manual with such things as, " on Page 3 replace step 4 with the following . . . next place the content of . . .  in the second bullet, the name should be corrented . . ." Then you have to go to their website to find corrections to these corrections. The manual is written in true computer geek language and not for the person that does not make his living working on and with computers. Parallels offers support at $30/call or by email that does not work. They only work during business hours on West coast time. Suggestion  if you need Windows, buy a PC of Boot Camp.

Of all the actors to portray Satan, Al Pacino gives the best performance as the prince of darkness over everyone else.  It is Pacino's performance as John Milton aka: Satan that makes The Devil's Advocate worthwhile; with every other actor to portray Satan, they always portray him as a menacing, relentless sum of all evil.  Pacino gives Satan a classy swagger never before seen, making the devil seem more human than previously imagined.  The film itself is great, with Keanu Reeves' portrayal of Kevin Lomax, a hotshot lawyer who gets his chance to work in Pacino's lawfirm.  The beautiful Charlize Theron and Connie Nielsen give good performances as well, especially Theron as Reeves' wife who senses something foul afoot, and eventually starts to lose her mind.  Jeffrey Jones and Craig T. Nelson give good performances as well, Nelson is rather good as a murder suspect who Reeves is picked to defend.  All in all, The Devil's Advocate is a great thriller, and Pacino is devilishly no pun intended charming as Satan.  A little side note: when Pacino and Reeves go to the boxing match, Pacino introduces Reeves to Don King and they seem to be good friends.  Whoever said that Don King made deals with the devil might have been right afterall.
summary: Al Pacino gives the devil his due

If not a true Sabbath fan might want to just pick up a sabbath greatest hits that hit the high points of this album.  The albums you really want to hear all of are Masters of Reality and Paranoid.  Still Great cover art and what a great send off.

text: This is a good product. I am new to French skincare but I do not think I am ever going back lol. It was recommended by my dermatologist, he recommended effaclar duo specifically. But I saw this in the trio and figured it was a good deal. If you can use it over a weekend when you will NOT go out in the sun, that is a good bet. Certain products in it make your skin sensitive to the sun, it says that on the packaging. The first time I used it was at night so I did not notice it, the next morning when I used it and headed to work, my skin was on FIRE. I have sensitive skin and I am African American so it really REALLY hurt. I did not get a sun burn thankfully.  The gel cleanser has sort of a minty tingly feeling, the clarifying solution just makes your skin feel clean and soft. I use the duo as a spot treatment if I have a pimple. One day I had a blackhead on my forehead near my eye, I put the duo on it and when I woke up in the morning the pimple was gone. I mean COMPLETELY gone. Again be careful with this product, use it every other day until your skin gets used to it. And do not forget the sunscreen.
summary: Good product but be careful in the sun

I had this album back in 1975, and fell in love with it.  This is without a doubt their best.  I picked up the remastered CD AM 2002, and it sounds much better than this LP.  Which is surprising given that most albums deserving of 180G remastering that I have heard get a proper treatment and sound wonderful.  The highs are lacking, the overall level is at least 6 db lower than most of my albums, and it sounds thin.  It is absolutely full of pops and clicks brand new out of the sleeve.  I was so looking forward to getting this, and now I am so disappointed.  Why bother?

Furthermore, in doing a little more research it seems that most of the Back To Black vinyl series were poorly done.  From what I gather they are taking CDs and essentially pressing vinyl from them which totally defeats the purpose.  They are going to be just as thin and lacking as a CD with the added bonus of pops and clicks.  Yippee.  Capitol Valuts is another one to stay away from.
summary: The music is great, the mastering is very bad

text:
Did you ever think that Spinal Tap was a real group? Then you were probably appalled at their appearances on the late shows! But if you were like me you became an instant fan once you knew the secret.
So, is the Criterion DVD good?  Yes!  But do not go searching for the Break Like The Wind stuff because it are not there. Several of the best videos were included on the 1992 VHS release.  But they are missed in this DVD form.  What IS included is great!  A lot of outtakessome funny, some not. Although several bits I feel could have stayed in, you will agree that they used the best stuff for the final film. It is interesting to note that most drug references and all the nudity was clipped from the film. Also, the actress from the movie "Just One Of The Guys" was clipped.  The new lead guitar player was a very interesting idea.  Perhaps that should have stayed in.  Other material: commercials, promotional materials, complete videos, interviews such as the Flower People press conference, and more. Plan to spend almost 3 and a half hours on this DVD. It is great fun! The DVD interface is one of my favorites; with new stuff recorded just for the DVD presentation.
So put this in your machine, crank it up the sound quality is pretty good and put Spinal Tap on BEFORE the puppet show!

Amber Lea Easton is an extremely talented writer, and her style of writing keeps you turning the page. I fell in love with this novel.

This story tells the tale of Jessica Moriarty. a college graduate who has decided to take a gaptrip to Europe in order to visit Italy before she starts a new job with a firm of Boston architects.  As in life, things never go to plan. While in Italy she meets the gorgeous Jacques Sinclair, a very sexy photographer.

This is a coming of age story. Without spoiling the plot  Jessica must choose between the love of her life, or her career and family back in the States. She has always been a good girl and given into the pressures of living responsibly. Now she wants to let her hair down and escape all the rules and regulations  she wants to feel!  The story is full of emotion, hot romance and angst as she strives to reach her decision.  Does she stay or does she return to the States.

This is a book you will not be able to put down.  Enjoy!
summary: A great coming of age story with a compelling plot!

I I do not have an MP3 player so I can not say how well that works, but my wife's CDG discs play great. I am hoping this item will last better than the portable singing machines my wife has bought in the past. I bought this to put my leather Inductive Study Bible Kay Arthur the leather one in, and it fits perfectly. You can either use the pockets in front and back to insert your covers into, as it was designed, or you can just place your Bible inside the cover and use those pockets for notes etc. Even with my bible inside, and eight pages of bible marking symbols I printed to use with my study that are tucked in the front pocket, there is still room to place a notepad on top, and zip it up easily. There are two pen loops, made of elastic, one on the front, one on the back. They will hold any kind of pens, even large ones that write several different colors. Besides all this, it is a lovely cover. It does not look cheap. The zipper zips easily and seems like a heavy duty zipper. Several reviewers asked how long this would last. I do not know, but I am very careful with my bible, and do not just throw it around, so would expect it to last a long time. I love the teal color, and the smooth feel. James Caan is at his best as a thief who hooks up with the wrong people. Caan plays Frank a thief who always works alone and with minimal help from trusted aids Jim Belushi in an early role and never takes a job to high risk. Agianst his better judgment he hooks up with Leo Robert Prosky a mobster who enlists Frank to do a high profile job. Frank has problems of his own like his new wife Jessie Tuesday Weld and trying to adopt a child, not to mention the police know he is in town...Well of course things go wrong and Leo informs Frank that he is not a man to be messed with. By the end Leo finds out Frank is not either. Willie Nelson has a small but pivital role as an inmate friend of Franks.
Not sense the Godfather has James Caan had a better role. This movie is the kind of Great drama we can expect from Michael Mann who brought us Heat, The Insider, Manhunter and Ali. Caan is both menacing and vulnerable at the same time. He seems like nothing bothers him on the outside but let us you in just enough to understand.

Martin Fan Is Impressed.
I have played Martin strings on my Martins all my life. But recently I read some reviews of these D'Addarios that made me try them.
I am impressed, like really impressed. Blown away impressed.
I was in the studio and just not getting the clean sparking sound I wanted for a really fast acoustic guitar song. I replaced my main string, Martin 80/20s,  with these and the guitar just sang.
We had to cut the highs a little because it was so sparkly. We did not cut the lows, though, who would even think about that... and when we listened to the takes, the bass notes were so boomy we could not even cut it enough with 4 different EQs.
We had to rerecord the takes after meticulously resetting the mics EQ on the preamp and board. That is amazing. This never happened before. These F'n strings SING! They blew me and everyone away. WTF? I got a case of Martins I do not want to use now.

text:
First, let me say that I love TurboTax.  I have been using it for years to do my taxes and it has made it relatively painless.  Up until now, if you purchase the Deluxe version you get free Federal efile, because the IRS does not charge for this service.  Remember when they did?  TurboTax used to charge a fee.  But, now they do not because the IRS does not.

So, the State of California sent out notices this year saying that they have free efiling.  I assumed that when I did an automatic upload of any changes to the taxes this year that TurboTax would also upload the fact that the State of California has free efiling.  However, they still charge an extra $20 for efiling the State return.  I looked at their community question and answer sections
, and it appears that many states now offer free efiling, and other tax payers also assumeD that meant TurboTax would file their state return for free.  However, TurboTax just takes the $20 out of your tax refund.

So, if they do not change things next year, without increasing the price on their software, I will no longer be purchasing TurboTax.  If I have to fill out the same information a second time on the State of California tax website, why do I need TurboTax?

DOWN WITH THE $20 FEE TO EFILE THE STATE!
summary: This May be My Last Year with TurboTax

text: I do not leave home without mascara and I have olive skin, so I am always looking for a good new black mascara.  Japonesque Lash Loading mascara has some very good points.  The black is a deep flat black. I can pull it off with olive skin and I bet if you have porcelain toned skin this would look amazing.  It does really cover your lashes  the mascara itself is a good texture.  The flaw for me was the brush.  It is fabulous, reminds me of the Definicils brush which is my alltime favorite.  But it is a bit too long.  I do have small eyes and a small face, so this might not be a problem for you, but that extra millimeter of length made for a slower application lest it become sloppy.  One other note.  This is not waterproof  which is an issue for me because I workout and shower during the day.  So I am using thsi as my Saturday night mascara.  When I have the time  and will not be working out  this is a great dark black look.

I have purchased at least 5 different brands  some are good, but none are as nice and comfy as the Vitalsox.  The best thing about this sock besides the compression is the padded sole. This is a necessity to me, even with ultra soft insoles in my shoes. I run about 70 miles a month, not a lot maybe but enough that makes my feet want a soft impact. This sock fits well in all my running shoes Brooks, and Asics does not slip, seams are not irritating, they do not bunch up, they stay up, they fit just below my knee and support the knee well. Another brand I bought high end and expensive did not go up high enough and the sole was too thin. This is not only an affordable sock, it is better than those that cost twice as much and the compression supports the calf, helping shin splints to stay at a minimum. Ankle compression is excellent, giving support where I need it. Cannot say enough good things about it. These really do help, not only in running but recovery.
summary: My favorite compression sock for long runs!

text:
I am learning to do metal stamping and wire work and I decided copper would be the metal I worked with.  Easier to choose one so I can keep one set of chain and findings around.  I bought these to practice stamping.  The finish is lovely actually better than some larger RMP copper square blanks I also bought and is protected by plastic films on each side.  It matches my other bright copper materials headpins, eyepins, jump rings, etc. so finished pieces incorporating these have a professionallymade appearance.  The films are a bit difficult to remove but you should remove them before stamping.

This is a good width for lettering, although I am primarily using symbols instead of letters just personal preference.  So far I have done pretty well in my practice attempts at stamping with a steel bench block, one pound hammer, and ImpressArt stamps there were a few other branded stamps in there I tried, as well.  I am able to punch through it with a EuroTool metal punch so I can put holes in the ends.

Whether or not you need to smooth out the edges depends on how you use these.  There are a number of affordable rotary tools on Amazon if you decide to smooth out the edges.  I have one from Black and Decker.  You may want to run over the surface with a polishing cloth, but the surfaces were pretty good to begin with better than some of the other copper stamping blanks I bought.

Overall I felt that these were high quality and I would buy them again if I run out and/or buy more blanks from the same company.
summary: nice finish; matches my findings; stamping works pretty well on these (even if you are a beginner)

Obviously, Carrie listened to all of the Nashville critics, and actually made a straightforward Country album.  As many of you are well aware, Nashville did not throughly embrace Carrie as a Country artist, since her debut album was more of a Pop Album with Country undertones.  However, she made a bold move, and dropped the Pop sound entirely, and went ahead and made a Country CD..... and it does not work, for a number of reasons.

This album sounds forced from beginning to end.  There is none of that free flowing, goosebump giving kind of music that the first album offered.  I listened to this entire CD 3 different times, and realized, there is really not a good song on the entire CD.  "Last Name" would have to be the best song, if there is one.  "All American Girl" sounds forced, and I am not buying it.

This was an enormous letdown, and I am completely baffled by the many positive reviews this album received on here.  It is simply NOT a good CD, at all.  Carrie's still adorably beautiful though. Happy face or smiley
summary: Straight Country Isn't Working For Me

I had the following problems with TurboTax Premier 2012:
1 One inactive cell.  On one occasion, TubroTax had a prompt asking for a number to be entered in a highlighted cell, but the cell was inactive and would not accept any entry.  This single dead cell resulted in a return with an error, and TurboTax as a result would not file my returns despite lengthy efforts.
2 The stepbystep instructions on filing K1 forms are muddled to the point of being impossible for me to use  even after repeated attempts.  Twice TurboTax asked for information that went beyond that provided on my K1 form itself, and which I had no idea how to answer.  One prompt suggested something like "enter negative one in column A".  I had no idea to what the prompt was referring.
3 TurboTax reported one discrepancy in values between those on my Federal and State returns although the values on my State return were loaded by TubroTax itself from my Federal return that TurboTax had just prepared.  Though unlikely, it seemed possible that the discrepancy was generated by TurboTax itself.
4 One error message 3 above offered no clear to me indication of where the error was occurring or how it might be fixed.
5 No useful help was available to troubleshoot any of the difficulties above.

A Very Country Christmas: A Free Christmas Short Story by Zara Stoneley

Tippermere has love in the air. Charlotte Lottie Brinkley is in line to inherit the Tipping House Estate where she lives with Rory Steel.
Lottie really wants a quiet Christmas with just Rory and her and has hope that perhaps this Christmas might be special with Rory giving her an engagement ring even though he already proposed. She has a special Santa costume already set to woo Rory.
But the things at the Tipping House Estate are never as simple as that. Lady Elizabeth Stanthorpe is the current owner of the Tipping House Estate and is Lotties grandmother. She really wants to help Rory surprise Lottie.
There are missing turkeys, loose horses and troublesome terriers all to make for some wonderful excitement. The ever so quiet Christmas that Lottie is hoping for never stands a chance. One invite leads to another and to another. A meal for 2 turns into a meal for 10 with lots of excitement and surprises.
Lottie prepared some of the Christmas meal at the main house on the estate but the meal itself was going to be at Rory and her place. Lottie was reminded to be sure to steam the pudding.
Lottie is disappointed that her ring was not under the Christmas tree. She was going to try to not let the romantic dream that did not happen spoil the day.
Rory thought of a horse for Lottie and it has a special surprise in his bridle. Lottie got her special Christmas gift!!!
summary: Lottie got her special Christmas gift!!!

text:
I have purchased two of these, one to replace my jawbone and one for my network technician.  I have not soaked it in beer, buried it in sand, nor gone swimming with it.

Sound quality is OK ambient noise will overwhelm it.  Wind noise makes it cut out in 12 second instances making it unusable outside when there is a breeze.

Fit is a compromise between durability and comfort.  It works, the neck strap is very handy.  It appears durable enough to stuff in my pocket when not in use and the ear clip is free swiveling so I am not worried about breaking it and having a stash of spares.

Update I dropped it in the parking lot, someone ran over it.  Apparently military durability does not include the ability to withstand crushing forces.

I am not sure I will buy another.  The device had decent sound quailty except when a slight breeze would cause it to cut out.  Other headsets transmit a static sound, this model just cuts off when the wind sound occurs.  I am back to searching for a decent noise canceling headset again.
summary: so far ok-don't run over it with your car though

Holly Sissy Spacek, a 15yearold girl living in a North Dakota town, falls under the influence of twentysomething social misfit Kit Martin Sheen.  When her father Warren Oates stands in their way, Kit kills him and hits the road with Holly, who thinks she is in love with him.  They hide out in the wilderness for awhile, and then go on the run, killing several people along the way.

Director/screenwriter Terence Malick has given us characters that are emotionally barren, as reflected by the barren landscapes of North Dakota.  They occasionally seem happy together, but most of the time they seem emotionally flat and detached from their own feelings; Holly seems as if she is in a constant state of shock.  Malick's style is almost like that of a documentary, presenting the events and trusting us to draw our own conclusions.  Sheen and Spacek, both at the beginnings of their careers, show a great deal of talent./
summary: Cold, stark portrayal of young killers

This latch is nonreversible.

The back side is open and on the inside the lever has two notches cut into it leaving a tab for a sprint to go over. The box also has a tab for the other end of the spring. They are offset from each other so the the lever is either in or out, the spring is bent into somewhat and S. This is what gives the feeling of the lever latching into something.

Cannot use but one of the holes on my Wayne Dalton doors to attach this latch. Drilling a hole is not as good as using the punched holes because you do not get all the surface for the screws threads. I am using some Nutserts to attach the latches.

The latches I received also did not look as what was pictured. I did not expect them to either. Most notably, no red cover over the end. Not a deal breaker.

I do not own this box specifically but I did buy a box of 30  Stic pens years ago. I am a pen junkie and felt the need to over indulge on pens while I was in college. This is a classic pen from BIC brand and they are always reliable. I have had these pens sitting in a plastic bag for years. I recently went to transfer all of my pens to a box case, while updating them, seeing which of my pens still worked. Oddly enough, all of my BIC staic pens were working, even the ones baring advertising from various companies. I was quite surprised, seeing how I have owned the pens for well over five years, rarely if ever used.

I prefer to use the fine point stic pen but the medium works fine. It does write well, ink flows smoothly, never had ink blots and the ink does not bleed through papers. Ink if wet will not bleed on the paper. Overall for a cheapy, well known and classic pen these are some of the best and most reliable pens I have bought to date.

text:
The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

This is a story about abandonment, about being caught between two worlds, and about making your way in the world.

Violet Minturn grew up in a courtesan house in Shanghai in the early 20th century, the daughter of the American madam. She observed how her mother, Lulu, engaged her clients, the wealthiest Chinese and American men in the city, in conversation about their businesses and their power. As far as she can tell, her mother loves her business more than she loves Violet.

When her mother abandons her, she makes her living the only way she knows howas a courtesan. For a time, she falls in love and leaves that life behind, but her joy is shortlived when her lover dies, and his legal wife claims Violet's children as her own.

Tan weaves a vivid, epic tale about Violet's life, and toward the end she reveals what really happened to Lulu.

My greatest concern is that young women will read this book and perceive Lulu and Violet's lives as a courtesan romantic. The story details the inner workings of highclass prostitution, and makes it seem glamorous. I do not think that is Tan's intention; between the lines I see conviction that the sex industry is exploitation. Nevertheless, there it is. The writing is fabulous. I recommend the book with that one caveat. It is the reason why I cannot give it 5 stars.
summary: The workings of a high-class courtesan house.

text: I just installed these shocks on the rear of my Silverado.  They have really tightened the ride and do a great job of smoothing out bumps.  They come with a green plastic strap holding them compressed in the box.  These things are a beast to recompress, so you probably will not be doing it one handed.  What I found to work well was to place the shock in the lower bracket and run the bolt through.  I then tightened the nut by hand to keep the bolt in place.  Getting ready to slip the bolt through the upper bracket, I slid the green strap off the top of the shock and controlled its angle and speed of decompression with my one hand.  As the shock slid up to the upper mount I quickly slid the bolt through the shock and bracket with my free hand.  This worked great on both sides, I did need to tap the bolt a bit with a rubber mallet on the one side to finish pushing it through though.  Finally, tighten the nuts, cut the packaging strap and you are good to go.
Great design  worked perfect!
summary: No lights in the water - no wind pushing me off the trailer!!

Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

As a guy that listens to rock and hip hop, I never was a N sync fan. That is until I had to do security at their  Oakland,CA "Popoddesy" tour for two days. I was surprised at the stage, 100 foot screen TV, fireworks, conveyor belts, The works to make a successful show. After I worked the show, I went and purchased the CD.On thier third effort, J.C and Justin managed to pull off some of the dirtiest pop I have ever ran across. Thier CD is well built on up tempo dance music. And they have also did some production themselves.
Songs like "the game is over" is pretty darn good for a boy band. But you have funk driven beats like "girlfriend" and "Celebrity" that put this CD into mainstream rotation big time. I predict this CD to go Diamond 10 million. As far as the boy band reputation goes, they have earned my respect and I look at them totally different now.
summary: Surprisingly Good, for a BOY BAND

It is funny, so many cheaper brands of facial lotion fail because they try to do so much. They try to be the deepest moisturizer ever, or get rid of wrinkles, or for some unknown reason think it is a good idea to heavily perfume their lotion so we will feel luxurious or something.

What I love about this straightforward and simple face cream is that it does exactly what it says and nothing more. It moisturizes my combination skin perfectly, not too heavy, not too light, and the sun protective factor works great. I cannot smell it at all, which is perfect.

On most days, I spent about 1 to 2 hours out in the sunshine gardening. If I forget to use sunscreen, I definitely feel some soreness on my face and neck. So having sunscreen included in my normal daily facial moisturizer is great.

I was also really impressed that the pump dispenser dispenses an accurate amount to cover my face. When I first used it, I snickered at how little it gave me and I pumped out three globs of it and started covering my face. I quickly realized that this facial lotion goes farther than most brands do, so one pump was actually perfect for my face, and I will use a second pump for my ears, neck, and back of my neck. Given how little you need to use for effective coverage, this actually seems like a pretty good deal as well as being an effective product.
summary: Unobtrusive facial moisturizer with effective sunscreen

text: Classic!

The compact on this powder has a pretty design, a goodsized mirror you can see your whole face, and a soft sponge for application.

This powder itself has a light, smooth, airy feel. Actually, a velvety feel, so it is aptly named. It is purpose is to set makeup and give skin a matte finish, and it delivers those results as promised. The "mattifying" lasts for several hours, probably longer if your skin is very dry.

The shade is sort of an eggshe will white, which the manufacturers say is universal. This is true, to some extent, but I would caution those who use it to APPLY WITH A LIGHT HAND. I mention this because if you apply it heavily, you get a "lightening" effect. In other words, you will see white on your face. This is not to say the product has any glitter or pearl. It does not. Still, use too much, and you will notice that white look.

Four stars instead of five because of the color, which is a little tricky to apply at first without getting a toopale look.

text: This is said to be the most poplar tea brand in the UK, and it is not hard to see why.  This decaf has as good flavor as most of the popular USA brand nondecaf teas, and tastes almost exactly like the tea I was brought up on.  PG Tips even works well in my Keurig brewer using a Melitta Java Jig filter but NOT using any of several other filter rigs I have tried.  Your mileage may vary, but try it!  Flatten the bag out as evenly as you can in the bottom of the filter, but do not tear the bag.  Drop the bag into the mug for a few moments after running the brewer if you want your tea stronger.  These bags are a little harder to accidentally tear than most, so there is less chance of ending up with leaves in your tea.  These bags also seem to be geared a little more toward making a potful than a mugful, so do not let your tea steep for more than a minute or two unless you like it really strong!
Very good high quality and great price on Amazon.  Saw it for $30.00 more at a local retailer.

I have used TTax for a number of years.  As of yet, I have not had any problems or have been audited.  I am a simple, retired, taxpayer with uncomplicated taxes.  What I want is easy and cheap.  I have not been a fan of "online" taxes in that they may not be available when I need them.  And, then, there is the possibility of someone hacking your personal data.  TTax continues to make doing my simple taxes easy and quick.  I am not just looking for a maximum refund, I am looking at not going to jail!  What I do not like is that they continue to try and extract more money from you by offering more services.  But, they are a "business" and maybe you should expect this or expect to pay more for their s/w, or, maybe it might be a good service for you.  Every year, I look at other tax programs and they just do not seem to measure up for about the same price.  TTax at least inputs my basic previous data like name and SSn.  I have not had to use more advanced services.
summary: I Think I'll Have to Buy It as Long As I Live

text: Family Tree Maker is the premiere geneology software available for consumers, and has tremendous capabilities for discovery, tracking, and creating documentation to share. It is also very timedemanding to use, both from a learning curve aspect and from a product usage aspect. It can also be expensive in the longrun if you maintain a subscription to Ancestry.com. I have casually used other geneology software years ago, and this package beats previous generations hands down in it is professional interface and plethora of features. Cooperative efforts over the internet through TreeSync with other family members can be a force multiplier. One newer feature, the photo editor, is a waste for me, since I have several other more capable software packages, but for some it may be helpful. If you have a great deal of time available to explore the software and web site, Family Tree Maker Platinum could be a powerful discovery and documentation tool. Frankly, I am not as committed to tracking my geneology as this software requires.

text: The reason I am not giving this a 1 is that it is wellmade, attractive, light, and easy to take apart and put back together.  The problem is that it is also easy to climb out of if one is an eight week old Golden Retriever.  She can just barely reach and hold on to the top rail when she is stretched out as far as she can.  Then the back legs come up and find good footing on the second rail up from the bottom and it does not take much time from that point.  The worst part is that she is then up 24 inches and the trip down is not nearly as gentle as the trip up.  It actually works quite well when I am sitting next to her and can discourage her plans, but unattended it would only work on a much smaller puppy.  Only a barrier without horizontal rails would work for mine.
summary: A nice product but flawed for a larger-breed puppy

After replacing both the batteries and probe element on my Milwaukee Martini ph56 to no avail still does not work, and I Am out another $50, I ordered this for checking the pH of my brewing water. Note that this meter is roughly half the price of the probe alone on the ph56 if you get a good price on that part. I find it easy to use and calibrate. I actually like the mechanical, setscrew calibration because its very quick. This meter also seems to settle down very quickly. I use twopoint calibration with 7.0 and 4.0 solutions not the reference packs provided, which use slightly different reference values and requiring mixing because I have them available in bottles; after spending half a minute doing that, this meter seems accurate. I am going to buy another to keep on hand, since pH meters have a limited life expectancy. I like the idea of just replacing the whole thing when needed. Note that there is a similar model that has twodecimal accuracy 0.01 for a few dollars more. You must rinse the tip before and after using this or any other pH meter, as the manual recommends for proper maintenance. The manual instructs users to simply put the cap on tightly after the final rinse, but since I only brew every 46 weeks, I Am concerned the probe will dry out, so Ill probably store it with a piece of buffersoaked sponge in the cap to keep the probe tip wet. I wonder if other users of this meter have any experience with this.
summary: Excellent value and easy to use and calibrate

text: I am a woman in my 40s who has switched to shave soaps  a brush after years of canned foam. The Proraso green soap/croap is my favorite, and the white is very similar. Both are more of a "croap" cross between hard cream  soap rather than a straight up hard puck of soap. It lathers crazy easily with a wet badger or boar brush  the "Marco method" if you are new to wet shaving or having trouble making lather, google it  you will not regret it, and provides a good, close, irritationfree shave. I lather in the plastic Proraso bowl directly on the soap, then go straight to leg. I have also done a separate bowl lather with this, and it worked nicely. After use I leave the lid off for a couple of hours to let the soap dry somewhat I shave in the shower  store my soap there, so there is a lot of water and then store it with the lid on. The white has a slight menthol feel, but considerably less than the green. In my opinion, the white has a light scent of roses  fresh cut grass. It is very light and clean, and I think it could be considered the most "feminine" between the green, red  white Proraso soaps. I had issues with irritation from the red Proraso disappointing, since I loved the scent, but neither the green or the white because any problems for me. Overall I am extremely pleased with this soap and it will definitely be in my regular rotation.

text:
This early Woody Allen comedy is often quite a bit of fun.  Check out some of the other reviews here, which recount a few of the better sight gags and funny scenarios to see what I mean.  Just be warned, though, that Woody still had a way to go before the jokes got really sharp and the storylines moved with supreme smoothness.  I do not want to overstate the criticism, as "Take the Money and Run" never sinks to boredom, or choppiness in the story telling.  It is just that Woody's best period was still three or four films ahead of him at this point and a certain lack of polish is still evident.  But the movie is still definitely worth a look, even though I am not as big a fan of it as some other folks.

Unfortunately, the fullframe version of "Take the Money and Run" is the one most easily available on DVD in this country.  On the plus side, however, I noticed no obvious and offensive cropping of the image while I watched the movie though I guess something must have been cropped somewhere to create the fullframe image.  Also on the plus side, the print is sharp, clear, and bright.

But, alas, like most DVDs of Woody's films, there are basically no extras, just a trailer.  But we have come to expect that from Mr. Allen, have not we?  To his credit, the man does not like to go on and on about his movies, preferring to let them speak for themselves.
summary: He had better days ahead, but this is what put Woody on the map

text:
The wacky humor BrocoLee, varied level designs underwater, pastry factory, space station, etc., a cardboard cut out look and odd concept Come on, what other game has you saving the world by eating evil vegetables while collecting magical poo? of The Munchables add up to one of the most fun gaming experiences I have had in some time.

This is classic 3D platforming done in a way to appeal to gamers as young as 5 or as old as time.  Yes the control is simple and more experienced gamers will not be exceptionally challenged by the gameplay but few other games will get you laughing or feeling as good as The Munchables does.  The biggest challenge comes from figuring out how to beat some of the bosses which can take some trial and error.

In the main game you earn bonus items to decorate your character with 3D glasses, pirate hats, etc. by collecting acorns.  Once the game is beaten, you earn a radar upgrade that points out acorns you missed on your first go round.  This is a feature more platform games should incorporate.  Another feature that opens once the main story has been completed is Mirror Mode which has you go through each level in reverse under a time constraint which is actually pretty tough to complete in later levels.

Bottom line, do not dismiss The Munchables.  It may look easy and childish perhaps it even is, but by not playing The Munchables you miss out on a uniquely fun experience that you will remember long after the controller is put down.

text:
Weak sauce... maybe 56 screws hang on at a time. I am a pro, and bought this to speed things up like hanging fence boards.
It would be sweet if it included a STRONG magnet; but it does not.

It would be sweet if the magnet wrapped all the way around your wrist, so it works ANYWHERE; but it does not.

It only works in a narrow area, maybe half of the wrist band; not all the way around where you "cannot miss," instead, you have to aim for the hidden weak magnets.

If this were done and built right, it would be 5 star, to me. But as is, meh, 12 stars. have not used it since the first try, for 15 minutes, and had too pick up half my screws off the ground.

It may be useful for a crafts person, or someone needing to keep up with tiny screws etc., but this just does not have the holding power, or useable area that would make me a satisfied customer.

12 stars from a professional contractor. Your mileage may vary for the better with light duty tasks.
summary: Pro- contractor: too weak for my needs.

text:
If you play a classical guitar or an acoustic with nylon strings, you play because you love the tone and the fact that the nylon is easier on the finger tips.  Once in a while, more volume is needed.  That means using a microphone or a pickup.  There are pickups everywhere, but not so many that will work well with nylon strings.  The Docooler is one that will.  Pickups are often tricky to install.  For some, you even have to restring the guitar or even drill a hole in your guitar.  Not with the Docooler pickup.  It can be inserted and removed with ease in moment without marring the finish on your guitar.  This pickup was actually shipped to me FROM CHINA.  I thought I would have to wait for the proverbial "SLOW BOAT", but delivery was made in about 6 days.  Money well spent.

If you are a guitarist with a Hard Rock or Metal band, this is not what you are looking for.  If you play real classical guitar or acoustic and need an occasional volume boost, this is for you.
summary: For the money, a great buy

Overall I am impressed. My rig is a 25 Ft Attitude toy hauler. I bought it used and it had a mixed set of scissor jacks. One side took a hexagon type socket handle and the other used a different kind of handle that is very different. Also the amount of torque it took to crank each jack varied. It was unpleasant so I replaced all of them with this kit. The old jacks were secured on using much too small self tapping screws. These screw up and down smoothly, they are solidly built and the handle has a hinged socket that makes cranking more comfortable. The part that I did not like about these is the mounting screws that come with it. They are beefy lag bolts but are not self tapping so you have to drill your own holes and thread them in yourself. It is a bit of a challenge. I used a step drill and then threaded them in using a large ratchet and socket. They are secured solid and work great.

This bag arrives flat and is made so it pops up to form a storage bag; voila! The bag seems sturdy and will not cave in. It looks like denim on the outside and the inside is blue and white polka dots. It is very well made and the stitching all looks good. You can carry it by the attached handle or clip on the adjustable shoulder strap. The top zips together with a zipper on both sides so you do not have to use one zipper to go all the way around. The inside has no pockets wish it had at least one large one, but is roomy enough for quite a few skeins of yarn. There is a large pocket on the outside along with a few smaller ones where you could put crochet hooks or needles. The top has 2 slits for yarn to pass through without getting all tangled up I am really good at getting yarn tangled; ugh, and you could feasibly put 4 different colors through the slots each slot has a hole on each end if you are doing a project with different colored yarns.

This will now be my goto bag for my knitting/crocheting group. Right now I have 3 large skeins of yarn inside the bag along with my current crochet project. In the outside pockets I have some crochet hooks and accessories. I am really liking this bag and I am sure any knitter/crocheter would. My only suggestion might be to put in a few more pockets; I can never have enough of them.  Happy face smiley

Absolutely one of the best games I have ever played!  My wife and I play this game constantly.  Although it might seem complicated at first, the mechanics and rules are actually really simple and intuitive.  After one play, we were very comfortable with developing different strategies.  There is really no luck involved in this game  everything is based on your decisions, so if you are into games where you can strictly try to outplay your opponent, this is the game for you.  There are a lot of characters/factions to choose from and each seems to be pretty balanced with what they bring to the table, so replayability is very high.

The artwork is fantastic, and the pieces are very wellmade.  I really appreciate the fact that they seemed to go out of their way to make the artwork great even the back of the game board is beautifully decorated.

This is another game that comes with a LOT of pieces.  I built some trays out of foam core to hold everything and it makes set up and clean up much less of a hassle.

If you are a casual gamer, this one might seem more complicated and involved than other workerplacement games, but it is still really fun and definitely worth the time to learn and play.

Other than the darkness that comes with the 1880's London streets, I found this Sherlock Holmes movie excellent.  Its the first version I have seen of the Jack The Ripper case, where the movie does not depend on reenacting the grisly murders. Instead of getting caught up and distracted by visual scenes of blood and violence, you are allowed to focus on the way in which an intelligent investigator applies his knowledge and logic to connect the clues and unravel the scroll of mystery.

The acting might be somewhat dry by American standards, but that could be a plus. Without the hollywood tricks to entice the senses, the descriptive english language of the period gives the story so much intelligence and truthfulness.

Murder By Decree is truly a thinking persons movie that requires attention, as well as reasoning, in order to follow the methods of Sherlock Holmes and Dr. Watson. Christopher Plummer and James Mason make a very fun pair to travel through London with.

Sherlock Holmes indictment of a political leader's allegiance to party over humanity:

"you create allegiance above your sworn allegiance to humanity. You will not feel for them or acknowledge their pain. There lies the madness."

This is just divine. I love every single I Coloniali product I ever tried. I find their mango shaving soap and rhubarb shaving cream to be very close or even on par with Acqua di Parma, which for me is the best shaving cream in existence, not just in terms of performance but also the scent and packaging, I love the rhubarb after shave balm but this hibiscus shaving cream, I believe it has no equal and I have tried a number of highend shower products. The cream has a consistency that is hard to describe but is just right, foams easily, washes off easily, leaves the skin supple and soft and with a scent so delicious that I keep smelling myself for hours after the shower, it is just gorgeous beyond description. I also love the bamboo and rhubarb scents, respectively, they are just as good and some people might actually prefer one or the other to hibiscus, but for my taste hibiscus is sheer perfection when it comes to fragrance. By the way, I do not really know what hibiscus smells like, this definitely smells nothing like hibiscus tea, which was the only hibiscus scent I ever had a chance to try but it is a classy, elegant fragrance that just makes you appreciate life. Taking the morning shower with this baby is the perfect way to start the day.
summary: This product makes you love life first thing in the morning.

This this is very heavy, but you are not buying an otter box if you are looking for streamlined good looks and lightweight materials, they are designed for serious use, and can take drops no electronic device should expect to survive. I have only had my iPad a week and it has already flown off my dash, hitting my shifter, then slamming to my truck floor. Good thing I have an otter box.

My main complaint is the 3 viewing angles need a fourth. You can only have the iPad vertically in the portrait orientation, if you try to use it vertically in the landscape orientation you have to put it in crooked and prop up one of the legs. It is a minor discomfort that means if you want to set your iPad up like a tv to watch at a standard viewing height, you have to do some propping.

The other reason they did not get four stars for this product is the fact that the screen protector is utterly useless. Until you design something better otter box, why give the consumer just another piece of plastic to throw away. That being said, the built in screen protector rips right out. I got the zagg shield, which is way better, but it is sticky, I just hate screen protectors in general.

The case is easy to put on if you are familiar with otter box, this is my third case of theirs so I did not have any trouble.
summary: Could use a vertical landscape viewing angle.

text:
This delightful book combines history with a travel narrative. Captain Cook made three Pacific voyages between 1768 and 1780 to every part of the Pacific, discovering countless lands, bolstering British claims of sovereignty, and creating maps of surprising accuracy. Horwitz, with his alcoholseeking sidekick and travel companion Roger Williamson,  retraces Cook's voyages, relying mainly on air travel, and inquires how Cook is regarded in historical hindsight in the various places he explored. Obviously the indigenous peoples of the Pacific view him negatively, and Horwitz examines both the proCook and the antiCook perspectives.

Areas visited by the author include Tahiti, New Zealand, eastern Australia, Niue, Tonga, and Hawaii, as well as Yorkshire and London in England. My favorite part was Horwitz's account of his visit to the Aleutian Islands of Alaska, where yearround storms make travel dangerous even in large modern ships. One marvels that an 18th century explorer in a primitive wooden vessel would make a similar voyage, knowing that even if all went well, it would still take a year to return to England.

The book was a bit overlong in places. In some instances, I felt I was reliving Horwitz's travel experiences in real time. But all things considered, this is a wonderful interweaving of history and travelogue.
summary: Wonderful synthesis of travelogue and history

text:
I purchased these headphones thinking that they were inexpensive and could come in handy. Well, you get what you pay for!

The sound quality is decent. There is just one teency tincy little problem. The left and right channels are swapped and there is NO WAY to fix it, at least while paired to a Windows 10 PC. The driver does not have an option to swap L/R. There are no button combinations that do this, either.

The only "fix" is to take the earpieces off and swap them, so that the cords come off the top of your ear and rap around, placing the reciever on the back of your ear where, of course, the microphone is completely useless. This is not a comfortable fix, to say the least.

Maybe I just got a bad copy? Regardless, I will not be making the same mistake again.

This software is very easy to install and operate.  Within 2 minutes of being installed it located a Trojan threat that my MacAfee had not found on the system.

The tutorial tour is quick and covers the basic task performed by the program. I installed this software first on my sons problematic computer. It quickly fixed pop ups, and eliminated viruses that he had picked up on the internet.

After a complete scan and restoration, I performed the Norton security backup procedure.  It was easy to create my storage cloud, and I have the relief in knowing that it is protected by Norton.

I also noticed that Norton scans all the links on my Facebook wall to protect against viruses on active links.
summary: Norton has cleared up the most problematic PC we own.

text:
I have been a Spyro fan since the 80's, and have nearly every CD, except the compilations. This is a very welcome mix of
styles from the band, and everyone seems to be in top playing form, despite all the years that have passed. I would give this review
five stars had it not been for the recording quality. In most cases Spyro Gyra recordings have been pretty clean, with levels set
accurately and an overall great sound. However this particular recording, in a new venue, with new engineers....definitely has
something to be desired. Trust me.....I am not an audiophile snob, but I do have a pretty nice set up. I think I am able to tell when
the problem is not with me or my system .  In this case I actually tried to make adjustments to render the sound more accurately.
  Overall the engineering is not bad, but for some reason Jay Beckenstein's sax seems levelled way to high, and when the entire
band is jamming at full strength.... the sound is just, well....distorted. It is a bit fuzzy and not well defined. And with today's excellent
recording equipment, etc.  there is just no reason that should be the case.  I guess it is a bit more evident on headphones that it
is through speakers, but it is evident none the less.  So, bottom line for me is, the music is just fine.....but the recording could use
some fine tuning. But certainly do not let that stop you from enjoying new stuff from one of the longest lasting "smooth jazz / pop
jazz" bands to ever exsist.

The front socket the side you plug you device to/ on the front of the unit is a bit tight. Also a few times I got sparks when plugging in devices. Not terrible the sparks were not across the lines but were due to the difficulty of plugging anything into the socket. On the flip side, if you plugged this into a device for long term power measurement, that tightness is great. I was testing Christmas lights.

When I was using this as a multimeter I found that I liked using it with an extension cord because I could not unplug the device without ripping the P3 off the wall.

Overall  a handy little product for measuring you AC connected devices.

I have been listening to both Love is Hell Pts 1 and 2 since they came out but have hesitated until now to read listener reviews. As much as Ryan gets slammed I did not feel like getting PO'd with negative reviews. Man I am happy I was worried for nothing. What I have been reading here for the most part is a real love fest and I would like to throw my 2 cents worth in.
Ryan's usually pulling more critics in the "slam" wagon than the "band" wagon and I cannot figure it out. Its not like he is the only artist I listen to and my musical tastes are all over the map. I must be missing something.
Ryan has a talent possessed by a small group of artists past on Elliott Smith and present Lucinda Williams who can write about the real side of humanity, put the words to some great chord changes and beautiful melodies, and make you feel good.
In Love is Hell Pt 1 and 2, he continues to demonstrate the talent for making great songs. If you pick one up, pick both of them up, for together they make one of the best albums to come out in 2003.

This is the most powerful handheld vacuum I have ever seen. It runs circles around the competition. And like the rest of the Dyson line, it maintains a strong suction even as the chamber fills up. It is pretty expensive, but it is so much better than anything else I have seen out there, I think you get what you pay for.

I know other reviewers have complained about the 6 minute runtime, but I do not think it is that big of a deal. It seems to run at full power right up until the battery goes dead. And if you need to use it for more than 6 minutes on a single charge, you probably should be using a fullsize vacuum instead.

My only complaint is that I cannot use attachments from my upright Dyson DC14 Animal. They are so close in size  they are just a few millimeters difference in diameter  that it would have made sense to just make them interchangeable. That is the ONLY reason I am not giving it the full 5 stars.
summary: Unbelievable power; I wish attachments were compatible with my Dyson upright

This film is one of my personal new 'classics' of horror, although it is also a scifi film. The plot centers around a small group of 'mutants,' long before the 'XMen' made them cool, who have the unique ability to scan the thought patterns of others, thus knowing what people are thinking. However, as always, not all mutants play nice, as actor, Michael Ironside, has a great role as the demented Revok, who likes to scan people's minds just a bit too long, leading one to lose one's head, as in the infamous exploding head scene! Revok leads his bands of rebel mutuants against the establishment, and only another Scanner with equal ability can stand in his way. Even though this film is dated somewhat and campy in parts, it is definitely entriguing and fans of grossout effects will eat this film up!

I have recently repainted the majority of my house and, like I have done in the past, I went straight for the blue tape.  I have been a Scotch man most my life adult life that is and I am usually loyal unless I have been burned.  Well, with this hefty project underway I decided to try my hand at the new Edge Lock Blue Tape, feeling confident that it will do what it promises.  In the past, using the standard Blue tape, I have never had a problem with bleeding occasional, but nothing drastic and so I trusted that this new breed would be better than the last.  Sadly, it was worse.  For a tape that promises edge lock protection, I have NEVER in my life had so much bleed through.  The tape's adhesive was not up to par and the big reveal felt overshadowed by the noticeable bleeding.  I was outraged, to put it lightly.  All my hard work felt ruined by this pack of lies.  If the product had been a carbon copy of the previous, that would have been a letdown but nothing detrimental.  The fact remains that this product is WORSE than the one that came before it.  Stay far away from this tape.  Not only is it of poor quality, but it costs more than the standard Blue Tape, which works far better.

This was one of the games I got for Christmas when I got my own Nintendo System.  Yup, I was spoiled then... I even got R.O.B. with the package!  But we also got this game and a few others so needless to say, I played Nintendo games for the rest of my Christmas vacation and this was one of the games that dominated the machine.

You can play 1 vs. 1 or fight all the way up to meet "The Great Puma" in this one.  How scarey is it that I remember!I used to play as either 'Amazon', a wrestler that had two special moves  chomping on the face of his opponent and... I forgot the other, but he used to look at the referre when told to stop and shake his head, promising not to do it again.  I also used to wrestle as Starman because he used to fly off the top ropes and his rope work was always pretty entertaining, although if you missed it was bad news for him.  There were others too that I liked but those were the main ones.  The game was a bit easy to finish once you figured out the 'secret'.  But it still provided loads of fun.

I still recommend it.  It is a very simple, neat, classic Nintendo game that provided lots of fun.  There was not any blood or gore in it like the wrestling games of today and you could not whack people with chairs, etc... this was an old 1980's game, for better or worse, and it is one that me and my family enjoyed.

text:
By this point, the instrumentalists had gelled into a tight unit, what little looseness may have been found on "The Real Thing" is gone, but most importantly, vocalist Mike Patton is clearly integrated into the band and is obviously more comfortable, both with himself and the material I suspect.  The result is stunning Patton delivers vocals of endless diversity, everything from straighforward rock singing, screaming, rapping, crooning, and even some of the vocalizations that became much more prevelent on his later work.

The material on "Angel Dust" moves through a number of moods, and is at its best when its at its most experimental take standout track "RV", a song from the point of view of a middleaged white trash father, spoken word vocals alternating with extraorindary singing over a countryish jazz sound, or "Small and Smaller", which pulls you in with its grunting bass and brilliant vocalizations and really is the sort of melodrama the band excels at.

Admittedly, there is quite a bit of straightforward material, but much of it is of consistently high quality "Land of Sunshine", the haunting "Midlife Crisis", "Everything's Ruined".  In fact, what little is uninteresting is always saved by either great bass work "Kindergarten", vocals "Caffeine", or outside guitar noise "Malpractice".

Granted, there is a couple misses "Be Aggressive", with its cheerleader vocals sounds like a better idea on paper than it is on record and "Jizzlobber" is kind of a mess although still fairly enjoyable, but all in all, this is a great album.  Recommended.

text: I know I could get punched for saying this, but I like this CD even better than their first one Shake Your Money Maker but yes, I love that one also.  Being a guitarist, I love the guitar work on By Your Side. The guitar riffs by Rich Robinson are catchy and heavy throughout the CD.  Chris sounds fantastic and enthusiastic.  There is scarcely a dud on the entire CD.  The feel of the CD is very upbeat and optimistic.  There are radiofriendly songs such as Kicking My Heart Around, Go Faster and a couple others, but there are also great songs that you would probably never hear on the radio.  Some hot spots for me include Go Tell the Congregation, By Your Side, Then She Said My Name, Virtue  Vice, Heavy.  If you like rock  roll, I do not see what you would not like about this CD.  Great music for a party or for when you just feel good and want to jam.  I think this is their most underrated CD.  Buy it.

text:
I am far from skinny, however, I really like to dance! My friend from work told me about this game, and after I researched it, I decided to buy it. So far...so good! I am loving Just Dance 2! It is a pretty good workout too, which is what I mostly do it for. I usually play the Just Sweat feature, which is nice because you can start with 1 song, or do 3, or dance to 6, which is what I usually do.

As much I love this game, I have two "negative" comments about it. First, sometimes the Wii remote does not pick up all of my moves even though I am doing them exactly. Second, some of the songs are a little random and not really fun to dance to. Like I said, I use this game mostly for a workout, so my opinion is coming from that sense. I like upbeat songs where I can move fast for exercise, and although I wish Just Dance 2 had more upbeat songs, I have to remember not everyone is doing this to workout like I am. If that is the case, you will definitely have fun just dancing by yourself or with your friends.

You cannot really go wrong with this dance game. If you like to dance for fun or a workout this game is for you!

This is a very good, generalist office type color laser printer. It does very well with business graphics. Manual feed is a tiny bit tricky but not bad. Install is easy if you know how to install a WPS printer on your network. Note that Apple routers have no button and you will need to look through the menus to find the "connect to WPS printer" option. it does not do well with photographs but illustrations in documents look very good. The glossy paper you can get for this is really only 32lb even though they say 80lb  apparently different kinds of paper is rated differently but it tends to be double sided. It is thick enough to look good but do not count on printing card stock. Card stock tops out at 43lb and that is hard to find.

3/14/17 Having cycled through a set of toner cartridges, a couple of things have cropped up which are quite annoying. First, the printer has the habit of suddenly stopping accepting jobs for no apparent reason, though it could be related to being low but not out of one of the toner cartridges. This usually results in 20 minutes of fiddling and power cycles before the printer decides to start working. Second Brother tech support has been totally ineffective at offering any reason for this. They seldom actually read my questions and typically respond after days or even weeks with canned responses that do not address the issues. So you might want to avoid this printer based on this mysterious failure mode and the lack of a good tech support system.
summary: Great for a low cost Color Laser Printer, best for business graphics and text

We have RES turtles, and they LOVE these!!!

I want to give 5 stars, I really do.  The boys even know the sound this bottle makes when you pick it up and the plankton rattle against the sides.  They come zooming across their tanks, frantically jumping up and down, waving their arms, begging like you would not believe a turtle can!

I had to remove 1 star because the plankton lose their color and become virtually invisible after a minute or two.  They are wasted when this happens because the turtles cannot find them.  They end up clogging the filter or stuck on the bottom, creating a slightly fishy smell in the tank until the water is changed.  That is quite a hassle!!

Another issue is that the quantity is NOT as advertized.  I would only fed 1/3 of the plankton to the boys when I reached the powder.  I do not know if the plankton itself is so delicate it disintegrated into powder due to rough handling or if the powdered plankton was included intentionally, but it cannot be used.  All it would do is ruin the tanks if I put it in the water; the boys cannot possibly chase down and eat each grain.  Since 2/3 of this was garbage, 2 more stars were lost.
summary: Does not contain as much as you think

Overall I am happy with this. It does slow down my computer but not as much as other antivirus software I have used. As someone else noted, I had hoped to use this on a second computer that has yet to be purchased. Unfortunately, you only have 30 days to install this for a second or third user  something that should be clearer to consumers. My biggest issue has to do with tweaking some of the settings. I access my office server via my personal laptop using the Kaspersky and cannot find a way to avoid the repeated warnings every time I need to retrieve a document. I am pretty computer savvy and have yet to find a way to make my work server a trusted source to avoid this, which slows down my work productivity. Same thing applies to my digital camera card. It is annoying to have to go through extra steps for every individual photo I want to transfer to my computer. Again, if there is a way to disable this for selected sources, I have yet to find it. Does not mean it is not there, just that is it is not obvious or user friendly.
But it does give me peace of mind, which is what it is supposed to do. I just wish that there were more settings options when it comes to trusted sources.
summary: Good overall product, could be more user friendly.

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

I have been using KAL brand stevia powder for years and I love it. Since my bottle was getting low, I decided to go on Amazon and order more. But before doing so, I decided to read some of the reviews and saw that the ingredients had been changed and many people said it tasted bad. So instead of  the KAL brand, I ordered SweetLeaf Stevia Extract Powder. BIG MISTAKE!!! The little .9 oz bottle says that it has 1000 servings in it, so I figured I only needed less than half of the tiny spoon that came in the KAL brand the Sweetleaf Powder did not come with a measuring spoon, but instead said that a serving size was 1/80 teaspoon. How on earth can you measure that? Anyway, 1/2 of the tiny spoon did not sweeten my coffee in the least. For the next cup, I used a full tiny spoonful. It still it did not taste sweet to me, but I decided not to add more as I was afraid I would make the coffee bitter. The coffee was drinkable, but afterwards I had a bad taste in my mouth. I would not buy this brand again! So once again I am back to my search for the best tasting stevia powder. I have already tried more brands then I can even remember and only KAL has ever met my approval.
summary: Not sweet at all, and it left a bad aftertaste in my mouth
