The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

I have used the 2010 and 2011 versions of McAfee's security suites and was not impressed; bogged down the systems after awhile.  My Norton 360 had just expired on my home PCs  a Dell Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberryS with Windows 7 in my study, and a Dell 8400 running Windows Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry in the guest room so I gave this McAfee LiveSafe a try.  Installation was straightforward using the code inside the package to download from the McAfee site.  Took about 15 minutes for installation.  Setup was simple and McAfee runs unobtrusively in the background.  Also installed on my HTC One Android phone easily.  No problems so far after two months.  My only concern is that after each Windows automatic update, the PCs slow down a bit but NOT solely due to McAfee; that happens with all brands of security suites after Windows updates.  Removing temporary files and defragmenting improves speeds a bit.  This McAfee free trial is for one year so I will consider renewal if the price is reasonable.
summary: Improvement over previous McAfee security suites.

text:
The singleplayer campaign is so much more cinematic this time around, and the bosses add a nice touch to the pacing of the game.

The scale is incredible, not only in the setting, but also the bosses and enemies.

I have played a few hours of multiplayer so far I will probably log a few hundred hours into this one, as I did with the first.. I have only played competitive. I will play cooperative at a later time.

If you are a firstperson shooter fan, I definitely recommend it. Insomniac delivers again.

I have come to adore the writing of Nora Ephron since I read
her book, "Heartburn" years ago.  I do not know how she does it
but she is sustainably funny from novel to collection of
essays on a multitude of topics to her book, entitled, "I feel
Bad About My Neck," which most women could relate to. In "I Remember
Nothing and other reflections," she very aptly tackles the topic
of aging and getting older in ways that you might not I did not
have thought of reflecting upon in her unique style. Good for a bedtime
read without having something electronic on your chest. Light and funny.

Sybil BlazejYee
Librarian/Children's Book Author/Artist/Dog Walker

Author of
The Honey Boy Story c2009
Beagle Boy Watson c2010
Leroy Goes To The Olympics c2011
summary: "I remember nothing" is memorable and funny!

text:
This is a story about Love, forgiveness and coming of age.

Moojie starts his life in an orphanage and is adopted by his mother and father. But his mother dies in a freak accident leaving Moojie and his father alone. Father does not accept the boy because Moojie does not talk or walk like a normal child. His father leaves him to live at St. Isadore's Fainting Goat Dairy. There Moojie befriends a group of "LightEaters" that teach him about life".

This is an excellent first book by Robin Gregory. The characters and imagery come to life on the page. And I felt like I was there besides Moojie with all his problems. I would recommend this book to everyone.

I won this book in a LibraryThing member giveaway.
summary: A Book of Life, Love, and Frogiveness

text: This card is great for ESXi. If a person wanted to they can pass each individual port through to a different VM as this card uses a PLX PCI Express bridge to give dedicated PCIe lanes to each controller. There are two USB3 1042a controllers Which may need to be downgraded to a lower level firmware as ESXi represents the PCI Device IDs incorrectly, and two Marvell storage controllers which I have not messed with much.
summary: Great card for ESXi Passthrough to Individual VMs!

Needed something in the car that could charge my iPhone and the wife's Droid Razr at the same time. This item arrived super quickly and I was pleasantly surprised to see that they included a USBtomicro USB cable in the box.

The charger fit snugly and securely into my Subaru Forester's charging port the Powergen charger of the same type was very loose and floppy in the socket. The charger glows a cool blue when activated.

Hooked up my iPhone to the 2.1 amp port and the wife's Razr to the 1 amp port with the included cable.  iPhone charged great. Nothing happened with the Razr. As it turns out and from reading other reviews, the included cable is very low powered and will not charge certain smartphones.  No biggie to us since we had our own cables anyway, but they should have been more clear about this in the documentation to avoid confusion. Charger works great with both the OEM Motorola cable and also a cheap Mediabridge cable I got on Amazon. We get quick power for two devices.

So works great for two heavy smartphone users who are on the go often. Just do not count on the included cable to charge everything.

I guess I am more a Western saw person in that I like a push saw because the sawdust does not interfere with the marking gauge line.  I am getting  used to this one which is incredibly sharp and cuts very well and gives a nice thin kerf.  It is not a high dollar saw but certainly works as well as one that a friend owns.  It is slightly short but for joinery, it is plenty long enough.  The handle is plastic and has a turn knob to exchange blades.  However, it does not do any good because the packaging was all Japanese and you do not have any idea how to get a new blade.  Fortunately, they are inexpensive enough that I will probably get a new one to wait in the wings.  So far, I have made about 1015 hardwood dovetail boxes with it and have not lost a tooth or seen any dulling yet.

Edit as of a couple months after purchase :  I keep track and have now cut dovetails on 24 boxes with this saw and I have no desire for anything else.  I have used it on several hardwoods of different thicknesses and have not lost a tooth yet.  I am very pleased at how it has not lost any sharpness from the day I got it.  One of those rare cases where inexpense is not a comprimise.

text:
Even if you are upgrading from Windows Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry, it makes very little sense to buy this.  If you are upgrading from Windows Tongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry you can buy a new computer that is 20 to 50 times faster than your old computer and has enough memory at least 4GB to run newer programs more efficiently for 300 to 600 dollars.  You get Windows 8 included!

If you are upgrading from Windows 7, you actually lose the functionality of Windows Media Center since it is not included in Windows 8.  You would have to buy Windows 8 Pro Pack for another 89 dollars to get that functionality.

Since Windows 8.1 will address the Start Menu fiasco and will make keyboard and mouse navigation a little bit easier, you could buy this.  I would wait for the Black Friday and Christmas season for specials on Windows 8.1.  There will also probably be promotions after Windows 8.1's release around October 17th.

I do not recommend Windows 8 or 8.1 as an upgrade until Windows Media Center is included as part of the system.  I run two home entertainment computers and without Windows Media Center, they are useless.  Since you are actually losing functionality if you upgrade to Windows 8 from Windows 7, the only real benefit is an "arguably" slightly faster operating system and a few stray benefits such as Skydrive.  The tiled look is fine for phones and tablets, but you want productivity and an operating system built for a pc, not one built for a tablet or phone.
summary: It makes no sense to buy this unless you are upgrading from Windows XP

text: D'Addario strings are awesome!  These strings speak with a bold,defined and POWERFUL voice.  The bass strings boom with thunderous lows and the treble strings glisten with sparkling highs without being too harsh.  They are very sweet to the ears and tonally balanced across the board without one frequency overpowering the other. I have tried a lot of different strings, DR's, Ernie Ball, Dean Markley, Elixir, GHS, you name it.  After putting a set of EXL110's 1046 gauge on my Gibson SG special faded and comparing them to Ernie Ball I noticed a huge difference, not only were they brighter but they lasted longer.  I used to change a set of Regular Slinkys every two months but with EXL's I was changing strings every five to six months. They work in a variety of applications, metal, hard rock, jazz, blues, reggae, etc. and respond great at any dynamic level.  D'Addario is "The Player's Choice" for a reason after using these I cannot see myself using anything else!  They feel good,sound great and are exceptionally consistent from set to set. If you have not used them yet, give them a try and see what you are missing.
summary: D'Addario is the way to go!

I ordered one of these earlier in 2011 from the companies actual website and was pleased with what we got and how fast it came. We put it on our metal hammock stand that sits half the day in the shade and half of it in the sun. It was comfortable to sit in and it supported really well.
About a month or less after having it the color was significantly faded. This was a little disappointing because I really liked the initial color. I know sun can fade things but this was dang fast. I made a sleeve to go on the hammock to help with the elements when we were not on it. It did help it not fade anymore and kept it pretty dry when it rained.
About 2 1/2 months after we bought it our 9 year old went to sit on it and the strings on one side snapped. He does not weigh more than 90 pounds and this hammock is rated for 500 lbs. There is no way this should have happened. When I contacted the seller Rada Hammocks via email I received no response what so ever.
I would not recommend buying anything from this company. I understand things like this will eventually wear down but it should not happen in 3 months during the summer with hardly any rain. I should not have to put it up and take it down after each and every use. This would just be annoying.
The only reason I give them two stars instead of one is because I did initially like the hammock until it feel apart.

The Highlander by Zoe Saadia is a comingofage novel detailing the relationship between two young men whose friendly rivalry develops into a competition reflecting that of their own nations. Kuini and Nezahuacoyotl meet each other in the wilderness and are fascinated in the ensuing exchange in culture. The Highlands are an alien world to the Lowlanders, and both communities have engaged in warfare against each other throughout their recorded history. Only when Coyotls sister Iztac is given to an Aztec ruler, it is done in the interests of peace although neither he nor Kuini can accept her fate. The two young warriors unite in a common goal that may affect the future of both nations entire.

Once again the author draws from her rich knowledge of Azteca history and folklore in providing an authentic and compelling backdrop to the narrative. Yet we find deeper issues being discussed, the foremost of which is womens rights and the freedom of choice. Iztac represents hundreds of millions of women to the present day forced into arrangements of convenience. We see both her halfbrother and her soulmate joined in a common goal to change her fate regardless of the impact upon their society and its mores. Saadia sees fit to explore the longterm effects of this decision, and that is what sequels are for.

The Highlander by Zoe Saadia is an inspirational and entertaining tale of romance and social change amidst one of historys most fabled societies. Pick up a copy and you will not be disappointed.

I will try not to repeat all the negative comments of which I generally agree.  Office 2007 is not intuitive. If it was, Microsoft would not have gone to the great lengths it has to show users how to find the functions they are looking for  see their website.  I was forced to convert from 2003, which had its deficits but it was intuitive and it worked most of the time.

An example of problems with Word 2007: I have a simple table for printing file folder labels. When I tried to navigate around or select items text, rows, columns, etc., only the keyboard works, NOT THE MOUSE!  I spent an hour researching the problem and could not find a solution, only confirmation that you have to use the keyboard working on a table. Also the table now prints unwanted gridlines. Again I have spent far too long without success to prevent them from printing, changing a number of settings to no avail.

Word 2007 is the only program I have tried so far, but I dread trying to use the "new" Excel or Outlook.  I anticipate the learning curve will be huge. So far I see NO advantage to Office 2007.  If you are using 2003, do not change!!! I see nothing to gain and a lot to lose.
summary: Thank Goodness Microsoft Doesn't Design Anything Important Like Planes or Cars!

This is a great game, the story reminds me of something Hollywood would come up with such as treasure in a jungle, well armed locals trying to stop you, and a sidekick reporter. The graphics are topnotch for an early PS3 title and the controls are intuitive. Since this is an "Indiana Jones"esque title, there are, of course, puzzles and traps. The health meter is also inventive in that you do not have one, the screen slowly fades to black and white as you take damage. Many of the trophies are easily obtained since the majority are acquired through weapon usage and finding treasures. Now for the bad stuff. In the beginning, the difficulty is balanced. At about halfway through the game, it jumps when the enemies have unlimited ammo and the ability to cause head shots from very far away. This can be a problem when you are being swarmed. Also, many of the later puzzles can become needlessly difficult due to the camera, but once you figure them out you can easily finish them. Overall, this is a great game with some very frustrating as in hurl your controller against the wall moments.
summary: Who Wouldn't Want to Scour Ruins for Lost Treasure...and Pirates?

This was a really good story. The Stafford brothers are some HOT men. Whew! Greg the heart throb, local TV star, is the son who is struggling the most. He just does not know it. His heart and pride were severely broken, and he has decided to get back at the one who left his heart tattered and filled with scars. So, how does he do that? By becoming a complete manwhore and sexxing every female he finds attractive. But, then he finds himself on the front page and the cover story that he normally reports.  He has shamed himself, placed his job in jeopardy, and becomes isolated by his family. Forced to comply with mandatory counseling, he meets the sexy Sex therapist, Rhani who rocks his world.

This is a story of forgiveness; forgiving others and yourself. Second chances. Love and starting over. I thoroughly enjoyed this story. I really liked catching up with the entire family, and getting a status update on the brothers and their families. I was surprised by the outcome. But I love that even when all hope looks lostfaith, love, and family will help you see the rainbow of new possibilities.

I purchased 3 different sizes in this slipper after reading reviews and not sure if they would be too big or too small. I would consider myself a 8.5/9 in my regular shoe size. I purchased a 39, 40, and 41 and never plan on wearing socks with these slippers. The 39 was definitely too small and could easily check that off my list. The 41 felt slightly too big, but maybe could work?? I was worried that if they stretched at all they would be annoying and hard to keep on my feet. The 40 initially felt a wee too snug in the back. I felt the back of my heel rubbing against the stitching and frankly did not know what to do. I continued to read more reviews and many people seemed to face the same problem and all said that after wearing the slipper over 24 hours the slipper stretched slightly and molded to their foot. Well, I made the decision and picked the 40. I wore them around the house, and sure enough, within an hour or so the rubbing went away and my foot fit perfectly in the slipper. They are now hands down the best slippers I have ever worn.

I have only ever worn shearlinglined slippers in the past and was super skeptical about these being able to keep my feet warm. However, my heel would always weardown the shearling after a year and they would become uncomfortable to walk on.  I have tried Ugg, Cabela's, LLBean  all the same. These keep my feet soooo warm! I think better than shearling. I also like the foot support these slipper give and the rubbersoled bottoms are going to last a long time. I highly recommend these slippers!
summary: After trying 3 different sizes, I still think these are the best slippers I have ever owned!

text: You get what you pay for. First, if it is really capable of 350 GPH as advertised, you should be able to fill a 5 gallon pail in less than a minute. Based on my very unscientific test, it looks more like 200250 GPH. Secondly, the bottom "foot" that contains the filter pad attaches to the pump body by pushing it on, i.e., it is just a friction fit, and it sometimes falls off when you disturb the pump. On the plus side, the 25' cord is a nice feature. I use a very simple trick to to keep it pumping when the water is full of debris like rotting leaves which otherwise would quickly clog the filter pad. I place the pump in the pouch of my leaf rake and use the long pole handle to place the pump wherever I want it. The leaf rake pouch, which resembles a bag made of fiberglas window screen acts as a prefilter and is very effective. If you are not in a rush, just run the pump long enough to establish a syphon and pull the plug. It drains at a rather slow rate, but who cares? Next morning the job is done.
Excellent product. Seller 100 responsible.

For anyone who is not familiar with Genesis' early stuff... this CD is a must have.  To hear Peter Gabriel's heartwrenching, soulful sound is quite extraordinary.  No Genesis library is complete without their early stuff and Trespass is NO exception.  Only six songs on the CD, but each song is a treasure.

You could hear even then, that they would be HUGE!  The talented artists who put together this album may not have all made it into Genesis' later recordings, but this one in my opinion, is a classic!

I still get shivers when I hear Peter opening on "Looking For Someone" and "Visions of Angels".  In my opinion, two of the prettiest melodies ever produced by Genesis.

I know this is the album that did it for me all those years ago... one listen and I was hooked.  A fan for LIFE!

text:
OK there are several approaches to what is a good... after playing mostly evans on toms and BD for the last 17 years, including the new 360s, I feel the need to make the case for Remo.

All my drumming years I have not found a better snare drum head than coated Ambassador... why is that? I thought it was my mind being used to or brought with that tone.

Remo is not as high tech... but man, they do sound great... a tone much less plasticky than other heads... the term "warm" is such a clich... but if there is a deserving piece of gear to give you a "warm" tone are these.

Recently "good" heads are those that any idiot can tune in 3 seconds...  But after using these in all toms tecently I have to say RESPECT.

I have all kinds of batter heads I use... Evans G2 clear and coated, Ec2, REMO vintage Emperor, Ambassador coated... all have their good qualities... this review is more geared towrads those in doubt and with a perception that these are obsolete or limited heads... it is a complete 180 from that.

These are the most versatile and musical heads there are...  Totally.
summary: inimitable sound... and in fairness, set the record straight

This 20 minute EP, cut on the cheap in 1987, contains some of the most legendary songs in the Pixies catalog.

Songs like Caribou, Vamos, Holiday Song, Nimrod's Son, Ed is Dead and Levitate Me all became Pixies concert staples and would belong on any Pixies "best of" compilation.

The amazing thing about this effort is how fully developed the Pixies sounded even at this young age.  All of the classic Pixies elements are present on Come On Pilgrim.  Black Francis' demented vocals about reincarnation, incest and whatever the hell else goes through that mind of his.  Kim Deal's outstanding bass playing and angelic backing vocals.  Joey Santiago's latin tinged surf rock guitar and David Lovering's versatile drumming.

If you want an idea of how incredible it is for a band to come out this strong on their first release, consider Radiohead's mediocre first album Pablo Honey or the Yeah Yeah Yeahs amateur sounding self titled first EP.

Packed with unforgettable songs, Come On Pilgrim is simply one of the most original and creative 20 minutes of indie rock that you will ever hear.
summary: One of the Greatest Debuts in Rock History

text:
Fantastic. I learned so much, about so many things, and was incredibly touched by the Lacks' story. I have not been able to get the family off my mind.

It also brought to mind some of my own medical history and samples I have given and realized that even thought I remember "good" informed consent practices, I now realize how little I understood to be signing away at the time. For the record, I would have still signed, but I believed at the time that I would be made aware if my sample ended up in a discovery in the course of their research. Lots to ponder here, and lots of modern, ongoing implications for society.
summary: We should all be educated about Ms. Lacks - for multiple reasons

text:
I am not much of a fan of the cottage industry known as Henry Rollins, inc., but "Weight" has to be the musclebound exBlack Flag singer's best work after Black Flag, of course.

What makes this Rollins Band album work so well is the players and their chemistry. The lineup has since changed, but this incarnation of the band is solid and absolutely powerful. The addition of bassist Melvin Gibbs gives the band a fluid, jazzy rhythm foundation that locks in well with Sim Cain's drumming, and Chris Haskett let us loose with some of his best guitar playing. Haskett is a tasteful player who utilizes space and minimal amounts of notes for maximum impact, ala David Gilmour, which I suppose would not be an altogether unfathomable comparison. The grooves that the band creates almost comes close to upstaging its namesake at times, but Rollins still has plenty to shout about. There are only a few weaker tracks here"Tired," "Step Back" and "Shine," which seems as if Rollins is preaching a bit too much in the latter. These tracks are weaker, lyrically, than what is expected from such a poetic lyricist as Rollins. Anger is the primary emotion Rollins is about in his lyrics, but he conveys it pretty well on "Weight." Songs like "Disconnect" and "Civilized" effectively communicate Rollins' anger and feelings of hatred toward those who have the misfortune of getting on his bad side.
summary: rollins' finest moment, post Black Flag

I rarely purchase shoes on the web unless I know the brand and the fit.

They fit perfectly.
I have no complaints and really enjoy these shoes and thank the people that let me know they ran wide...so I am passing this on too.

They have a wonderful brushed leather sole that is wonderful against bare feet.
I also noted my Doctor has a pair, so they must be comfortable for the amount of standing she does daily.

I did note they do not have a pronounced arch and have a negligible heel.  This means I do have to be careful wearing them too much, as I have issues with heel spurs if I do not have either enough arch or enough heel.
summary: They do run a bit wide

This book made me experience the following emotions: Sadness, anger, fear, and closer. The reason I felt all of these things is because I was closely connected to the Connolly family. The author really has a skilled talent for storytelling. Especially from a human aspect nature level.

Right from the moment I started reading to the last page I was hooked. Thus this made for a quick, easy read. I especially liked the way that the story went back in time at different periods in Jake's life. It gave me a better insight to just what type of person Jake is. Then there is the Connelly family. I like that they really bonded together and fought for Jake's honor even when the odds seemed against them. The subject matter of this book could have made this story depressing and dark but it was not. It was very wellwritten. I am looking forward to reading the next book by this author. In Finding Jake, I found me a new author.
summary: In Finding Jake, I found me a new author.

I ordered this part for a 2003 Chevrolet Tahoe as the original part failed when the fan continued to blow air when the car was shut off even when the key was not in the ignition.  I had to pull the cover off passenger side  2 7mm screws and unplug it so that it would not kill the battery.  I had originally ordered a more inexpensive part but it would not fit due to the fact that the 2003 Chevrolet Tahoe had dual automatic climate controls.  Amazon Prime shipping is the best and it is something that I highly recommend.  The part came in 2 days once I placed my order.  The original part had a 3 prong connector and the new part was not but the 3 wires in the Tahoe were the same color as the new part and so I had to cut the old connector off.  I then had to use a wire cutter to strip the 3 wires and I used 2 bunt connectors to connect the two larger wires.  I just used electrical tape to connect the smaller purple wires and then I taped all 3 wires together for additional support.  If I had some solder I would have used instead of the bunt connectors but the  black electrical tape worked just as well.
The part is working fine and Amazon does offer the best price for this item compared to my local parts store.
summary: Perfect fit for a 2003 Chevrolet Tahoe...with some minor cutting.

The Microsoft approach to business software continues to offer a vast array of options, of which the average user will only use 20.  Office accounting Professional is no exception.  There are a lot of great features here, and they are included in the price even if you never plan to use them.

The latest Accounting offering from Microsoft almost anything you would expect from Peachtree or a similar competitor.  Microsoft was late to this game, but they definitely did their homework.  All of your favorite functions and then some are there.

Some of the better functions also require monthly fees.  The integrated eBay and Paypal functions are excellent if you take your selling on eBay seriously.  They also cost pay ten dollars a month to take advantage of, which will take a chunk out of your sales.

The main problem with the software, however, is that all those features you are not going to use are still slowing down the user experience.  The program is big, bloated and slow, like anything from Microsoft.  While competitor programs are not exactly lightweights either, Accounting Professional just feels too slow for comfort, even on a fast computer.

The features, integration with the rest of Office and Windows, and the price may be attractive to many users.  The monthly fees, bloat, and a desire for a more mature product will turn others off. As with any software, try the demo and competitors' demos first.
summary: Lots of Features Flawed by Slow and Bloated Interface

Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

text: I have used many USB flash drives over the years and LOVE the retractable connection on this unit. Other models I own have the USB connection permanently extended and come with a cover that always gets lost. Then the flash drive picks up fuzz and other contaminants in my computer bag when traveling that ultimately end up in the USB connection on my computer when I use the drive leading to damage. By allowing me to retract the connection, Transcend has spoiled me forever and I will only buy this type of drive in the future. To use the drive you simple slide out the connector and plug it in. Once extended it locks into place until you want to put it away and then a slight pressure on the slide will allow you to retract the USB connector for storage. The 32gb size is perfect for today's dataintensive applications and provide enough space for me to carry all my files as well as a few movies and TV shows for the plane. Also, the flash drive is fast enough to play these shows right from the unit and does not require me to transfer them to my computer for viewing. Love the drive and will buy another one soon.

If you want a microscope that you will be able to focus, prepare your own slides, and actually enjoy, do not buy this one!  This is extremely cheaply made.  It looks great on the box and it comes with tons of little accessories some prepared slides, some empty slides, a box, a thing to squeeze liquid with, etcwhich is nice.  For small kids that just want to play and pretend more than actually see stuff, this is fine.  For my son, who is almost ten and loves science, this was very disappointing.  It was nearly impossible to focus on the slides that were included.  It was nothing more than a frustration for us.  After ten minutes of messing with it, we decided it was just going to take up space on the shelf.

I would not recommend this.  I gave it two stars only because I think it could be played with as a toy for kids that want to pretend to be a scientist, but if you want a real microscope that is easy to focus, spend some more money and buy something better!
summary: It is a toy, nothing more.

For years I had a large aluminum roasting pan which was really hard to clean. The handles make it easy to lift the food out of the pan. The lid can be used as a chafing dish. I have used it to cook the au jus from the prime rib on my stove top. The finish keeps things from absorbing into the pan which the aluminum one was famous for. This is a great roasting pan.

Who do we hate? Who do we support? Why do we support this Jonas? The only interesting part is the SPOILER ALERT when they leave this plot hole ridden society with this baby we are sympathetic to because he is not perfect. Very boring. Please, just pick up any other dystopian future book like ANTHEM by Rand Ayn or THE HUNGER GAMES by Suzanne Collins or ANIMAL FARM by George Orwell It uses animals as a metaphor towards real life political problems, which is convenient. Even though they are full of Republican ideas, they make you think harder than this boring attempt that does not deserve the hype Sorry, Lois Lowry, but it is true.

I have bought two of them so far, one for a journal, one for work stuff. After receiving them and being somewhat taken aback to by how nice it was for what it costs, I ended up buying less fancy notebooks for my daytoday scribbling, vowing to save these for something special  a project, or perhaps when I am ready to make time to journal regularly. Something I intend on archiving rather than something I intend to toss in a pile for a while, then throw out eventually.

The biggest deal, for me, is the blissful fact that it does not have the brand name and a bunch of worthless nonsense permanently emblazoned on the cover why are so many notebooks like that? ugh!, and how much less expensive it is than other notebooks that are this decent. The only area I am not raving about is the paper, not that there is anything wrong with it, it is a nice ivory color and pleasant to write on, it is just not thick decadent amazing paper. Not that I would expect that at this price! Just want to be clear, it is a perfectly serviceable notebook, and worthy of being archived, but I do not think I would use those mediumtipped disposable fountain pens I love in them or anything. Not on both sides anyway. Holds up fine to Pilot G2s in aqua, caramel, and burgundy, mostly.

text:
We bought the Nintendo DS Lite for our daughter for her 5th Birthday and she LOVED it!  I have found it to be great for her; we have bought her age appropriate games that she has enjoyed and have helped her with learning different things.

Our daughter was critically ill 3 months after her birthday and nearly died; when she did start recovering she had very limited use of her right arm and hand she is righthanded; but she was so determined to play her Hello Kitty game on the Nintendo that she started using her right hand to hold the stylus so she could play her game.  She did get frustrated because she could not grip it and kept dropping it but after a couple of days her strength in that arm got better and better and is now completely back to normal.  The nintendo definately helped with her recovery and the doctor said it was her version of physical therapy!
summary: BOUGHT FOR OUR 5 YEAR OLD --- HELPED HER RECOVER FROM CRITICAL ILLNESS

Now I installed new Valterra A010141VP antisiphon valves also from Amazon and they work much better than originals. No leaking,easy to install and remove as they are well made plastic. That equals no corrosion and no locking screw to rust onto your hose bib! Good Luck.

Josef Von Sternberg was in love with, and frustrated by, Marlene Dietrich. His obsession reached its apotheosis in "The Devil is a Woman". Miss Dietrich declared it her personal favorite of their 7 films together "I was at my most beautiful", and vehemently denied that the film was a reflection of their somewhat strange relationship. Since Miss Dietrich's passing, it has come to light that this film was a reflection of their relationship. Von Sternberg photographed this film himself, and Dietrich does look impossibly beautiful, like an evil goddess. Her costumes codesigned by Travis Banton and Dietrich are masterpieces of fantasy Hollywood/Spanish. The sets, lighting, photography, costuming, et al combine to make a glittering vision of a very sad and painful story. Von Sternberg announced that he and Miss Dietrich were to go their separate waystheir last few films, this one especially, did poorly at the box officethe Spanish government wanted this film DESTROYED! To call this film "exaggerated" is like calling opera "exaggerated". Oh course it is! This was not intended to be a documentary, or a "slice of life". However, under all of its baroque extravangance ,lies "The Awful Truth". I think all of us have either been in a similar situation, or know someone who has been in a similar situation. Maybe the individuals who disliked the movie could not admit that the film "touched a nerve"foreshadowing the critics' violent, horrified reactions to Hitchcock's "Psycho" 25 years later.

text:
Hackett has a serious problem and his therapist by the name of Loebner is not helping at all.  Hackett has told him again and again that his dream every night is always the same. Hackett dreams that a mysterious caller rings him up and tells him he has to drive to Cleveland. In his dream he gets dressed and goes out to his car where a briefcase is waiting for him on the passenger seat. He drives the briefcase to Cleveland and then drives back. Since the very real drive takes four hours to get there and four hours to get back it is exhausting.

Hackett needs help and Loebrer is not doing much to help him. Telling his dream over and over again is not doing any good. Something has to change.

This is one of those short stories where one thinks it is going to go one way and instead it goes in a far different direction. Once that is accomplished author Lawrence Block ups the ante by throwing in a couple of more twists. Cleveland in My Dreams is a fast and ultimately very funny read.

This short story ebook also includes Chapter One of the new book The Burglar Who Counted Spoons.

Material was picked up during the authors recent free read promotion for my use in an objective review.

Kevin R. Tipple 2013
summary: Hitting the road in "Cleevland In My Dreams" by Lawrence Block

The  case is firmly snapped together around the phone but can be opened very easily when needed unlike the puzzle of a case otterbox made.

The downside to this case is the cosmetics could be better. It has a shiny plastic look on the front that looks cheap and I have found that the hole for the headphone buds is to small for some plugs. The hole for the charger is to small also for some cords.

If the looks were improved and the holes fixed this would be a 5 star product.

summary: Absolute lifesaver for tomatoes with blight!

While I am not really a fan of the color/decoration of the case, I really like having all these hooks together in one place provided I remember to put them back!. After buying several Clover Soft Touch Crochet Hooks as singles, I decided to get this set to replace/supplement my other hooks. The Soft Touch Crochet Hooks are very nice to work with. Metal hooks without the Soft Touch handle can be hard on the hands, and plastic hooks, while having a little flex that is better for hands, can also be less sturdy  while teaching a friend to crochet, he snapped a plastic one in half! We replaced his hook with a single Soft Touch hook.

I have had no problems with the Soft Touch hooks; they are my favorite to work with I have not used any of my other hooks since! It is really nice they come as a set and I think it is even cheaper to buy them this way. Despite not really liking the appearance of the case, it does it is job keeping the hooks together, with a flap to prevent them from sliding out the top. I highly recommend!
summary: Great way to get the Soft Touch hooks in multiple sizes

I have seen reviews that say this album suffers from childlike lyrics and simple concepts. I say, "So What?" It sounds great and it is full of hooks. It is definitely evocative of the Beach Boys' Sunflower album to me, with its breezy feel and gorgeous harmonies. All the standard instrumental highlights are there  bass clarinets, sleigh bells, flutes, all those sounds that make me think of the Pet Sounds album.

 My favorites after the first couple listens are "Soul Searchin", with a very emotional Carl Wilson vocal; "A Friend Like You", with Paul McCartney, which could have been lifted off of McCartney's "Flowers in the Dirt"; and "Fairy Tale" best lyrics on the album. The Eric Clapton guitar work on "City Blues" does not work for me, and comes off as too heavyhanded, like Eric is trying to show that he can still rock also see Toots and the Maytals "True Love" for other evidence of this.

 But, like everyone else has said, give Brian Wilson credit for just being able to do this, let alone produce something that sounds this good.
gift

My wife, my son, and I all agree that we really like the taste of these chips.  They do not too salty like regular pretzels, even though the sodium per serving is 610mg 26 of daily value.

The garlic parmesan taste is subtle but pleasant.  Personally I could not pick out the garlic and parmesan tastes specifically, but my son could.  If I had been given these without being told the flavor, I never would have figured it out.  If you are a big garlic or parmesan fan, you might be a bit disappointed in the flavor, but for me it was just right.

The serving size one bag is just right, and I like that they are much lower in fat than, say, potato chips 2.5g total fat per bag.

I have had other Pretzel Crisps, and have never been disappointed.  In general, they are a good snack, and these are no exception.
summary: Very tasty.  Garlic and parmesan flavors are subtle.

This is AIC's best album/EP. It will not take one long after hearing "Rotten Apple" and "Nutshell" to decide that this is the most depressing AIC album there is. But do not be soon to dismiss it as a whiny, slugging record. Oh no! This album has some of Jerry Cantrell's most complex pieces, not to mention what is popularly called "Staley's doowop vocals from hell." A voice teacher's nightmare, Layne's voice oozes with emotion and often makes one actually FEEL his drug hell. True, his voice is an acquired taste, but true fans acknowledge him as the greatest rock vocalist of the 90s. The joint songwriting of Staley and Cantrell tell the story of a million druggies, bipolars, and broken souls. All tracks are nearly flawless, the centerpiece being "Whale and Whasp," an instrumental that does what so many contemporary rock instrumentals do: make you think.
The song rivals Nine Inch Nails' "A Warm Place" for best pop composition of the 90s. The song makes an unexpected turn at the end with a jazz/blues number, "Swing On This," which makes one think of Layne's then inability to fight heroin addiction.
Quite possibly the saddest Iwant togowriteasong song ever, "Nutshell" never gets old in the fact that it applies to someone somewhere in the world each time you hear it. As Layne moans the lines "if I cannot be my own, I would feel better dead," you cannot help but thank God that his tormented life is over.
Rest In Peace, Layne, You Left Us All With A Legacy.
summary: One of the most disturbingly relaxing albums ever...

I have been using Clarisonic facial cleansing brushes for years. This is the top of the line Smart Profile model. The Clarisonic leaves my skin feeling smooth, fresh and glowing. The Smart Profile includes a "turbo" button for deep cleaning and rough skin, It boasts 4 speeds and includes an adjustable TTimer this beeps when it is time to move on to a different skin zone. This unit is designed to be used with different brush heads all over the body.

This package includes 2 brush heads face and body, the Smart Profile unit, USB Charger and directions.

There are fake Clarisonic units on the market. And some of them look good visually though they do not tend to work well or last. I did due diligence on this one checking all the signs and this is a genuine unit. text:
I was not impressed at all. A close friend read this in its native Japanese and found the description to be so beautifully written that it came highly recommended. However, in my 45 years of prolific reading, this story came across as tedious. The descriptions were overly long and minute details, although often very important to a masterful story or poem became unbelievably tedious and myopic.

I believe the problem is with the translation, as apparently many other translations of Master Murakami are apparently quite compelling. Others have said similar things so I am confident I am not off the mark.

The storyline itself was interesting and the title, 1Q84 if you understand Japanese is brilliant. There is great potential in this story, and many of the historical points discussed and the locations are of personal interest to me as I have lived in Japan for 25 years and actually been to the stations, and towns used.

My recommendation? Pick a different Murakami novel if it is your first time and you are curious about this award winning author

text:
Richard Bach may be one of those authors which one either loves dearly, or loathes unconditionally; he can occasionally come across as overlyhokey and melodramatic, but his stories are wellcrafted and deeply personal.
_The Bridge Across Forever_ may be the best book he is written yet, and is an excellent way to expose oneself to his style of writing; it was the first book of his which I read, and it caused me to run right out and snatch up all the others I could find. I have not yet found one that surpasses this one, but almost all of them contain wonderful gems and insights.
_Bridge_ is a rich, warm story about slightly metaphysical connections in life, through time, space, and personal growth. As he writes of his future wife, Leslie, the absolute love he feels for her is crystalclear, and may at times bring tears to the reader's eyes. His love of flying is beautifullyportrayed as well, and he does a wonderful job of introducing the reader to the absolute joy and freedom of being airborne. In fact, Bach's descriptions of nearly everything are alive and vibrant, putting the reader Right There in that moment with him.
It is easy to recognize Truth when we see it  this book is full of truths that we perhaps always knew, but did not quite know that we knew  it is that kind of book. I really recommend this to anyone who does not absolutely detest probing books with a real soul.
While Ms. Roberts' books will never keep you spellbound, the paranormal ones are extremely entertaining.  I do not particularly care for just the romantic ones but these will keep your attention.
summary: Good way to spend a rainy afternoon

text: After 3 years, and one charge, this baby the old one finally passed away. I look forward to another 3 years, or more, with this one.

It has been a few months since I started using this rod and I am loving it very much. My shower wall is about 60" wide and this adjustable rod holds onto the wall well and does not slide down.

I love the simple, smooth design of the rod. It is adjustable and where the two rods connect is a smooth bump so my curtain hooks glide over the hump without getting stuck, which makes opening and closing the curtains easy.

The finish is a nice bronze. Some reviewers have mentioned the two connecting rod pieces so not match color. It is such a discernible difference and you hardly notice the color difference. And once you have the curtain and hooks on, you cannot even see the subtle difference in color.

Other notable feature is that the two ends where they push against the walls are not bulky and big like those curves rods have. Curved Ross need a bigger surface area to support the curved rods and hence the ends have huge pieces. This is a straight rod and the ends are nicely small and has a simple look I prefer.

If you are thinking of getting a curved rod to gain more room, I suggest getting this straight rod and installing it a couple inches farther out of the bath tub so the curtain falls still within the tub area but you will gain a few more inches of elbow room. I did that and it worked out perfectly. And it gave me just as much room as a curved rod did.

I am thoroughly satisfied with this rod and highly recommend it.
summary: Sturdy rod with a nice bronze finish

text:
I have several photo programs on my computer and several others that I did not care for laying around. My favorite, easiest to use and quickest one to use has been the Microsoft Digital Image Pro 10. I also have the Corel Paint Shop Pro Photo XI and I have used it for my more advanced editing.
  Now this Corel PaintShop Photo Pro X3 takes the place of both of them. All the basic editing functions are pretty much intuitive and easy to find and use. It will switch from photo archive to basic editing to advanced editing and back to archive very easily. It comes with a book showing how to use it and there are online tutorials for its use too. I have not got very far into its more advanced uses yet but I think this will be the last photo program I will need for a long time.
  There is just one thing that I did not like about it and the installation of it. And that is it does not give you any choice, it takes over, on its own, and it goes through the entire hard drive collecting ever image file on it and puts them all in its photo archive. I would much rather be able to have the CHOICE of which photos and folders to put in its archive. But then that is something that just about every photo program I have ever tried does when its first installed.
  So if you want something more than just the Microsoft Digital Image Pro 10, or something to go with it, I suggest trying this one.
summary: A nice user friendly program for my digital pictures

Troubles, Rock Wit YOU, and The Life are very jazz like. I also like her ballads which are Why Do I Feel So Sad, Goodbye, Butterflyz, and Caged Bird. Piano  I is pretty much an intro. Also, there is a bonus track at the end of the CD, which I actually happened to stumble over that sounds gospel like. Overall, this album is a mix of RB, jazz, blues, classical, and hiphop. This deserves to be in everyone is CD collection.

I have several favorites from the arcade DDR that were not to be found on previous PS2 releases. Finally, I can play almost all my favorites at home! One of my new favorites that I had not seen before 'til now is Polovtsian Dances and Chorus Naoto Suzuki feat. Martha.

The other DDR versions that I own are DDR Max 2 and DDR Supernova 2, however DDR Extreme 2 is by far my favorite.

Through the last 20 years my husband and I have used a lot of office software. Right now, WordPerfect is my default, and OpenOffice is his. However, he switches to WordPerfect office for some specific things, and I do not use OpenOffice for anything, because WordPerfect does everything I need.
It saves nicely in a lot of formats and has all the applications you expect from a good office suite. It is intuitive to use, and common enough that if you do get stuck, it is easy to find a solution to the problem without having get customer support.
Where WordPerfect excels for me, and the reason my husband switches to it every so often is in straight word processing. In this, it is so much better than Microsoft Office. Most of my writing is craft instructions, and it was easy to create the various templates I wanted, and it is easy to format the documents professionally.
About PDFs I do not use the program to make PDFs, my husband does and he is happy with the pdfs he makes using it. Generally I save in .doc format then create the pdfs using Acrobat for greater control and the ability to add in fillable text fields easily.
I still prefer the full version, because a lot of my use is commercial, and the Home and Student edition is not meant to be used that way. However, it has the same functions, and works just as well at a lower price making it a great choice for students.

I LOVE the look and comfort of these shoes for style and lifting weights. Super cute and flezable. BUT for running, absolutely not!! It might just be my pronation/supnation and these shoes just do not work for my personal stride. I run about 24 miles every few days. Average of 8 miles a week and then sprints twice a week on a treadmill. Just after running with these 3 times, I am having major back issues that I have never had before.

MY STATS and other shoes:
I road and trail run. I run on my tip toes on the treadmill and a lot of heal on the road. I am 5'6 169lbs with more muscle than an average runner. Built more like a sprinter than a marathon runner.
I LOVE Nike FLEX bottoms. They really give me support and flex needed. I have also used Asics and Puma.
summary: Hurt my knees and back running

I have used another receiver lock for years and it still works fine but it is not long enough for a Class IV receiver and it requires a key. The type that need a key are more likely to gum up if left on the truck and need to then be cut off.

The Trimax has a very simple design so there is less to gum up and a coating once a year of WD40 should be all it takes to keep it operating smoothly. The little plastic boot is a nice touch though time will tell if it stays on or does not deteriorate and fall apart.

The length of the straight section is 3.10 inches so while it can work with a 21/2" receiver it is a very snug fit.
summary: Barely long enough for Class IV receiver

text:
In my review from: Sage 50 Premium Accounting Sage Peachtree 2013 [Old Version] CDROM, I wrote the following, which still applies to the 2014 version:
"I do not know why the makers decided to change the product name from Peachtree which everyone recognizes to Sage, but this does appear to be a wise upgrade to an already decent product. Tech support is good; Internet videos are good. So far Sage 50 Premium does everything I want it to do to run a duallocation business with inventory, branching out with Internet sales."

Currently, I am using Sage 50 Premium Accounting 2014.  Installation was no problem. Setting up Accounts Payable  Accounts Receivable is straightforward, with the initial entering of information taking the most time. Entering additional amounts and data is easy. I like being able to accept one check from a vendor and move it among several Accounts Receivable.  Also, how nice to be able to invoice by email or snail mail!

The 2013 version removed the Payroll Processing  Tax features and made them a separate program; unfortunately, that separation continues in 2014.
summary: Good program, does everything but payroll/tax.

Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

text:
I first heard some 'snippets' of this CD while listening to the Tom Joyner Morning Show, and from the first few cuts, knew I had to have it!  All of the artists do a great job playing tribute to Frankie Beverly and Maze, while maintaining the intergrity and funk of each song.  I love Raheem DeVaughn's version of "We are One",and  Joe's version of "Cannot Get Over You" and his video for this song. Frankie's son did an outstanding job on this project, and the other artists appreciation of the music of Maze is apparent in this tribute album, one of the better ones out there!
If you are a fan of Maze, you must add this to your collection!
summary: A Must for Frankie Beverly and Maze Fans!

I purchased one of these for home use.  It came covered in graphite which you continually need to reapply.  Also the instructions say the string should extend several inches beyond the outside lip I do not like that.  I also did not like having to manually cut the line to the proper length.  Research this product before you buy it YouTube, Internet.  I recall seeing one YT video that said  his lasted only a couple of months.  Based on what I have read, it does speed up your trimming time.  However, it the product only lasts a few months, then I do not think it is worth the $60 dollars asking price...Plus there is no way to cut the excess line, except with a pair of cutting pliers or a knife.  And you have to keep applying powdered graphite to the oring bushing or the wheel will not spin.  My neighbor has one and he does not like it, based on that and his comments, I am giving this one 2 thumbs down and 1 star.
summary: Nice product idea but I prefer to use my trimmer as-is

A personal account of Mark Berent's experiences in Cambodia while assigned to the Defense Attache`  Office in Phnom Penh, Cambodia in 1973.  This is almost exclusively a personal account with just enough information about the situation at large to put those experiences in context.  An interesting if narrow window into YOU.S. operations in Cambodia, it is well written with a few editing glitches.  Surprisingly to me, Berent, a fine author, misuses me and I in this little memoir.  This seems to be a not uncommon occurrence in modern writing.  This review is from the free Kindle edition published April 26, 2012.

text:
This is a 1959 Western about a town, Warlock, Utah.  There is more than one movie named "Warlock".  This movie is a solid, if not great western.  The cast is excellent.  Henry Fonda, Anthony Quinn, and Richard Widmark are all major stars.  DeForest Kelley plays the role of a cowboy before playing "Bones" in Star Trek.  Tom Drake, from Meet Me In St. Louis, to me, seems out of place as a brutal cowboy in this movie.  The movie is of high quality but was not a commercial success.

On the negative side, I feel this movie runs somewhat long.  The story could have ended sooner than it did.  There seems to be too many action climaxes.

On the positive side, I like this movie on several levels.  I like the cast.  I enjoy the cinematography.  I suppose most of all, to me, this movie seems to be a series of moral dilemmas and moral ambiguities.  Men are part saint and part sinner, much like life.  Thank You...
summary: A Solid 1959 Western With A Great Cast

I decided to do away with my old 3 bolt system in favor of the hardware Waste King supplied with this Unit. Once you get the drain plate / stopper installed, Unit handmounts very easily. Jack Nicholson is simply a virtuoso actor.  No actor of the modern times can bring such intensity, humor, and tragedy like he can.  'One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest' is the shining moment for this alltime screen legend.  He plays a man who faked insanity to go to a mental ward, only to find out it is just as bad as prison.  Along the way he find outs many of the patients are not that insane.  Many of them are in the ward voluntarily, but do not have the will to leave.  He rebels against the authorities and the result is a tragedy no one can stop from happening.  This is one of those rare films that everyone should see.  An unforgettable ending and an unforgettable performance from a one of a kind actor.

Great lock system.  My husband and I are remodeling our home and the search for locking systems seemed endless  who knew it would be some difficult to agree on a lock!?!?

Any way....we went back and forth between several different brands Schlage, Kwikset, Yale, Brinks, etc... and ultimately decided on the Kwikset.  Our decision was based on the style, durability we really put these things to the test at the store, ease of use was the handle comfortable, did the keys work easily, did duplicates work easily, etc, availability at stores/online and the parts for changing over interior and exterior doors, and finish type.  There are a lot of comparable lock sets out there, but this felt and acted much more heavy duty than the others we liked in this style.  It was between this set and a similar Schlage set.  This set won for 2 reasons  1 we liked the handles better, on the doors and the front door set and 2 the SmartKey system.  We have 4 exterior doors to our home, so we thought the SmartKey would be ideal.  System works great, easy to use handle, and the door closes snug every time.

Tips about this set  our first install was on a basement door.  We replaced an original wooden door with a new fiberglass door.  Love the entire set up and the new lock set looked great, but the handle was absolutely freezing to the touch.  We ended up taking the lock set off and cutting a piece of foam insulation to fit behind.  Problem solved!  It did not impact the usage of the lock or handle and cut down on the cold handle/cold air leaking through.
summary: Quality lockset with great SmartKey feature

text: It is OK

The "todo" list of a recent purchase of a used motor home included the need to update the entry lock. The original lock of the same design was broken because the potmetal plunger broke in a thin place and would not retract. Fortunately another item on the todo list was a defective window lock so we were able to gain access, remove the trim around the door, and with the aid of butter and spackling knives manually retracted the plunger. When the door opened the spring and plunger shot out of the lockset onto the ground. This is otherwise such a wellmade piece of hardware, I cannot understand why this crucial safety and security feature is so underengineered. The defective latch is cast white metal common pot metal where it should be forged steel to ensure strength and longevity. This is after all a motor vehicle door latch. Just look at the construction of the latches on your car or pickup. Other than this singular but major defect I find the lockset to be of high quality with very smooth action of the key and inside manual functions. I would gladly pay another few dollars for a completely wellmade lockset.
summary: High quality lock made with poor quality materials.

text:
We have a lab with skin issues. We have had her on all kinds of food. She is been vegan, she is been vegetarian, no luck. We use a dry food Wellness and she seemed to like it well enough, but we wanted to infuse some "real" food into her diet. Enter THK.

We went with Zeal because her system seems to handle fish proteins best. We had no idea how much she was going to love it. She sits and waits as we make it, and wolfs down her food immediately after we put the bowl down. We have had her on literally dozens of foods, and she cannot get enough of this stuff.

Yes, this smells fishy  probably because it is real fish! It also cleans out of the bowls much more easily than any other food we have given her. Kind of creeps me out to wonder why the other foods stick to the bowl and this does not.

We only put 1/4 cup into her dry food 2x/day, because this stuff is obviously not cheap. But she eats so much better when this stuff is in her bowl that we make it work.

This was a waste of $15.00.  When I initially inserted the batteries and tightened the cap, the pump did not even turn on.  I had to unscrew the cap slightly in order to get it to work.  Even then, it was intermittent.  I used it in my aquarium, which is one of the recommended applications.  In less than one minute it felt as if the tool was clogged, since the motor blades stopped spinning.  There were no instructions on how to unclog it, so I had to improvise.  I began by pulling the shaft away from the battery compartment which was a big mistake.  The motor is contained at the end of the shaft with cables leading down to it.  As soon as I pulled it apart, the cables broke off the motor.  This means that there is no way to clear a clog.  And if you are using this to transfer gasoline, I would be very hesitant to stick a cheaply made electric motor into a gasoline container.
summary: It broke within minutes of use

This is a review of Under Armour Men's 9" Armourvent Mesh.

Extremely comfortable with a waistband that is great. The transition from the actual waistband to the body of the underwear is so smooth and comfortable. It does not seem like it will soon loose it is stretch either. The body of the underwear is very lightweight yet provides subtle support around my thigh. Feels really great. The pouch provides enough space to keep things in check without being too restrictive.

My only complaint other than the outrageous price is that there are about 3 long tags attached to the inside back of the waistband. They can be carefully ripped out but you have to be careful otherwise you could pull one of the threads holding them on to the underwear and possibly have an unraveling of the stitching. I hate tags on the inside of my underwear.

I would never spend this much on a pair of underwear but if you are inclined to do so, these are certainly worthy of your attention.
summary: Really comfortable and the waistband is great but the price is shockingly high

I received this for an honest review and I have to say that I fell in love with this story. This is Dex and Chrissy's story.
Dex and Chrissy have similar backgrounds and have known each other since they were 8 years old. Both their fathers are gamblers but for these two similar people life takes a very different turn for both of them.
I loved this story because it shows how they grow up and how intertwined these two are. It also shows how stubborn men can really be. I think that for me is always enjoyable. I fell absolutely in love with these two so much that I really did not want the story to end.
This is actually the first book I have read of Michelle Lynn and I have to say I can not wait to read more. This book can be read as a standalone although it is part of a series..I can not wait to read more of the invisibles and of course the next book that will be coming out will be Robs!!?!?!?!
summary: ... and I have to say that I fell in love with this story

My mother started a baby blanket with this yarn years ago, before her Parkinson's kicked in and discouraged her from finishing it.  When my niece was expecting her first child, Mom became motivated and picked up the blanket and hook again, and got to work.  I found another skein of the yarn here on Amazon, in case she needed more to finish it.  The original jumbo ball finished the size of the large, tightly and beautifully crocheted blanket, and she used the new skein to crochet a scalloped edging around the entire blanket.  Years later the yarn colors were just a touch different so as to make a bit of a glow on the outer edge of this hard fought and gorgeous masterpiece.  Baby Mirella already has the blanket, or I would have submitted a photo.  I am so proud of my mother!  She is now venturing on to make a cardigan...  Rock on, Mom!

They came sharp, which I read others say they did not...so I guess they could vary. I know how to sharpen a blade so no big deal. They screwed into my shafts well. I Am shooting easton axis traditional 500 spine. They fly true no planing of any kind what so ever. My only issue with them is they seem a bit weak. I am concerned that if it hits any sort of bone passing thru the deer the blade will be chipped and bent, here is why. I was shooting them the other day and as a testament to the flight, I almost Robin hooded two of them at about 25 yards. I heard the arrows connect and upon retrieval noticed the blade the hit was chipped/bent just by hitting another carbon shaft. The shaft it struck had only a little cosmetic damage and the broadhead is going to have to be re profiled. Other than that I am satisfied with the purchase. The price was right for me and if they stay at that price they are easily replaced. I can fix the damage with a small amount of work on a file so I am not too worried. IMHO I think they are a good buy. I would buy them again any day!
summary: Just what i expected and im happy

I think it was some weird fungus I picked up in the hospital years ago, because that is when it seemed to appear. I tried all sorts of creams to get rid of it and after reading up on the benefits of extra virgin coconut oil I decided to try it myself. The area has healed and I still use this as a moisturizer for my face every night instead of all of the expensive products that I used to buy containing "peptides" etc. I also have started eating it and feeding it to my pets every day. Robin Lee Hatcher departed from her usual book settings in THE HEART'S PURSUIT and it was not a mistake. She always creates a historic romance that takes you back in time when life was simpler if not harder and often dangerous.
Jared Newman is a bounty hunter who was set on this path searching for the man who murdered his family. Silver Matlock is the daughter of a local merchant left at the altar. How their lives intersect and the subsequent journey will hold you captive.
 I found the story compelling as it unfolds. What will be revealed next, where will the journey go and what will be the outcome?
Ms. Hatcher is a skilled author who writes hearttouching books covering various historical periods. I have never been dissatisfied or disappointed when reading her books. I enjoyed The Heart's Pursuit and found it hard to put down until I finished.
I received this book free for an honest and fair review from Zondervan and Thomas Nelson Publishers.

In BLUE RIDGE, T.R. Pearson follows two storylines with the slimmest of connections; his two protagonists are cousins.  The far better of the two tales is that of Ray Tatum, a former city cop who is now a deputy sheriff in Hogarth, Virginia. Trying to put a family tragedy and failed marriage behind him, Ray discovers a body along the Appalachian Trail and with the assistance of a rather fierce Park Ranger from DC; he pursues the trail which leads to one of those places that are very difficult to deal with in a small town. This part of the story feels very authentic to me, the story stretches just far enough to hold your interest and the relationship between Ray and the ranger, Kit just feels very real. The dialogue and settings work exceptionally well.

It is the tale of Ray's cousin, Paul, and his trip to NYC that reads like a bad pulp story. Paul is called in to identify the body of the son he never actually had anything to do with after his original conception. From there Paul becomes involved with a dopey duo of cops, a conniving actress, and a criminal who almost seems omniscient in his portrayal by Pearson. Wasting time with a trip through the seamy side of Manhattan and finishing up with an outrageously ridiculous ending, I could not help but wish Pearson had focused all his energies on Ray's tale and left Paul in his notebook; Pearson's dialogue and settings seem to ring much truer in the South.
summary: Two tales of crime, one much better than the other

So far it works well and it is cool that it sharpens different sizes and shapes. It is also cool that it stops when sharp. The issue is that it is really hard to get the pencil in and out. Our kids have a hard time using it by themselves. In a classroom situation, I would hate to have a pencil sharpener that kids could not just use!

It seems to sharpen well and be powerful, it just takes a good amount of force to get the pencil in. I would also think that with as hard as it is to get pencils in that that would mean that the pencil would be centered well. Unfortunately, you can tell that pencils are not centered well because the wood is nearer to the point that it should be on one side.

The off center and the hard to get the pencils in both make this hard to recommend. I want to like it. I mean it does seem to work and sharpen quickly. I just do not know that I can really suggest it. If it were not so expensive it would be easier to recommend.
summary: Sharpens quickly and consistently. But part of that consistent is off-center. Hard to get pencils in.

text:
Added "CeraTec" into my last oil change, everything went well, be sure to shake the can rigorously! It comes out initially a creamy orange color, like spicy mayonnaise. I added the CeraTec to new oil before pouring into the engine, I then shook the oil and ceratec mixture again to ensure complete saturation. I noticed the engine was much quieter and smoother than before after running it for a few hundred miles.Audi A3 w/ 2.0 Turbo FSI. Although after 2000 miles the engine is nearly as noisy as it was before, but still very very smooth. I have not noticed any change in MPGs though.

When adding this to an oil change make sure to compensate and not add to much oil solution to your engine, you can damage your engine by adding to much fluid overall. My engine takes 5 quarts, so adding this container is nearly 1 additional quart to the 5 quarts of oil makes for nearly 6 quarts, I simply poured out 1 quart of oil into an empty oil bottle to add into the engine at a later time 2.0 FSI engines are notorious for drinking oil.

I cannot be sure this stuff really does anything without some sort of scientific testing? The engine runs smooth though it always was, but is not much quieter, and MPGs have not changed at all. I really cannot tell any difference, but hopefully this will add to the engines longevity. The product is not expensive, so it cannot hurt to give it a shot really.

I found David Vann`s "Caribou Island" phenomenal. It is certainly not an easy, or even a pleasant read. It is not for those who need actionpacked thrillers. It is rather a read for those who enjoy relentlessly building tension.  The characters are certainly less than perfect, but they are not less human for that. Readers looking for easytotell heros and badguys will be disappointed. Readers who admire sparse yet beautifully rendered prose will enjoy "Caribou Island", as will those who enjoy careful depictions of landscape and setting. But most of all, to enjoy "Caribou Island" requires a willingness to tackle the very toughest themes about family: the gradual estrangement between parents and children; the trauma of a parent`s death "Caribou`s..." must one of the most exquisitely devastating first paragraphs ever written; the collapse of marriage and the foretold disaster of an upcoming marriage. Not your usual "nice summer read" material, and certainly not for readers that require happy endings. But I will certainly be looking for more by Vann.

Reading the conclusion to Cameron and Jaci's story definitely contained a twist I was not prepared for, but I was riveted at how it all came together.

Cam and Jaci finally reveal the true extent of their feelings for each other and, in a twist of fate, his secrets are revealed to Jaci, causing her to understand just how much he had to suffer at the hands of his aunt and her friends as a teenager. She feels his sorrow and pain deep down and hurts for him, wanting nothing but to "make all the bad things go away."

Throughout the series, we have known that Jaci was struggling to deal with Richard and Annalee Roberts and the reputation of hers that they tried to keep tarnished. In the final installment, Jaci and her friend Moriah have been conspiring to catch them admitting to what they did, but when the meeting is set up at Moriah's, Jaci walks into the most unexpected situation.

There is so much more that could be said about the story, but I do not like to include spoilers. I was glad that Cam and Jaci were able to get past their secrets and progress in their relationship

Great little plug for one use. This is a one trick pony. The tone has little effect and the gain is basically another volume. This does not behave like a tube amp, contrary to some reviews. It sounds pretty much the same whether I am using the bridge or humbucker on my Les Paul and similar to all pickups on my HSS strat. The bottom line is it is not responsive, AT ALL. However, the upside is that is gives a nice classic distortion sound and is absolutely perfect for sitting around practicing. I use a set of earplugs and just put one plug in my ear while sitting on the couch watching tv and practicing. I have a tube amp and a couple of modeling amps that I use when I want to turn up the volume but this little amplug gets used more often. If you want a way to keep it down, and only a set of headphones to plug in, this thing is perfect. For $30, every guitar player should have one to avoid playing your electric guitar unplugged when working on your chops. I would give it five stars if the manufacturer was a little more honest about how the circuit emulates tube amps which it does not.
summary: Does one thing quite well- rock

I own at least four of these Speedrite electric fence outage alert devices, and I purchased at least two of them from Amazon. I have been using them since about 2003, and I love them.

They are welldesigned, wellengineered, and built to last. I have never had a problem with any of them.

While the device runs on a very inexpensive and easilyavailable CR2032 lithium flat cell battery they sell for about $6 for a pack of 20, and while it is quite easy to open the unit and replace the battery, the reality is that the batteries almost never need replacing. In my experience, even in heavy usage, that is, settings where the fence alert goes off quite frequently, one battery lasts at least 3 to 4 years, and in settings where the fence alert that is, the flashing light is rarely triggered, a battery lasts well over 7 years.
summary: I love them. They are well-designed, well-engineered, and well-built!
