ELEMIS Biotec Skin Energising, Day Cream.
First time trying this right out of the package only the oil side would come out
It took quite a bit of work to get the white cream side to pump out.
Then now that I am able to get the full product to dispense as intended I think it needs work on the pump system.
It says to use two pumps daily. I am finding that the spout part I guess you would call it is not far enough away from the base and so much slides down the side that I find myself trying to scrape it up.
If i try to pump at an angle into my hand to combat that problem then the lotion side barely comes out.

Now aside from the issue of the pump itself the product results I am pleased with so far.
The scent for me being with with allergies is just on the edge of being too strong  but I am learning to deal with it.
Thankfully for me it does not linger too long.
After about ten days now I am noticing the skin on my face seems to look brighter and certainly more hydrated.
Leaves my face feeling refreshed for a good part of the day.
Just not sure for me that the cost would be something I could justify since I have other face creams that seem to work ok enough.
summary: ELEMIS Biotec Skin Energising, Day Cream

text: Peachtree accounting became known as Sage not too long ago. Peachtree has been a trusted name in accounting software for decades. I first used Peachtree software in the mid 90's for payroll purposes at a company I worked for at the time. I am primarily a Quickbooks user but I wanted to give Sage a shot. it is definitely a solid product and while I did not get to the point of using the payroll function, I was surprised to learn that payroll can no longer be entered even manually without a fee. I can understand a fee for the automated service but the fact that there is a charge even for entering it manually strikes me as a really bad and annoying idea. I am glad that I will not have to take that step as I will not be using this software for payroll, but please be advised that this will be an issue for those who do. otherwise, it seems like a wellplanned out piece of software and I could certainly see myself using it on a daily basis just not with any recurring fees
summary: Solid accounting program from a long-time accounting software powerhouse

Bjork's most recent album, "Vespertine", is my favorite and considering her incredible body of work, that is saying a lot. On "Homogenic", Bjork seemed like a woman searching for love and contentment, whereas on "Vespertine" she seems like a woman who has found these things. This album is full of seductive love songs "Pagan Poetry", "An Echo A Stain", otherworldly lullabies "Heirloom", "Cocoon" and secular hymns "Aurora", "Undo" that shimmer with passion and inventive beauty. Bjork is the kind of rare artist that can be experimental, strange and optimistic all while creating songs that her listeners can still relate to. The word "masterpiece" is thrown around a lot, but when it comes to this album it truly applies.

text:
Our coffee table gets a lot of use. We eat on it, we work on it and our cats treat it like an expressway. That last reason is why we bought a can of Super Grip. We were sick and tired of the cats tearing across the coffee table and sending drinks flying all over the table, rug and furniture.

We applied two coats to all of our placemats and coasters, allowing a full day drying in between reapplication and use. We have been using them on our wood table for a week now and they do not slide and there is no residue whatsoever on the table.

Seeing the cats tear across the table, expecting the mats to slide them across it for the first time after we sprayed them was pretty funny.

I am now thinking about spraying the bathroom rugs that they like to bunch up all the time. I am also wishing I would known about this sooner; this would have been a great way to transform some of my mom's rugs from fall risks into a safer option.
summary: Great to keep items from sliding around

text:
Reviewed weather stations for a few days before deciding on the WS2080. This is my first experience with home weather monitoring and I believe I made the right decision. Assembly was straight forward and simple. I placed it on a temporary pole, hooked it up to my computer using the supplied USB cable, installed the software also included and have been monitoring all week. Everything works great. Test the rain collector and it registers, wind speed is slow updating but I can live with it. Temp, humitity all appear to be accurate.

Another name brand appears to have many defects and parts expiring too early base on web researching. Then there is one that cost 3 times what I paid for the WS2080 and you cannot even monitor the data collected on your computer. My choice for the WS2080 was a no brainer for a hobbyist and so far very happy.
summary: I am happy with the Ambient Weater Station WS 2080

1st entry:  Just began reading it a couple days ago and cannot put book down.  This is essential reading for anyone hoping to survive a natural or manmade disaster of Biblical proportions i.e. Hurricane Katrina comes to mind, and perhaps, the next flu pandemic.  Work, cooking, exercise keep getting in the way of reading this book.  This is an oral history of a future world war between humans and zombies.  The undead are infectious!  Its like some form of viral rabies pandemic.  The zombie pandemic can be traced back to "Patient Zero", a child whose father may or may not have been bitten and disappeared during a dive into the submerged ruins of the Three Gorges Dam in China. Each chapter corresponds to a time frame pertaining to before, during and after the pandemicreferred to as World War Z because the only viable response to the pandemic was to "eliminate" the infected i.e. the zombies.  This is not the first pandemic zombie work to come out this year.  So far so goodand a vastly superior work relative to Stephen King's zombie story Cell: A Novel although King's novel may have some more interesting literary goodies like allusions to genocide and evolution I have yet to mull over.
summary: Vastly Superior to King's Cell: A Novel

text:
These felt good the first time I put them on, and I have been using them as my everyotherday elliptical workout shoe for about seven months. No signs of wear at this point, which is mildly surprising given their lightweight construction. Excellent fit too, without a lot of foam to cover up for shoddy design.

I want to highlight the one way in which they are superior to almost all the other athletic shoes I have had in the last ten years  they never come untied. They have flat laces that feel like mostly cotton, instead of the oval, nylon laces that come with most shoes. I simply never have to stop and tie them, and that alone is worth an extra ten bucks a pair in my book. Why do not more athletic shoe manufacturers get this?

I am not crazy about the flashy, reflective cosmetics. However, I know running shoes often have that to make them stand out when people are running at night. So there is a good reason for the bright colors in the trim, and I will not downgrade them for it.
summary: Lightweight, comfortable for aerobics, and they STAY TIED!

Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

In her introduction D.G. Kaye says "I wrote this book to share the negative experiences and obstacles I have encountered in my own life. I have tracked my own insecurities and the selfesteem issues of my past in an effort to recognize and conquer the negative image I had of my youth...all so I could finally learn to love myself."
Anyone who has read her previous books knows that you can count on D.G. Kaye to be open and candid and in her own words, "baring my raw self to the world." Her honesty and transparency makes for a book that allows the reader to relate with the yearnings in all of our hearts and souls to be our true selves.
This is a book that ought to be on parents' and educators' to read and reread list: "...words linger much longer than physical wounds. The damage done to our delicate egos, especially when we are small, stays with us through the rest of our lives."
What is comforting is that D.G. offers sound advice on how to repair our damaged egos and take care of our sense of self. She provides concrete examples of her own life and how she conquered her fears. "If we do not take responsibly for our own choices, we can become ruled by someone else's power. This results in us giving up pieces of our own identities to satisfy the whims of someone else, leaving us with little selfesteem...Everyone has something beautiful to offer."
This time around, D.G.Kaye has this beautiful book to offer.

Overall, this is an excellent pencil sharpener and setup is as easy as unpacking it from the box and plugging it in: no tape, extra packaging, etc., to take off and wonder if you got it all.

Sharpening is very fast  just put in the pencil, apply a little pressure, and out pops a supersharp pencil without shavings hanging around the end that will smudge your work.

One of the better features of this sharpener is the desktop footprint: it sharpens in the portrait or up and down method vs. horizontal method, which means the hardware and waste tray spend more room going up instead of taking up more desk space.  While that means less of a waste tray in terms of trash / shavings volume it can hold, to me the space issue is key with everything else that is on my desk.  Emptying the waste tray is easy, and does not leave residue on your desk as others can.

This one is a few dollars more than the traditional electric sharpener from Boston or Atco that take up more room on your desk.  If space is important to you, I would recommend this one.
summary: Excellent Pencil Sharpener and Saves Room on Your Desk

If I could give this thing 10 stars I would. My 5 year old 1tb external hard drive spontaneously just stopped working. It still turned on, the fan still blew but my computer would not recognize it. I am only slightly tech savvy but I knew that the drive was not irreparably damaged. Just not cooperating with me. I live in the boonies of Arkansas so I decided to send it into a data recovery facility for an evaluation. They told me it would cost several hundreds of dollars to recover the data and put it on a new hard drive. Knowing this was unlikely I asked to have it sent back. After much arguing. They finally did. I ordered this cable set so I could do some evaluating of my own. Took my external hard drive out of the case, plugged it up, and lo and behold my computer recognizes the drive no problem. Inferring it was the case that was the issue PCB. So instead of being scammed out of several hundreds of dollars, I saved tons by buying this and recovering the data myself. I cannot say that this would work for everyone but it worked well enough by me and I am extremely satisfied. I plan to keep these babies on standby for the future.
summary: I can't say that this would work for everyone but it worked well enough by me and I am extremely satisfied. I plan to keep these

text:
autocad LT 2010 is a good substitute for professionals who need 2D drafting tools, but who do not want to pay for the full version of Autocad. This is NOT the tool for someone looking to make basic drawings of their home, business or DIY projects.

I work for is a steel stocking and manufacturing company. We receive drawings from customers in Autocad format every day. All of our work is 2D, and Autocad is an essential tool in our portfolio of applications. The full version of Autocad is several hundred dollars more than this `Lite' version. That being said, make sure you compare the features of the Lite vs full versions at [...] so that you do not end up missing a feature that you need.

This is NOT the program for an average person looking to do casual drawings, floor plans, flow charts, etc. If you are an average user, the best program to use for you is likely to be Microsoft Visio. While it cannot do many of the technical things that Autocad can do, it can allow you to make floor plans, simple part drawings, etc.

Comparing v10 to previous versions:

You are going to either love or hate the ribbon. I like it. So do the people in my drafting department, including people who have been using Autocad for 10 years.

The alignment functionality saves a lot of time. Worth the price of the upgrade by itself.

Layer management has been improved. Also worth the price of the upgrade.

If you are in need of training, or a refresher, I highly recommend the DVDbased training available through CADD Train  [...]
summary: A good substitute for professionals who need 2D drafting tools, but who don't want to pay for the full version of Autocad.

I researched a number of digital calipers before purchase and made the conclusion that the iGaging ABSOLUTE ORIGIN 06" Digital was a pretty good unit for the price. I also saw the most of the folks felt the Mitutoyo was top of the line, but may not be worth the additional cost  $95 vs $40. I purchased the iGaging ABSOLUTE ORIGIN 06" Digital calipers but I am returning them because of the display, which I have not seen discussed on this forum. I also purchased the Mitutoyo calipers. When comparing the display on the iGaging ABSOLUTE ORIGIN 06" Digital vs the Mitutoyo you very quickly see the reason for the price difference. I expected to find a quality difference between the two, but was blown away by the clarity, size and quality of the display on the Mitutoyo. 50019630 I cannot fault the iGaging ABSOLUTE ORIGIN 06" Digital as it appeared to be accurate and pretty well made, but for a tool that I plan to use for many years, I decided the price difference was worth paying. Bottom line, you will not be disappointed in the accuracy of the iGaging ABSOLUTE ORIGIN 06" Digital, but if you can afford the Mitutoyo calipers, go for it.
For those that are concerned about fake Mitutoyo calipers, the one I ordered came from Amazon LLC, and the calipers came in a sealed package that had to be cut open. Not the box mind you, but the actual packing that contained the calipers. All the included paperwork, box battery etc. said made in Japan. I do not think for a second that the calipers I received were not genuine.
summary: iGaging ABSOLUTE ORIGIN 0-6" Digital vs Mitutoyo

I am a recess aide and on my feet all day long. I tried these shoes on in the store before purchasing them on Amazon. They are very lightweight and comfortable. I was surprised how great they felt. I have not had a pair of Nikes since Nike shoxs came out. They are so much more lightweight than those. I wore them an entire day the first day and had no problems. The second day; however, I got a pain in my hip to the point where I started limping. As soon as I got home and took them off, the pain was gone the rest of the evening. I am only 30 by the way. Nothing else in my daily routine changed except wearing these shoes two days in a row. I do not understand why it would make my hip hurt since they are comfortable on my feet, but I am sure that was the problem. I wore different shoes today and had no pain. I do not think as much as I am on my feet I will be able to wear them an extended amount of time. I will have to rotate wearing them every other day. For normal wear, I believe, people will be fine. I am literally walking or standing six hours a day straight.

UPDATE: So, initially after wearing them, I had hip pain after wearing them. I do not know if they just needed to be broken in, but I wear them all the time now and have not experienced any pain since the first couple times of wearing them. They are comfortable, and I love them even more now.

I bought this version as a reference to compare with my Mauersberger recording. Butt is a very articulate, subtle, discerning and knowledgeable musicologist. ANd experienced performer. The Mauersberger recording is as good as Karl Richter's, which many people think is the gold standard for The St. Matthews Passion. How does Butt's version stand up to these giants? The text translation is better. The sound values benefit from contemporary technology. The counterpoint/ harmony and musical lines are clear and well articulated. The performance is stripped down to its essentials, with the 8 voices doubling as necessary. And the orchestra is as Bach would have had at his disposal. Rather than the great "Romantic" orchestras and choral forces used in the last century. Butt's Consort and singers are not super stars, and this showed at times. But, overall this is a very competent, and even, at times, exciting, performance. Clean, clear and very accessible for someone coming to St. Matthew with an open mind. I would recommend it.

You really get a sense of what plantation life was like back then, and what it took to survive. You learn what heros her ancestors were and all of the things that they had to do to keep this mansion thriving. There is a lot more to this story than what I am telling you know. I am not saying much because I believe that it is worth the read. If you like this genre of book you will not be disappointed by this story. It is well worth the read. I highly recommend.

I wanted a carryorganizer to replace an upright drawer type organizer that had quite a few compartments for storage of 410 bolts, screws, washers, etc.  This is one of a couple I have found that might do that adequately  is well made.  I often need the parts on a job  carrying a drawer type is a disaster.  Although the lid is not as stiff as I would like it to be, it seems like it will maintain small parts in their intended compartment.  It is about the right depth to hold enough parts in a compartment but not so deep as to bury the bottom parts if you are storing slightly different size parts.  The latches seem robust  audibly snap when they are closed.  The compartments are removable  they can be somewhat reconfigured in the organizer.
It seems like a large container but it does allow the parts to be stored more openly so you can see what you have.  The yellow color helps with visibility inside the compartments, especially for small parts, as opposed to some organizers that have black interiors.
Although I do not recommend it, it seems robust enough to not break if stepped on.  However, it may not survive a driveover.
I will be purchasing at least one more.
summary: Works for me for the 2 days I've owned it.

I am trying to come up with a way to use this as I cannot return it.  After getting the product and planning to attach it to my iphone I have decided not to because I sometimes carry my phone and my wallet together.  The strong magnets in the Steelie mount on the back of the phone will erase your credit/debit cards if they come close to the magnet.  Magnets are great and they have their uses.  But one use I do not want is the potential of being stranded at a gas station and my credit card not working because I inadvertently set my phone on my wallet.  Great idea, horrible application with potential to do damage.

So I am trying to figure out how I can use this in my wood shop.  Maybe a camera mount, or possibly a light mount to a piece of equipment.  One thing that it will not be attached to is my phone.
summary: Not on my phone, maybe somewhere else.

text:
Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

I have been a Far Cry fan since FC2. Never saw the original. FC3 was excellent. In FC4, the game seems a little disjointed. The side missions and battles in Shangri La just do not seems to flow with the main story line. Very disconnected. The vehicle controls have changed and I find them a little awkward even after hours of playing. And, typical of the Far Cry series, you are never really short of funds as there are plenty of chests to loot, cash laying about, bodies to loot  even though your weapons are free once you liberate the necessary radio towers or perform the required sidemissions. I would actually like to have to be a little more concerned about finding enough coin. Make things a little more difficult to come by, like having to take out more enemies just so you can scrounge together the money for ammo or syringes. Speaking of syringes  I still have not figured out how to craft them in this game. Unlike FC3, it is not that obvious how it is done. I have not really needed them to tell the truth.
There are many features I do like. The crossbow, the buzzer, the animals, the main storyline, etc.
It is still a great game, just not an excellent game.

text: Informative and enjoyable book.

Anyone with a green thumb will tell you that there is no such thing as a watering schedule that is based on the need of the plant.  Varying soils, temperature, humidity, sunlight, and of course the size and variety of the plant are all factors that determine how often a plant needs water.  So the question is, do you have the understanding of perception and the instinct to know when your plants need water.  I do, but my wife does not.  As a result, we have lost several plants to overwatering.  Hopefully this helps the situation.

This unit is extremely accurate.  I borrowed a professional one from a neighbor of mine to test against this unit and this one is amazingly close.  No plants except maybe some orchids need a closer definition of the exact water conditions.

Be sure to stick the tip well down into the plant however, as it will only measure as deep as you go.  If you only put the tip down one inch, it will only tell you what is at that level.  The top of the soil NEVER needs to be wet.  It is the roots that drink the water, and good quality soil will wick any water that is lower up to those roots.  This unit has a nice long probe on it, so use it to your advantage to get the most accurate reading possible, then make mental notes of it to associate what you see and feel to the actual readings.  This can actually help develop your natural intuition with regard to what plants need because you associate the reading with your observations.

I received a free sample unit for my evaluation and honest review.  I have no association with the company.

Should you try out the hotel hot tub while on vacation or try the pool instead? This magazine has excellent advice for everything from travel concerns to fitness and beauty advice.

Recipes for natural salt scrubs with buttermilk mingle with the hottest advice on commercial beauty products. Do the new stickon manicures work? What is the newest information on cancer prevention?

Dr. Andrew Weil has a 5minute section with holistichealth advice where he explains why Wild Alaskan salmon and blueberries will keep skin youthful. Is the air in your home as clean as it could be?

Fun product pages offer seasonal comforts. For summer you may find yourself looking up beach blankets and fans. Special sections show you how to lose weight, even when on vacation. Interesting advice on how to beat stress and why you should find ways to increase the release of oxytocin.

The only thing in the magazine of concern seems to be the advice section which I read, but take some of her advice with a big pinch of salt. If someone thinks they are suffering from an addiction, they probably are. I am at times rather surprised by her answers that seem to lean towards a casual approach to serious lifechanging situations, although she seems to give women great advice about health issues when it comes to making them feel better about breast cancer or work situations.

This is really one of the best rap albums to come out in the 90s. Yes, there are some bad songs and some of the intros are really annoying. For example the one intro when Biggie is banging some girl is really unneeded. All in all the intros are the weakest part of the album and by far the easiest parts to skip over. But enough about the bad when there is so many good things to say about this masterpiece. Things Done Changed is a cool back in the day song and is indeed enjoyable, then comes the very catchy Give Me the Loot. Although the subject matter of that song is laughable the chorus is very catchy. More highlights are the spectacular Ready to Die, the classic Juicy great hip hop bass line, and the dance party favorite Big Poppa.
However the greatness of this album is all about the producing. I saw Biggie live and he did not sound the same, he sounded more flat and not as impressive as he does through a stereo. Every song is recorded prefectly. Big Poppa for example has each part in perfect balance. I can hear Biggie rapping and every little nuance in the background music. For some reason rappers today cannot get that down and they spew their inarticulate lyrics at lightning speed and everything turns into a blur, but every single one of Biggie's songs is produced perfectly. Puff Daddy really knew what was up for this aentire album.
Also the entire album embodies the American myth of rags to riches and then an early death. Sonehow all of his lyrics are prophetic of what would happen to him and they all create the narrative of an amazing life of an amazing rapper.
R.I.P Biggie

Lana Del Rey nee' Lizzy Grant is a bit of a odd bird of a singer.  Stylistically, she looks like she is trapped in the 1960's, with no desire of 'escaping'.  Musically, her haunting voice can be undermined by an incredibly disinterested demeanor when she sings see her recent "Saturday Night Live" performance for a good example.  Yet, he has an undeniable presence and new era style to her music.

  "Summertime Sadness" is the type of song that will take Lana from being a novelty singer, appealing only to a niche audience, to becoming a larger mainstream presence on this charts.  Her ode to heartbreak and obsession, combined with a strong EDM hook, helps make this a 'take notice' song for Lana.
summary: Interesting song with more energy than her typical music

I am fairly new to the harmonica and have only ever played Lee Oskar's.  This is my fifth and my absolute favorite.  I could get a clear 3 and 4 draw bend immediately after opening and it just sounds pretty.  I still have problems with overblows on all of my Lee Oskar's but it may be due to technique rather than instrument's fault.  I am sure everyone has their particular brand of harmonica.  I definitely need to expand my horizons and try another, but if you want a really well built and great sounding harmonica, buy a Lee Oskar and have it around to always fall back on.  No regrets.
summary: Lee Oskar Harmonica = awesome as usual

text:
The PS2 is one of the best systems around. I have owned game systems starting from the Atari 2600 all the way up to the PS2 and I would have to say the PS2 offers the biggest bang for the buck. First off, you have a HUGH selection of PS1 games. Then add to that an almost equally hugh selection of PS2 games and you have got a nearly endless array of games covering just about all genres. Many of these games can be found cheap on the used market.

This particular model is the SingStar Ceramic White PS2. It comes with two microphones and the Singstar gamealong with 1 controller. I own the Silver PS2 already and have really enjoyed it the last 3 plus years. I decided to add another PS2 to my collection as a backup. I liked the look of this model so that is why I chose it.

Lastly for those into retrogaming, the PS2 has some of the best compilations from companies such as SNK, Taito, Sega, Activision, Capcom, and Atari. Interestingly, a collection from Konami for one of the newest systems only has 3 games. Most of the compilations for the PS2 has at least 20 gamessome a lot more  for a modest price too. Great system with a long history and a wide assortment of games.

The stand is just a bonus on something that someone did their homework on...
summary: Best case out there despite the low price...

Of all the true DD books I have read, I liked this one the most. In many of these stories the woman always seems to be portrayed as person who I just cannot connect with on any level. But Reggie she seems more real. In some stories the women are just described as not being aware of themselves or whatever. That is not the case here. Now, maybe Reggie does not take good care of her health she is sick and not in bed but she is not all flighty or 'oh I just forgot to eat' nonsense'.

  Alex is a straight up guy but he is not a jerk. He does not come across as some bully to me. He comes across as truly caring about her and not just wanting to discipline her. It comes across as a romance novel..not a spanking story.

The only negative thing I can say about story is that it is too short, but I have noticed that about DD stories. I assume it is just part of the genre. I do wish more time was spent on character development. I think it would make the stories that much better.
Works great

My wife has been struggling with the accounting for her business for a while; she understands the basic accounting concepts she is taken classes but has not been able to find a good program that does everything she needs it to do and is affordable. We were lucky enough to receive Sage 50 Premium Accounting 2014  3User and she absolutely loves it! The interface is easy to use, the way everything is set up is pretty intuitive, and it more than meets her needs.

Her one objection to this software is the autorenewal feature. It is always annoying when companies do this. In this particular case, you have to provide your credit card information in order to get the thing started. If you forget to cancel at the end of the year, you are in for a big surprise... and not a happy one.
summary: Great product, but BEWARE of the auto-renewing policy...

In the 70's, I actually taught Social Statistics in a minor state university.  The only thing I knew then was Fisher's "Frequentism". I retained interest in the subject long after leaving academic life.  This incisive exposition has taught me concepts I should have known long ago.  Chapter 8Bayes Theoremintroduces the interested student to a controversial idea now becoming accepted.  The author writes in a personal style with frequent anecdotes.  For example, he briefly played"TexasHoldthem" professionally. Despite that, and whatever the author implies, this book is aimed at an audience with a collegelevel understanding of statistics, mathematics, and risktheory. No doubt, it will incite heated replies.  I suspect that this is the author's intention.

I am not any sort of theatre expert, so I will not pretend to offer the critical analysis that some other reviewers have provided rather snobbishly, I might add.  Ultimately, I think that this recording is absolutely brilliant.  In contrast to some critics, I think that the musical variety contained within this show is stunning, yet I felt like Schwartz was up to the challenge throughout the show, regardless of the style which he was using for a given song.  Take note of "In Pursuit of Excellence" as a perfect example of a totally unique, but absolutely engaging song.

For whatever it is worth, I have some serious theological issues with this show.  I would not actually recommend anyone to casually watch the show because I think that there are some unfortunate misrepresentations of the character of God.  However, there are also some powerful moments of personalizing the story of the human experience within God's creation that become real in ways that only theatre can provide.  And it offered hours of good conversation for my wife and me afterwards.

Specifically related to this album, I love it.  I would recommend it to anyone who likes the musical theatre format but who wants some more depth than many Broadway shows.
summary: As good as any musical recording...

The Pomona 3788 BNC F To Minigrabber Test Clips are handy to keep around the electronic workshop. They come with quality minigrabber clips and allow the connection of BNC devices such as oscilloscopes, counters and frequency generators to devices under test. The BNC is female, so it will connect to double male BNC cables.

A final comment. Some mingrabbers are of poor quality. It is hard to get them to grab on to components and stay put. This is not the case with the Pomona 3788 Minigrabber Test Clips. They work extremely well, grabbing easily and holding on as they should.
summary: Handy Electronic Test Cable with Excellent Minigrabbers

text: We have two four year old male Maltese pups. They were on Castor and Pollux puppy chow from the beginning and after an unfortunate ordeal with vaccines they refused kibble. Our vet suggested either Hill's or Iams products. After some experimentation we decided to go back to Castor and Pollux canned food and the change has been remarkable. Since they still refuse kibble we make sure to have chew items to keep their teeth clean.

OK IF YOU HATE SHAVING?!?! Get this , then go to YouTube look up how to use shaving soap. Watch several videos. Then break out your soap/cream and play around with it practice and then give it a try! If you do not find this to be thee best shave ever keep practicing because your missing a step or have not gotten it down yet.

I hated shaving! My skin always got irritated and burned after! Then I tried this stuff after watching hours of videos, I broke down and gave it a whack. Now mind you I am in a wheel chair so it is harder for me to shave and I get worn out in my chair quickly!!!! After using this I look forward to shaving I cannot wait for the stubble at 5pm or 5am to show up because I am going to shave... I will spend the extra 10 min to get outta  bed to go through the procedure to shave ! My skin comes out so smooth and irritation free!!!!!! And the girlfriend really noticed a difference! Spend the money, spend the time to learn , spend the time to treat your self to something fun and comforting !!!

text:
I have five cats. They ALL love this toy. I could barely get it out of the box before they were attacking it. It is a simple little toy but it drives my five wild. Yes, it is a cheaply made toy but if your anything like me you L O V E to see your kitties enjoy a toy.

 My cats have had it a few days and they are still very interested in it. The base is quite light so they can tip it over during play. You can simply tip it back up to get it going again. My cats have actually "learned" to play in such a way as to NOT knock it over.

The toy makes a slight whirling noise  not annoying and barely audible  The fluttering action is very life like. Our toy has been in heavy play but it is still works great. The butterfly is made of thin plastic. My cats have bent and bitten little holes in the butterfly but it is still attached to the toy.

The toy takes one AAA battery. It goes through them pretty quickly. I purchased a whole pack at the dollar store.

I recommend turning the toy off and storing it in its box  when onto in use I have to put mine on a shelf in a closet My cats will not leave it alone if I leave it out.

Overall, this is a fantastic toy ! My family and I have gotten hours of joy watching our cats play with it. I highly reccomend this one!
summary: 10 stars ! My five cats adore this toy

I do not understand why George Lucas refuses to give fans a highquality transfer release of the original theatrical cuts of the Star Wars trilogy. For those of us who do not like the tweaks, the lame revisions Han shot first or the overdubbing I liked the original Boba Fett, thanks very much, this release is just another slap in the face to film buffs, historians, and preservationists.

They say if you whitewash something long enough, people will cease to remember it. Sadly, that is what Lucasfilm seems to want to do  whitewash the superior versions of the Star Wars films until newer generations do not know any better.

Shame.

I really enjoyed this book, but I generally do whenever Kelly Oram releases a new one! I love the originality of her characters and her storylines. I found Grace to be a little annoying at first but, I did grow to like her. I loved Ethan. He was a bit bratty at first, but I could kind of relate to the pain that he might of felt because he did not really fit in anywhere. What annoyed me the most about Grace was her insistence on not wanting to I will say "date" for the sake of not giving too much away! Ethan but, she kept throwing herself at our old friend Russ. Sigh...I got frustrated with her and her reasoning but thankfully that did not take too much away from the story for me. Overall, I would recommend this story to others. I think it was a great read and I cannot wait for the next in the series!

The product I received does not match the picture in the product description. I bought this for the Easy Clean and STATITE features I have enjoyed with a Bemis seat we have in another bathroom, but this one does not live up to the expectations. The model number on the packaging match the product description on the Amazon page, but it is not the right seat.

First, there are no Easy Clean hinges. The seat is stamped Easy Clean too. This one has fixed hinges so you cannot remove it to clean underneath. I should have stopped and returned it at this point, but thought I could live without the removable feature. The STATITE does not really stay tight. When you install the seat, the posts will snap off underneath when the appropriate tightness is achieved. You would think that this means the seat is as tight as the manufacturer intended. However, I found out a week later that if you shift your weight on the seat, it moves. I thought that because this was Bemis' retail line that the quality would be the same as with Bemis products, but I have found out this is not the case.
summary: Not Easy Clean and doesn't STA-TITE

My dogs really like this Nutro Wild Frontierand I have to add, the packaging is beautiful. There are a couple of 'meals' in this dog food. While I used to think meal is a cheaply made food, I did some research and found it really is not. The quality of the meal depends on the supplier of the food. If chicken meal is used, the whole chicken minus bones is ground up, turned into meal and driedand this renders a higher concentrate of protein than if just chicken meat is used. It appears to me that the Nutro food is highly nutritious and made with quality ingredients and made in the US. My dogs, all three, really seem to like this food. While I did have a lot of reservations in the past, I think the 'meals' in foods are goodit just depends on whether or not the suppliers are using high quality ingredientssuch as chickens that are not too fat, or the meant is not spoiled, etc.

I really like this food and will try a bigger bag with my dogs.

This book deals with the Arian controversy of the 4th century, and how Christianity was accepted and eventually made the state religion of the Roman empire.
It is a story of how the Christians went from being the oppressed to being the oppresors, and the formation of Christian theology that has dominated the religion for seventeen centuries.  The two opposing views of Christ held by the followers of Arius and the followers of Athanasius led to bickering and bloodshed, all in the name of Christ, the prince of peace.
Perhaps this book can she would some light on why after seventeen centuries, bloodshed and violence continue to be a part of Christianity.  It is a story of power, control and politics from the 4th century that appears to be ongoing today.
Recommended!

text: This is definitely not your dad's mapping program.  I expected this to be an upgrade over something simple as MapQuest, but this obviously much more than that.  From the moment you start using it, you will realize this is indeed for business and not for personal use.  There are a lot of business terminology that confused me and took time to learn what it all means.  The interface is average and actually shows its age as it is not innovative, but those who used Windows programs before should be able to recognize it.  I was able to plan out a simple trip, which included cost and gave me an array to choose from of what to do during the trip, but as mentioned, it took several hours of program use just to figure out what I was doing.  Bottom Line is this is definitely for business use.
summary: Good program but with a steep learning curve.

Purchased as first sewing machine for 13year old, along with basic notions and materials for first projects  pair of 18" decorative pillows with zipper and pull on pajama pants. Although there are many other, less expensive entrylevel sewing machines, it did not make sense to me to ask a beginner to fight with her equipment while learning. Added used hardback Reader's Digest sewing manual. In the 2 weeks since Christmas, the child has completed projects on her own, by referring to pattern instructions and sewing manual; and she has been digging around closets for unused clothing to mend or refashion, as well as make clothes for younger sister's Barbie dolls. If she takes care of her machine, it should last into adulthood. The only she might miss is the variety of automatic buttonholes available on a more expensive sewing machine; however, I was nearly 40 before owning a machine with an automatic buttonhole feature. The Brother XL26001 has 1. I am just down the street; and my Singer has 7 buttonholes that she can use as her interest expands come to think of it...inherit.

Should add that it was the abundance of Amazon reviews that informed my selection of this sewing machine. It is definitely the best, feature rich machine in its price range.

This Zwilling J.A. Henckels 5Piece Grooming Set comes packaged in a nice heavy black box with minimal markings on the outside. The inside of the box looks remarkably like the cover of a romance novel, perhaps one with vampires. That was unusual, and surprising. I guess it adds some interest, but I think the packaging would be classier looking without it.

Inside the box you will find first a lightweight pouch with a flap protecting a very nice looking leather zipper case. These are described as tools for men, but I am not sure why. Each and every one of the five tools inside can be used by women as well. The tools are nice looking and a most of them are a good weight. The nail clippers are different from any that I have seen before, and frankly they seem to be not only the tool most often used, but they do not seem to be sturdy enough to last long. I may be wrong, but they are lightweight and fold flat. That is a nice feature, but it is also what makes me a bit leery about their long term use. They are also rather small for a man's hand in my opinion.

All in all, I think this is a nice set. It would make a nice gift for anyone who travels, or who likes to have nice looking grooming tools. Perhaps I am missing something, but aside from the case, I do not feel that these are much different from grooming tools that you can purchase almost anywhere. I am certain of one thing, you will be paying mostly for branding here.

text: I ws looking for an underhelmet thermal cap with a windresistant front panel, and overear protection. This fit the bill. Made from a tightly knit thermal microfiber, I washed this the first evening I received it and it was completely dry by the next morning. Wicking is an important feature for me as I perspire from my head when exercising. The cap is thin enough to fit comfortably under my helmet and provide a smooth and comfortable cushion layer without any pressure points. I wear a large hat size and this cap fits my head perfectly and does not feel overstretched or excessively tight. There is a thicker inner liner that wraps around the front panel back to the ears to block the wind. The rest of the cap is made of a single layer of thermal microfiber. The only shortcoming I found with this cap was that the first language on the labeling was Chinese, and there were no washing or fabric care instructions included. This should not be a problem if you handle this cap like the rest of your microfiber active wear. Tomorrow will be a chilly day, highs in mid 50's and overcast, so I will be giving this cap it is first field test. Unless I post an update, you can assume that it performed well.
summary: Great Thermal Cap for a Good Price.

If you want your scope to look nice around your neck, this one will do it for you.  Let me say that it does work, I can do BP and hear heart and lung sounds with this scope.  With that said its just not put together with the tolerances needed to acheive an air seal at the head.  The stem fits loosely in the head.  When you turn it to "click" for either the small bell or the diaphram side, it feels sloppy.  If you take the tubing off of the head and blow into the stem, air leaks out around the stem regardless of where you have the stem turned, pushed, or pulled.

I would love to know how to disassemble the stem, and possibly add some orings or silicone to the stem to attempt to get an airtight seal, but as it is, it will never be as sensitive as it could be.

If you were willing to give up the bell, you could probably epoxy the stem in place, and seal up the bell hole to get a sensitive, working diaphram side, but really, it should just work out of the box.

I bought Norton AntiVirus 2006 and it caused my computer to totally crash. It became totally useless. When I tried the regular support number I could never get through.

In despeation, I called their 900 number and up front I told the rep I would not pay as Norton caused the problem. He went along with that. It turned out Norton AntiVirus is incompatible with another Norton product, and that caused the crash.

When my phone bill came I was shocked to see I was charged $132 for the privilege of having my computer crashed. After numberous calls, I was told by Norton customer "service" in a foreign country that it was impossible for them to refund my money.

So if you want to have major problems with your computer, like losing all your data, buy Norton products. You can not only get a crashed computer, but will be charged through the nose to recover  .

BUYER BEWARE
summary: AVIOD THIS COMPANY AND ITS PRODUCTS

We originally bought the Renaissance wax on the recommendation of others who have used it in the past to protect their art. Once we saw the history of the wax and the fact that it is museum quality, we decided to try it. Hubby has used minwax paste wax on furniture before. However, when the wife used this on her new chair, he was amazed at the ease of application and the shine it leaves. A little of this wax goes a long way. It dries quickly, and easily buffs to an amazing shine. After letting the chair sit for a couple days in between coatings, it did not feel like there was ever a waxy buildup, and it feels like there is a strong protective coating. It is also very slick, I can see how other reviewers commented on using this wax on jointers and table saws. The next thing for the hubby to wax will be the table saw. We also will not hesitate to use this as a protectant on metal ornamentation, furniture, leather handles, or any other projects that require protection and a high gloss finish.
The first time the wife used it, she did not wear any gloves while applying the wax, and she complained afterwards how it made her hands feel. We would definitely recommend gloves.

Pros:
Amazing gloss
Easily buffs
Dries quickly
Easy to apply
Very slick finish
A little goes a long way
Feels like it is a strong protectant

Cons:
Makes your hands feel slick if you apply it without gloves
pricey
summary: We bought this to protect art furniture, we didn't expect the amazing shine!

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

text:
Imagine a cross between a platform game and a pinball game and you have kirby tilt 'n tumble. This is like a platform game in that it is got many levels, obstacles, and there is always a boss in the endwhich is absurdly easy. However, to really enjoy the game, you go back to the old theory during the Atari's era: score as high as you can. This game has a surprising amount of depth, with many hidden areas to cash in on stars. The red stars are more difficult to get than regular stars, but when you get six, the red stars on the rest of the level become 1 UPs! I have gotten like about 50 lives this way. It is too easy if you play it like a platform. Instead, if you explore every nook and cranny of the levels, you will really get some nice rewards, not to mention the game's all too few minigames.
  Buy this game if you want a game that is challenging and it never grows old. I would not reccomend playing it in the car though. Unless you are on a smooth road, the bumps in the road could just steer you into a pit.

Ordered this in January, 2012, but had no reason to use it until March, 2012, AFTER the expiration of the Worx 30 day satisfaction guarantee and the Amazon return period.

First time out, it shocked me every time I touched it anywhere near an assembly screw.  It does not vacuum that well.  The reviewer who said it works okay if you only have a few leaves to vacuum is absolutely right.  I would add to that:  If you also have a lot of time to waste.  To be fair, they were cottonwood leaves, quite large, but dry and loosely piled against a wall by the wind.  I gave up after 11/2 bags.  I was worried about electrocution.

I called Worx customer service about the shock and also mentioned that it does not pick up leaves as well as is shown in the video.  They are sorry I do not like the performance, but I missed the window for the satisfaction guarantee.  Fair enough.

As to the electrical shocks, they suggested wearing gloves while operating the product.  They blamed static electricity.

For some reason, Worx is sending a replacement motor unit under the two year warranty, but since they do not expect it to change anything, it seems pointless.  Never buy on Amazon unless you can test the product in the 30 day return period.  I say that as someone who buys a lot on Amazon and should know better.  I blame myself and not Amazon.

I would have no problem getting information with this radio during an emergency situation.
The light on this radio is good enough to navigate throughout the house if need be.  This radio is a little bassy for my musical tastes, but that is ok because it is not being used for that.  The hand crank is a nice feature just in case.  It seems to turn crank smoothly and does not feel like it is going to break like I have heard from other radio's .  All in all a nice radio.

I found a Cooking Light magazine from 2009 and tried their banana bars with browned butter pecan frosting. Can I say delicious the bananas are roasted with brown sugar and butter first, but I think personally I would about half the sugar. When they say light in this magazine they seem to mean reducing fat. So the recipe had 8.4g of fat but 35.1g of carbs . I think if they are going to say a recipe is healthier they should also reduce the sugar. So next time I will remember how sweet the cake was and lower the amount of sugar to say 3/4 cup instead of 1 1/4 cup. Light to me at least seems to mean less fat AND sugar. I did not play around with the recipe because I only had three bananas and could not afford to get it wrong on the first try. I will try other recipes in this magazine if I find any in the future but I will remember to pay attention to the sugar.

The Rebecca Review
summary: Roasted Banana Bars with Browned Butter Pecan Frosting

first thing first: it works. the kit is great in what it consists of and the price is just right i think. to call someone to clean my dryer vents i got quoted from 80 all the way up to 200 bucks. so if you were able to do it yourself you will need to invest a bit more in a "construction" vacuum that cost about 80100 bucks and start the savings basically from the second time you do it.

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

text: I have been using the Proraso shave cream with great success.  I purchased this "Soap in the Bowl" to support a recent vacation as I did not want to travel with my ceramic bowl.  This product provided a very comparable lather and since it was the same ingredients as the cream in the tube, I did not experience any breakouts as a result.  This is a must have for travel or for anyone not wanting to mess with the separates.

Photomatix offers a relatively strong and lowcost way to get into HDR photography, and I find it a great creative tool.

The program's support for RAW format images seems to be good  it handles RAW from my Nikon D300 and D3x without problems, although the large files that come from my D3x seem to take a long time to process. A fast computer and lots of memory help.

Assuming good basic technique, the images come out amazingly well. Although the basic idea is to stitch together images taken with different exposures, sometimes it is handy to use the program's tone mapping capabilities, even on a single image.

I tend to start my workflow with Photomatix, outputting HDR TIF images that I usually bring back into an editing program PhotoShop for further tweaking. Photomatix is good at HDR  you still need something else for many of the other changes you might want to make to your images.

Overall, I find the software a great creative tool and it is helped me think in new ways about contrast and dynamic range in my images. Definitely worth the price.

I am loving this Baxter of California toner that I received from Amazon Vine. I have been using it for a few weeks now, and the results have been positive. It is very easy to apply, dries fairly quickly so you can put on any moisturizer you want before leaving for the day or going to bed, and leaves the skin looking good. It has a pleasant smell  the mint is a nice addition. The 10 fluid ounces you get is actually going to last quite a while. I am guessing I will not have to buy a bottle of this until maybe 3 or so months from now. So, it seems expensive, but it is pretty low on a costperuse. Overall, I am very pleased with this toner and will be sticking with it.

Despite the price and plastic construction, this thing feels very solid. The included charging plug is great! Now when my dog or a friend accidentally does something to yank on the USB cord, it will not damage the USB port on the phone itself. Great peace of mind.

It fits the HTC One in an Otterbox Defender case brilliantly, with room to spare. The USB port, volume buttons, and headphone jack are all easily accessible. The camera has a clear line of sight in case you want to use it as a dashcam. The grippers feel very stable. The top gripper the large, single one actually rides on two rods that are spring loaded, so you just pull it up, pop the phone in, and release. They are quite strong and the phone is held very firmly. I do not foresee it ever falling out of the dock.

All in all I am very happy with this. I have bought, over the last two years, three different car docks for my old phone. From various electronics stores Microcenter, Fry's. They all cost $2035 and are utter garbage compared to this.
summary: Works with HTC One in Otterbox Defender case. Welcome change from the garbage you find in any electronics store.

Corel PaintShop Pro 6 has many improvements over X5! First it is now 64 bit which gives the program more power and makes handling larger amounts of information faster, like huge pictures for example! This is one reason to upgrade from an earlier edition to this one right there. You can handle bigger photos and more all at the same time and you can edit them with great rapidity.

The format has changed from the last version and there are a lot of new or enhanced features. The Smart Selection Brush is awesome! And other features like Object Remover and Smart Carver seem to be easier to use.

Of course, there are going to be new features to learn and getting used to the new format was bit awkward for me. But, one of my favorite features, helps with all of this and that is that they "learning videos" that help you figure out how to use the new and enhanced tools that come with this software.

Allinall this program is a big improvement over earlier versions of this software.

text:
Appears a lot of comments slamming the cost of ownership.  I would agree it is quite high if you have little need for the product to begin with.  Else, for a firm that generates real money, it is relatively little to pay.  Professional services would cost a lot more and it is very hard to find high quality low priced professional services these days.

Else, the product itself shines with a myriad of options that fit almost all aspects you can think of.  The learning curve is steep especially if you never have used one of these accounting suites before, or for that matter have any accounting skills.  Those who do will pick up the strengths quite rapidly.

Overall, a very good product.
summary: Good product for businesses that need it

text: Absolutely in love!!! I am a server at a restaurant and we have rugs that we have to sweep under the tables with a broom. Lots of breadcrumbs to clean up. Using a broom takes forever and makes you sweat like crazy. Regular vacuum will not go under the booths and too loud. This shark is perfect. The head swivels around poles and the handle bends so you can get into places and under things without having to bend over. Picks up the crumbs and big things like crayons with ease. It even sucked up a glove half way into the vacuum cleaner and I had to pull it out. Takes me just a couple of minutes to clean under the tables and I can use it when there are still customers because it is very quiet. I vacuum at home almost every day now because it is always there ready to use without having to plug it in and very super light to carry up the stairs. Vacuuming is almost fun with this Shark.
summary: Absolutely in love!! Vacuuming is almost fun with this Shark.

So I saw this in the store and the cashier says, "yeah they ported it over form PSP." I should have known there would be issues.

GooTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry
It keeps with the scary, dark theme, although a little too dark for my tastes.
Yes, I agree, being able to finally use your fists is cool.
Graphics  not bad, gruesome and creepy, just how we like it.
That is where the good stuff ends.

BaTongue sticking out, cheeky, playful or blowing a raspberry
Camera controls  Are so bad and frustrating that you will want to drop the controller 1 hour into the game.

Health and stamina  Do not pick up a health or stamina drink unless you NEED it. They are not stored even though you can store tons of huge items. Once you pick it up, it is used. They are pointless anyway because my health meter never changed once even though I found 2 health drinks in a row.

Weapons  Yeah they break. Usually while you are still using it and then trying to change weapons has a delay which means you get hit if you try to equip another. If you have a large weapon in your hand and they attack first, you lose that weapon. You do not DROP it, you lose it forever.
If you are a diehard fan, you will get used to this game and play it thru.
Buy at your own risk.

Anyone who thinks they do not have a problem with lint should look at these pictures.  My house is only 10 years old and this is what came out of our vent.  That does not even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit.  This product is very easy to use.  I definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they do not separate in the vent.  I broke my cleaning into 4 cleanings. Fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension.  After ensuring that section is clean I added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean.  Given the length of the brush with all four sections, I found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drill.
I noticed that when I turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening.  Unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing.  I will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so I can remove those pieces.  A little price to pay for a clean vent.
summary: Excellent product and showed me that my vent obviously needed a cleaning

I decided to look at benchmarks for two new Samsung microSD cards and I looked at them against the same quality and capacity for a PNY microSD card.

The first card is the Samsung 64 GB "Evo Select" which is a higher performing card with a maximum Read speed of 80MB/ sec and a maximum Write speed of 20 MB/sec.

The other card is Samsung's Premium card, the "Pro Pro Performance" card and this one is a 32 GB card all of them "Class 10" card.  The Pro has a stated maximum READ speed of 90 MB/sec and a maximum WRITE speed of 80 MB/sec.   This is quite a jump from 20 MB/sec to 80 MB/sec.

Both cards were tested against the PNY which has a stated, maximum READ speed of 90 MB/sec with no stated WRITE speed.

A good app to test out your microSD cards is "A1 SD Bench"

 The Results 

PNY 64 GB

REASadness 63.7 MB/ sec.
WRITE: 28.24 MB/ sec.

Samsung "Evo Select" 64 GB

REASadness 67.41 MB/ sec.
WRITE: 23.68 MB/ sec.

Samsung "Pro" 32 GB

REASadness 62.86 MB/ sec.
WRITE: 27.52 MB/ sec.

The better of the two Samsung cards, I would have to say is the "Evo Select" although, I would be satisfied with any of the the three.  I am really most surprised that the PNY card held its own against Samsung.

I got the camera because I always get everything with a new launch. However, there is not much to do with the camera so far. They PS4 comes installed with a few mini games, but after a hour playing it all you most likely will not ever go back to it.  The quality of the camera was not as sharp as I thought it was going to be, but I do have a 60inch, so maybe my screen is too big? I do not know I was just expecting High Definition.

It just started doing voice commands. So you can say "Playstation", then "Killzone", then you can start it. Turn off the system with your voice. Just real simple things. When you first turn on the PS4 you can have it recognize your face. But the camera has to pick up the light bar on the controller and you have to have good lighting for it to work. It is just easier to click on the user.

The camera comes with a neat little rubber think that can bend and hang onto the top of your television. Other than that it is just a camera with no real games for it. I think Just Dance came out, but from what I read, the game is not that good with the camera at all, so if you do not get that game, the camera will be collection dust until something else comes. Hopefully there will be more games to come, but there is no rush into getting it.

I read the reviews for these shoes and was very excited to get them. Based on the reviews they sounded like walking on clouds on some user put it. So when they arrived I was super excited to try them out.
I have several pairs of clog type shoes most in Merrell or Keen brands so heavier shoes. i was looking for a lighter pair and for that they fit the bill. However I think they are a bit too thin. The material is very light/thin almost to the point where I will not wear them until spring time which is a shame.
The shoe feels ok on my foot. It is light but the arch support is not there. I guess I am use to ones with better support inserts that these were just well flat. The soles are very light and thin, so there is not much impact. I am not running in them or anything but I feel like if I had to jump I would feel the entire impact in my foot.

I have sesnoiditis and have a pretty bad bunion on the same foot. I have to wear comfy shoes at all times with good support. These shoes fit the comfy part to a T. However the support is lacking so much that I can only wear them for short periods of time.
I would suggest them only to people that do not require a lot of arch support.

first thing first: it works. the kit is great in what it consists of and the price is just right i think. to call someone to clean my dryer vents i got quoted from 80 all the way up to 200 bucks. so if you were able to do it yourself you will need to invest a bit more in a "construction" vacuum that cost about 80100 bucks and start the savings basically from the second time you do it.

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

with all that said, if your vent duct does not have to many bends, and you want to take the risk maybe i had a defective kit that the brush broke, you might save a lot of money doing it yourself!

This Cat Eye MTB is a great bike mirror at a bargain price. It has a convex lens so offers a nice wide angle of view, and a ball joint to swivel it into the right position.

The fitting is like an expandable cavity wall fixing, i.e. you screw it into the handlebarend and tighten it with a crosshead screwdriver until secure.  It is hard plasticmoulded, not metal, but quite robust enough for normal use so long as you do not crash the bike when in any case the mirrorlens may break, regardless of the fitting.

Some reviewers complain the mirror shifts position when you go over bumps, but this has not happened in my experience: however it is fitted to a hybrid road bike, and a mountain bike may need a more substantial mirror if you are going offroad.
summary: Budget-price bike mirror: easy secure fit, good view behind

text: This was another sexy little tale from the Taking Advantage series. Greg meets Tessa when her car breaks down in the parking lot and he gets to rescue her by driving her to her yoga studio and having her car repaired. text:
I create video files mostly for business training and for my Amazon and YouTube reviews.  I have been using Corel Video Studio 12 which is a simple program that does just what I need it to do.  However, I am always on the outlook for something better and when I got the chance to try this one out I was very interested.

The Cyberlink Power Director Ultra 13 has features that my other software does not have, including the ability to create 4K files and discs.  I was hoping that it would correct for color and convert my files to smaller files quicker than my Corel software does.  Maybe it can, but I have not been able to get much done with it.  Sometimes it will accomplish small tasks with minimal problems but most of the time it get hung up for hours.

I have a fast, relatively uptodate computer that was designed to gaming so I am pretty sure that my hardware is not the problem.  I have been using the Cyberlink for about a month and I will continue to work with it a post my updates here.
summary: The jury is still out on whether this is a worthwhile product or not

In all, a satisfying snack, and healthy for those who do not have to limit salt.

This is a oneyear subscription to Office 365, which can be installed on one PC/MAC and one tablet/phone.

This includes all the standard office products: Word, Excel, OneNote, Access, PowerPoint, Publisher, and Outlook.

The only office product available for Android is OneNote. This used to be one of my favorite office products, but it is been really crippled by the move to integrate it across platforms. It is not nearly as flexible as it used to be. In the desktop version you can still create section groups, but they will not sync with the mobile version. You also cannot add more space to pages the way you used to.

The other office products work as well as ever. I wish at least Word was available for Android, though. I guess Microsoft wants to push people toward their mobile OS, though.

I am not a huge fan of subscription software in general. When I buy something, I want it to be mine. I did not like having to setup a Microsoft account to use the software. I have been using OpenOffice for a long time and I do not anticipate fully switching to the Microsoft products. For one thing, the subscription runs out in a year. Also, I feel OpenOffice protects my privacy a lot better.

If you have to have office, then you have to have office. It Access and PowerPoint are definitely worth the price of the software, also.

text:
I am a little concerned about what it says about me that I read this kind of book.  I am not sure why reading the gory, graphic doings of a violent serial killer is considered entertainment.  But I have read the entire Beauty Killer series.  All five of them.  And I watch Dexter too....  Hmmm......

Anyway, if your character is similarly flawed, you will enjoy this series.  You must read the books in order though.  In my opinion they are not intended to stand on their own as they tell an evolving story of Gretchen beautiful psychopath and Archie detective caught in her web.  This installment of the story moves with breakneck pace, reveals some history that explains some of Gretchen's motivation and is spiced up with great side characters.  I could see a Susan spinoff series!!!

My only complaint about this series is that I just do not buy how Archie keeps being under Gretchen's spell.  He shows some signs of having broken free in "Kill You Twice" but you get the distinct feeling that she is still pulling the strings even when she is incarcerated.  I would like him to wake up once and for all and do her in.  He is a strong enough character he could carry the series beyond Gretchen.  Whatever happens though, I will be reading book six and beyond.

I read 'Persepolis' and 'Persepolis 2', and thoroughly enjoyed both. After living in Uzbekistan for two years, a nation with a similar history and culture as Iran's, I became fascinated with the role of women in Muslim society.  As a man, I did not have many opportunities to understand this world, and it was this curiosity that made me want to read
Ms. Satrapi's graphic novels.  Both novels were funny, touching, and poignant.

This set contains the basic tools needed to repair iPhone 4 and newer. I would have paid a little extra if a sturdy plastic opening tool were included with the set, but I am satisfied overall. Decent not excellent, but on par quality tools, as reflected by the price.

I bought this in January 2006 and used it as battery backup for an Apple PowerMac G5.

Using a WattMiser, I measured the power used by the PowerMac at about 350 watts and this product provided enough power for an orderly shutdown. That is, until September 2008 when storms knocked out power in my area for 8 days. Once power was restored and the Belkin fully charged, it would no longer provide backup power.

I am still in the process of getting Belkin to honor their 3year warranty, but I was told by Belkin Support that they no longer produce this product. I will update this review once my warranty experience is complete.

Belkin's Bulldog software for Mac OS X is also unreliable  if this product is used with an Apple computer, just use the builtin UPS monitoring found in System Preferences.

text: Stepmom is definitely NOT your usual cliche'd movie about divorce and how it affects the children involved; it is MUCH, MUCH more!  Emotions run high throughout the film and the bitter tension, jealousy, and friction between  the characters is so strong it is almost palpable!  The acting in this movie  is excellent; the dialogue is so believable, that you almost feel like  you are evesdropping on real people's lives!  My opinion?  If you have not  seen this movie yet  you REALLY, REALLY should!  Just be sure to have a  box of tissues handy.  You are going to need them!
summary: THIS MOVIE PACKS AN EMOTIONAL WALLUP!

Wearing glasses and wanting your eyes to pop I need to use eye shadow and mascara. Having sensitive eyes and removing that eyeshadow and mascara is another subject.several of the other eye make up remover left a residue that made my eyes sting.

Ghost Hold  PSS Chronicles 2  by Ripley Patton
I received this book in exchange for an honest review by the Author and the Lovers of Paranormal Group on Goodreads.com
This is a brilliant  book that I absolutely loved.
Ghost Hold is the second book in the PSS Chronicles series and picks up a few weeks after Ghost Hand ended...and so the tale of Olivia Black and the kids with PSS  Psyche Sans Soma  continues. This book has well crafted elements of mystery and intrigue and will keep you guessing until the very end.  The plot is excellent, and very well thought out.  The style of writing is rich and descriptive and flows well, making the book an easy read.  The characters are well described and true to life.  This book is a real page turner that will have you hooked until the very end.  If you love books with a Supernatural theme, then you will enjoy this one. I cannot wait for the next book in this series to come out.  I will definitely be looking for more of this talented authors work.

I won this book in a contest and I was not sure what to expect.

It was so delightful.  A Romantic Paranormal Comedy!

Damian, a drop dead pun intended gorgeous vampire, won the vote of a leading magazine amongst the supes as the most eligible bachelor.  He thought he would like the attention, but discovered that he hates each new encounter with a lust filled female.  Its even interfering with his work and daily life.  Only his best friend, Jo, a troll, can ease his tension.  Damien comes to his best friend for solace, camaraderie, and a moviewatching partner.

The plot was cute, the little world about Mysterious lane was fun, and the main characters were endearing.  I laughed out loud several times and felt so sorry for Jo at times watching all those females come on to Damien and having to deal with him being oblivious to her feelings for him.  Loved how the scenes are simple and everyday.

My only complaint is that it was too short.  I loved hanging out with Damian and Jo.

Recommend for a nice light read.
summary: The Romantic Misadventures of a Most Eligible Vampire
