Tull was a controversial band back in the 70's.  Were they a rock band at all?  Were they even a prog. rock band like Yes and Floyd?  Or were they something totally unclassifiable?  With an enigmatic leader, Ian Anderson, they have some of the biggest hits ever, Aqualung and Locomotive Breath,  both with plenty of radio play, and followed up that success with two albums that had only one song each Thick as a Brick and A Passion Play, both which strangely became 1 albums how is that possible?.  Then in 1977, after a couple of other very successful albums, they popped out Songs From the Wood.  This album rocks in a real woodsy sort of way. The title track sounds great on the remastered version, especially the vocals.  Hunting Girl is a real standout too.  This album stands as a musical work that will never go out of style.  It is timeless and a keeper in your collection.

I should also add that the company offers you a token amazon gift card if you review their product after you buy it; I do not know if they still do that but it might count for a lot of premature 5 star ratings.

This was an enjoyable little story  very simple, straightforward, but enjoyable.  In the afterward the author reveals that it was written for an eighth grade science class, hence it seeming simple.  But this could easily be the plot of a "Star Trek: The Next Generation" episode.

I was a bit surprised at just how short this story is.  For some reason I was expecting something a bit longer, more of a novella.  This really is a short short story, emphasis on short.  You can finish it in about 20 minutes.  Based on the description on Amazon, I was expecting the story to start with humans exploring the solar system and finding the wormships.  But no, the book basically reiterates the information on the product page, in about as much detail.  The events of the story cover about 4 days of time.  And yes the ending really is compressed.  Nevertheless, for what it is, I enjoyed it.

I have not tried it out, and I do not usually review without testing out product.  However, it will be a while, and seller deserves feedback.  Looks like a good quality solid sewer hose.  I like the fact that its light not heavy, and that you can pull or push the accordion folds to expand or contract at will.  Fittings look high quality. Avoid actually putting any on your roots or your scalp to avoid weighing your hair down.  If there is not enough product, repeat again in tiny peasized increments.  Style as usual.

I love this particular leavein conditioner not only because it plays well with heat and dryers but also because it is equally effective at smoothing frizz without help.  I have combination Eurasian hair: my mother's Asian dead straight and fine hair plus my dad's curls so I end up with a somewhat frizzy messylooking crop with its own mind.  My hair's personality varies with humidity and since products meant for curly hair weighs it down due to the straight bits and straight hair products just don;t cut it, I am always in search of something in between that will work. This cd is a vast improvement over Forty Licks and is truly career spanning. This is the Greatest Hits cd we have all wanted for a long time now. But I have noticed in the reviews here that the songs are described as being in chronological order and this is simply not true. They are in relatively chronological groups but the order is not the order in which they were released. It would take up too much space to give examples, but very little of it is in truly chronological order. If you want to, look it up on Wikipedia or another music site. I am not being a nitpicker here though it may seem so. Anybody who went wild for the Stones in 1964 and grew up with all these songs knows their real order and for many reasons would usually want to hear them that way. They the label,not the group came close this time but no cigar. The thing is the songs are on the right disc together; would it have been too much to arrange them correctly? And must there always be the "one missing song" on so many hits collections? Would it have been that impossible to include Mother's Little Helper  and really, Lady Jane belongs here too. Was there no Summer of 1966? But at least they included the nearly lost and forgotten We Love You from the late summer of 1967. Oh well, at least it is the computer age and we can rearrange things. And despite my griping, it is The Stones in all their glory in one of the greatest careers in music history. Get it!
summary: Great music but not really chronological

The lint eater is amazing! We recently bought a house that was built in 2001 and previously owned by an older lady, so I assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned. Before setting up the dryer, I wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safety's sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible. Well, I am glad I did! The exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time, and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that I got out were shocking! It seemed like every time I ran the LintEater through line, it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff. When I first hooked up the shop vac inside the house, and went out to the vent exit, there was almost zero air getting sucked in. The wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and I had to keep going inside to clean it out. After all was said and done, my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new. Glad I spent the money on this product!

Helpful tip  when I started, I just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line. It is way too unwieldy this way, and every time you hit the power on the drill, the rods get kinked and knotted up because they are so flexible. Start with one, and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line, add another. Repeat as necessary and you will have a MUCH easier time.
summary: Excellent choice for cleaning out dryer vent line. Worth every penny!

text: Grandkids love collecting!

A lot has been written about these sonatas and their various interpretations.  So, it is only with a certain level of apprehension that I write some more.  This is also due to my general reluctance to comment on music, something whose sublime is equaled mostly by the subjectivity of individual perceptions.

Once premises have been established, allow me to say it here as well, "Beethoven was just like you and I, only that much more."  To the extent these words ring true to you, then we can agree that Beethoven's music is about LIFE.  Having listened to so many complete cycles of these sonatas, I would only say that it took a Californian in London to render these masterpieces lifelike.  Indeed, Kovacevich comes the closest of all to revealing the liferange encompassed by these works.  Too bad we cannot learn what had informed Kovacevich's interpretationwas it his own life, Beethoven scholarship, or what?

As for the critics of this interpretation, most of them are probably right, in their own ways.  However, what are those ways relative to LIFE itself?  Noise!
summary: What is, possibly rightful, criticism of this edition relative to LIFE itself?  Noise!

first thing first: it works. the kit is great in what it consists of and the price is just right i think. to call someone to clean my dryer vents i got quoted from 80 all the way up to 200 bucks. so if you were able to do it yourself you will need to invest a bit more in a "construction" vacuum that cost about 80100 bucks and start the savings basically from the second time you do it.

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

with all that said, if your vent duct does not have to many bends, and you want to take the risk maybe i had a defective kit that the brush broke, you might save a lot of money doing it yourself!

text:
Honestly, I have purchased some incredibly saturated longlasting lipsticks for less, as well as for more, and have come to the conclusion that I would rather pay less. Is this a good lipstick? Sure! It applies smoothly and easily, has a beautifully matte finish, and tends to mostly stay in place. It is not as opaque as I would like, slightly sheer and more stainlike than a traditional lipstick. I was hoping for something thicker.

Because it was more like a stain, it also had the advantage of staying fairly consistent in its appearance and not coming off easily. I only had to reapply once in the span of my day, and the color looked beautiful.

All in all, I will keep my cheap ones that are probably leadfilled and horrible and need reapplication, because they look thicker and come in some wild colors, but if you have extra money and do not know where to find the awesome offbrand stuff, this is also really nice and has an almost powdery silken finish. Very nice!
summary: more like a matte stain, silky powdery finish

text:
This application comes in handy every nowandthen for me. . . but. . . honestly. . . there is a "free" version, and depending upon how often you use it, you might be able to get by with that.

You also have to consider how long it is going to take to upload large files. Even though you have the "ability" to do it, is it going to take so long that it would be easier/faster/better to burn it to a disc and mail it to someone.  It all simply depends upon your needs.  It is certainly nice to have the "option" to do it this way.
summary: Yes, it works, but the "free" version might be all you need

I have been using this after meals since I have braces. It helps remove all the food that gets stuck around the brackets. Other than that, I do not think it is that great. The orthodontist said the priority should be flossing and brushing, not the Waterpik. He said the Waterpik does not have enough pressure to remove plaque. This is really just for getting the big chunks of food before I brush and floss with OralB Superfloss.
Before I got braces, I occasionally used the Waterpik but I cannot say it did much for me.
It has been a year and I have noticed a puddle of water around the Waterpik after I turn it off. I think the handle is now leaking.
After my braces come off I will probably throw the Waterpik away.

UPDATE: I was right. The handle does in fact leak. I could buy a replacement handle for $10 but I do not want to. Overall, the Waterpik lasted about a year, which is not acceptable for a $50 item.
summary: I don't think it is that great. The orthodontist said the priority should be flossing ...

text: This is a very nice, high quality science kit. It is recommended for ages 10 and up. Our 8 year old is enjoying it, with adult support. There are materials and clear instructions for 20 projects. The first is examining the enclosed rocks using the magnifying glass. The booklet is excellent. Each project has a "what To Do" section that includes lots or thoughtprovoking questions rather than just a prescription for action. That is followed by "Why Is This Interesting?" and then "What Do You Think?" Advanced projects have you growing several varieties of crystals. This would be a great gift.
summary: Great gift idea! Excellent science kit!

text: This story was well rounded and most of the characters were individually created to be separate throughout this science fiction book.  The author has a good grasp of story telling and I found it fascinating to follow through the pages and learn about Titan "dust."  I do not tell the story in my reviews.  Unfortunately, I give a 4 because of the distracting parts that showed me it needed editing and someone missed a lot of typos, duplicated words, missed words and misspelled words.  As far as the story goes, the main character, David Carpenter, known by the neat nickname of Carp, reminded me of Han Solo in his mannerisms and characterization and it made me smile to visualize him going through the stunts, thoughts and piloting the ships.  The other characters were a bit less memorable except the really bad guy...good job there.  I hated him as much as Carp did, so good writing there.  I was given this book as a gift in exchange of an honest review and I appreciated the chance to do so.  This author's creative mind will lead to other good books, I am sure.  Just please...have it edited and a 5 from me.
summary: A creative story with a memorable hero

I bought this for my aging Dell Precision T5500 with H310 to give it some oomph. It is much faster now. I kept my HGST 2TB spinners for data storage and run all my programs and OS on this. I reserved 128GB for overprovisioning. DO NOT USE SAMSUNG MAGICIAN. you will hate yourself if you did. Only install it temporarily if you need to upgrade firmware, then remove it. To overprovision an SSD drive go to Disk Management in Windows. Select your SSD partition Usually C. Right Click on it and select shrink volume. Use a value that gives you at least 25GB of free space. More is better but 25GB is the minimum. I would really recommend that you use 50. Now create a new partition in the free space you created and quick format it. Disable the power saving features that put the ocmputer to sleep and let it sit idle for a few hours so the TRIM process can complete on the OP partition. After it has sat for a few hours right click on the new partition and click Delete Partition. Leave it as unallocated space.  You will never have to deal with garbage collection routines and the performance degradation it creates. Your hard drive will live longer as well.
summary: Awesome Performance upgrade. Make sure you Overprovision and don't use Samsung Magician!

Steve Jobs and the Apple team did it so well. Beautiful products, well constructed, packaged and far ahead of their time. You really get what you pay for when you purchase an Apple product.
Twelve South not only has the same concept but they also deliver. From the moment I opened the Amazon Box, I knew, just from the packaging, that I not only am going to get my money's worth, I am going to have an exciting "unboxing" moment.
Taking the BookArk out of the box, I immediately felt the weight It is well constructed out of hard steel with rubber points were the BookArk meets the desk and on the top, for the iPad. It comes with two rubber inserts. One for the iPad Mini and one for the "regular" sized iPad. My Mini sits very nicely in the holder, with normal everyday tapping no problem. However the holder is NOT designed and the instructions state thisfor gaming or any aggressive use. Common sense should prevail here. A charger fits very nicely underneath to charge and sync your device.
Sorry, Amazon. I have found my last iPad stand and will not be looking any further for one.

My dog wears between small and medium normally, but the Large is a little snug on her.

div id"videoblockRTO8TWI202HB1" class"asection aspacingsmall aspacingtopmini videoblock"/divinput type"hidden" name"" value"httpsSkeptical, annoyed, undecided, uneasy or hesitant/imagesna.sslimagesamazon.com/images/I/D1l41iw47IS.mp4" class"videourl"input type"hidden" name"" value"httpsSkeptical, annoyed, undecided, uneasy or hesitant/imagesna.sslimagesamazon.com/images/I/51C9u8K2t1S.png" class"videoslateimgurl"This Western Digital drive is built for Mac users right down to its aluminum casing. The metal she will gives this product a heftier feel over Western Digital's other My Book products that are usually made with flimsier plastic cases. It will make full use of the USB 3.0 ports found on newer Macs but will still function on older Macs that have slower USB 2.0 connections.

On my Macbook Pro with Retina Display, the My Book delivered read and write speeds of about 150 megabytes per second using a video performance test from Black Magic Design.  This is on par with a similar Thunderboltbased drive I tested from Seagate last month. It is certainly more than adequate for most desktop computer tasks and will make for an excellent Time Machine backup drive.

If you are using this as a backup drive I would suggest buying two. The reason being is that it is always a good practice to have your important data stored off site in addition to an onsite backup. Mac OS X supports multiple Time Machine drives making it very easy to maintain a good offsite backup strategy.

Other than that this is a very simple hard drive that just plain works. No need to install any software or configure it. Plug it in and it is ready to go.
summary: Fast, Well Built, and It Just Works

text: This book opened my eyes about parenting adult children and helped me understand the dynamics between my adult daughters and me.  I do not have major issues with my children, but I felt hurt perhaps because they grew up and I felt that I was no longer important in their lives.  My role changed from "indispensable mommy" to a casual consultant in regards to making decisions in my children's lives.  The transition to parent young children to adult children feels to me like being demoted from captain of the ship to petty officer third class... but this book helped me understand that dynamic and finally I understood that my role might have changed but never the love between my children and I.  I really recommend this book, not only if parents are having issues with their adult children, but even before any issues arise and just to help understand the dynamics between parents and adult children.
summary: Great book to help understand your grown-up child.

text:
This stove has had mixed reviews in the light and ultralight backpacking community. Common concerns are the various pivot points/joints and the very thin adjuster. As with most ultralight gear, if you take care of this stove it will hold up just fine.
It sits a bit lower than similar MSR stoves, which is a plus I think. It fits well with a 600750 ML pots, but not much bigger. The flame pattern is sufficient for boiling water but it would be a challenge to cook or simmer with it.
Bottom line, if you want the lightest gas canister stove out there and you mainly just boil water on the trail, this is your stove. It weighed in at .87 oz on my scale. It is worth it even if you have to take extra care to handle it well on the trail.

I happen to be a fair welder, and have decent technical drawing skills, so I am really digging this pen. It took about half of a tank of ink to get used to it, and then I was able to make some neat things.

I was able to make a few small, reasonably attractive, lightduty items with only about 30 minutes of practice.
Also, my kids 8 and 13 really like this.  This would have been a big hit at Christmas time.
summary: Cool toy - A combination of welding and drawing

text:
Let me start by saying I am a HUGE fan of Hogue grips.  I like everything about them.  However, for pistols with an alreadythick grip, an aftermarket Hogue grip "glove" is not necessarily the best solution.  Therefore, I am glad I read the reviews here before I proceeded to purchase a Hogue for my Glock 19.  This Pachmayr was definitely a better choice.  The bottom of the grip is just above the bottom of the pistol's grip, so there is no overhang.  Installing was also very easy.  It gives you just a little better cushion, which has helped me control the pistol a little better.

It is important to note: I did buy a Hogue grip for my Glock 21SF.  For that pistol, the Hogue is the better choice, in my opinion.  It is considerably harder to "install", but in the end, I am happy I made the effort.
summary: The right aftermarket grip for this pistol

text:
When I first started playing, it did not matter what kind of pick I was using. I was too concerned with what my fret hand was doing. But after a while I began to take notice of which picks felt right versus which ones did not and I began to single out my favorites. I had settled on Fender mediums as my pick of choice yet felt they could be better. After all, you take an aggressive song with a couple good pick slides in it and your Fender pick looks like Jethro's gaptoothed grin and the edge is completely worn away.
 Once I discovered the Dunlop Delrin picks, I have not used another brand or style. Simply because they were exactly what I was looking for. Just enough resistance to keep the string attack clean and enough flexibility to keep the pick firmly within your grasp. The materials from which the Delrins are made offers superior wear resistance. Greater wear resistance  longer life  using fewer picks. I used to go one or two songs and need a new pick. Now one pick lasts me an entire rehearsal. Buy these, see for yourself!
GREAT

Thirty Three and 1/3 is George Harrison's first LP on his own Dark Horse label.  It comes after a good many months of personal ordeal.  Harrison made a concert tour with a show that mirrored The Concert for Bangladesh.  EastWest music.  All the top Indian musicians opened the show, and then George and his band took over after the intermission. A bright highlight of the tour was a visit to the White House, as the guest of Jack Ford, son of Gerald Ford, President.  This was perhaps the first visit to the White House by a Beatle.
 About half way though the tour his voice was thrashed.  He became sick with jaundice.  To fulfill his EMI contract, he recorded Extra Texture Read All ABout It, where he even made a joke at his own expense Ohnothimagain, Oh, not him again.  His wife left him for Eric Clapton.  Drank a good amount of brandy. However his association with A  M Recordswhich was the parent company of Dark Horse Records BEFORE Warner Brothers Records took it under its wing, brought about his meeting Olivia Trinidad Arias, whom he married and had a son, Dhani.
 So, this album represents a George whose life had just gone from the lower depths, to heaven, in just a matter of months. Other reviews have already given a good detailed description of the tracks on this album, so I will not try to duplicate those efforts here.
  One of the photos that accompanied the original album art was one of Harold Harrison Sr., George's father, with George, posing outside Friar Park.  George had his father, as well as his brother Pete, residing with him on his estate in Henley on Thames, just outside London.  Pete stills resides there to this day. 12/06

Ni Cad batteries do not hold up unless you are constantly using them, and even then do not hold up like Lithium Ion batteries which you can let sit for a year after charging them, and will have 90 of their original charge, ready to work. Ni Cads will be dead, and may never charge correctly if you leave them sitting for a year. I looked into buying Lithiumion replacement batteries several years ago, but they were so expensive that I got an entire set of Makita lithiumion tools and 3 batteries for less than a hundred more than the Milwaukee batteries and charger would have cost, so when I saw these, I jumped on them. I like my Makita, but I like my old tried and true Milwaukee as well, and am very glad to have it back in service again. Prices fluctuate, but these were a really good deal when I bought them, and if you want to use your older Milwaukee tools, these are great. I have had them for several years now, they hold up, and have more a$$ than my Makita's do even thought they are supposed to be the same amp hours. Milwaukee has been sold and sold, and I understand sold again since I purchased mine, I am not sure the newer tools are as good as the older ones, so I would not take the gamble, I would upgrade the batteries if you are torn between new batteries and a new set of Milwaulkee tools.

Interesting note: I have one USB cable that will not charge at more than 150 ma, which would take 10 hours to charge the phone.  Another cable does it at nearly 1000 ma about the rating of the wall wart.  The first must be a data only cable, which only allows a token charge.

So, if it seems your phone is taking forever to charge, try another cable.

text: Good Album.

After 4 years I finally called it quits with the Every Day magazine. The magazine has changed in size, layout, and target audience to the point where I feel I am NOT that demographic. The magazine has become aimed at the more wealthy members of society. The recipes are a bit repetitious or made with "one shot" ingredients, i.e. expensive ingredients that are hard to find. Ingredients used once then you are stuck with something you will never use again.

I am really disappointed to see Rachael Ray go off on tangents about her expensive vacations. It is disheartening to see her monthly product page filled with items like jeans that cost $150. I thoroughly enjoyed the start of the magazine, but I do feel ostracized by recipes I cannot afford to make or that include ingredients so unique that making the recipe costs a lot of money. Sorry, Rachael.  My budget has no room for you now. I love recipes, but yours have become too far off course.
summary: No Longer For The Ordinary Person

In this book Rawles does a great job of training the troops for the end of the world. I do not know how anyone would have enough money in today's economy to actually do half of the things on the lists in this book, but it is a good guide. Buying a hideaway and equipping it like a fortress is beyond most people's means and the weapons and ammo, bunkers to hide it and keep it from rust and vehicles that would survive an EMP are really costly. This lifestyle would require that you form a cell of like minded people who would train as military combatants, learn home medical and surgery techniques and share in the cost of setting all this war fortress and cashes up and maintain them through years of normalcy, like the bomb shelters of the 1960s. If I had several millions of dollars I would love to set this up. There is some solid advice in this and other books by Rawles on not putting all your eggs in one basket, having some gold and silver as monetary backup and having some firearms for self protection. I would recommend the book to everyone for the survival information whether you can afford to do all the things he suggests or not.
summary: Great book for how to survive

Download and setup of this suite was uneventful  download and installation took about 20 minutes. I was not even asked to restart my computer when it was done.  After installation, all the apps booted correctly and I was able to easily locate all my Office files in OneDrive.
Most of the work I do with MS Office is done on my laptop PC  my primary reason for having Office on my Mac too  is for the simple convenience of being able to access and work on my files if I am at my home office where my desktop computer is a Mac.  For that, Office 2016 for Mac works flawlessly.  I keep all of my MS documents in the cloud via One Drive. Although i do the lion's share of my work on the PC, its nice to have that flexibility.  I have found the Office software runs smoothly and reliably on the Mac platform. Whether I am using Powerpoint, Word, or Excel, it all works pretty much the same on both platforms.  I will mention that my Mac has an up to date processor, a solid state drive and plenty 16GB of RAM  and El Capitan.
summary: Easy to install, excellent workhorse applications!

UPDATE  Since fixing the oring seat and damaged section of hose from the oring, I have managed to get this thing to work a lot better.  I have found that if you put the coolant tank as high as possible it will pull enough of a vacuum and actually produce a decent mist.  I was able to put my coolant tank above the nozzle head, and it has consistently been working now.  However, if I put the coolant tank as far below the nozzle as the hose will allow, it will not pull a consistent vacuum, and thus the mist will be intermittent at best.

I do some detail carbide and diamond drilling in glazed ceramics and glass, so I was hoping to use this to keep the drills cool, while pulling the coolant back up from the drilling catch basin.  This does not really work.

It barely pulls any vacuum to make a mist unless you cut out the damaged section from their poor oring setup clamping down too hard on the tube and remachine and reseat everything.  Even then you have to run it at an absurd pressure, over 90PSI for me, to get it to pull anything.  At 90PSI every air fitting joint leaks.  I tested this with pure water, no cutting additives at all.

Fortunately for me, I only wanted it for the air nozzle and not the mist feature, but someone that expects a proper vacuum mist system will be disappointed. Even only wanting it for the air nozzle, it is fairly marginal at best.
summary: Meh for Mist, OK for Air

text:
Having worked with, and studied the Dramatica theory of story development, and also looked at and read a few of the examples it is based on, it seems to me that Dramatica 4 is a product somewhat ahead of itself.
By this I mean, that to convey the principles of Dramatica the prior art examples are  either too archetypical with no real requirement for the use of Dramatica by those who intend writing such archetypes, or are too flawed so that they do Dramatica no favours due to them being little more than the nearest point of common reference.
But by treating Dramatica as a philosophy and an abstraction, and not using it to see how prior art can be aligned to its principles, one can quickly see how Dramatica will enable the writer to create stories and forms hitherto unattainable, simply  because the organisation of the story's elements and form would have been too difficult to keep track of.
Therefore, in order to get the desired results from using Dramatica, the user has to gain expertise in the way of defining and structuring a story's elements with Dramatica, and not be trying to defend the outcome on prior art which is a close call. This is the hard part to Dramatica, since  ideal prior art probably does not exist, from which to refer,  except for the possibility of future works skilfully created with Dramatica.
Now there is a chicken or the egg paradox.

This movie is great. It is sickeningly disturbing and a great movie that twists your mind. It is a movie where it expounds on the life of a rich wallstret suck up who is going insane, and indeed does crack a little. With a surprising, believable twist, with Ptrick Bateman played by Christian Bale going on a murder spree. No plot spoilers here, what I said was in the trailers.

The sad, miserable life of this rich man finally empties his soul of what little emotion he had left, where he vents his frustrations on his assistant and on unwitting victims.

Watch the movie to see the suck up go from polite to maniacal. A little too disturbing for my tastes, some parts seemed sad because Christian Bale plays such a supreme performance. I never thought I would have pity for a rich person, let alone a murderer.

Also, they do not have a lot of nudity. What they show are a few porn scenes but with literally one or two butt and boob shots that are about a split second, but I swear they let your imagination FLY. Man. The power of the mind.

This is an album that makes you love Mendelssohn even more.  The interpretations are perfect  I get flashes of Mendelssohn when I hear Daniel Barenboim's playing.  He certainly seems to do a lot of research  into the composer before attempting a recording...he must have the original  manuscripts and not those which demand excessive pedaling work which was  not the style of Felix Mendelssohn at all, well, as far as I know anyway.
In my experience some players get Mendelssohn all wrong.  Though many of  the Songs Without Words do not require virtuosity to play, they require  something special to "sing".  I have never heard any other pianist  do this as well as Daniel Barenboim.

text:
Update: 62516

We still have our goggles. I have read some reviews that said they leak. It is very important for for all goggles, not just these, but for all, for you to clean the goggles after you use them. Especially after swimming in a chlorinated pool. I spoke to our kids swim instructor my kids go to year round swim lessons and she suggested rinsing them after swimming. I noticed with our first pair that after awhile they would leak and I had to buy another one. After rinsing very well every time the kids swam the new pair it has lasted us 4 years. Very happy!



I like these much better than the regular speedo goggles. They do not squish my kids eyes and they actually like wearing goggles now. It is very easy to change the fit of the goggles to have it fit your child. You just pulled the string in both directions and there you go. When my children were first learning how to swim, I had them in the regular speedo goggles. They hated putting those on and complained about how it would squish their eyes. I finally found these on Amazon after seeing another kid wearing them at the pool. Now my kids are happy and love to swim and to see underwater too!
summary: No more squishy eyes! And an UPDATE.

text:
Bought this card to augment the number of Firewire ports in my new MacPro only design flaw I find in that computer...not enough Firewire inputs for professional use. It replaced the first Sonnet card I bought as that one a combo USB/Firewire card did not play well with my computer for what I needed word to wise  before buying a PCI card make sure that your peripherals will work with it. Firebox, for instance, needs a specific chipset and Firewire only cards to work...something buried on their website.

Card installed easily and has worked beautifully with no problems.

Big rave to Sonnet's customer service, by the way, for helping me troubleshoot and giving me all the information I needed. About the best I have encountered.
summary: Does what it should and does it well

YS Eco Bee Farms raw honey was the best honey deal I found on Amazon. Locally I can get honey for about the same price $7 per pound. However, this honey is creamier, tastier and thicker which is just the way I like it. This has many benefits too numerous to list here.

 I use it in tea whenever I get cold or flu symptoms. If you drink tea with honey and lemon 23 times a day it will usually resolve your cold symptoms within a day or two. You can also use this to prevent constipation. Just use a tablespoon in a small glass of warm water. I do this almost every morning before breakfast. When I forget a get a little constipated. As long as the price stays fair I will definitely buy this honey again. I highly recommend it for the taste and health benefits.

This is a review for a 7800 powerpack.
Relatively heavy, but seems all battery chargers are heavy.
I liked a lot its feature of showing the exact percentage of charge left.
Became really useful during my trip to Peru, when I could not get to the power supply any time I wanted.
It took 1 hour and 55 minutes to charge the powerpack from 35 to 57.
Charging Ipad 2  added 38 from 62 to 100Drunk or confused in 3 hours and 30 minutes.
For Iphone 5 it needed 1 h and 20 minutes to add 65 from 35 to 100Drunk or confused.
PNY itself drained from 100 to 35 after these efforts.
I have not used it very often, and it may get pretty efficient with multiple uses, but it falls short of the performance it is advertised for as are pretty much all the battery chargers. Still, I guess you can get 1 full charge for a tablet and 1 full charge for a phone iphone5 in my case. I am not sure if I have used it for a phone only too heavy for that, and there are lighter and more convenient chargers, including charging cases, for phones  unless you think that you will be out for a while and need to charge the phone several times. It is great for a tablet, though.
summary: Acceptable size, enough charge for a tablet

Bought a used Camry for my wife and needed to change rotors but they were rusted and stuck on to such a degree that all conventional method to remove them failed. I tried hammering, heating, lubing and cursing. Then I ordered this and with in 5 minute of receiving I was able to pop those old rusty rotors right off. It does take some energy to crank the drive bolt, I used a breaker bar for the right leverage. Here is a WARNING, when the rotor does pop off it happens quickly and with great force so make sure your toes or fingers are not in the path. Even buying this tool and doing the job yourself is still cheaper than taking car to mechanic plus you will have the tool for any future jobs.
summary: Wow This Was A Real Life Saver. Works Perfectly As Advertised.

First off, this is a very capable scan tool for a wide range of cars. I am not an auto shop so it is hard for me to fully evaluate the full range of capabilities. The solid side of the tool is that it gives you an amazing amount of data and will allow you to tinker and discover issues with your system. The battery is not so good and you will want to ensure it is charged before you plan on using it. If you have a shop and want to use this on a daily basis, then leaving it plugged in at night is a must.

The other side to this machine, is that it is android powered. This is a good thing and a little bit of an issue. The good thing is that the platform is flexible enough to have add on capability as long as it will work with Android 4.4 and above. The bad side, is that I am not sure this device will ever actually be upgraded to 5 and above. As of today, the current android OS is at 7.1

This may be fine for the near future, but at some point down the not so distant future, it will no longer be supported. Good for having folks re buy the item very few years, but not so good for the end user.

So in short, a very powerful diagnostic tool with a limited life due to the android os integration ....
summary: a very powerful diagnostic tool with a limited life due to the android os integration ....

Cut branches fast.

Its for garden use only, not for construction. Unless you are 100 sure all the lumber has no nails.

DO NOT  use this for demolishing works. Its not designed and made for that.

The teeth will dull easily when come in contact with any metal, even the smallest nails.

For its intended use, the blade itself is designed to be a bit thicker than most saw blades,  so it has very low tolerance for side to side movement , it will break off at the base quite easily.

Do not use brute force to jam it through. Just lightly guide the saw and let the blade cuts through the branches by itself.

And it will do exactly that very well.

text:
first thing first: it works. the kit is great in what it consists of and the price is just right i think. to call someone to clean my dryer vents i got quoted from 80 all the way up to 200 bucks. so if you were able to do it yourself you will need to invest a bit more in a "construction" vacuum that cost about 80100 bucks and start the savings basically from the second time you do it.

so what is with the 3? my brush broke inside my vent!!!! while i was pulling it out, and yes i was using a drill, all the pieces came out except the round brush. i had to climb to my attic and push it from the other side to come out... what was supposed to be an easy task ended up with me spending over an hour extra in climbing in my attic, disassembling the HVAC pipe so that i can get in there and push down on the brush...

another minus for this kit is that while it is fairly bendy, it will not go very smoothly through your flexible insulated pipes and most likely push the pipe out from its connector.

with all that said, if your vent duct does not have to many bends, and you want to take the risk maybe i had a defective kit that the brush broke, you might save a lot of money doing it yourself!

This review will cover the original score by Hans Zimmer and not the Nina  Simone pieces. This score took a while to grow on me because it is so  unconventional. Once I accepted it, it became amazingly unique. The tracks  are inspiring and beautiful, sad and tragic. The score, except for guitar  and the male voice is electronically orchestrated. It works beautifully,  this soundtrack is something you can always listen too, I love it  while  driving. A few of the tracks feature soulful male vocals, they are here to  accentuate the score. Overall the tracks are driving and pulsepounding,  with some quiet moments.  Hans Zimmer's score conjures up visual imagery  and emotions that portray someone moving to New York and unknowingly  falling in love with a mobster and becoming part of a monstrous  scandal....the trial....going on Barbara Walters....the book....the  movie.....

I have been fascinated with our family tree since I was little as part of the family was REALLY into researching ancestors.  Unfortunately, the one who promised to document everything and share decided to change their mind, so I am going to start fresh, and as a novice, this program is pretty helpful.

Please note that I have NOT used the free 3 months to Ancestry.com yet.  I want to get a little more done and explored on my own before I use that.

I had no problems installing the software or loading it.  I am making a point to regularly save a backup of my work, and when I am more comfortable and have a lot of time, I am going to really put that 3 month free access to Ancestry to work for me!

Meanwhile, there are some great video tutorials and a helpful book to help me along when and if I run into any issues.

The software makes it easy to work on your family tree, and so far I am having a great time simply talking to relatives and filling in what we know.  There are even places to save pictures and stories, as well as other documents.

This is really a great tool for a novice to work with.  Just remember to make sure you backup your work.
summary: Family Tree Maker Deluxe: Helpful and Useful

text:
At first this contraption was a little confusing. I read the directions about 3 times before I felt okay about going through with the project  was not fully confident as there were a lot of warnings about making sure the drill was going the right way/you turned it the right way so you would not lose rods in the dryer vent. Scared me a little. However, the project turned out really well. We did not lose any rods thankfully and we got out the birds nest that had taken residence in our dryer vent!!
The part that was for the lint catcher was convenient as well and is actually recommended to be used at least once a month in order to clean out the lint catcher. I do need to keep up with this but it is not convenient to have to put together and tape the rods each time when you only really use it for a couple of minutes. However, if you have a handy space to keep it already together, I can see how this would be even better for keeping up with cleaning the lint out.
Thank you.

LOST SCREW.  HELP!
It was bound to happen, and I am proud to say it took 2 years to lose it, but I lost the screw to the battery door on my Carrera Digital caliper.  I really hate to toss it out or hack it with tape.  Has anyone measured the screw size by any chance or has anyone found a screw for it?  Amazon has micro screw assortments but it sounds like they are mostly for computers, and therefore, far from 'micro' which does not help at all.  Does anyone have a source or a small set of assorted microscrews that might work?  I have tried different drill bits into the threaded hole itself as a 'go/nogo' gauge and it looks like 1.6mm is very close
Thanks in advance.

Victor
summary: I really hate to toss it out or hack it with tape

I checked out various video reviews on this case before deciding on its' purchase and was impressed by what was said about it.  When I received itvery fast by the way, I was equally impressed by the actual product in my hands.  I am not too worried about it not being waterproofnonsubmersible as I am very careful with all the cellphones I have ever owned anyway.  But, I am sure it will protect the phone in the rain as long as you do not let it get soaked.  As far as impact protection, this case will definitely provide enough protection as long as you do not intentionally slam it into the pavement.  The holster is really handy for clipping it to your vehicle's sun visor or fastening to your belt or back pack strap.  One of my favorite features is the built in screen protector  it really does not interfere with the touch sensitivity of the phone.  I have purchased other OtterBox products and have never been disappointed.  So, I would recommend the Defender Series case to anyone looking for a high quality, protective, fully functional case for their iphone 5.
summary: More than adequate protection for your iphone

The left speaker stopped working after only one month of use out of nowhere, even though I took very good care of its handling. For the month that it worked though, it had very... clear sounds. No additional bass or shine to it, it reproduced music faithfully to its source even in a relatively lowend setup with no DAC, tried it on my lossless collection. The leather bag it came with was really handy.

Now, customer support with Sony was pretty wonky. No repair shop in my country that dealt with audio, and sending a ticket to their repair shop in the USA turned out to be a pain. I probably should have gone through Amazon itself, but what is done is done. It is a shame since they are a really good pair even in fit and I can wear it for an extended period of time for gaming and music. I would get a second pair if I was guaranteed that they would not get wrecked so quickly and Customer Support was efficient in the case that they did.
summary: Great product... if it kept working as intended.

I have been woodworking for only a few years, but quickly realized I was not going to get too far without a jointer. My budget and space limitations had to be considered when looking for a jointer. I wanted something that was portable, would last, suit my needs, but also not break the bank. I checked out the reviews on the Grizzly G0654 and they sounded promising, so I went ahead and ordered one.
The hardest part was contacting the shipper to arrange for lift gate service. Having to pay $34 extra to have someone get the jointer off the truck onto the ground seemed like BS to me, but it was a small price to pay.
 Cleaning all the cosmoline packing grease off was probably the most annoying part. A little laquer thinner did the trick. I had the jointer put together and running in about 3 hours. The outfeed table adjustment was pretty simple and the test pieces I ran through turned out great.
The jointer works great and I am very happy with it. It seems like a great deal to me.

For someone who does not usually go for feathers in bedding due to allergies, this was a good choice. It has not made me itchy. It has put off a few small feathers, but overall was the right choice to make a nice duvet cover feel elegant. It is warm in the winter, but not too warm in the summer. It is actually much thinner than you would expect. Even months after we took it after the packaging and let the filling decompress, the thickest parts are not more than 1/2 inch thick. This is good because it is not too heavy on your body at night, not too warm... really a pretty good mix of all factors. It is still down vs. a synthetic material, but I am learning to love it.

I tried to give Rick the benefit of the doubt here, but his selection of covers needed more consideration. I mean, most of the songs are ballads, and he does not improve upon the originals. I liked this album, but that is about it. I do not understand why Rick chose to remake songs almost identical to their originals. I really did not enjoy his version of The Dream Academy's "Life In A Northern Town" or Foreigner's "Waiting For A Girl Like You". I did not understand why he got Richard Page of Mr. Mister to redo "Broken Wings". I mean, why get the vocalist of the song to do the song again? His version of Human League's "Human" also failed. However, there was something likeable about his version of The Church's "Under The Milky Way" and John Lennon's "Imagine". The only original song, "Cry", cannot hold a candle to the other classics on the disc. Why is that Rick would do an album of covers not even two years after releasing his first album of original material in five years? All I can say is that I am glad he got this out of the way so he can move on to better things.
summary: You,Too, Can Have Rick Sing At Your Wedding.

It has a strong petroleum smell.  But, it adheres to drywall extremely well.  Note: One can does not go very far.  I barely covered about 24 square feet with one can and I mean barely.  Plus, the nozzle began to clogup even though I was constantly shaking the can to keep it mixed.  If you get some overspray on something, wipe it up while it is still wet.  When this stuff dries, it is difficult to remove.  You have to scrape it off.  Other than that, it does what it is supposed to do.
Update:  I bought 4 cans.  Two cans worked okay.  On the third and 4th cans, the nozzle cloggedup immediately and the cans are unuseable.  The contents of the cans has become pasty like dried toothpaste, and clogs the nozzle.  Very frustrating.  Homax needs to redesign the nozzle !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
summary: It works well (when it works).  Nozzle tends to become clogged

At first this contraption was a little confusing. I read the directions about 3 times before I felt okay about going through with the project  was not fully confident as there were a lot of warnings about making sure the drill was going the right way/you turned it the right way so you would not lose rods in the dryer vent. Scared me a little. However, the project turned out really well. We did not lose any rods thankfully and we got out the birds nest that had taken residence in our dryer vent!!
The part that was for the lint catcher was convenient as well and is actually recommended to be used at least once a month in order to clean out the lint catcher. I do need to keep up with this but it is not convenient to have to put together and tape the rods each time when you only really use it for a couple of minutes. However, if you have a handy space to keep it already together, I can see how this would be even better for keeping up with cleaning the lint out.

text: fast delivery and card worked

I have used this program for short films, and played around with examples for selfpublished book promos. I have played around somewhat with the special effects and animation capabilities, and I am happy.

As is expected from a budget program, this is not Adobe, and it is not blockbusterlevel studio quality. However, it is a solid, affordable program, and I have gotten good use out of it.

I really like the title and subtitle functions and effects it practically constitutes a program on its own! and the special effects are definitely something to be considered.

To put my review in perspective, I use this program with an athome green screen and manipulated photo stills to create a "moving comic" style of work classic comic in some cases, anime in others, real image/animation mishmash, and mine and my husband's personal art styles, and it absolutely excels at this. In conjunction with Corel's PaintShop Pro, I cannot ask for anything better in this price rangeand cannot ask for hugely better anywhere else.

For my needs, it is great. I cannot comment on featurefilm capabilities not quite there yet but I would imagine, if you know how to work it, it will yield similarly solid results, assuming you are not planning on creating the next "Avatar."

My biggest complaint is that it is not exactly intuitive. It is not impossible to figure out by any means, and compared to certain programs, it is an absolute cakewalk. I just get irate when I cannot learn a program in less than an hour.

That said, this is a nifty program. For smallerscale projects, it is fabulous.
summary: A Little Complicated; Not Adobe; But Entertaining and Extremely Useful
